msgid "5ce8f962de1e4ea2842e31e185b420aa"
msgstr ""
"The Noble Great Vehicle Sūtra The Teaching on the Great Compassion of the "
"Tathāgata"

msgid "bf4ccc92e0e54c67847a3a7af98649bf"
msgstr "Homage to all buddhas and bodhisattvas."

msgid "16d2e7d8935045fa83694766a13ae147"
msgstr "Thus did I hear at one time."

msgid "7b575299355a4cee9889216a98d89889"
msgstr ""
"The Blessed One was dwelling on Vulture Peak, near Rājagṛha, a sacred site "
"blessed by tathāgatas, a great stūpa where previous victors dwelled."

msgid "eab1407c37f74b3485dcb645adee4f45"
msgstr ""
"It is a Dharma seat praised by bodhisattvas and a place worshiped by gods, "
"nāgas, yakṣas, gandharvas, and asuras that inspires toward roots of virtue."

msgid "03afaa760b2d401c9d8374168ecf3605"
msgstr ""
"It is a site where tathāgatas appear and where gateways to the Dharma are "
"promulgated, where bodhisattvas appear and where infinite qualities spring "
"forth."

msgid "1fb3b715f07e47e59aa088d647b48b43"
msgstr ""
"In the tathāgata domain, the Blessed One had fully realized the sameness of "
"all phenomena."

msgid "bb32ccf91ade4249bc1d1f0aa1872429"
msgstr ""
"He had turned the wheel of the Dharma and now commanded a vast host of well-"
"trained disciples."

msgid "b7c780143d264950bf988071519fa4c1"
msgstr "He had achieved mastery over all phenomena."

msgid "d96e0aaa0d6f4c789164d6fbc30d2673"
msgstr ""
"He knew well how to fulfill the intentions of all beings, he had discovered "
"how to bring their faculties to the highest perfection, and he had become "
"skillful in terminating their karmic traces."

msgid "8d7a858f995f4fdd89793349eea7d727"
msgstr ""
"In his spontaneous and uninterrupted buddha activity, he resided in the "
"company of a large saṅgha of sixty thousand monks."

msgid "16ae4509ab7b47ca91babce9420cef4e"
msgstr ""
"All of these monks were of noble lineage, mighty elephants who had done "
"their duties and performed their tasks. They had laid down the burden of "
"existence and attained their own goals for themselves. They had brought "
"their entanglement in existence to an end."

msgid "74b59867d52147059233dd8a14f2fe50"
msgstr ""
"Their minds were liberated through perfect knowledge and insight, and they "
"had brought the karmic traces of afflictive emotions to an end."

msgid "e9daae1f63e14f7f8af5b543c2a9bcfa"
msgstr ""
"These sons of the Dharma king, the Tathāgata, were skillfully established in"
" the profound Dharma."

msgid "334d8d2749ed4a24b8895b1d14cc3a8e"
msgstr "They were emancipated through the teaching on non-objectification."

msgid "c058724e7d134b47a513dd83a7087ef6"
msgstr ""
"They had exquisite and elegant comportments, were great objects of "
"veneration, and were fully grounded in the tathāgata word."

msgid "7cf2356a92d3478288046cef74946a0c"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, the Blessed One resided in the company of a vast saṅgha of "
"bodhisattvas."

msgid "d6b2d81602824f60a2c9bda6cd6e6d60"
msgstr ""
"These bodhisattva mahāsattvas were all-knowing and had achieved perfection "
"through dispassionate conduct."

msgid "9809a34a4b664041895096a785efe2ed"
msgstr ""
"From a Dharma cloud of great benevolence and vast compassion, these "
"bodhisattvas sent forth the lightning of special insight, knowledge, and "
"liberation and rained down showers of divine nectar, through which they "
"pleased all beings."

msgid "2bcddb9c9a824710a0cab74797ab192c"
msgstr ""
"With a disposition that encompasses everyone, like the earth, they felt "
"affection for all sentient beings and lacked hostility."

msgid "739a586bcb0f4e1093f41c5eb846ce18"
msgstr "They increased the crops of the diverse factors of awakening."

msgid "a9b0cd49b9044123900e3224fe225dc9"
msgstr ""
"By sending out rays of insight brighter than the sun, they revealed that "
"they had achieved the path of clearing away the darkness of ignorance."

msgid "5168150b79894b318f255d6fb2a7a31b"
msgstr ""
"They opened sentient beings like lotus flowers, brought the roots of virtue "
"to maturity, and dried up the rivers of craving."

msgid "32d234c9db78452e90e14f29eb49d946"
msgstr ""
"Focused on the task of knowledge, they were driven by the mighty higher "
"knowledges and tranquil abiding."

msgid "b86e83c5ff8c41b3845a9e11782b9762"
msgstr ""
"Like the moon, they displayed a waxing and waning in brightness, since their"
" disposition embraced all beings, and they were skilled in the means to "
"pacify and appease them;"

msgid "9a79bde5d2b84e52b9c3ffd738e93e4f"
msgstr ""
"with their noble intentions like Mount Meru, the jewels of the Brahmā abodes"
" were firmly established."

msgid "704458c314bf4ee89dd2855c577f35e2"
msgstr ""
"They illuminated and displayed all buddhafields, which were superior in "
"quality to our world and never buffeted by gusts of wind from any of the "
"four directions."

msgid "85bfa18aa13c444387ea513034140d24"
msgstr ""
"Like a great ocean, they were vast containers of retention and mindfulness, "
"filled with the water of Dharma, and their precious bodhisattva conduct "
"nourished all beings."

msgid "71af4ddc33414b12bca7cf77937177e0"
msgstr ""
"Like the king of beasts, they had the legs of truth, a full tail of loving "
"kindness, and eyes of tranquil abiding and special insight, and, since they "
"were unintimidated by the profound Dharma, they subdued all adversaries."

msgid "eabc2dc15b75404b831ca2271c9f36c6"
msgstr ""
"Their bodhisattva conduct remained undisrupted for countless eons, so they "
"were endowed with all qualities."

msgid "a5ebb0d8446b495b8af9a81dfbdc205b"
msgstr ""
"including the bodhisattva mahāsattva All-Illumining and Unobstructed Gaze,"

msgid "ee53a0430d6347118a1321f6f45cd9e2"
msgstr ""
"the bodhisattva mahāsattva All-Revealing Continuous Display of All "
"Buddhafields,"

msgid "d5d1092100a04b57a77ae7af77492f05"
msgstr ""
"the bodhisattva mahāsattva Intelligence in Conduct Stemming from the "
"Tathāgata Lineage,"

msgid "419c99dbc0c94c4d966fb5f090693468"
msgstr ""
"the bodhisattva mahāsattva All-Revealing Unperturbed Subjugation through All"
" Conduct,"

msgid "8c3735f7fddb4fcebc1b2ad802e62e0d"
msgstr ""
"the bodhisattva mahāsattva Topping the Victory Banner of Endless Courage "
"with Miraculous Melodies,"

msgid "f98c3296a10e4025825d4cb22c8110b5"
msgstr ""
"the bodhisattva mahāsattva Brilliant Light Rays of the Collection of Fine "
"Gold,"

msgid "b07969f6686747eda0d99bf5db4dd355"
msgstr "the bodhisattva mahāsattva Eloquence in Language via Insight,"

msgid "935b2a143ca84c8cbf15ad0324e0f27b"
msgstr ""
"and the bodhisattva mahāsattva Gathering of Stable and Immeasurable Merit "
"and Insight."

msgid "a63254c3f8124cc292a403f1c026f6dc"
msgstr ""
"Thus the Blessed One dwelled in the company of countless bodhisattva "
"mahāsattvas"

msgid "4a510edb077a4007bffc29cfbb3c9666"
msgstr ""
"The Blessed One proceeded to teach the Dharma discourse The Gateway to "
"Unobstructed Deliverance through the Bodhisattva Way of Life."

msgid "4183ca41e5724f19a23bce90384ca50f"
msgstr ""
"Sixteen years had passed since the Blessed One had become fully awakened, "
"and he knew that the sacred conduct had unfolded."

msgid "4cd601510e9d4e478cdc495efe120731"
msgstr "He beheld the great assembly of bodhisattvas."

msgid "26f3b8955592413aa0982f8e78a798dc"
msgstr ""
"Once he had understood these assembled bodhisattvas to be holders of the "
"treasury of tathāgata Dharma, he thought,"

msgid "b9380f5ad34049229c1318a4aacd22bc"
msgstr ""
"“Because I care deeply for the bodhisattvas, I shall teach the Dharma "
"discourse The Gateway to Unobstructed Deliverance through the Bodhisattva "
"Way of Life, drawing on the magic and miraculous displays of tathāgatas, in "
"order to lead the bodhisattva mahāsattvas to the domain of the Tathāgata.”"

msgid "a50b2ce17f8e422faa735a78bbf0ca49"
msgstr ""
"Then the Blessed One attained the tathāgata absorption called display of the"
" emanation of the buddha domain exactly as it is."

msgid "ae3371fb21ff417cbbb83e77d5f48e1b"
msgstr ""
"As soon as he had attained that absorption, by his buddha power a pavilion, "
"a veritable buddha abode, appeared in the atmosphere between the desire "
"realm and the form realm. This occurred due to the roots of virtue of the "
"Tathāgata."

msgid "d3b778c219024f42ba402078525fcb98"
msgstr ""
"It purified the thinking of bodhisattvas, illuminated the realms of the "
"worlds of the ten directions, fulfilled the aspirations of countless "
"sentient beings, eclipsed the palaces of the gods, and inspired bodhisattvas"
" everywhere."

msgid "fec72f99faa240f89fb36a035a82a433"
msgstr "This pavilion had a foundation shaped like a white beryl."

msgid "38142e595e514c8293bbacba1b5d25d1"
msgstr ""
"It comprised mansions made of gold extracted from the Jambu River, archways "
"of red gems, portals of emeralds, terraces constructed of jewels, and altars"
" crafted from radiant gems."

msgid "0d310063819c45f280eb9ef2acf0a60e"
msgstr ""
"Its upper stories consisted of brightly glowing precious stones with "
"coverings of all kinds of jewels and adorned with dangling pearl rosaries, "
"parasols, victory banners, raised standards, and fluttering silk tassels. It"
" was praised and as vast as the extent of the trichiliocosm."

msgid "afb2247f3a784c48800b7bc37342b978"
msgstr "The pavilion was anointed with rare and precious sandalwood."

msgid "0f9d11f180ca4f08b1f1bcd0c67cbb7f"
msgstr ""
"It was perfumed with the enchanting fragrance of superior sandalwood. It was"
" scented by the noble essence of aloeswood, the best of fragrances."

msgid "3ddada7d46614bcb823baa0b9d3807d3"
msgstr "It was strewn with precious flowers and nāga pearls."

msgid "d96c86b723024f0e9b008398b9642a03"
msgstr ""
"It was adorned with flower arrangements of scattered flower petals, fine "
"trees, and gorgeous ornaments."

msgid "6fe6fa5fe37743f1ab94398d818f6eaa"
msgstr ""
"The pavilion was everywhere aglitter with variegated arrangements of "
"beautiful ornaments, as many as exist in all the world systems."

msgid "8275b9248f4645d89b48cc7df72eeb50"
msgstr ""
"It also featured many strikingly beautiful lion thrones—many tens of "
"billions, countless, of all different kinds, alluring, lofty, superb, broad,"
" and immense."

msgid "9e9616a6b4ff4373beca21d40e5c547f"
msgstr ""
"In this world system appeared four thousand staircases framed by terraces "
"the height of seven men and half a mile across."

msgid "33d83642b09846beb69eb7a58e882c5c"
msgstr ""
"They were fashioned from precious sapphire and deep blue sapphire and "
"adorned with canopies of all other manner of gems."

msgid "967508a8b46f421f8ce7456f8d45182b"
msgstr ""
"They were festooned with golden jewels and other precious stones and "
"enveloped by the sound of filigrees of chimes."

msgid "4f19bd9635ef40f5907be1d1b472b7fd"
msgstr ""
"These stairways soared from the ground level all the way up to the pavilion."
" They were straight and steady."

msgid "51ad6cd79d6849d9847a38fd9453ad89"
msgstr ""
"Just as in this world system, such great staircases rose in all the world "
"systems of the trichiliocosm."

msgid "8cbc2620196c413aad5ade0cf8e3a116"
msgstr ""
"At this point the Blessed One mindfully and deliberately emerged from that "
"state of meditative absorption."

msgid "5cc7e1fd544046c9ba52a504a08ba197"
msgstr ""
"As soon as he did, the world systems of the trichiliocosm trembled six times"
" and were brightly illuminated."

msgid "f59cfb4d5f5c426abf6fbcb4f59a0040"
msgstr ""
"Then the Blessed One was together with a host of bodhisattvas and a host of "
"śrāvakas, the host of bodhisattvas surrounding him and the host of śrāvakas "
"in front of and behind him."

msgid "d55c15df75fd47779e381b06e7e0ccdc"
msgstr "Gods and nāgas praised him and caused a great rain of flower petals."

msgid "c92abe9dffbb4c1184e610d31e093e86"
msgstr ""
"They bestowed many garments on him and caused a great rain of copious "
"powders, perfumes, and lotions, all to the sound of cymbals and various "
"melodies."

msgid "544cb9a24d8b41f7834801cadd4afa17"
msgstr "The entire universe shook and lit up brightly."

msgid "748d86b692ce4c2b8de5d81f4e5dfb19"
msgstr ""
"Thereupon the whole assembly departed from Vulture Peak through the might of"
" the Buddha: his miraculous powers, miraculous displays, great leadership, "
"blessing, splendor, benediction, and magical abilities."

msgid "3d7dcf438cbe4e4eb3d26fd8262c453c"
msgstr ""
"Many tens of millions of gods, nāgas, yakṣas, gandharvas, asuras, garuḍas, "
"kiṃnaras, and mahoragas followed in order to attend the Buddha, ascending "
"the central jewel-encrusted staircase leading to the pavilion."

msgid "271f46b535294c798573c5d306591528"
msgstr ""
"Aware that the Blessed One had proceeded to the staircase, the "
"Catur­mahā­rājakāyika gods, such as the Catur­mahā­rājas, showered clouds of"
" divine flower petals on him in worship."

msgid "b68af1b328b2463fbbe596b7d6d597ea"
msgstr "They joined their palms and praised him with the following words:"

msgid "5c50779fdf994ea9b15fe42fb10fba71"
msgstr ""
"“The light of the sun, the moon, fire, and jewels, and the immaculate divine"
" light of the heavenly realms, are all outshone by the light of the Capable "
"One, which pacifies the three lower destinies."

msgid "dded9157e4894e38bd793a0c91296ecf"
msgstr ""
"This light razes Mount Meru and the surrounding peaks, and it illuminates "
"the buddhafields."

msgid "3b10738f9e2d4d92b06a72438e1be669"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, we joyously take refuge in the Victor who has accomplished all "
"aims.”"

msgid "3d8dbd3c90a547a4aa01b12327eb56e2"
msgstr ""
"After the Catur­mahā­rājakāyika gods had praised the Blessed One with this "
"verse, they joined the procession to attend to him."

msgid "3d783f626dea4b7e985609d8a607d9b2"
msgstr ""
"At this point, the gods of Trāyastriṃśa, such as Śakra, the lord of the "
"gods, became aware that the Blessed One had proceeded to the staircase, and "
"they showered clouds of divine perfume on him in worship."

msgid "fc2274257092456a82f218254c0274f3"
msgstr "They joined their palms and praised him with the following words:"

msgid "fb76afe29eae41f9984bb427d1f2b608"
msgstr ""
"“You attained the most excellent miraculous powers and display unrivaled "
"emanations."

msgid "10b25f44237c4f9a8e0e63b1bf917ccb"
msgstr "You rose like the supreme sun pervading vast numbers of buddhafields."

msgid "316bb9ce6ea6466bbe84dd936f62e98c"
msgstr ""
"The Buddha adorns all buddhafields, beautifying them with his own qualities."

msgid "832c1885c39b40358d4a7cd2827a1d73"
msgstr "Homage to the unrivaled and unmatched master of miracles!”"

msgid "b50b74cbd7324f3f95f1a2c3af2849d2"
msgstr ""
"After the gods of Trāyastriṃśa had praised the Blessed One with this verse, "
"they joined the procession to attend to him."

msgid "be47127ef0714546884a8fee45df52dd"
msgstr ""
"At this point, the gods of Yāma, such as Suyāma, the king of the gods, "
"noticed that the Blessed One was ascending the staircase, and they showered "
"clouds of divine garments on him in worship."

msgid "d35586f9f5be4aa2b532dcf956c91d32"
msgstr "They joined their palms and praised him with the following words:"

msgid "c27da9c0face4fcd8bb06e0a4409d958"
msgstr ""
"“Sugata, your knowledge is vast and boundless, so you know the wishes of "
"beings."

msgid "8d6e751fca9a4040b00ce9941ccb300a"
msgstr ""
"Your omniscience, vast as space and without attachment to the threefold path"
" teachings,"

msgid "f1a59b51b2f54f2bbcef584bbd03fc2b"
msgstr ""
"Fathoms the whole range of thoughts of sentient beings through a single "
"mental event."

msgid "9e929556675d4184b4e19ddcfd21b7c8"
msgstr "Therefore, you deserve praise from everyone in all three existences.”"

msgid "0797a6fa5f724ce69582a0aa850c28c7"
msgstr ""
"After the gods of Yāma had praised the Blessed One with this verse, they "
"joined the procession to attend to him."

msgid "4317ba2e61834345a29d10928f45785d"
msgstr ""
"At this point, the gods of Tuṣita, such as Pramodita, the king of the gods, "
"noticed that the Blessed One was ascending the staircase, and they showered "
"clouds of divine jewels on him in worship."

msgid "aaea51f9ed354499b0f8d64566f46744"
msgstr "They joined their palms and praised him with the following words:"

msgid "e0e19ba28d894f4b8d35070f835e7114"
msgstr ""
"“Since phenomena are without sound or expression, without coming or going,"

msgid "8984f4cf2ac1421abfd30e31bfa6b3b2"
msgstr ""
"You know them to be without motion and untrue, like a mirage or "
"hallucination."

msgid "bd06592e10a843d3b81921a55dd46d0e"
msgstr ""
"The Blessed One teaches the supreme Dharma out of compassion for the sake of"
" beings."

msgid "83f7073d1ab24e6380c027103a401278"
msgstr ""
"We pay homage to the Victor who is skilled in the nature of phenomena and "
"who teaches no self.”"

msgid "b8e7c8cef5414836858cb24d1007ffdc"
msgstr ""
"After the gods of Tuṣita had praised the Blessed One with this verse, they "
"joined the procession to attend to him."

msgid "ef718f0f787040df806f3196c03929dd"
msgstr ""
"At this point, the gods of Nirmāṇarati, such as Sunirmāṇarati, the king of "
"the gods, noticed that the Blessed One was ascending the staircase, and they"
" showered clouds of divine ornaments on him in worship."

msgid "98a89c1a952c4c9f9adb0230f6f8922a"
msgstr "They joined their palms and praised him with the following words:"

msgid "e6fe424eb72a423b824776d16335395f"
msgstr ""
"“Through the boon of the Dharma, you possess ten space-like strengths and "
"luminosity."

msgid "17d26512878445c08885228578c34325"
msgstr ""
"Because you possess compassion, you appear tangibly before sentient beings "
"with loving regard."

msgid "f624c89d477042fdb0087c5d4b85f42e"
msgstr ""
"Although you have entered the nonduality of phenomena in the manner of a "
"ship,"

msgid "d682e00d9af94dac8bd01c3525be0e3e"
msgstr ""
"We pay homage to the Victor who has accomplished all aims with a special "
"intention enhanced by Dharma.”"

msgid "20f5b11ef3d742449424aae24cced8c9"
msgstr ""
"After the gods of Nirmāṇarati had praised the Blessed One with this verse, "
"they joined the procession to attend to him."

msgid "1934a6046cc6409599098a3d78251788"
msgstr ""
"At this point, the gods of Para­nirmitavaśavartin, such as Vaśavartin, the "
"king of the gods, noticed that the Blessed One had ascended the staircase "
"and was now facing the pavilion, and they showered clouds of divine pearl "
"garlands on him in worship."

msgid "73cf80cb6a694dfcb02fe9df097f9c11"
msgstr "They joined their palms and praised him with the following words:"

msgid "b07240821c334a71b4174db7c7e05c61"
msgstr ""
"“We pay homage at the feet of the master, whose moral conduct is stainless, "
"pure, perfected, and excellent, and whose absorption is stable, The "
"incomparably intelligent one who is like the ocean, who is liberated from "
"existence."

msgid "c024dc8050a64ff7b657be364191cafb"
msgstr ""
"We pay homage to you, the Lion Sugata who progressively delineates the "
"various aspects of the true path out of compassion filled with loving "
"kindness, And who dwells in the way stations of the three liberations."

msgid "4b7fc017415a4faaaa83d728bf85fa3e"
msgstr "Who broadens the river of compassion through absorption,"

msgid "9e71ad88668146ec9353df996ee39593"
msgstr ""
"Who opens the petals of tranquil abiding on the flowers of liberation,"

msgid "15c5dffe371240d48e3dc83dce8cd0d1"
msgstr "And who is attended by an assembly of disciples like swarming bees."

msgid "a5a148de21bd441cb8451275d382609b"
msgstr "“We pay homage respectfully to you, Lotus Sugata"

msgid "1e69ca83858943d69920b3d584505c58"
msgstr "Who is established on the ground of firm moral conduct,"

msgid "8f752d121c2947f982f34e51aa2e8d19"
msgstr "Who has risen up through the power of unrivaled energy,"

msgid "a73d994aa4434fcbbc883f076ee2a0d1"
msgstr "And who is not shaken by the great tempest of the winds of objects."

msgid "24000f1decea428d8f060a348032e4d0"
msgstr "“We pay homage to you, Sacred Mountain Buddha"

msgid "0670bba3efa24392942a1144a5893286"
msgstr "Who is a pure maṇḍala of melodies,"

msgid "214df4d38d2c4ab6b3cccf3e5fec1fa7"
msgstr "Whose mind treasury of supreme intelligence is overwhelming,"

msgid "08c689c6367944ee9f77c7b6b60fe10a"
msgstr "And to whom hundreds of sentient beings attend with many offerings."

msgid "6164217b16b34f90b52bc2b3294428cf"
msgstr "“We pay homage to you, Moon Sugata"

msgid "789b805c20574a41b82dc95e4ff3a72e"
msgstr ""
"Who proceeds on the path of full emancipation of peace, which is like the "
"sky,"

msgid "642e9b024fee4d8dad1223cddcb11704"
msgstr ""
"Who suffuses the expanse of the ten directions with the rays of insight,"

msgid "7479293c0e2f44129d4933485a586648"
msgstr "And who opens the incomparable lotus flowers of many beings."

msgid "e3a0197020b34518b7ce943db43e86a4"
msgstr "“We pay homage to you, Noble Sun Buddha"

msgid "bfaff713492148de8eca4b064cfb99c5"
msgstr "“Master, in the three worlds and ten directions"

msgid "09d21ef6b1c24e5bb2d45a0b5fdebdaf"
msgstr "We find no guide equal to you."

msgid "b4aa5caa665641ce9cb45b9ee6b22d2c"
msgstr "You who have accomplished all the buddha qualities—"

msgid "786186d210d94790aa31b1ba20d0d5de"
msgstr "We can never get enough of praising you."

msgid "bf997452871746b0909270de2dfccd59"
msgstr "The celestial rulers, nāgas, and asuras pay tribute to you,"

msgid "12fa2023191f4fb0843158d427f03aa3"
msgstr "And many hundreds of supreme gods truly extoll you."

msgid "5edd2693e89a465d9f471c2275b285ad"
msgstr "You are truly extolled by many hundreds of eulogies.”"

msgid "d6160420b5d44307ae02af794e60ec3d"
msgstr "“We pay homage to you, Honorable Sugata."

msgid "a9ad1c25eceb406e825e9e502d2b9125"
msgstr ""
"After the gods of Para­nirmitavaśavartin had praised the Blessed One with "
"these verses, they joined the procession to attend to him."

msgid "3b0ac1776fce4c21bc2d773428880892"
msgstr ""
"After the many gods had thus praised the vast display of the buddha domain, "
"the Buddha entered the pavilion called Jeweled Array."

msgid "cb7278a7883e47468fa7c37b721864d8"
msgstr ""
"Just as they realized that the Blessed One had gone to the pavilion Jeweled "
"Array via the staircase in this world system of Endurance, they realized "
"that he had also done so in all the world systems of the trichiliocosm."

msgid "47a7490f44d9486d9f2fc0ce36d9dcde"
msgstr ""
"At this point, the Blessed One sat down on the lion throne that had been "
"prepared in the pavilion Jeweled Array, encompassed by the trichiliocosm."

msgid "c90c34ae92fa4a298ffe2f86ee07d032"
msgstr "The bodhisattvas and the great śrāvakas also took their seats."

msgid "756295a0c31747ea905ba605bbc21a0c"
msgstr ""
"At this time, the Blessed One attained a buddha absorption called buddha "
"play in unveiled liberation."

msgid "b8fc08905c2748c19478f6b5948e667b"
msgstr ""
"No sooner had he attained that absorption than as many light rays as there "
"are grains of sand in the river Ganges shone forth from each and every pore "
"of his body."

msgid "a9135f93bc8d44fea9e61ce16d117b0d"
msgstr ""
"They illuminated all the world systems in the eastern, southern, western, "
"and northern directions. They illuminated the zenith and the nadir, and the "
"intermediate directions as well."

msgid "1c1052b558874f1cb475c57e9096d0b8"
msgstr ""
"As soon as all the world systems had been illuminated in this way, the "
"suffering experienced by sentient beings tormented in the hell realms "
"ceased."

msgid "3d421d9df7f846b9999ee3033f07347e"
msgstr ""
"The suffering experienced by beings in the world of Yama and the suffering "
"experienced by beings in the animal realm also ceased."

msgid "b8a1c9fb1f034017a1ebfb0df65dbfed"
msgstr ""
"In that instant, attachment, aversion, delusion, and all the other "
"afflictive emotions ceased to afflict sentient beings, who all became kind "
"and loving, and considered beings to be like their parents."

msgid "18e4d106784d4953bb03126f83132c01"
msgstr ""
"In order to invite the bodhisattvas through the Buddha’s might, the "
"following verses emanated from the light rays streaming from the Tathāgata:"

msgid "062f640063af411a86d910a68516ce99"
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha sets out thanks to a vast, expansive, and enduring energy."

msgid "0af029d7ef78429f9ade2a1f354e3e5c"
msgstr ""
"Through this great energy, he has refrained from turning back throughout the"
" ages."

msgid "2bf53536f3c1457dbf14786d8f719b4c"
msgstr "His qualities are conveyed forcefully in the ten directions."

msgid "00ee995ba3414225818899b395e2aaa1"
msgstr "The radiance of Śākyamuni is beautiful in illuminating all destinies."

msgid "7deeb9a7d32044009c61e0da0af40047"
msgstr ""
"“Some pay homage at his feet in order to listen to the vast, unsurpassed "
"teachings."

msgid "6f4a41df68c24b968503906c83772d36"
msgstr ""
"Those firm in learning and intelligence listen continuously for countless "
"eons."

msgid "b5a93c0a11874a7aaf55cd42d95332ff"
msgstr ""
"Those with open minds generate contentment through their aspiration for "
"perfect awakening."

msgid "ef42418b39e346f9a6743d35598f62b9"
msgstr ""
"The Capable One radiates light with his wish for sentient beings to be "
"happy."

msgid "49ebe6631cce477ab41c93d15ae4c69c"
msgstr ""
"“Since the master has energetically conquered hosts of powerful demons and "
"non-Buddhists,"

msgid "d3f3ad589a9345ef8da5bab68e05842a"
msgstr ""
"He is eminent like a lotus in bloom, beautiful like the Merus in the ten "
"directions."

msgid "e0f764b25b554b6b9f02eae7ded64d32"
msgstr ""
"Like the sun, he illuminates all destinies with the radiance of his physical"
" form."

msgid "350d69a0833e4c84bff375d11e482e99"
msgstr ""
"We pray that the Victor comes so that the great meaning in his Dharma wheel "
"may be heard."

msgid "e56d6ab547d04de09a4193a32e97d506"
msgstr ""
"“Out of heartfelt love for beings, he will today, with his ten strengths, "
"turn the sacred wheel, Which he has not yet turned, which is unrivaled, and "
"which is turned by all the victors."

msgid "dc3e8e788dfe4ea7ba028713ecfe4f10"
msgstr ""
"Upheld by living beings, today this vast good fortune, so rare for beings to"
" encounter, will arise."

msgid "5dbeae1e722f47e2bdfd0553cd5b47ab"
msgstr "Today may those with pure and vast faith behold what they seek.”"

msgid "845acd7972404b8090b75db96b8d3dec"
msgstr "The light rays transmitted these words to all buddhafields."

msgid "e8cab57396a44307844a9d4cfce85ce7"
msgstr ""
"They invited all bodhisattvas, made all world systems tremble, made all "
"sentient beings happy, and purified all elements of the afflictive emotions."

msgid "e017624fa41546d69b8b18b9afb908fa"
msgstr ""
"The light rays illuminated Tamondha­kāra and obscured the dwelling places "
"of Māra."

msgid "bc7f4537705f438d92be6d1e1a042e30"
msgstr ""
"They then returned to the immense circle of bodhisattvas and the world "
"system of Endurance, where they disappeared into the top of the Blessed "
"One’s head."

msgid "88a62a96d9c34951860a0da44bef51b5"
msgstr ""
"The light rays first invited the bodhisattva "
"Puṣpaśrī­garbha­sarva­dharma­vaśavartin to come. He resided in a buddhafield"
" situated in the east, called Endowed with the Vast Display of the Precious "
"Merits of Endless Qualities, of the Tathāgata Immaculate Pure Precious "
"Light, Sovereign of the Uninterrupted Luminous Display of Dharma Endowed "
"with the Factors of Awakening."

msgid "beda93f13f0c4adc82af965d2c707524"
msgstr ""
"As soon as the light rays reached this bodhisattva, as many bodhisattvas as "
"there are grains of sand in ten Ganges rivers surrounded and followed him in"
" honor. They all left that buddhafield together and arrived in an instant in"
" this world system of Endurance."

msgid "260b4ddc7ad64e7183c4ade41bda0b41"
msgstr ""
"Once they had approached the Blessed One inside the pavilion Jeweled Array, "
"they prostrated at his feet."

msgid "3013e04a2e9a481caf4031603909bd12"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated him ten thousand times and in worship showered a "
"multitude of divine gems and beryl upon him."

msgid "590a357713794c8c9a44e00c55fda183"
msgstr "Then they praised him with these words:"

msgid "150fe2e994f74c719c45bf5208558571"
msgstr "“Blessed One, incomparable and endowed with perfected qualities—"

msgid "41f1b60191ae439aa699c9c56ff78056"
msgstr ""
"Garlands of praise in honor of your qualities reverberate in all ten "
"directions!"

msgid "8c87cf87e84645f5b63de37ead2a365d"
msgstr "Your qualities are many—a treasury of good qualities."

msgid "fdc968097b0948ff8cdb06534daf5d91"
msgstr "We come here in pursuit of the Dharma."

msgid "ebe285548bad425484ca4823c6a25fbd"
msgstr ""
"“Just as there is no conceptuality in the sameness of the realm of "
"phenomena,"

msgid "3924dde632fe4084b3e5fa19b58eeccb"
msgstr "So the Blessed One knows sameness through his stainless light."

msgid "411d8b88170b4115ae83213ae0a28beb"
msgstr "Like a well-trained magician, the Dharma king"

msgid "9ec2f3b8f17148d5a3c8717f25cc6064"
msgstr "Presents various Dharmas in order to liberate sentient beings.”"

msgid "ff1fe390076649119d4ba8a7433e8063"
msgstr ""
"Once those bodhisattvas had praised the Blessed One with countless "
"bodhisattva eulogies, they withdrew to the eastern corner of the pavilion "
"and sat down upon seats created by their own miraculous power."

msgid "73a64bf532fc4ad78b9f0586b2cba970"
msgstr ""
"Then the light rays invited the bodhisattva Ratnayaṣṭi to come. He resided "
"in a buddhafield situated in the south, called Buddha Courage, of the "
"Tathāgata Countless Qualities Precious Courage."

msgid "d30a30c26e22452ca01208fc3ede0bd1"
msgstr ""
"As the light rays reached him, as many bodhisattvas as there are grains of "
"sand in ten Ganges rivers surrounded and followed him in honor."

msgid "3a906f43ef474cfbb56347ec0825ce15"
msgstr ""
"They all left that buddhafield together and arrived in an instant in this "
"world system of Endurance."

msgid "0226565c143f490fa14dcb6ecc29eb82"
msgstr ""
"Once they had approached the Blessed One inside the pavilion Jeweled Array, "
"they prostrated at his feet."

msgid "a77aad1ded16459692f35d4ee8d0bf99"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated him ten thousand times and in worship draped the "
"Blessed One with filigrees of gold."

msgid "d687f609d2484321b36509fc93e8c335"
msgstr "Then they praised him with these words:"

msgid "4327f66b8c8a47fe914e21eb637a61e4"
msgstr "“Blessed One, you fill the whole world with clouds of compassion,"

msgid "ab0ef9c8a9134e2082ca1ab82cdec1bb"
msgstr ""
"You wield the lightning bolts and roar the sounds of ‘empty’ and ‘no self,’"

msgid "0105bb7ec53c42379643a76f352fa699"
msgstr "You pacify it with the waters of the eightfold path,"

msgid "49e69fa09c2d49aeb0784076d76f3458"
msgstr "And you bring to maturity a forest grove of virtuous strengths."

msgid "d6fad2c6cbfe4993afc3666173768b87"
msgstr ""
"“You dispel the darkness of ignorance with the light of the sugata wisdom,"

msgid "1c382cb4f1464784ac0a2d0f2301755a"
msgstr ""
"You awaken sentient beings from their long slumber in the ocean of "
"existence,"

msgid "8b336fa7ac77483f900cc71216d0e737"
msgstr "You show the path and cause craving to dry up,"

msgid "215a085219e34d97a6a4c4270e85c585"
msgstr ""
"And you purify the vision of those dwelling in the city of liberation.”"

msgid "3987c98ce9d44110ae69f73d3d2a5ef7"
msgstr ""
"Once the bodhisattvas had praised the Blessed One with countless bodhisattva"
" eulogies, they withdrew to the southern corner of the pavilion and sat down"
" upon seats created by their own miraculous power."

msgid "7c16290d05fa4a9fa1ba617f75629c60"
msgstr ""
"Then the light rays invited the bodhisattva Sovereign of Powerful "
"Reverberating Sound to come. He resided in a buddhafield situated in the "
"west, called Illuminated, of the Tathāgata Illuminator. As the light rays "
"reached him, as many bodhisattvas as there are grains of sand in ten Ganges "
"rivers surrounded and followed him in honor."

msgid "4a6f310a052f491a9cdd9951b3fd1e1e"
msgstr ""
"They all left that buddhafield together and arrived in an instant in this "
"world system of Endurance."

msgid "b19b0490c7c6424d8cd7060f82d26f76"
msgstr ""
"Once they had approached the Blessed One inside the pavilion Jeweled Array, "
"they prostrated at his feet."

msgid "430a83e78f2949ffbd6e1978e3790f2d"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated him ten thousand times and in worship draped the "
"Blessed One with filigrees of pearl necklaces."

msgid "f3b0edcb5c734a4fae9260a32b34ea25"
msgstr "Then they praised him with these words:"

msgid "a1cff84abf2b4dc3b112ee019adc939b"
msgstr "“Your physical actions resemble the domain of space."

msgid "ef7879fe303d42649ea24f119ca52c6f"
msgstr "Your virtuous prayer is endowed with boundless purity."

msgid "96e63ec176764477adcb2b4dd639eacc"
msgstr "Since it is stainless, pure, and without defilements,"

msgid "ac2e402631ab4871a45627c13d45cad2"
msgstr "It purifies the inconceivable buddhafields of the ten directions."

msgid "a0112bc992aa4b75a0d08a6b7739aec7"
msgstr "“Your speech is steady, illuminating, and coherent."

msgid "abef317de6414f60ab63908b4cc9cc89"
msgstr "It appeases the dispositions of beings with uniformity of thought."

msgid "26d2038240114e71a02ca3e5f20475d6"
msgstr "Even though there is not the slightest mental movement or conception,"

msgid "d2b23a5962e349a0957d2734a45726cb"
msgstr "Victors arise in the minds of sentient beings.”"

msgid "a4ce6f25bf654748bbd95133ac31b4d8"
msgstr ""
"Once the bodhisattvas had praised the Blessed One with countless bodhisattva"
" eulogies, they withdrew to the western corner of the pavilion and sat down "
"upon seats created by their own miraculous power."

msgid "24cbfa87e2e246f1a1827348f9e03e48"
msgstr ""
"Then the light rays invited the bodhisattva Ocean of Supreme Intelligence to"
" come. He resided in a buddhafield situated in the north, called Fully "
"Adorned with Jewels, of the Tathāgata Countless Qualities Precious Courage."

msgid "f3cdf406ef1a4416b2eb1d32e8073850"
msgstr ""
"As the light rays reached him, as many bodhisattvas as there are grains of "
"sand in ten Ganges rivers surrounded and followed him in honor."

msgid "b2cc1071e70a4b8db20e119627794b12"
msgstr ""
"They all left that buddhafield together and arrived in an instant in this "
"world system of Endurance."

msgid "3a249ed7cfe545d5a8bf53b5d739de8f"
msgstr ""
"Once they had approached the Blessed One inside the pavilion Jeweled Array, "
"they prostrated at his feet."

msgid "475b6f5c8c5c4e86a0b8351b01be0415"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated him ten thousand times and in worship draped the "
"Blessed One with filigrees of crystals and jewels."

msgid "3c0bae22d7e14cc4ae4e4c34f90ce800"
msgstr "Then they praised him with these words:"

msgid "8df4cab6e2454a158695c901e428226d"
msgstr "“Your golden body is like refined gold from the Jambu River."

msgid "a1f3fda64487462e8749cdb1c5a3cdd0"
msgstr ""
"Possessing the all-seeing eye, it shines throughout the ten directions."

msgid "002ada8343664500b58a73d546b04369"
msgstr "The beings who think of this unique form"

msgid "5489d5907ad243b9bdce2308516c562b"
msgstr "Will achieve flawless bliss and joy."

msgid "696f9e9508684f868e7b1b267ca8dcc4"
msgstr ""
"“Even when one gazes upon the Victor, The unique knower of the world, as "
"tall as Mount Meru,"

msgid "81b88d4d83554a50ad277b655bcaf52c"
msgstr ""
"Because of the force of all his miraculous powers and the display of his "
"energy One is unable to see this Victor’s crown protuberance.”"

msgid "1a7db1ad56c74d52b383a6375ee0657d"
msgstr ""
"Once the bodhisattvas had praised the Blessed One with countless bodhisattva"
" eulogies, they withdrew to the northern corner of the pavilion and sat down"
" upon seats created by their own miraculous power."

msgid "95506c9adcab47eca98be3a96fab0ed6"
msgstr ""
"Then the light rays invited the bodhisattva Illuminator to come. He resided "
"in a buddhafield situated in the southeast, called Sorrowless, of the "
"Tathāgata Conqueror of All Sorrow."

msgid "cbf05a8aacb04ac3846c4dc972bfc558"
msgstr ""
"As the light rays reached him, as many bodhisattvas as there are grains of "
"sand in ten Ganges rivers surrounded and followed him in honor."

msgid "9e7249ec23c54b22817c396e95a29a41"
msgstr ""
"They all left that buddhafield together and arrived in an instant in this "
"world system of Endurance."

msgid "33ee4c202b1c43129ba6cdd6464c71af"
msgstr ""
"Once they had approached the Blessed One inside the pavilion Jeweled Array, "
"they prostrated at his feet."

msgid "ef427f6fb12245ef8ca63c74d6e72847"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated him ten thousand times and in worship draped the "
"Blessed One with filigrees of jewels."

msgid "fad3a3918d5546a1bcc7d906ee5cf008"
msgstr "Then they praised him with these words:"

msgid "80ed64fb8bed47a79e5c292d09deb8c9"
msgstr ""
"“Although each of your bodily hairs contains boundless buddhafields, Neither"
" the beings nor the fields themselves are compressed."

msgid "b21e0e6c005e4b4f9213245e41c4ec65"
msgstr ""
"Hence those without eyes to see find it difficult to fathom the domain of "
"the Victor."

msgid "ae13c8629293480a83a2d0a46e6a4735"
msgstr ""
"The children of the Buddha know it correctly through the benevolence of the "
"Victor."

msgid "6a8483b80b0e41029d913a4e3539adfb"
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha demonstrates a multiplicity of fields in the space of a single "
"field."

msgid "ec7d69d02e7d425382a2c0b48118ff2d"
msgstr "Although he displays this, there is neither increase nor decrease."

msgid "27168accfcee4dddbb5619d75647d100"
msgstr "To those who are suited to it and whose intentions are great,"

msgid "1360c5f4c0b04e0ab17b595f59985a1f"
msgstr ""
"He demonstrates it through the display of his vast miraculous powers.”"

msgid "049a5e6fa74f4ed2a4b1d4a73e0dba2f"
msgstr ""
"Once the bodhisattvas had praised the Blessed One with countless bodhisattva"
" eulogies, they withdrew to the southeastern area of the pavilion and sat "
"down upon seats created by their own miraculous power."

msgid "d2397821c2e74517b70d08142191dd6a"
msgstr ""
"Then the light rays invited the bodhisattva Mind of Great Compassion to "
"come. He resided in a buddhafield situated it the southwest, called Virtuous"
" Eye, of the Tathāgata Gazing at All Beings with Great Compassion."

msgid "b7da21ccee3f49578c429b910c175e3f"
msgstr ""
"As the light rays reached him, as many bodhisattvas as there are grains of "
"sand in ten Ganges rivers surrounded and followed him in honor."

msgid "bf991171ee82442d834566a63d683e7f"
msgstr ""
"They all left that buddhafield together and arrived in an instant in this "
"world system of Endurance."

msgid "18e482a423ca4339b8b4882a8c718c16"
msgstr ""
"Once they had approached the Blessed One inside the pavilion Jeweled Array, "
"they prostrated at his feet."

msgid "5c93df250caf4717acb1ff6832250ae4"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated him ten thousand times and in worship draped the "
"Blessed One with filigrees of fine robes."

msgid "99fee6d9e2c74d5fb64cf58fc6c0a14b"
msgstr "Then they praised him with these words:"

msgid "1d2ea04c57124e2fbd18e25ba0c31f9b"
msgstr "“Just like a noble person who uses a flywhisk to chase away flies,"

msgid "83165c2752d44447ac052bc6ba873088"
msgstr ""
"The Buddha protects his stainless moral conduct as if it were a valuable "
"jewel."

msgid "601742068347445ab72bdf2ed8e68525"
msgstr ""
"When the protector gazes at those without moral conduct, he feels "
"compassion."

msgid "8485fafec19e472ab28b8223d11ee54e"
msgstr "He neither praises himself nor denigrates others."

msgid "223a19f44e8f46a399341fd49d10f306"
msgstr "“Like Meru, you are a stable, weighty, and vast support."

msgid "097b3d22b60844f8a658a00fe7b7fa7d"
msgstr ""
"Like the depths of the ocean, you are exceedingly difficult to fathom."

msgid "3946c627528f4d13bdb73dae9f8b508f"
msgstr "You have cast aside the primeval fetters of existence."

msgid "b74e50b35fe1485a9bff9788b1040f85"
msgstr ""
"You have liberated multitudes of beings from the fetters brought about by "
"great flaws.”"

msgid "93a030e664d34162997f46af2abe99d1"
msgstr ""
"Once the bodhisattvas had praised the Blessed One with countless bodhisattva"
" eulogies, they withdrew to the southwestern area of the pavilion and sat "
"down upon seats created by their own miraculous power."

msgid "405a5cf1a5e0411c8498a8dd63b8ee0b"
msgstr ""
"Then the light rays invited the bodhisattva Light-Web Bearer to come. He "
"resided in a buddhafield situated in the northwest, called Free of Darkness,"
" of the Tathāgata Sovereign Light Display. As the light rays reached him, as"
" many bodhisattvas as there are grains of sand in ten Ganges rivers "
"surrounded and followed him in honor."

msgid "333d76ea942a4824b20049c8404de76d"
msgstr ""
"They all left that buddhafield together and arrived in an instant in this "
"world system of Endurance."

msgid "b611cf297d0b4ba98d311bd4a12518f6"
msgstr ""
"Once they had approached the Blessed One inside the pavilion Jeweled Array, "
"they prostrated at his feet."

msgid "ef17c247207c4d9e9aefae506f4cd543"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated him ten thousand times and in worship draped the "
"Blessed One with filigrees of ornaments."

msgid "6d579439524e4a99b2e057691ffdb64b"
msgstr "Then they praised him with these words:"

msgid "5878ba8c27664a4e9753c42fcc204b50"
msgstr ""
"“Because you understand the nature of existence to be the nature of a "
"mirage,"

msgid "1f558a37e30a4e3f9dff5ca0f2b1f090"
msgstr "You reveal that actions are like illusions and lack substance."

msgid "4d92eb5ab0c24362b2745bb48440fc13"
msgstr "Even though you train the domains of beings, which are like a mirage,"

msgid "d373f3c4d6924082a39c9679bc65f604"
msgstr "Neither the domains nor the sentient beings exist for you."

msgid "398a98649a00467da00e697a955e6c81"
msgstr "“To give an analogy, in the dream of a sleeping person"

msgid "dbd2b05b30ab4cbaa259ebfaad5ddd10"
msgstr "The perception that sees form is not true seeing."

msgid "b970c7a77d034a87890cf5da5db2ba72"
msgstr "You teach that conditioned things lack substance, like a dream."

msgid "4b68b183649244918a91736a44331db1"
msgstr "Even though phenomena manifest, they do not come into being.”"

msgid "fbd1254bd8fe46ce860dd05a26c0bbea"
msgstr ""
"Once the bodhisattvas had praised the Blessed One with countless bodhisattva"
" eulogies, they withdrew to the northwestern area of the pavilion and sat "
"down upon seats created by their own miraculous power."

msgid "305c0ab33ca14b9c93f3a65c4c82bfcb"
msgstr ""
"Then the light rays invited the bodhisattva Immaculate Limitless "
"Intelligence to come. He resided in a buddhafield situated in the northeast,"
" called Pure Immaculate Dwelling, of the Tathāgata Immaculate Center of the "
"Sky."

msgid "9fcd84030e634474844044332a2185bc"
msgstr ""
"As the light rays reached him, as many bodhisattvas as there are grains of "
"sand in ten Ganges rivers surrounded and followed him in honor."

msgid "1dbb18d7db2f44aca2f723b1b52d101e"
msgstr ""
"They all left that buddhafield together and arrived in an instant in this "
"world system of Endurance."

msgid "82593ba0a25c40e2bebafd77170abd31"
msgstr ""
"Once they had approached the Blessed One inside the pavilion Jeweled Array, "
"they prostrated at his feet."

msgid "6e61dbf8ebaa45289a02df1a7236ebd7"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated him ten thousand times and in worship draped the "
"Blessed One with filigrees of continuously sounding cymbals."

msgid "13417b6da2764380a294f49e1682409f"
msgstr "Then they praised him with these words:"

msgid "7077c698adee4eec9005cb482793c7e0"
msgstr "“Skilled in profound Dharma and intent on peace,"

msgid "5b092fa6eede4751b501928f7808f4de"
msgstr "You know all phenomena to be empty and without conceptual signs."

msgid "1820bb18f3c04d8cab7f978c9140eeba"
msgstr "No one in the world can discern the intent of your mind;"

msgid "0f89481abe4a4308a977ce4d6ca88486"
msgstr "With vast intelligence, you understand the mind’s thought processes."

msgid "ddf94bfc060143ce914984401afd8601"
msgstr "“Just as you know the behavior of one being,"

msgid "91690f02cacc4a65a3090b28654ea9c7"
msgstr "You know the behaviors of all beings within the three times."

msgid "9926837496404a80b30e8855e2cc1395"
msgstr ""
"Without entertaining the notion of a being, you have mastered the full "
"knowledge"

msgid "5d761fd015274f0ea27663222fbf536c"
msgstr "Of the perceptions of those whose mental perception is obscured.”"

msgid "7e70b6bc2f13449a81840b84e22aebe0"
msgstr ""
"Once the bodhisattvas had praised the Blessed One with countless bodhisattva"
" eulogies, they withdrew to the northeastern area of the pavilion and sat "
"down upon seats created by their own miraculous power."

msgid "06dfdc247a4540999fd1ab9fa793ed16"
msgstr ""
"Then the light rays invited the bodhisattva Ornamental Display of Courage to"
" come. He resided in a buddhafield situated in the nadir, called Appearing "
"as Illumination, of the Tathāgata Glory of the Precious Red Lotus."

msgid "c198633ec2fd4168be9dd4ee136c04e8"
msgstr ""
"As the light rays reached him, bodhisattvas as numerous as sand grains in "
"the ten Ganges rivers surrounded and followed him in honor."

msgid "8664de1c84a54c38a795a8afe5c246cb"
msgstr ""
"They all left that buddhafield together and arrived in an instant in this "
"world system of Endurance."

msgid "d7c7edc2cb4540b9b481913a67998508"
msgstr ""
"Once they had approached the Blessed One inside the pavilion Jeweled Array, "
"they prostrated at his feet."

msgid "7117b338b5724317b240b11ad5e9d465"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated him ten thousand times and in worship draped the "
"Blessed One with filigrees of garlands from the isle of precious jewels."

msgid "7b8fd735b4134e81a095afa18b346c60"
msgstr "Then they praised him with these words:"

msgid "46a0375493cd497da61d838d0f939ca8"
msgstr "“As many atoms as there are in the multitude of buddhafields,"

msgid "cba8559822d04a9182f2bb17123adac1"
msgstr ""
"That many children of the tathāgatas have come together in front of the "
"Victor."

msgid "55d47afea6fb4baeb88a04b2ccca2b8f"
msgstr "With a single timely reply, he answers all the questions they pose"

msgid "f43d92d0a8564ac0913de350380d0cea"
msgstr "In the course of millions of eons."

msgid "d1eeeb3ee109428abe09b3ded190400e"
msgstr "“You have accomplished intellectual skills and wisdom."

msgid "6f6a70470c1248e0a75e0be8a53ac37c"
msgstr "Your retention, perfect absorption, and merit are vast."

msgid "f955d5b34e4e44bfaaba73732a201491"
msgstr "Even if we were to articulate eulogies for a vast number of eons,"

msgid "0fd9e00dd4034a3abfa3a981dd31ac4f"
msgstr ""
"They would be insufficient, just as the tip of a hair cannot hold an ocean.”"

msgid "347129ed29734e4592056fe426f2b775"
msgstr ""
"Once the bodhisattvas had praised the Blessed One with countless bodhisattva"
" eulogies, they withdrew to the lower part of the pavilion and sat down upon"
" seats created by their own miraculous power."

msgid "489469905b59427fa257163e30e399fc"
msgstr ""
"Then the light rays invited the bodhisattva Sovereign Who Emanates All "
"Phenomena to come. He resided in a buddhafield situated in the zenith, "
"called Adorned by Ornaments, of the Tathāgata Sovereign of Supreme "
"Reverberating Sound."

msgid "e0c19008ba2a485189c4eb529aa7cb6c"
msgstr ""
"As the light rays reached him, as many bodhisattvas as there are grains of "
"sand in ten Ganges rivers surrounded and followed him in honor."

msgid "99980703aa67436ca6fe7e8c704ef364"
msgstr ""
"They all left that buddhafield together and arrived in an instant in this "
"world system of Endurance."

msgid "1fc6ae45e4d848e78b0608d3ad162f8f"
msgstr ""
"Once they had approached the Blessed One inside the pavilion Jeweled Array, "
"they prostrated at his feet."

msgid "8590f95b725e4a8ab70178cd3c9c74bc"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated him ten thousand times and in worship draped the "
"Blessed One with filigrees of all kinds of ornaments, precious bells, and "
"tinkling bells."

msgid "902a0a98e8c747249ca056e4de9a2886"
msgstr "Then they praised him with these words:"

msgid "a1a081f2ecc844dfaade8a79724b8012"
msgstr "“The physical activity of the Sugata defies measure."

msgid "ed553d7982864f40a61eed15704e60a7"
msgstr "The speech, mind, and conduct of the unsurpassed ones are limitless."

msgid "c523816d24c040099ad2b4eae0b1dc18"
msgstr "The Buddha knows that, but other beings do not,"

msgid "f0c8ffa69f9c48b2b761fce822b39ced"
msgstr "Just as ordinary beings cannot grasp the limits of space."

msgid "ad4af5853aac4ac989f700bd12211332"
msgstr "“Just as the conduct of the incomparable one defies measure,"

msgid "b3e7ea2facab4dbcb7bb3c15ee9c39c4"
msgstr "So the wheel of awakening is nothing but nirvāṇa."

msgid "44eefdd427c04eff8ab3c99bc89697a1"
msgstr "Just as fruits emerge according to the seeds sown,"

msgid "713f25cc4292458dbf097d7e1d26e253"
msgstr ""
"So the state of the Victor knows no bounds anywhere in the ten directions.”"

msgid "206ecd94d1d745c2a59c5dbcdf0b2bf2"
msgstr ""
"Once the bodhisattvas had praised the Blessed One with countless bodhisattva"
" eulogies, they withdrew into the space above the pavilion and sat down upon"
" seats created by their own miraculous power."

msgid "fd419d4f1a174c8abea4505f9af82a96"
msgstr ""
"Thus the light rays invited the ten bodhisattvas of the ten directions, "
"together with their entourages of countless other bodhisattvas. They arrived"
" in an instant in this world system of Endurance, and they sat before the "
"Blessed One within the pavilion Jeweled Array."

msgid "3a974c9e146241608a5a6c0df30cd1fa"
msgstr ""
"As the Blessed One mindfully and deliberately rose from that absorption, he "
"cleared his throat and produced a sound, a melodious sound heard throughout "
"the entire trichiliocosm."

msgid "64078da57d2c454d8cde065317ff0af2"
msgstr ""
"Once all the faithful in the entire trichiliocosm, including the monks and "
"nuns, the laymen and laywomen, and the humans and nonhumans, heard the sound"
" of the Blessed One clearing his throat, they grew satisfied in body and "
"mind."

msgid "c6ca6376494144f9884528e3d6949c01"
msgstr ""
"By the power of the Buddha, they also arrived at the pavilion Jeweled Array "
"in an instant, that very moment, by means of the miraculously manifesting "
"staircases."

msgid "6f4e32f7f7664c2d8891bc9b42f06c21"
msgstr ""
"They prostrated at the Blessed One’s feet and took their designated seats "
"off to the side."

msgid "8e4bd59f50914838b6ec708588244273"
msgstr ""
"The sound of the Blessed One clearing his throat also inspired the gods of "
"the following realms: Brahmā, Brahmakāyika, Brahma­purohita, "
"Brahma­pariṣadya, and Mahābrahmā; Mahāprabha, Parīttābha, Apramāṇābha, and "
"Ābhāsvara; Parīttaśubha, Apramāṇaśubha, and Śubhakṛtsna; and Anabhraka, "
"Puṇyaprasava, Bṛhatphala, Asaṃjñisattva, Avṛha, Atapa, Sudṛśa, Sudarśana, "
"and Akaniṣṭha."

msgid "a088a004aa1d4d1280da9466ab90e663"
msgstr ""
"They too hastened in an instant, that very moment, to the pavilion Jeweled "
"Array."

msgid "695d23617daa482fb25e815b907828ec"
msgstr "They too prostrated at the Blessed One’s feet and took their seats."

msgid "28f62128e51f4222be51104b3a3f680e"
msgstr ""
"Then, when the Blessed One had comprehended that this large retinue had "
"assembled, a light called display of the strength of bodhisattvas sprang "
"from his forehead."

msgid "e9dabf96c1d641c48fa6f80ea029e14f"
msgstr ""
"That light swirled around the whole group of bodhisattvas seven times and "
"disappeared into the crowns of their heads."

msgid "16be320fb649464fb69f367ca170eddd"
msgstr ""
"Then, as soon as the light had touched the bodhisattva "
"Puṣpaśrī­garbha­sarva­dharma­vaśavartin, by the power of the Buddha he "
"attained the bodhisattva absorption called array of all ornaments."

msgid "008a1f3a90244d8a860717ad55128b77"
msgstr ""
"As soon as he had entered that absorption, a beautiful throne for the "
"Blessed One appeared in the center of the pavilion Jeweled Array."

msgid "44b9759c06b64606b4b81c52a5fdee45"
msgstr ""
"It was a raised lion throne the height of a gigantic palmyra tree. It rested"
" on different types of embellished supports and was decorated with all kinds"
" of precious things."

msgid "6071411ca3694eb3b20ee810577cbaa9"
msgstr ""
"It was draped in various types of cotton cloth and sprinkled with a variety "
"of flower petals."

msgid "d14b09fe40714530a644fe35e61c5fa8"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattvas held up an incredibly attractive parasol above the seat, "
"and the seat was visible to the entire assembly."

msgid "a035a15431194f25aefffdd974ff2553"
msgstr "It delighted and deeply gratified all sentient beings."

msgid "dc38e3efc2f8471dba44209efeff7e8f"
msgstr ""
"After the bodhisattva Puṣpaśrī­garbha­sarva­dharma­vaśavartin had conjured "
"up the tathāgata seat, the great lion throne called limitless inspiring "
"praise, he mindfully and deliberately emerged from that absorption."

msgid "296c2d87407e48af80d5d8cf9240c28a"
msgstr ""
"He spoke to the Blessed One, his palms joined in reverence, and said the "
"following:"

msgid "e7f20d99cf2b4ac588ff7e56d513ae58"
msgstr "“Sunlight sustains the needs of sentient beings."

msgid "dd35b06be4a6406197450fba42c6354f"
msgstr "The radiant qualities of Indra delight the gods of Trāyastriṃśa."

msgid "17307ef144244468a377feee174830f0"
msgstr "The voice of Brahmā embellishes the realm of Brahmā."

msgid "5dfcff9c005742f6a6dff74577f40840"
msgstr "The domain of the Buddha’s power brings forth this manifestation."

msgid "3cf7b7c30e844814bc5a771a09103922"
msgstr "“Phenomena are immovable, space-like and void,"

msgid "0160c25ec1c84faab42013b5929300bd"
msgstr "Illusory like a mirage and the reflection of the moon in water,"

msgid "6d46f84710e9491bb2dbd61341f1c618"
msgstr "And without a master, creator, or agent of experience."

msgid "f86f3fd07cae455ba41395cc2dc270e1"
msgstr ""
"Knowing this, the Protector displayed his accomplishment in this world."

msgid "ad5a2ddf2dd94bdaa4060a5e161a0b38"
msgstr "“The mind with its powers of creation is itself formless."

msgid "9faadb251106462f8860f36f5a4658d7"
msgstr "All accomplishments are subject to the nature of the mind."

msgid "361be15fef5643a7b270d8a5848fb337"
msgstr "Everything that is created in this world resembles an illusion."

msgid "d058607e8f8a4cf4a0d38b79da7bfc38"
msgstr "These accomplishments are not my own and do not exist anywhere."

msgid "cc76f78bab534706adacbf9cc9428519"
msgstr "“For the one who knows the pure nature of the mind that has ceased"

msgid "53db3bae35d94feca37fa2d4dd589035"
msgstr "There are no adventitious afflictive emotions."

msgid "03e71b90038a4d41a62411b78606134b"
msgstr "A mind free of discursive thought, concepts, and discriminations"

msgid "bb43e60d5d654463904804c9c7c74c01"
msgstr "Displays different illusory manifestations."

msgid "c7d18c7d8b4c4199a192ead13b3dfef5"
msgstr "“In this place where no dust rises from the ground"

msgid "92d5919640064339af3d7e91cd8f87a1"
msgstr "And different types of jewels are displayed,"

msgid "1d8c8b0502a94414ad6ef0117b2cacf3"
msgstr "Seated upon which you will tame millions of beings."

msgid "d25d499213474f83bd9951bdcfe74a9b"
msgstr "I made you a beautiful lion throne,"

msgid "84d4476d1297436bae8cc03aec28121a"
msgstr "“I hoisted parasols, victory banners, and tassels made of silk"

msgid "8d42c5fd2e394028ab95837144d0ff99"
msgstr "That neither come from nor go anywhere."

msgid "adc7dbb8ee4a41fca8d0de1dfdaad0f4"
msgstr "While knowing whence phenomena come together,"

msgid "6716402a7795497bb4e378618aeb848d"
msgstr "You display the different manifestations of a noble being."

msgid "8d2ab6c06cda46f7a2c05ae6e2250d35"
msgstr "“Possessing the voice of Brahmā, your words are fine and reassuring."

msgid "09cd61dd01664cd4a26d0aed1f4b4bf9"
msgstr ""
"Since you are the lamp of the world, your deeds are filled with the "
"brilliance of merit."

msgid "f247e2fb50c84b1786384ad5e2357937"
msgstr "Ascend the throne and be seated there, out of compassion for me."

msgid "c6a9b39499c74aaf9448208df2245868"
msgstr "Please teach the Dharma that severs old age, sickness, and death."

msgid "6aed455a30d1443282565e1a39d0ae54"
msgstr "In order to pay homage to you and hear the Dharma."

msgid "bfd414bbdbb34bac91d055f2e68f7881"
msgstr "“These pure beings have come together from all quarters"

msgid "f864aea3f85b48dab01ebc63c557215b"
msgstr "Please fulfil the aspirations for which they have come,"

msgid "320ebc3780344f71a4541d32ac47b6c2"
msgstr "And explain the Dharma while seated on this lion throne.”"

msgid "d6e220976f954eeb894a707b6f4f5acd"
msgstr ""
"Recognizing the determination of the bodhisattva "
"Puṣpaśrī­garbha­sarva­dharma­vaśavartin, the Blessed One took his seat on "
"the lion throne."

msgid "3a11d43e40c44ee499832e0ee266b0b4"
msgstr ""
"The Blessed One, who had attained unobstructed liberation, thus sat on the "
"lion throne to teach the Dharma discourse The Gateway to Unobstructed "
"Deliverance through the Bodhisattva Way of Life."

msgid "1a168dae761b4183af70a51b5165e0ea"
msgstr ""
"This discourse focuses on setting out on the bodhisattva path that "
"accomplishes all profound buddha qualities: the strengths and four types of "
"fearlessness."

msgid "1219236f6509403984063eab0fa87fc0"
msgstr ""
"It is the source of wisdom, the gateway to the dhāraṇī seal that grants "
"mastery of all teachings."

msgid "5c9a136dea164fefb77ad48c80de670a"
msgstr ""
"It is a gateway that establishes the four types of discriminating knowledge."

msgid "b4b835d59bf34cb0b53efc85cac0b160"
msgstr "It is a gateway to the wisdom of great superknowledge."

msgid "390ca093320d4919ae94865b9651f2af"
msgstr ""
"It teaches the Dharma of nonorigination to the retinue of those who will not"
" be turned back from awakening."

msgid "0dcc40837f8d4b80a0e796aa0312e2a3"
msgstr "It condenses all vehicles into sameness, into a single vehicle."

msgid "44bda98c90014485a086ebaaf9b093e7"
msgstr "It enters the uncontaminated, unique realm of phenomena."

msgid "b12bdad917994572a8b939eb05b87a74"
msgstr "It engages the dispositions and faculties of all sentient beings."

msgid "2e767db8602241d8a6bee3e28f4398b0"
msgstr "This discourse is an essential teaching."

msgid "2e290179f8f6495596ad953af4e57ad0"
msgstr "It is a Dharma of total certainty."

msgid "14fe5371608d43bb948c3d8fa19ee4eb"
msgstr "It destroys the entire retinue of Māra."

msgid "627c6d1a39b84809af8d330e7b26fe3d"
msgstr "It leads to engagement in the appropriate Dharma methods."

msgid "403d08196a0046198fce42610c43e99b"
msgstr "It overcomes all afflictive emotions and views."

msgid "d76dd7f105a44c058e20e4e7d18f01a7"
msgstr "It accords with wisdom free of attachment."

msgid "65e79e87b4954e8e88c3e7066b3bc065"
msgstr ""
"It teaches skill in means and the wisdom of unobstructed dedication to the "
"roots of virtue."

msgid "c0a1201aabfc459893c9203b2a89fc2c"
msgstr "It leads to the wisdom of the sameness of all buddhas."

msgid "a6cf93f6a525447cbfafbced10cbde10"
msgstr "It is the gateway to the blessings of nonattachment."

msgid "7b3bdb17df2640f19da86329075e5583"
msgstr "It elaborates on the exact nature of all phenomena."

msgid "b77b517c32f245bc99eb52e7f42e7621"
msgstr ""
"This discourse leads to sameness free of discursive thought and concepts."

msgid "caa2978fbb514e9488da454469b2168b"
msgstr ""
"It brings about understanding of the sameness of the twelve links of "
"profound dependent arising due to accumulating all the collections of merit "
"and wisdom."

msgid "770ba38937f240dcb1cbe0d7e65526c8"
msgstr ""
"It is furnished with the ornament of the sameness of the body, speech, and "
"mind of the buddhas."

msgid "59a9dc62e15a422fa2d0f9bf7b6a6085"
msgstr ""
"It accomplishes inexhaustible mindfulness, intelligence, realization, "
"devotion, and wisdom."

msgid "6277f265757146e0b6404f91cca343d2"
msgstr ""
"It engages the method of the noble truths in order to tame beings through "
"the vehicle of the śrāvakas."

msgid "4249f85ddaf64a60aec2f410ca504f1f"
msgstr ""
"It knows the solitude of body, speech, and mind in order to tame beings "
"through the vehicle of the pratyekabuddhas."

msgid "2b93920f9e234a9d98a3e82e37d79c4c"
msgstr ""
"It attains the consecration at the stage of the wisdom of omniscience in "
"order to tame beings through the Great Vehicle."

msgid "6dbfe55fec074650b4efd7839b8a16f7"
msgstr ""
"Such a Dharma discourse leads to the mastery of all teachings in order to "
"express all the qualities of the Tathāgata. so that this discourse could be "
"taught, elucidated, explained, recited, memorized, and understood."

msgid "cf73c249a9ae4e2fb73207a07e23621e"
msgstr ""
"He did this to satisfy all the hosts of bodhisattvas, to display the "
"miraculous power of the Tathāgata, and to eliminate the doubts of the "
"retinue."

msgid "9f9262f8f6374439a6347a08e922443b"
msgstr ""
"He did it to defeat the entire retinue of Māra, to allow the teaching of the"
" Tathāgata blaze forth, and to perform great buddha activity."

msgid "63ddc8bd227641aca7e6810b338c5d43"
msgstr "The Blessed One took his seat on the lion throne"

msgid "8b39cd39ee944861b45982b638451fd0"
msgstr ""
"Then, by the power of the Buddha, the following events occurred. The "
"bodhisattva known as Ratnayaṣṭi attained the array of buddha ornaments "
"absorption and magically adorned the entire retinue with buddha ornaments."

msgid "0f2ce6d60e904a0e9e7414ce8dca537c"
msgstr ""
"Then the bodhisattva Sovereign of Powerful Reverberating Sound attained the "
"lotus array absorption and conjured up flower garlands and bouquets and "
"placed them in the hands of the entire retinue."

msgid "5ea1b829e152416aa6023d4848ccc833"
msgstr ""
"They proceeded to toss the flower garlands and the bouquets toward the "
"Blessed One and the gathering of bodhisattvas."

msgid "fc6d29c2ebf74e25b72e33db60d1e276"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattva named Ocean of Supreme Intelligence attained the fragrance "
"array absorption and magically infused the fragrance of sandalwood into all "
"the pores of the entire retinue."

msgid "000f39e2b49d46d5b4486ba11cff41d4"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattva named Light-Web Bearer attained the light array absorption "
"and magically imbued the entire retinue with limitless physical radiance."

msgid "446de1bdc82c4b7798656493f562ece8"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattva named Mind of Great Compassion attained the unblinking gaze "
"absorption and conjured upon the retinue an unblinking gaze when in the "
"presence of the Tathāgata."

msgid "a80cad42715d4f64a16015fd5a6f7341"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattva named Immaculate Limitless Intelligence attained the "
"absorption supremely delighted by the Dharma and magically imbued the entire"
" retinue with the zeal for righteousness and with delight in and devotion "
"toward the Dharma."

msgid "592f35aedd5f4d318481636494b0667e"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattva called Ornamental Display of Courage attained the completely"
" peaceful absorption and magically imbued the entire retinue with the "
"removal of the five obstructions."

msgid "38a5c04b2d7c4f0ea9b83c508196803d"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattva called Sovereign Who Emanates All Phenomena attained the "
"action devoid of forgetfulness absorption and magically imbued the entire "
"retinue with mindfulness of the thought of awakening and with remembrance of"
" the Tathāgata as the object of attention."

msgid "85a18ae36dc64514b49d37f68bbbb816"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattva mahāsattva Illuminator attained the undefeatable absorption "
"and magically imbued the entire retinue with the conquest of Māra and all "
"adversaries."

msgid "f0c611e1c4e94c9b9b53cb32af5286d0"
msgstr ""
"Then, at that time, by the power of the Buddha, the bodhisattva "
"Māra­pramardaka attained the conquering the entire retinue of Māra "
"absorption."

msgid "79cf680874af48878cf1b0ca8d9f82d3"
msgstr ""
"At the very moment that the bodhisattva Māra­pramardaka attained that "
"absorption, all the billion demons throughout the trichiliocosm, surrounded "
"by their armies and retinues of servants, disappeared very swiftly and "
"immediately from their individual residences."

msgid "b6ebe4bfbbbe41eaa0cbc80e7e0bdb17"
msgstr ""
"Appearing before the Blessed One in the pavilion Jeweled Array, they "
"prostrated themselves at his feet."

msgid "0361d8607ee94a59a4630cd554df2593"
msgstr ""
"They offered the Blessed One many hundreds of thousands of divine gifts, and"
" with their palms respectfully and reverently joined they asked the Blessed "
"One,"

msgid "bbe60d7505fb4e859344b5576fd4e3c2"
msgstr "“If we beseech you, Blessed One, ‘Please explain the Dharma!"

msgid "d6a55f29c3a548feb50d8b9050dfb3c7"
msgstr ""
"Sugata, please explain the Dharma!’ then, through the blessing of the "
"bodhisattva Māra­pramardaka, we will discard any demonic deeds and "
"henceforth will not perform deeds that confuse sentient beings."

msgid "527653a5adb946bcbb704dbd5e3e8dcc"
msgstr ""
"O Blessed One! Please grant us relief so that we may listen to the Dharma in"
" your presence.”"

msgid "31c4dff721d54e49bbcfdf5d21fc2fa5"
msgstr ""
"Thereupon, in order to grant relief to those demons, the Blessed One said,"

msgid "c25fd783f629420696b65468f1a54440"
msgstr "“Friends, very well, it is very good."

msgid "76cc428ce9e1497f8a349407ed6253f6"
msgstr ""
"Give up your demonic deeds and beseech the Tathāgata to teach the Dharma!"

msgid "a837e5bffe1f4cd7a4829fcdbc59f9d0"
msgstr ""
"This will indeed become the cause for leaving behind all the ways of Māra."

msgid "72bb95447d7c4f05852c38d5b7c0f522"
msgstr "Why?"

msgid "9ea336b870fc4dd6a791390cea10878b"
msgstr ""
"It will do so because it generates the power that produces the roots of "
"virtue for buddhahood."

msgid "5e30e6846f804e319c74efe53841f68b"
msgstr ""
"“Friends, just as complete darkness that has prevailed for many years can be"
" eliminated by a single lamp,"

msgid "dff2d1d09a49404dbf7e7fca8174a018"
msgstr ""
"in the same way, my friends, the complete darkness of the afflictive "
"emotions that has prevailed for a hundred eons can be eliminated by a single"
" generation of the power of wisdom."

msgid "c4391fe6453e48bb9e8ccb031acbed52"
msgstr ""
"Friends, just as the moon, the sun, or a large precious jewel can dispel all"
" darkness, in the same way, my friends, a single virtuous thought endowed "
"with insight can eliminate all the darkness of unknowing."

msgid "0bee0428c09d4b72975a45e2f0984d9a"
msgstr ""
"Friends, that is why, through this root of virtue, you will gradually remove"
" all the darkness of unknowing and attain the great illumination of the "
"Dharma.”"

msgid "3717c5e8c28049a69daf9667a630f062"
msgstr ""
"At this point, the bodhisattva Dharmeśvara­rāja, who was present among the "
"members of the retinue, said,"

msgid "404e8ae7695a4d11ba5cd2dbc92967fc"
msgstr ""
"“Blessed One, the buddha domain blessed and revealed by the Tathāgata is "
"inconceivable."

msgid "d147a0a53383495dbccc996cc2f5a12d"
msgstr ""
"I have no doubt that the Tathāgata will agree to teach the Dharma discourse "
"of the Great Assembly chapter called The Gateway to Unobstructed Deliverance"
" through the Bodhisattva Way of Life."

msgid "f2dcf6b0a94244658e6398d0d55cc094"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "695d1da725a440c7bf087241ca617eda"
msgstr "Blessed One, this assembly of outstanding bodhisattvas is great."

msgid "9f89854f0b1248e0b2df8885786003c4"
msgstr "“Blessed One, they have donned the inconceivable bodhisattva armor."

msgid "35be692443904c8c9ab620564cc13b12"
msgstr "They sport with the great wisdom of the superknowledges."

msgid "d38457f4b5c24f3f90d3aa449c5f4d68"
msgstr "They resound in the ten directions."

msgid "d96589a289ef427e914568da0cda9868"
msgstr ""
"They are aware that stains do not exist when the mind has become purified."

msgid "8c99fb4e721b4bed93996ef2faea7014"
msgstr "They are illuminated by liberation."

msgid "54fbbb9dcdf04268b36bafbec357f25d"
msgstr "They are praised and commended by buddhas."

msgid "f26548b8f0a446c6b49342593186be45"
msgstr "They attain sovereign mastery over all phenomena."

msgid "7a646bddaa5748259271f206dc72db32"
msgstr "They bring all perfections to perfection."

msgid "7b9ee3a53b734d33aec5c4359f4ffe77"
msgstr "They emerge through all sorts of skillful methods."

msgid "98c972ea08c448aaa40f700d03bc55dc"
msgstr "They dispel all demonic deeds, hostilities, and afflictive emotions."

msgid "6dd6020da04d4352b26865d7d41dd063"
msgstr "They tame all hosts of opponents and evil forces."

msgid "70e467ae0a894c8aa57558313044f736"
msgstr "They know how to analyze and teach all words."

msgid "748a096feddf4d81b60454f4e00e3cda"
msgstr "They attain perfect wisdom without attachment."

msgid "e428536dafff48d48eb862f7049f2465"
msgstr ""
"They have obtained mindfulness, intelligence, realization, modesty, "
"devotion, retention, and wisdom."

msgid "4f4665186f2646d2b84ce7443f2240cf"
msgstr "They have unobstructed blessing and uninterrupted eloquence."

msgid "13c8dd5959ea434eb1123418c2e1dfee"
msgstr ""
"They know how to distinguish the inferior and superior faculties of all "
"beings."

msgid "b29b6d2ae3984d5ba4ab81e41b1bf31b"
msgstr ""
"They teach the Dharma in accordance with the predispositions of all beings."

msgid "885a679420c349f9ba20a1f3878a212e"
msgstr "They teach the flawless Dharma without mistake."

msgid "3dfd3b8550cc400caa2ca6195f6508e2"
msgstr "They are skilled in the languages and dialects of all beings."

msgid "28f7b004485545849924e1603a2f56bf"
msgstr ""
"They are endowed with the voices of kiṃnaras, kalaviṅka birds, and cranes "
"and the melodious voice of Brahmā."

msgid "de21741f28ab476ba91ef822a307d99e"
msgstr ""
"“They establish all beings in nirvāṇa by acting as their spiritual friends."

msgid "b6f13ac32ba24944863c3fcf524c2ec6"
msgstr "They are motivated by great benevolence and vast compassion."

msgid "83599f195cfa40ee978c6c4efad594f3"
msgstr "They are stable, settled, and unwavering. They act on their words."

msgid "896300533a03488c8269e47622b17ce0"
msgstr "They hoist the Dharma banner."

msgid "23801106bba24936b9c72bfde70cab4b"
msgstr ""
"They are firm like a vajra and indestructible like the ring of mountains."

msgid "7f1de1707ec840b39bc97dfdf0025835"
msgstr "They make aspiration prayers free of any wishes."

msgid "aa90c0af252c452daab11cec248644ac"
msgstr ""
"They are established in profound dependent arising, which is difficult to "
"see and comprehend."

msgid "4fba3ec2496e49ab98eb2378d115c7b2"
msgstr ""
"They have cut off the two extremes of eternalism and nihilism, all views, "
"and the karmic traces."

msgid "d0fa11f34afa4a7bab91b335065a3edc"
msgstr "They command a following that befits a great king."

msgid "f8fe72c584234f54aedff7601e932fab"
msgstr ""
"They are great leaders who have for countless eons accomplished merit "
"through the Jewel of the Dharma."

msgid "e02250cb250e4ee5b62f3babf7168916"
msgstr ""
"They are great kings of physicians who cure the incorporeal disease of the "
"afflictive emotions of all sentient beings."

msgid "2b3c335b230c43c1b1a580ef8988f6e2"
msgstr ""
"They are without fear of the resounding of the great lion’s roar, of all "
"types nonsequential and inverted progression, and of the mystery of the "
"Tathāgata."

msgid "80f13cedeb79465ba2ac5b4124f04153"
msgstr "Their bodies will be well adorned by the excellent marks and signs."

msgid "7833cb2fc7b146898c9df77ba5994255"
msgstr "They make unstinting offerings."

msgid "c072544f6afd43188b109b3dd71bdce9"
msgstr "They are courageous in every respect."

msgid "554797ec23b94f4daa14c99a0bc61a66"
msgstr "They defeat the army of all afflictive emotions and the four māras."

msgid "dbb1dc6fe59f422994a77835ad98f2df"
msgstr "They are like ferrymen."

msgid "f6188981e7394b4bb00e695d9f6e0e03"
msgstr ""
"They thoroughly cultivate the spiritual faculties, the strengths, the "
"factors of awakening, the concentrations, the liberations, and entering the "
"absorptions."

msgid "1eda2425dae243098eed2153582b029f"
msgstr "“They exert themselves to fully liberate all sentient beings."

msgid "be6c258a0eee42778eecf3b8ea881047"
msgstr "They are like mountains."

msgid "fa2520da56ff4235ba47f46b7c830f4f"
msgstr ""
"They turn away from the eight worldly dharmas: gain, loss, fame, ill repute,"
" blame, praise, joy, and suffering."

msgid "ed27ed13f0ec4d67ba1b46ced410cb09"
msgstr "They are settled in the joyous, delightful, and rapturous Dharma."

msgid "f6de212c8652450485d31d78dc558cb3"
msgstr "They bask in the radiance of the Jewel of the Dharma."

msgid "847e3d0492254d82b041e56209ea3440"
msgstr "They achieve contentment through wisdom."

msgid "ca0b26a3ccd347c38c1d945e21546b43"
msgstr "Like a lotus, they are unstained by any conditioned phenomena."

msgid "5c945e17be2e4bbb893da0923772a51a"
msgstr ""
"They have pure halos that dim the light of the moon, the sun, Śakra, and "
"Brahmā."

msgid "d065bda3ad874e42ba8b00d59389e6fd"
msgstr "They attain the ocean mudrā absorption."

msgid "d39f59c6f6334c06b3bebf57553d58db"
msgstr "They engage in all aspects of the Jewel of the Dharma."

msgid "3df1004e38854535af6562640b37cdd5"
msgstr "They do not interrupt the lineage of the Three Jewels."

msgid "6e5841aaf63d4e42bc743f07ff53850b"
msgstr "They mature all beings."

msgid "8466309f61e9494a88ebf06c1de6c4ef"
msgstr "They perform subduing rituals."

msgid "ec74cb4c258f49b5a39a5263e757145c"
msgstr "They maintain the treasury of all the jewels of the Buddhadharma."

msgid "274c1444c3c04b908b27f16d4a5a1c41"
msgstr "They are limitlessly praised."

msgid "a95ba9fb9f434d8d98339cc74e0fc1ce"
msgstr "They accumulate infinite merit."

msgid "f9fbc9aa9b9d44d4933caeb165de67c5"
msgstr ""
"They approach the wisdom of omniscience, which is excellent in every "
"respect."

msgid "ce36ad91ddd24b3e9c205d32c6e0a5dc"
msgstr "Such is this assembly, which could be praised until the end of time."

msgid "7188486223684e25bf7e54be87c1d827"
msgstr ""
"“This being so, Blessed One, I had the thought that you would agree to teach"
" the Dharma discourse of the Great Assembly chapter called The Gateway to "
"Unobstructed Deliverance through the Bodhisattva Way of Life."

msgid "28c5ec88a14e411cb86c9788700616b2"
msgstr ""
"“Blessed One, it is wonderful that the appearance of a present buddha "
"benefits and appeases all sentient beings, generates the roots of virtue of "
"future bodhisattvas, purifies the intentions of the bodhisattvas who have "
"generated the first thought of awakening, uniquely engages bodhisattvas who "
"have entered the bodhisattva way of life, empowers in the Buddhadharma "
"bodhisattvas who are irreversible from awakening, does not let go to waste "
"the causes and fruits of bodhisattvas who are kept back by one last birth, "
"prepares conditions for sentient beings who are established on the path, "
"causes the practice of great compassion for sentient beings who are not "
"established on the path, and causes sentient beings who are definitely on a "
"wrong path to be placed upon the true path. To sentient beings who aspire to"
" the three vehicles, a buddha teaches their arrangements."

msgid "e0c51257ced1405d94f14b1fb8b5e1d8"
msgstr ""
"“The appearance of a buddha is an ornament of the world of gods, humans, and"
" asuras, because when a buddha emerges, wonderful and marvelous Dharma "
"teachings such as this will emerge in the world!"

msgid "3f1af3cf5b704e8980d989af006a2446"
msgstr ""
"“Blessed One, such a display of blessings through a single instance of "
"generating the thought of awakening, in this pavilion by these noble beings,"
" is beyond the capacity of śrāvakas and pratyekabuddhas to teach, even for a"
" hundred thousand eons."

msgid "835a42e4d3224360894f0b9fcff98b71"
msgstr ""
"“This being so, I had the thought that it would be utterly astonishing were "
"any beings, even after witnessing an amazing, miraculous, magical display "
"such as this, to aspire for the vehicle of śrāvakas or vehicle of "
"pratyekabuddhas with misguided understanding."

msgid "73019fb6093947dba3fbf209d3923346"
msgstr "Why is that so?"

msgid "b24e254d66904ab5a0c153c058d44925"
msgstr ""
"Blessed One, the very first generation of the thought of awakening of a "
"bodhisattva overpowers all śrāvakas and pratyekabuddhas."

msgid "e56296da1f29475d98904d5dbcbd1c99"
msgstr ""
"When someone discards the Great Vehicle and thinks, ‘I will follow the "
"vehicle of the śrāvakas or pratyekabuddhas,’ it is for me comparable to a "
"person with misguided insight who discards a precious gem of beryl and "
"thinks, ‘I prefer a semiprecious stone.’"

msgid "f71c6cb623de40598d342b3d5d96a5c2"
msgstr ""
"Blessed One, those sons or daughters of noble family who have generated the "
"thought of supreme perfect awakening with determination and all others who "
"do so will, within a short while, attain such a teaching.”"

msgid "8b93ac29e9a24766b448ba7ed5cc5860"
msgstr ""
"When the bodhisattva Dharmeśvara­rāja had given this account, an immensely "
"vast number of creatures among the retinue of many different beings, "
"including gods and humans, generated the thought of supreme perfect "
"awakening."

msgid "338ca2a9a98b40ba9873680fad4c2cf3"
msgstr "This concludes the Assembly chapter “Array of Ornaments.”"

msgid "3cb14f6dedba475b9685ae2058b69c08"
msgstr ""
"After the Blessed One had surveyed the great assembly of bodhisattvas, he "
"knew and rejoiced that the bodhisattvas who had assembled were holders of "
"the treasure of the Tathāgata’s Dharma striving for righteousness."

msgid "ac6d44e29f8d4fc38100162c552e53ac"
msgstr ""
"In order for the Dharma discourse The Gateway to Unobstructed Deliverance "
"through the Bodhisattva Way of Life to be explained, a light known as "
"fearless eloquence, the mark of a great being, emerged from the crown of his"
" head."

msgid "16f3b2004f04412f982a75cde03d6f46"
msgstr ""
"As soon as this light emerged, the Blessed One caused it to encircle the "
"entire bodhisattva assembly seven times."

msgid "709fe85cf155462ca794f076cd53fb9e"
msgstr ""
"He then caused it to encircle the body of the bodhisattva Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja "
"a hundred times, after which it disappeared into the crown of the head of "
"the bodhisattva Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja."

msgid "4038556dfe584b5dada8c0492de10351"
msgstr ""
"The instant the light touched Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja, by the power of the Buddha "
"the bodhisattva Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja eclipsed the radiance, lion thrones, and "
"bodies of the entire bodhisattva assembly a hundred times."

msgid "805ab57f470b4fd2a6b6ab0cd416ed5d"
msgstr "He was brilliant, majestic, and resplendent."

msgid "fb15ac7d227b4bd79b8996042bd254b7"
msgstr ""
"At this point, the bodhisattva Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja became aware of the "
"blessing of the Tathāgata and rose from his seat."

msgid "ed10eb5011db49fe9e27a1f435442781"
msgstr ""
"He draped his upper garment over one shoulder and placed his right knee on "
"the ground."

msgid "49d9ab43894a4b278cc12595869ca177"
msgstr ""
"He proceeded to bow, with his palms joined, in the direction of the Blessed "
"One and conjure up a precious parasol known as ornament of the Tathāgata in "
"the space directly above the crown of the Blessed One’s head."

msgid "3166301148a24835a6e26d99de2534d2"
msgstr ""
"With a handle of lapis, a cover of gold, a jeweled parrot at the center, and"
" spokes of precious sapphire, it had garlands of pearls hanging down as "
"pendants and was decorated with tassels of divine silk."

msgid "95c4be6c7b9d49c1bd3ecde7a1eb13d0"
msgstr ""
"It resounded with filigrees of chimes, was upheld by the bodies of "
"bodhisattvas, and was as vast as the trichiliocosm."

msgid "b7d26d205d3c483ea1f8b68ac488768d"
msgstr ""
"After he had conjured up such a precious parasol as an act of worshiping the"
" Tathāgata, Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja brought down a rain of flowers."

msgid "51346ca8f9394af3aa391163c3deff7e"
msgstr ""
"He intoned the sound of a constant uninterrupted melody accompanied by "
"cymbals, and he praised the Blessed One with these words:"

msgid "772d436a5cf048a4b72a8467c5be8136"
msgstr "“All-illuminating resplendent one!"

msgid "56df238373d64ffdbb1fc4362d8d0a3d"
msgstr "Teacher of all and seer of all!"

msgid "53ae32c0507f41419e45359c95ddcf90"
msgstr "You who are skilled in the essence of spontaneously arisen Dharma"

msgid "81551cac23ec4e15af5761cca5dfe623"
msgstr "And endowed with all inconceivable good qualities,"

msgid "472115c8d6544cedb267c48b828b4138"
msgstr "“You, leader of beings, emitted a light"

msgid "cb95bbc2c875475daa008013f9220ccc"
msgstr "And caused it to purify and illuminate my face."

msgid "58f35577a9424bb0bc3b0161f430e05c"
msgstr "O leader, you also caused the light"

msgid "22e6aa26c03747da9b51b231b9282344"
msgstr ""
"To circle my body a hundred times and come at last to rest at my crown."

msgid "3f789f21d4624e9f9b4895d56b288363"
msgstr "“When the light of the leader of humans touched me,"

msgid "86f948399a7a4a9f8a00495a6f420fd2"
msgstr "All that I had achieved before in terms of mindfulness,"

msgid "44c322cf298647bea0e0ddbb4aa6b9a0"
msgstr "Intelligence, eloquence, illumination, and retention"

msgid "9f0d6e9f38f3467bb3745ba7f05b5610"
msgstr "Was augmented a thousand times."

msgid "9427ed0335a04331854526a615869b08"
msgstr "“I became physically content, mentally clear,"

msgid "5415d5270fd84c5f8db75445ada08e75"
msgstr "Delightfully fulfilled, and serenely intelligent."

msgid "330d704d15334a3e9802e586eddeab48"
msgstr "Moreover, boundless buddha knowledge"

msgid "cb40191d39414667a1d514f947a145b5"
msgstr "And eloquence possessed my body."

msgid "9aea5fafe6ce4fb787a45784d0edd3dd"
msgstr "“The mighty Buddha is difficult to approach,"

msgid "4ca2756d2f2a463a8870769177234864"
msgstr "And the meek are unable to please him."

msgid "8d466056c6b34a9a8b38b49b1f6cb098"
msgstr "Having given this to the Buddha,"

msgid "6339869765d6499a9a72115f10886727"
msgstr "I make this request for the benefit of all beings."

msgid "7077c68e1e3a4f8797a065873affaea0"
msgstr "“I request entry into perfect bodhisattva conduct"

msgid "0c759f80cfbe4d20af601e8cedfe5770"
msgstr "And the emergence of spiritual leaders,"

msgid "2e04ca16f009420d9b02cf9519dbee52"
msgstr "The magical display of illumination and deliverance"

msgid "2725f26907034107a7f663100c5e274f"
msgstr "As well as consecration and wisdom."

msgid "71b57699e6064aed82980538cdc0513b"
msgstr ""
"“In order to benefit those who fully understand the excellent supreme "
"vehicle,"

msgid "1d24a10bc29d46b6b666713464b5d183"
msgstr "Who have joined the endless vast retinue,"

msgid "331d818d0819450c9fb74c0d9dc3a505"
msgstr "And who endeavor for vast righteousness,"

msgid "36b0c6a0d3dc4c25b80dbe4015bfe6eb"
msgstr "I make this request to the Buddha."

msgid "6648c0c26c2b4c5ca7bf1f42c2a2e305"
msgstr "“To subjugate the horde of Māra"

msgid "7747e50c1ed24a2dbe6a535a6d50a6e7"
msgstr "And to uphold this Dharma of the Buddha,"

msgid "d132275fc54a4c5786118393fd4d2fdf"
msgstr "Blessed One, this is the time to explain to embodied beings"

msgid "cbb69ed389ac4c01833eb2476cc0fe21"
msgstr "The noble Dharma treasury in which the aggregates are absent."

msgid "fa6093d2271c43e695e981c6eeb805d6"
msgstr "“The knowledge of the leader of beings is endless."

msgid "5de34e239b7144ce88364b48f37358e1"
msgstr "Blessed One, I cannot fathom it."

msgid "4f9a0ad5a89c4bd49fb4e8ac48151caa"
msgstr "Since my understanding cannot grasp the knowledge of the Sugata,"

msgid "0953a085b71b41f5a3fb65863eb8bc2d"
msgstr "I make this request to the vastly learned one:"

msgid "bd828567c83c46319680642b9ffecf70"
msgstr "“How does one access the knowledge of the Blessed One,"

msgid "fc7ba2db688b40688b9d64cdacedc60a"
msgstr "And for how long does one train,"

msgid "463a39190b99407b953d72c849e7571f"
msgstr "And what is the training of Dharmeśvara­rāja?"

msgid "2e21bdfa95c1486aad6a7381d6664372"
msgstr "Please explain the sphere of activity of the guides.”"

msgid "0b41ed5f148846b3b692eff0eb735d83"
msgstr ""
"After Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja had praised the Blessed One with these verses, he "
"added,"

msgid "9d554f624cdb4e949d34047cffc31bc1"
msgstr "“Blessed One, the domain of the Tathāgata is inconceivable."

msgid "4058f0006901425b87ed5b987e321008"
msgstr "The sphere of conduct of bodhisattvas is beyond measure."

msgid "64e2139bd43c4b3b8ca2842be80af571"
msgstr ""
"I understand that the Tathāgata teaches the Dharma untiringly, and I see "
"that he abides in great compassion, which does not leave any sentient being "
"behind."

msgid "eeefc3c677664b0f9a0ce063a52a3f3b"
msgstr "So I ask you this:"

msgid "c811aecc4e2d4ff1862ea6dd375fce15"
msgstr "Blessed One, what are the bodhisattva ornaments?"

msgid "e4e3360e540748ef87963934af980eb1"
msgstr ""
"Blessed One, by what ornaments are the bodhisattvas adorned so they become "
"beautiful while performing bodhisattva conduct?"

msgid "7456ac8c730140938ec4725adbda3d35"
msgstr ""
"“How, Blessed One, do bodhisattvas, who have attained the inconceivable "
"splendor of the Dharma, become free from the darkness of ignorance and "
"doubt, and how do they become fully trained in the great gateway of Dharma?"

msgid "6fe4ff1fb74245699ff208750e19ab56"
msgstr ""
"How, Blessed One, do bodhisattvas who never abandon any being become endowed"
" with the supreme foundation of great compassion, which never abandons any "
"being?"

msgid "1a6a115d8381432bb3adbca3c1b0ecb3"
msgstr ""
"“How, Blessed One, do bodhisattvas engage in bodhisattva actions, carrying "
"them out well without longing for their conclusion?"

msgid "9a23e2dbcbf24c408933ed82a6f31253"
msgstr ""
"Bodhisattvas will by any means conquer evil and opponents, leave behind all "
"doubt, and enter the Tathāgata domain."

msgid "6d5d5092dda94cefa2ae2bf1c6246c75"
msgstr ""
"They will come to prominence within the bodhisattva domain, engage with the "
"thinking of all sentient beings, and understand the mental conduct of all "
"sentient beings."

msgid "8587452eccdc415ea0b18b2c5c6fe6f6"
msgstr ""
"They will purify buddhafields, subjugate the hordes of Māra, fully grasp the"
" Dharma of the Tathāgata, and swiftly attain mastery of all teachings.”"

msgid "715036a61f2e48da8955e1b05178c5ea"
msgstr ""
"Blessed One, I request that the Tathāgata explain The Gateway to "
"Unobstructed Deliverance through the Bodhisattva Way of Life with firm "
"determination so that the following may transpire:"

msgid "2fb4395b4a514938a0e379eb6575d158"
msgstr "The Blessed One responded,"

msgid "a42932800e1745c383dbad792a25694b"
msgstr "“Excellent, noble being, very good!"

msgid "2348325141244f5c90f42b8302a5f57b"
msgstr ""
"It is really excellent that you decided to ask the Tathāgata with such "
"determination, after you had attained certainty about the immeasurable "
"conduct of the Tathāgata."

msgid "9c7bceb6ada94585a956878318bd69db"
msgstr ""
"Because of that, son of noble family, I shall explain to you how bodhisattva"
" mahāsattvas perfect these qualities, as well as the other immeasurable "
"bodhisattva qualities, and how they achieve mastery over all teachings. So, "
"listen carefully and keep this in mind.”"

msgid "529ba1af11824866bf3a2152a74580a2"
msgstr "“Very good, Blessed One,” replied Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja."

msgid "7e3cd49930f143868436b4b360db3632"
msgstr ""
"He then listened with full attention as the Blessed One started to teach."

msgid "1115f9e93cd64504af5bdb42fe5c4883"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, there are four types of bodhisattva ornaments:"

msgid "a4a76f1f627d49309eb06c74e528f61d"
msgstr ""
" the ornaments of morality,  the ornaments of absorption,  the ornaments of "
"insight, and  the ornaments of retention."

msgid "f048f5a0bd354284bc2106257fffefc2"
msgstr "Son of noble family, those are the four bodhisattva ornaments."

msgid "4033acf335f94740a9b7176be3ba3bcd"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may ask, ‘What are the bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality?’"

msgid "fb0192f7203045888f8f7de8ce4bd01e"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, there is a single bodhisattva ornament of morality:"

msgid "fc9f1f18e37c4563b528dd389cacf878"
msgstr "not harming any sentient being."

msgid "18df1f8e64974a5f8cce4855fa1f44fd"
msgstr ""
"A bodhisattva without a hateful disposition, who is pleasant and delightful "
"toward all sentient beings, is endowed with the single bodhisattva ornament "
"of morality."

msgid "471e5428c36b44eda4a8499607358a98"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are two types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality:"

msgid "0b736e44204747a9a71d31c748c42f5b"
msgstr ""
"closing the gateway to the evil destinies and opening the gateway to the "
"blissful destinies."

msgid "7428a115946f4998afbf03affc89d267"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are three types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality:"

msgid "e3e5fad1972b46159e749ec436da759e"
msgstr "purity in body, purity in speech, and purity in mind."

msgid "807b231eeee744d9ad25c468fd47459d"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are four types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality:"

msgid "330edead2ba04e1ba66dd0a98052df89"
msgstr ""
"achieving what one desires, accomplishing what one wishes for, attaining "
"what one longs for, and finishing what one begins."

msgid "6b1f38e33eca4c8894b8d376fcc26f36"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are five types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality:"

msgid "111d5f084f89499f88403f5097c69b53"
msgstr ""
"nondeceptive absorption, nondeceptive insight, nondeceptive liberation, "
"nondeceptive vision of liberating wisdom, and unsurpassed "
"mahāparinirvāṇa—all endowed with morality."

msgid "34127862d92f4b28941bb441a9e04926"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are six types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality:"

msgid "0f920487b83c466b8b6083f1fda82474"
msgstr ""
"morality that is flawless on account of being without mental attachment, not"
" degenerate on account of being without reproach, not corrupt on account of "
"not being adulterated, free of sin on account of increasing virtuous "
"qualities, unfettered on account of being voluntary, and autonomous on "
"account of being an understanding that does not depend on others."

msgid "b8f4266d8b194804b0069ccbd7257e6e"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are seven types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality:"

msgid "3ff6856a417b44a1aebdccf6db10465c"
msgstr ""
"pure generosity, pure patience, pure vigor, pure concentration, pure "
"insight, pure method, and pure conscientiousness—all endowed with morality."

msgid "700883123fd34aeb9a031948bee16e3f"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality:"

msgid "b0713a8c0c984e14a3784f298b3732a4"
msgstr ""
"excellence in eloquence, excellence in the spiritual levels, excellence in "
"lack of distractedness, excellence in lack of idleness, excellence in lack "
"of vindictiveness, excellence in appreciating the appearance of a buddha, "
"excellence in ease, and excellence in venerating one’s spiritual friends."

msgid "3b6222ae5725491eb2f25f52e2fc4077"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are nine types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality:"

msgid "1921673ee96a471bbaadc08413dc5309"
msgstr ""
"being fearless, being without anxiety, being determined, being tranquil, "
"being cool, being released from bondage, being flexible, being well bred, "
"and being accomplished in the stage of being restrained."

msgid "958ec99837be4441bd36977e47d1b6e7"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are ten types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality:"

msgid "4d0836c8cdfd4ce39a4775432a53737e"
msgstr ""
"the ornaments of body, since bodhisattvas accomplish the auspicious thirty-"
"two major marks and eighty minor signs; speech, since they act on their "
"word; mind, since they lack afflictive emotions; buddhafields, since they "
"accomplish their aspirations; maturing sentient beings, since the "
"bodhisattva intention is pure; birth, since they do not commit any sinful "
"deeds; bodhisattva conduct, since they emulate the tathāgata conduct; "
"understanding, since they lack pride; the seat of awakening, since they "
"dedicate their roots of virtue; and the ornaments of the strengths, the "
"fearlessnesses, and unique buddha qualities, since they do not discard their"
" grounding in the root of moral conduct."

msgid "0399fd26ad7045c6a7e6136616bb931a"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, these are the ten types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"morality."

msgid "265e13364cd244488ed8c4986c895361"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may ask, ‘What are the bodhisattva ornaments of "
"meditative absorption?’"

msgid "1640e69f7b994c96a1a0f254d38c14c2"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, there is a single bodhisattva ornament of absorption: "
"loving all sentient beings."

msgid "4369363c83504f0091c5331b0f9769af"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are two types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"absorption: honesty and suppleness."

msgid "5e6f5c7aeaa24cde84a8426a9516257c"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are three types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"absorption: lack of deception, cunning, and hypocrisy."

msgid "4630b495fd9a4d69aeb410ade72d426f"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are four types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"absorption: not being immobilized by desire, hatred, delusion, and fear."

msgid "2c42e993de324f5d93a5e513a4b0fabe"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are five types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"absorption: abandoning the five obstructions of sensual desire, ill will, "
"drowsiness and torpor, agitation and regret, and doubt."

msgid "678121d16adf48d39f1ac5535d1adc2e"
msgstr "These five obstructions are abandoned."

msgid "1b93d8ca16c740a8b4027aaa432b104a"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are six types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"absorption: recollecting the Buddha, the Dharma, the Saṅgha, generosity, "
"morality, and the gods."

msgid "6e3f7c20fea4499bb13f390a94e4622d"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are seven types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"absorption: cultivating the seven factors of awakening without forgetting "
"the thought of awakening: correct mindfulness, correct investigation of "
"phenomena, correct vigor, correct joy, correct pliancy, correct absorption, "
"and correct equanimity."

msgid "5a5a70f3d37c45c18dadcc7afb933c77"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"absorption: cultivating the noble eightfold path, that is to say, correct "
"view, correct intention, correct speech, correct action, correct livelihood,"
" correct effort, correct mindfulness, and correct absorption."

msgid "3e374ffe60c74a5caf2921153d7b29fc"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are nine types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"absorption:"

msgid "8c53640f2a1f47bb9791bb16626063e0"
msgstr ""
"that of bodhisattvas who, without being forgetful, dwell on the foundation "
"of great compassion, never abandon any sentient being, and then, detached "
"from desire, sin, and nonvirtues attain to and abide in the first "
"concentration, which has applied and sustained thought and is joyful and "
"blissful through detachment;"

msgid "20c429fb1b6340b0bc5830253a01da52"
msgstr ""
"that of bodhisattvas who are freed from applied and sustained thought, have "
"inner serenity, and attain to and abide in the second concentration, which "
"is joyful and blissful through absorption that is one-pointed and has no "
"applied or sustained thought;"

msgid "c73078af97fc4946a5d58e46efea7573"
msgstr ""
"that of bodhisattvas who are freed from the desire for joy, dwell in "
"equanimity, are mindfully aware, and attain to and abide in the third "
"concentration that is beyond joy, experiencing that physical bliss of which "
"the noble ones say, ‘this is mindful equanimity established in bliss’;"

msgid "72e1e15061ae4bb6969833f502d39309"
msgstr ""
"that of bodhisattvas who have abandoned bliss, having previously abandoned "
"suffering, whose happiness and sadness have subsided, and who attain to and "
"abide in the fourth concentration, which is pure mindfulness and equanimity "
"that is neither bliss nor suffering;"

msgid "70f0c7641c0b417c99c026bcd352c670"
msgstr ""
"that of bodhisattvas who have transcended the perception of form, whose "
"perception of physical obstruction has subsided, who pay no attention to "
"diverse perceptions but think, ‘space is unending,’ and who attain to and "
"abide in the realm of infinite space;"

msgid "89776dfb139f4f519be0d9388d021e26"
msgstr ""
"that of bodhisattvas who have completely transcended the realm of infinite "
"space and think, ‘consciousness is unending,’ who attain to and abide in the"
" realm of infinite consciousness;"

msgid "00642f3cb46840498ddeabb2997ec211"
msgstr ""
"that of bodhisattvas who have completely transcended the realm of infinite "
"consciousness and think, ‘there is nothing at all,’ who attain to and abide "
"in the realm of nothing at all;"

msgid "52a7290dfe144dad9b8ffd64ac69a306"
msgstr ""
"that of bodhisattvas who have completely transcended the realm of nothing at"
" all and attain to and abide in the Sphere of neither Perception nor "
"Nonperception;"

msgid "08359322de354acd80fdb26fea592014"
msgstr ""
"and that of bodhisattvas who have completely transcended the Sphere of "
"neither Perception nor Nonperception and attain the cessation of sensation "
"and perception, but though they attain it, because of skillful means they "
"refrain from manifesting the limit of reality and instead, due to previous "
"blessing, remain present and mature sentient beings."

msgid "cfc2d5a936674347b373ece5897c4777"
msgstr "These are the nine ornaments of absorption."

msgid "fc0649c90900440aae9dc35cc92987e6"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are ten types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"absorption: gaining certainty through imperturbability, perfecting tranquil "
"abiding, not forsaking diligent effort, withdrawing into meditative "
"seclusion, not squandering the roots of virtue, maintaining mental solitude,"
" maintaining physical pliancy, being discerning while thinking about and "
"evaluating phenomena, controlling the mind, and attaining the noble lineage."

msgid "d7c8bfe81b5a4b599cf4e09fe0956821"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, these are the ten types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"absorption."

msgid "be19dd92f54b48cc9004bea880fd7dee"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may ask, ‘What are the bodhisattva ornaments of "
"insight?’"

msgid "25783bac693c400ca4b3c3469f62381d"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, there is a single bodhisattva ornament of insight. It "
"is having no doubts about any phenomenon."

msgid "5abeeb2fa3cd4675a1b7a8c18add4be9"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are two types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"insight: having no regret and not being agitated."

msgid "fcdc384a47d148fea488007ab3bde1a5"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are three types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"insight: abandoning delusion, breaking through the shell of ignorance, and "
"dispelling the thick darkness of confusion."

msgid "88a0734e98d641ffa96b1951a5388d1f"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are four types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"insight: understanding the suffering that is to be understood, illuminating "
"the source of suffering to be relinquished, bringing to light the cessation "
"to be realized, and being empowered to cultivate the path."

msgid "50bd55fba20a43779d66227dc35ca0be"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are five types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"insight: purification of morality through lack of objectification, "
"purification of absorption through concentration endowed with supreme "
"insight, purification of liberation through nonduality, purification of the "
"vision of liberating wisdom through the sameness of the three times, and "
"purification of phenomena by means of the nature of reality free of "
"attachment."

msgid "ef55b1fde89d431daec6d82da345b2d4"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are six types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"insight:"

msgid "4f2df5f72a27445a87300ce6f1ba8dfd"
msgstr ""
"transcendent generosity purified of the three spheres—the sphere of the "
"agent purified because of being the same as an illusion, the sphere of "
"sentient beings purified because of being the same as a dream, and the "
"sphere of awakening purified through not hoping for results;"

msgid "c406c95c66384fbca1af23f0ed816ee7"
msgstr ""
"transcendent morality purified of the three spheres—the sphere of body "
"purified on account of being like a reflection, the sphere of speech "
"purified by understanding it to be like an echo, and the sphere of the mind "
"purified because of being the same as an illusion;"

msgid "54a2eab857b44ae8aa342822998218d2"
msgstr ""
"transcendent patience purified of the three spheres—purification in "
"abandoning aversion toward harshly spoken words, purification in abandoning "
"desire for praise and adulation, and purification of understanding the "
"dharmakāya in the offering of severed limbs and body parts;"

msgid "3306f829df7b4914a6f9176eccc38731"
msgstr ""
"transcendent vigor purified of the three spheres— purification in not being "
"disheartened through the conviction that saṃsāra is dreamlike, purification "
"in being stable through a vajra-like intention, and purification in neither "
"accepting nor rejecting through liberating oneself from all conceptual "
"signs;"

msgid "21bbfa6946184bb3bc3deaca39c0f5e0"
msgstr ""
"transcendent concentration purified of the three spheres—purification in "
"nonattachment to it through understanding its mutability, purification in "
"special insight through lack of obsession, and purification in focus through"
" generation of superknowledge;"

msgid "6626342a18f644f3b7f8b3882e9b23b5"
msgstr ""
"and transcendent skillful means purified of the three spheres—purification "
"in matters relating to gathering disciples by bringing beings to maturity, "
"purification in having retention through upholding the true Dharma, and "
"purification in aspirations in order to ornament the buddhafields."

msgid "812a61d1d4e54bc7b4071951d45749a6"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are seven types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"insight: being without mindfulness or mental engagement among the "
"applications of mindfulness, understanding the lack of arising and cessation"
" among correct exertions, being physically and mentally detached through the"
" bases of miraculous powers, understanding the spiritual faculties among the"
" sense faculties, annihilating all māras and afflictive emotions by means of"
" the strengths, understanding by means of the factors of awakening the "
"nature of all phenomena, and understanding that there is no coming and going"
" among the paths."

msgid "53d7f0c574874c46b2310a7927be5e4b"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"insight: understanding tranquil abiding on account of having deep serenity, "
"understanding special insight on account of lacking distorted vision, "
"understanding the aggregates on account of realizing the collections of "
"Dharma, understanding the elements because they are the same as the element "
"of space, understanding the sense fields because they are the same as a "
"ghost town, understanding dependent arising because it is without self, "
"understanding the truths on account of a lack of turmoil, and understanding "
"the definite realization of all phenomena on account of the full realization"
" of reality just as it is."

msgid "d93e47876a474a9ab49c481dd2f9367a"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are nine types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"insight: understanding the past by means of the beginning, understanding the"
" future by means of the end, understanding the present by means of the "
"intervening, understanding the determinate destinies given that causes do "
"not perish, understanding the indeterminate destinies given that conditions "
"may produce different results, understanding the destinies of those who "
"because of spiritual maturation are not predisposed to erring, understanding"
" that all buddhas are equal because they are distinguished by the "
"dharmakāya, understanding all phenomena to be sameness since reality is free"
" of attachment, and understanding all noble ones to be equal because they "
"are distinguished by the unconditioned."

msgid "a5bbd1de39404273bd71e1721f7c6cfe"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are ten types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"insight: understanding the nature of reality to be illusory on account of "
"the characteristic of accomplishment, understanding it to be like a dream on"
" account of the characteristic of conceptuality, understanding it to be like"
" a mirage on account of the characteristic of deception, understanding it to"
" be like a reflection on account of the characteristic of motionlessness, "
"understanding it to be like a hallucination on account of the characteristic"
" of being an assembly, understanding it to be like an echo on account of the"
" characteristic of being conditioned, understanding the realm of phenomena "
"as characterized by being uncorrupted, understanding thusness as "
"characterized by being nonabiding, understanding the limit of reality as "
"characterized by being unperturbed, and understanding the conditioned as "
"being characterized by being unconditioned."

msgid "7cb6bf3d23534355aec3e862e5641669"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may ask, ‘What are the bodhisattva ornaments of "
"retention?’"

msgid "cefefb0054fe470e9ec3caddebdd03f3"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, there is a single bodhisattva ornament of retention. It"
" is remembering without forgetting."

msgid "b8bc25103764454382f2885ed625b8a9"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are two types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"retention: full retention and retention."

msgid "a5f342cf3dd04c23ad3d062e885f6405"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are three types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"retention: skill in meaning, phonemes, and etymology."

msgid "d684e583edef44a19d7aafae15a0887d"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are four types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"retention: speaking words that are dispassionate, refined, liberated, and "
"without falsehood."

msgid "aeb3ad0ae523478cb20c95121db99501"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are five types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"retention: reliance on meaning among all one has studied, reliance on wisdom"
" among all collections of words, reliance on sūtras of definitive meaning "
"among all the sūtras, reliance on the nature of reality rather than all the "
"words of persons, and reliance on the supramundane rather than on all that "
"is mundane."

msgid "592258582be34e1ab09c18801979a02f"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are six types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"retention: acting in accordance with one’s words, employing statements that "
"correspond to the truth, using words that are suitable to be kept in mind "
"since they are without arrogance, using words that are acceptable because "
"they are without deceptiveness, teaching the Dharma that bears fruit because"
" it is joined with great compassion, teaching the Dharma continuously "
"through tactful knowledge of the audience, and teaching the Dharma in a "
"timely manner through understanding the ways of the world."

msgid "7c56e9c7afe64dd99e71b4c3cf49b2ac"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are seven types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"retention: possessing eloquence that is swift, forceful, quick, "
"dispassionate, uninterrupted, undistorted, and replete with etymologies."

msgid "2b85d77a53b642c59a5d3621a413cc60"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"retention: knowing the languages of the devas, nāgas, yakṣas, gandharvas, "
"asuras, garuḍas, kiṃnaras, and mahoragas, up to the languages of all "
"sentient beings."

msgid "8cfdc8f1fae647a29ea2237421124af9"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are nine types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"retention: not being intimidated in the midst of a gathering, not being "
"dejected among orators, being fearless in the midst of explaining the "
"Dharma, knowing discretion with regard to questioners, knowing how to give a"
" loosely organized teaching to arrogant people, knowing how to give a well-"
"organized teaching to those well on their way, manifesting as Vajrapāṇi to "
"the pretentious, teaching the destruction by fire at the end of the eon to "
"the deeply attached, and teaching the progression of the path exactly as it "
"is to those fully matured."

msgid "e8144d3780cb491c84ddfabc43a4bc5b"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are ten types of bodhisattva ornaments of "
"retention: knowing how to teach without doubt to skeptics, letting the mind "
"be a gate for the arising of Dharma, letting the lamp of insight shine "
"completely for others, inexhaustibly teaching words, uninterruptedly "
"teaching meanings, perfectly expressing boundless praise of the Buddha, "
"describing the endless flaws of moral pollution, teaching the immeasurable "
"praise of moral purification, engaging assiduously and without attachment in"
" accordance with all beings’ faculties, and understanding the application of"
" the discriminating knowledge bestowed on the level of buddhahood.”"

msgid "42cd2a3336984fdda10ddb659c65c11a"
msgstr ""
"Then, in order to elaborate on these points, the Blessed One spoke the "
"following verses:"

msgid "797cfd5988ca41de831bec288783e6b2"
msgstr "“What adorn the supreme and noble path"

msgid "e8928889060c48a290189ac9a606eafc"
msgstr "Are the four ornaments of those of great intelligence:"

msgid "f60f3f60626845eea8dc1bed35e88298"
msgstr "Morality, absorption, supreme insight,"

msgid "2d898843fd7f4e73b968c70798080339"
msgstr "And retention of the definitive meaning."

msgid "6c8d8452540a41eb96efbdef2e5d31b2"
msgstr " “Being pleasant and delightful toward all creatures"

msgid "5e3765ef545c4a4da84f67c36f2b5201"
msgstr "And pure in body, speech, and mind,"

msgid "68b2d4aeaf644fdc9bb2880dd85eaa78"
msgstr "Thus eliminating all downfalls—"

msgid "5104c55091724e73bdcaec00b9b581d9"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of morality."

msgid "15e6782d8db24b69ab676f3f5a4c6f28"
msgstr "“Being born as a learned being among gods or humans,"

msgid "4af7cbfd9ccc45ffbdf27e685faed75a"
msgstr "Accomplishing what one wishes according to one’s aspiration,"

msgid "4f4f4261bb24406380d804cf001adcb8"
msgstr "And being endowed with persistence and sincerity—"

msgid "c1ef051edf034ea9a3d18771d68c3644"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of pure morality."

msgid "917261a307ad4c859939b9f2c30c2218"
msgstr "“Absorption that is not illusory,"

msgid "1c57b002933c49c99234c2a2c1533cc7"
msgstr "Insight, liberation, and the vision of liberating wisdom,"

msgid "93a13221354e43f1b9fbfebf86a86107"
msgstr "And nirvāṇa that is not illusory—"

msgid "3c13e254ffe9485b84da140048170015"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of pure morality."

msgid "4e29f80261eb4563a3f54cd8bb1f43ba"
msgstr "“Flawless and pure morality,"

msgid "15e777bf5e394feebfbbbcc5def7180e"
msgstr "Morality that is not sinful or adulterated,"

msgid "f5c01b684c424decb2217a724bd27168"
msgstr "And that which is voluntary and autonomous—"

msgid "f7048dad46f04f7199b4838823268a3d"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of pure morality."

msgid "5d046700508247c69fc0d31e2d12486a"
msgstr "“Generosity and patience,"

msgid "9299903622314b06b3a3c5cbfcd6bb11"
msgstr "Vigor, concentration, and insight,"

msgid "a6ba86e5833f4d2695d7efd192a683ee"
msgstr "Methods and vigilance—"

msgid "fe25d1a85f12494898c57d1804fd4cd9"
msgstr "All are purified by morality."

msgid "83d54f6719494766a5bcc46e8d6329fb"
msgstr "“Remaining completely unwavering and still,"

msgid "a5946907939a4c61aa5c50966fae4c55"
msgstr ""
"Attaining the supreme levels and remaining focused in spiritual practice,"

msgid "aad4553c19ad4cb785e4454a23ad866f"
msgstr "Abandoning laxity, and being at ease—"

msgid "ac7f3d93390841f0a905f2de8067864f"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of pure morality."

msgid "7d8858783ca34bfd87ccfd7af94f46aa"
msgstr "“Igniting vigor and praising morality,"

msgid "8f1259cbc19948eca7251a3de78bf6d5"
msgstr "Being without mental anguish at all times,"

msgid "3a03ab970aaf4b01b5fb7059182da50f"
msgstr "And being free of attachment—"

msgid "62647dc41bcd47fc833f95ff14deb544"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of pure morality."

msgid "e15ef94b70ab4b68afe507decc6df1f4"
msgstr "“Being determined, tranquil, and serene,"

msgid "a0eee8a14ebf46a18a9ea61d2f18eb26"
msgstr "Without fear and neither anxious nor fainthearted,"

msgid "ee36cd4f784b40d781f446d0f426e00b"
msgstr "And to thus be released from bondage to these—"

msgid "ef7737358af748cba9fbf88490bb62d4"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of pure morality."

msgid "07a9bd0441e44c0598064a8523214d13"
msgstr "“Having a most praiseworthy mind that is flexible,"

msgid "348667a1c3ad427bb29d46f41a2ee824"
msgstr "Being disciplined and well bred,"

msgid "dd55dafcb8de4ce88cf58d46b369b958"
msgstr "And thus having one’s own body adorned by the marks—"

msgid "b9554883f77b48b6834b96be4cddd508"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of pure morality."

msgid "8cc45f43b4ac4ffc85aac66a140cfe2e"
msgstr "“Through conduct that is true to their word,"

msgid "95eb257d3dab40efb6a29485aeec1180"
msgstr "The skilled attain the ornament of speech."

msgid "546f355a735b4a999dcd82aa8ee42553"
msgstr "And are adorned by a steady mind free of afflictive emotion—"

msgid "5f29997461794a14a275ff4a9bee3b07"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of pure morality."

msgid "bcdc3dec30414f4bb2c87b6a26ce109c"
msgstr "“Excellently adorning the superb buddhafields,"

msgid "dbbcb034deaf45dfb6a7ffe859eda065"
msgstr "Bringing sentient beings to maturity in the supreme vehicle,"

msgid "4ada721d6cfa4066a4ec738bca184a84"
msgstr "And refraining from all sinful deeds—"

msgid "0e69ea0197e8428a9ed79c838b1d308f"
msgstr "These will cause one’s births to be well adorned."

msgid "e07e89fc36a844b1b8957e34da196df7"
msgstr "“Being constantly adorned by awakened conduct,"

msgid "4c50bdde153b4d9c8c5dd97b2050a0f7"
msgstr "Being adorned by the noble seat of awakening,"

msgid "3c84a8f916bc4418acd4874c27a99e2e"
msgstr "And being adorned by the strengths and the fearlessnesses"

msgid "96acd70fb1994426b5567bc234ad76e3"
msgstr "Is to be well adorned by understanding due to lack of pride."

msgid "6a05012b8168439994183d29ff074f0e"
msgstr " “To embrace all sentient beings with love,"

msgid "ba5455cf5c704bf9ba3bfd5821ea34c1"
msgstr "The skilled are ever honest and flexible."

msgid "cdac740470904b8bb799a574415f25f5"
msgstr "Being free of deception, cunning, and hypocrisy"

msgid "1adff9d604144ae89b95eb81681db51d"
msgstr "Is not to be driven by delusion, desire, hatred, and fear."

msgid "de688c7ce3104a538d847477dbcc62e1"
msgstr "“Removing the five obstructions,"

msgid "bc207b6d8a644362a64686225b19fd5e"
msgstr "Vigilantly cultivating the six recollections,"

msgid "ff6cfcd76a5a4a2b8ddb089541116d64"
msgstr "And cultivating the seven factors of awakening and the eightfold path"

msgid "7272895c1d1245c9bdd58a24388b268f"
msgstr ""
"Yields the concentrations of meditative absorption and, finally, the ninth."

msgid "7a531d956db44669bb242abd56d0e700"
msgstr "“For the practitioner to focus and abide in tranquility,"

msgid "1567253994024a31a30a20077f718dcc"
msgstr "To avoid letting correct behavior and virtue go to waste,"

msgid "b2d48ea1535942fba054b360021dc392"
msgstr "And to be detached, pliant, and discerning"

msgid "af99c4e2ffcf4b229be3179029f918a7"
msgstr "Is to uphold the noble lineage."

msgid "d26e48c9d10746b4ab3e3bc3ba8a4193"
msgstr " “Being without doubt regarding phenomena,"

msgid "b43ae0691ad44cf49d18bc86ea1fb1de"
msgstr "Having neither regret nor agitation,"

msgid "58e3b5dd9ba24f89993e673aed01077f"
msgstr "And being without ignorance, delusion, and confusion,"

msgid "04e5ed857be849c3af4042b1c12b1c52"
msgstr "One knows the deep understanding of the illumination of truth."

msgid "eac69bcf3aa64d098cc46c24b1832287"
msgstr "“Being without objectification purifies morality,"

msgid "bf0cae627aaa4414a8618a8c3d10b8ac"
msgstr "True insight purifies concentration and absorption,"

msgid "069810ef9a8a41789ff2d4b551e555bf"
msgstr "Eliminating dualism purifies liberation,"

msgid "10ea31717bfa43b2bff682f2d7bce417"
msgstr "And being without excessive pride purifies understanding."

msgid "fc22cb58263e4923a9594d8d5c82f712"
msgstr ""
"“Purifying the three times, one is not attached to the vision of wisdom."

msgid "047c5b17c5214fecb0fd1c43d04be809"
msgstr "Phenomena are purified by understanding free of desire."

msgid "3c405968c53a4adfacae0c540b2d7a3a"
msgstr "Having been purified, one has no arrogance about it."

msgid "6947ad8c3c3c42d280cc53c66903d4e4"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of those possessing insight."

msgid "b00788679f5c467298df1b23340256f3"
msgstr "“Insight that adorns generosity"

msgid "3d92500b4f4645128a69f4a56b076585"
msgstr ""
"Purifies three aspects: Agent, awakening, and sentient beings, Since they "
"are known to be illusory, unfindable, and dreamlike."

msgid "84cddb2d21b64a2d83464159d74fde11"
msgstr "“Insight that adorns morality"

msgid "6311ce5812de405fb46ed835810eb4ea"
msgstr ""
"Purifies three aspects: Body, speech, and mind, Since they are known to be "
"like a reflection, an echo, and an illusion."

msgid "6a3bc1d50b684237bc04bfce03cf1d2d"
msgstr "“Insight that adorns patience"

msgid "f0eb60ea6c9a4a9a82043eea49771d26"
msgstr ""
"Purifies three aspects: The learned are neither elated nor dejected, And "
"they maintain the steady realization of true dharmakāya."

msgid "4edcee7a624f46e7a2bf52208e66ba83"
msgstr "“Insight that adorns vigor"

msgid "feff12b194984bdea591afc3a48e3460"
msgstr ""
"Purifies three aspects: Not being disheartened, keeping a stable intention, "
"And neither accepting nor rejecting."

msgid "82ddef63f36446ada8f568f18813a2f8"
msgstr "“Insight that adorns concentration"

msgid "b37f750e0f9c4e18a83cb162183e2bab"
msgstr ""
"Purifies three aspects: Nonattachment, special insight, And gaining mastery "
"and superknowledge."

msgid "80b59f9c73c04ef6ab3954111e6c5bb4"
msgstr "“Insight that adorns method"

msgid "6799066dfa494d8d91a36bf44a3392d6"
msgstr ""
"Purifies three aspects: The means of attraction, retention, and aspirations "
"Related to beings, the Dharma, and the buddhafields."

msgid "a1b60f6df7ad4a449570a7f4f50d8ab5"
msgstr "“One does not engage mindfully in the applications of mindfulness,"

msgid "69261d71782e4eb88e0e46694d1abb55"
msgstr "One is free from duality regarding the correct exertions,"

msgid "4edc16b4928d4f1b8a889e3bb96c8c3b"
msgstr ""
"One is physically and mentally detached through the miraculous powers,"

msgid "abdf131e2e0d4ce7a0a300ce1357793e"
msgstr ""
"And one has all the spiritual faculties that are not known to sentient "
"beings."

msgid "a6b2ccef74174b95a39c890d6ae8043d"
msgstr "“One is not overpowered by the māras or afflictive emotions,"

msgid "76d1fdb402d4461c9ce29b79bd42e025"
msgstr "Correctly realizes the nature of phenomena,"

msgid "73ba0588cbe1485da8bb8febd8d684dd"
msgstr "And is without coming and going with regard to the paths—"

msgid "fc27d3c1afec44f182a4df6442b8df74"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of those endowed with insight."

msgid "257718ff5950496ebf7947dff772af78"
msgstr "“One understands tranquil abiding through serenity,"

msgid "3c5758d5367d4a46ba89c6485c6c50ac"
msgstr "And the special insight based on this is boundless in scope."

msgid "1797082a3ec347c6a4dd7b109533867a"
msgstr ""
"One understands the aggregates just as one does the collections of Dharma"

msgid "c3ae6cec0b2b4fbb9512770b5b12cdf9"
msgstr "And that the elements are similar to space."

msgid "1e533851f0934d04a3411aed06ecb64a"
msgstr "“One understands the sense fields to be like a void"

msgid "240365d8488d4a2c91980408d6999ff0"
msgstr ""
"And that phenomena are unoriginated because they come together dependently."

msgid "dd49eec2189a42779512be8da9065914"
msgstr "One understands the ultimate truth without turmoil,"

msgid "5f37344878b145e69bd52a55158e7d5d"
msgstr "And one properly understands definitive realization."

msgid "e4d3bce8d3be4a76a056ca06e34fc696"
msgstr "“Engaging in wisdom unattached to the three times,"

msgid "4e94f866f7a048d4ac8f2bdde32f1b38"
msgstr ""
"One understands the three collections in terms of their classification"

msgid "ec0a850f1f4c49ffa9611b1d821caad6"
msgstr "And the single characteristic of the Three Jewels."

msgid "b6dbf1df8e0241e9a51aacf6a35f2694"
msgstr "These are the ornaments of those endowed with insight."

msgid "011b009a074d4b58ae85e589a63978ab"
msgstr ""
"“One understands that the characteristics of fabrications are like an "
"illusion,"

msgid "ed99f428637b428ea0fa3140df413289"
msgstr "That the root of false imaginings is just like a dream,"

msgid "cbeb5a3431d649fcbe019bc30f6a5212"
msgstr "That the characteristics of projections are like a mirage,"

msgid "445e634c49cd4c93aab1faa8610bdacc"
msgstr ""
"And that motionless phenomena have the characteristics of a reflection."

msgid "7c73b0e6288043f182c6529915777d53"
msgstr "“Composite things are like a hallucination."

msgid "4b5a6a10af6f4c0d92aee089d161f31e"
msgstr "Dependent on conditions, they are just like an echo."

msgid "bb764871cfba4809998f726646ed693e"
msgstr "One understands the realm of phenomena to be always uncorrupted—"

msgid "53cfc7656f3c419eb44be0c3ee3c6a3b"
msgstr "It is suchness, which is groundless."

msgid "7c15fdb7f8b64b30917e09e530d68ffa"
msgstr "“The limit of reality, the ever-motionless reality,"

msgid "85f677a5402e458e84de989a69a888c2"
msgstr "Is without the duality of the conditioned and unconditioned."

msgid "1c6f8fae81514305a81b93025b354268"
msgstr "Adorned with such deep and vast understanding,"

msgid "8298f1b4c787449fad75ce05d0a48a1d"
msgstr "One seeks out the qualities of a buddha."

msgid "d8e670585dd9405a89f5c9003267afd7"
msgstr " “Having memory that never forgets,"

msgid "43f842370a334a078db399d7237d3866"
msgstr "One strives to retain and fully retains the teachings."

msgid "61297d4c32a04282ab9590f7e64168a4"
msgstr "Ever learned in meanings and phonemes,"

msgid "f9f83a3713fb4c748e0f325bd92958a0"
msgstr "One knows etymologies and always gains comprehension."

msgid "b950a7f8083548fda68e07a5639bb966"
msgstr "“One speaks words that are dispassionate and refined,"

msgid "d84fac2dce4e45cda244f4ece883d4ee"
msgstr "Liberating and without falsehood."

msgid "d6453b531fb549f8b7b082863655bec1"
msgstr "Always realizing the meaning of what has been studied,"

msgid "51e435bb7aca476db66686da2ac83cd4"
msgstr "The learned rely on wisdom."

msgid "a36800ce20814447a25f2bcd5ea85b3e"
msgstr ""
"“Being well acquainted with and understanding sūtras of definitive meaning,"

msgid "ede1c057d72348ca9c896b345c9fe791"
msgstr "Relying on the true nature that is devoid of any person,"

msgid "7cefc8591bb24e40ba43a7957fe1d9e4"
msgstr "And relying also on the true nature that is supramundane,"

msgid "57ea6b1b4f344ee8949508b1cf633484"
msgstr "One is adorned with retention."

msgid "bbd0f9bb2bd1457ebc7b778bd8f152f9"
msgstr "“One’s words correspond with the truth—"

msgid "903f75c293354808bcb5324f4e06ff5a"
msgstr "They are suitable to keep in mind and suitable to the occasion."

msgid "4c84749c4bf74e89be570a39e508f7b0"
msgstr "One’s teaching of the Dharma bears fruit,"

msgid "f07dd525641140b4991ddf878001c7b5"
msgstr "Is appropriate, and is always delivered in a timely manner."

msgid "0f2956a1b5f14ef9ba45582a6972756b"
msgstr "“One’s eloquence is swift,"

msgid "03a8ff1fb462454184845cc895ab254d"
msgstr "Forceful, quick, and always dispassionate."

msgid "7c97683da92b47afac5172c9ae8ab2d9"
msgstr "It is uninterrupted, undistorted, and replete with etymologies."

msgid "14357791e9f44c89b47235ff3ccd722b"
msgstr "It is ornamented like a nicely threaded rosary."

msgid "ac2a6a58fe4441df9841a170a4982073"
msgstr ""
"“One knows the languages of all beings: Devas and nāgas, Yakṣas, gandharvas,"
" asuras, Garuḍas, kiṃnaras, and mahoragas."

msgid "e6643f57ce564e5880e7c3f3492f720c"
msgstr "“Knowing how to join a gathering without being intimidated"

msgid "d29edff8b7374a5890565c1b33712fc5"
msgstr "And not being dejected when watching orators,"

msgid "de5e5891a6fc4af18eb35ade6cd69ce4"
msgstr "One gives Dharma lectures fearlessly,"

msgid "f64faa9ae8d0431684e95a7e4a0aafdd"
msgstr "Exercising discretion toward questioners."

msgid "3f053f92814544da9c8f8f00d4f9f84c"
msgstr "“One gives a loosely organized lecture when noticing the arrogant"

msgid "2dff7a424b574854aff38d03f48eb68e"
msgstr "And a well-organized lecture when noticing practitioners."

msgid "ffe0bba82ae347fa9557144198429f78"
msgstr "One manifests as Vajrapāṇi to the proud"

msgid "f29dd9418c324201a6457f250a98af6b"
msgstr "And the end of the eon to those who cling to objects."

msgid "1041391a938e42ac8a0d0fc01dc07268"
msgstr "“Giving lectures about the progression of the three vehicles,"

msgid "eec32b6a22734ff9b2380f74e198ab18"
msgstr "Eliminating the doubts of all the skeptics,"

msgid "94522a8c1fc14e1cb83f554771729382"
msgstr "And revealing the Dharma teachings with one’s mind,"

msgid "85c324c869ad44ceb9ddf38516385ab4"
msgstr "One never allows one’s understanding to depend on others."

msgid "de1219b460e949c3af25cf29be060b20"
msgstr "“One never runs out of words,"

msgid "902fe5f1702b4790b0885a658cf9a558"
msgstr "And one keeps the subject matter decisive and consistent."

msgid "f8e1caa64a7340a2a27097db6fdf45bf"
msgstr "In describing limitless buddha qualities,"

msgid "fdac99149ea34b8fb9af500ce1b98dc8"
msgstr "One is adorned by retention."

msgid "55aa35f8537149d28a05898003b5c107"
msgstr "“One knows the limitless flaws of pollution"

msgid "6179eb425415488e86f107d2e4de89eb"
msgstr "And the infinite benefits of purification."

msgid "75b2d46cfcad4143ae18540717cd8d81"
msgstr "One knows all the capacities of beings"

msgid "de1618d14d4549c588820c4ed9a5af74"
msgstr "And attains the discriminating knowledge granted by the Buddha."

msgid "dcdf197c972f4888a57e4ec25839b04e"
msgstr "“This is to be adorned by retention."

msgid "abbee9feddc64e0aab4a4e87f23946cc"
msgstr "Even if one were to express these and other qualities"

msgid "cce6c0a3c3ea45f2a8ca93af48a7bd73"
msgstr "For eons without interruption,"

msgid "cd170e467ef34b4f8aeb252186068a94"
msgstr "One would be unable to reach their limit.”"

msgid "ac4f59c99b8f406aa51f5ec5f0bbe597"
msgstr ""
"Then the Blessed One spoke the following words to the bodhisattva "
"Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja:"

msgid "25c974d976bd447f8dd3a61865b2f1fa"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight bodhisattva illuminations that "
"brighten bodhisattvas so that they are free from the thick darkness of "
"confusion and engage in pure bodhisattva activities."

msgid "cb2d343b00ae45718911eca0ce3ef6b1"
msgstr ""
"They are the illuminations of  mindfulness,  intelligence,  comprehension,  "
"phenomena,  knowledge,  truth,  superknowledge, and  accomplishment."

msgid "e5c539ae46a9474d87cc3445ca819475"
msgstr "Son of noble family, those are the eight bodhisattva illuminations."

msgid "5af29f5957354de09107d7e2b3c04f7f"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, you may ask, ‘What are the bodhisattva illuminations "
"of mindfulness?’"

msgid "51e3c6bca81c4d6fa1988b296cc4980e"
msgstr ""
"There are eight bodhisattva illuminations of mindfulness: when one prevents "
"the roots of virtue performed in the past from going to waste, accumulates "
"roots of virtue that have not yet been performed, does not forget teachings "
"that one has heard, ascertains their meaning, is not carried away by the six"
" kinds of sense objects, abandons nonvirtuous factors, and accomplishes "
"virtuous factors, then mindfulness has become vast and excellent."

msgid "8f2a0b0ebb484f78b8c37497fff2a938"
msgstr ""
"Realizing that the bodhisattvas’ mindfulness has become excellent, the "
"blessed buddhas appoint them as guardians of the city of the Dharma."

msgid "f1814cf33c2344eb8a9d67a6e25cb3fa"
msgstr ""
"Finally, on the strength of the preceding types of mindfulness, one reaches "
"illumination with respect to all Dharma teachings."

msgid "de01a3002cfc43bc9f43d78c3f109e5c"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, those are the eight bodhisattva illuminations of "
"mindfulness."

msgid "a627cbc5d7c0448086131c0c870af670"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight bodhisattva illuminations of "
"intelligence:"

msgid "5fde2bbf3a0a4e1ca4a395e84cb31c68"
msgstr ""
"intelligence with regard to meaning rather than words or syllables, "
"intelligent wisdom rather than intelligent consciousness, intelligence "
"involving Dharma instead of afflictive emotions, intelligence involving "
"reason instead of what is contrary to reason, the intelligence of bodhicitta"
" rather than the intelligence of a śrāvaka or pratyekabuddha, tremendous "
"intelligence rather than lesser intelligence, the intelligence of a buddha "
"instead of the intelligence of Māra, and compassionate intelligence instead "
"of intelligence that is hostile toward sentient beings."

msgid "4d07bbfa872949e7804e91c194cc9e17"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight bodhisattva illuminations of "
"comprehension:"

msgid "8e55a46ed9ed448a9970cf3b37616140"
msgstr ""
"gaining comprehension of all teachings, of the underlying intent of what was"
" taught, of the dispositions of beings, of the knowledge of the types of "
"discriminating knowledge, of profound dependent arising, of the teachings "
"via nonsequential progression, of the teachings via reverse progression, and"
" of all the qualities of the Buddha."

msgid "b65d844b17704af7baaa79022054172f"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight bodhisattva illuminations of "
"phenomena:"

msgid "e86979aaa36146428b15a6db0b2e5c20"
msgstr ""
"the illuminations of mundane factors through teaching sentient beings to "
"engage in appropriate deeds; of supramundane factors through insightfully "
"teaching those who wish for liberation; of unobscured factors since they "
"have cultivated the path; of uncontaminated factors since they do not take "
"up the defilements of desire, existence, ignorance, or views; of "
"unconditioned factors since they have accomplished the certainty of the "
"noble ones; of factors of pollution since they comprehend well the "
"adventitious afflictive emotions; of factors of purification since their "
"minds are naturally luminous; and of the factors of nirvāṇa since phenomena "
"are totally pacified."

msgid "e45eb1c85e214bc28b9a85673d0b99f5"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight bodhisattva illuminations of "
"knowledge:"

msgid "936a0de279ef4786ab363959584ef7d6"
msgstr ""
"the illuminations of knowledge of someone who has eight existences "
"remaining, a stream enterer, a once-returner, a non-returner, an arhat, a "
"pratyekabuddha, a bodhisattva, and a fully awakened buddha."

msgid "70e8e9847d9841a290fcf49521657974"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight bodhisattva illuminations of truth:"

msgid "39a3faa6419741cd85c4b0c5871bf973"
msgstr ""
"the illuminations of the cultivation of the truth by which they enter a "
"state of certainty, by which they attain the first fruition, by which they "
"attain the second fruition, by which they attain the third fruition, by "
"which they attain the fourth fruition, by which they attain "
"pratyekabuddhahood, by which they attain the acceptance of a bodhisattva, "
"and by which they completely and perfectly awaken to the awakening of a "
"buddha."

msgid "949e9be9e8a24de48083935276b6950d"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are eight bodhisattva illuminations of "
"superknowledge:"

msgid "1f4a53aa317844b1be0de000aba7e4c9"
msgstr ""
"the illuminations of clarity because bodhisattvas see all forms with the "
"divine eye, of comprehension because they hear all sounds with the divine "
"ear, of recollection because they recollect countless eons of previous "
"existences, of natural luminosity because they gaze upon the minds of all "
"beings, of the unobscured sky because they move by miraculous power through "
"boundless buddhafields, of knowledge because they accomplish a knowledge "
"that is free of defilements, of the accumulation of merit because they "
"sustain all beings, and of the accumulation of wisdom because they eliminate"
" the doubts of all sentient beings."

msgid "5481443102b94fc7a5510ac19df0bf5b"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are nine bodhisattva illuminations of "
"accomplishment:"

msgid "db8370e8e5f84c779b79c8e79d389291"
msgstr ""
"the illuminations through accomplishment of wisdom, insight, understanding, "
"correct view, tranquil abiding, special insight, the intentions of beings, a"
" liberated mind that is unperturbed, and the final illumination.”"

msgid "fa97806a341247f4ac87a93212863c7c"
msgstr "Then, the Blessed One spoke the following verses:"

msgid "ea3b8412559e4035abfea402ab1949c8"
msgstr ""
"“Bodhisattvas imbued with mindfulness Do not waste the roots of virtue "
"accumulated in the past."

msgid "26854ac9a6a24dc3828142aee3090a78"
msgstr ""
"Their excellence in subtle dedication Accomplishes buddhafields for the sake"
" of the future."

msgid "1c5e8df79a6a4bc2a60b27c47df5e908"
msgstr ""
"“They never forget the teachings they have heard, And they swiftly reach a "
"state of certainty."

msgid "f9aab8d1b7c9496e9608ec89585904a2"
msgstr "At peace, they are shielded from the sense objects."

msgid "a673fd0239444d88b7917ab9d14e55ad"
msgstr "Endowed with mindfulness, they are freed from nonvirtue."

msgid "8dd18f3dd99c4bd6877c87b83fb84e30"
msgstr ""
"Having accumulated vast mindfulness, They discern which actions are to be "
"performed."

msgid "cb45f51927fc4d96bfe4b38a64227a98"
msgstr ""
"“With the blessing of the self-arisen victors Who know that they are endowed"
" with mindfulness,"

msgid "b85d24456e5e43d29756b8b30262e90c"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattvas guard the city of the noble Dharma And teach Dharma to "
"beings."

msgid "d8ee7c83a4b94ca891651fb7d9b29500"
msgstr ""
"“Endowed with wisdom and separated from gloom, They accomplish the benefit "
"of gods and humans."

msgid "a041894b421f44df9688edc3d76c02fa"
msgstr ""
"Having attained the illumination of excellent intelligence, They eliminate "
"doubts and hesitations."

msgid "210378b2e46e42f49ec73879024837db"
msgstr ""
"Endowed with mindfulness, their spontaneous wisdom Brings swift realization "
"of awakening."

msgid "930de585f8ac4be796df7324b794919d"
msgstr ""
"“Bodhisattvas are endowed with intelligence regarding meaning Rather than "
"words, letters, or grammar."

msgid "3ba01aefb88e4e1db2906893639ef19a"
msgstr ""
"Pure beings endowed with the intelligence of wisdom Do not long for the "
"intelligence of ordinary consciousness."

msgid "412c147cc1634379b0fe1b0030df596b"
msgstr ""
"“Endowed with intelligence involving Dharma, They dispel intelligence "
"involving afflictive emotion and are freed from delusion."

msgid "c040d836b00b49ef80514e9623421c24"
msgstr ""
"Knowing the ways of insight and method, They do not contravene the awakening"
" of the Victor."

msgid "87429463533e49348edbfe6120068a0e"
msgstr ""
"“Their intelligence is focused on becoming buddhas, Not on becoming śrāvakas"
" or pratyekabuddhas."

msgid "adbbb009f0d141b3909b688a612ad247"
msgstr ""
"They are constantly endowed with tremendous intelligence And do not long for"
" intelligence of a lesser kind."

msgid "252b2b16a0864673a75ca688293ba0c4"
msgstr ""
"“They are perpetually endowed with the intelligence of a buddha, Which does "
"not turn into the intelligence of Māra."

msgid "5c3e667db1d841e3bac0f7bb341be871"
msgstr ""
"These intelligent ones are committed to great compassion, Not to harming any"
" beings in any way."

msgid "5c20aa2190504337b9777fbe20abbdef"
msgstr ""
"“Bodhisattvas comprehend and are free from hesitation Regarding any of the "
"teachings that the Buddha has taught."

msgid "3a291abfa00847f58853c1f35f299811"
msgstr ""
"They become skilled in communicating their intended meanings, And they "
"understand the conduct of sentient beings."

msgid "a626b936b1a548b3a436a50324754f6e"
msgstr ""
"“They comprehend discriminating knowledge And have no attachment to the "
"application of such knowing."

msgid "5e36afda200246baa20ad2ecc0278bb6"
msgstr ""
"They know well that conditioned phenomena Are dependently arisen and have no"
" creator."

msgid "2458d0e3f5744b03aefa1a3c762e187a"
msgstr ""
"“They are learned in the causes of nonsequential progression, And they "
"comprehend the ways of reverse progression."

msgid "f7e7d8e5f2384e46a4c26aa411afd9ae"
msgstr ""
"They attain comprehension Of the whole spectrum of the teachings of the "
"Buddha."

msgid "5a008be7e4f242188ef60dec19469d52"
msgstr ""
"“By means of their illumination of mundane phenomena, Bodhisattvas know the "
"deeds of gods and humans."

msgid "ba5bb02f28244e278f1721017778703c"
msgstr ""
"Through supramundane wisdom, They are endowed with the illumination of "
"insight."

msgid "7bce2af4f86b40d2b1d6ebb33ce3b0e4"
msgstr ""
"They apply exceedingly bright wisdom Both to those with and without fault."

msgid "fa15384bccb54f42a4be393feeacc1d7"
msgstr ""
"“Because bodhisattvas have cultivated the path, They always teach the Dharma"
" that bears fruit."

msgid "1eb84e4397044d958faa61f82cde59c8"
msgstr ""
"They apply its illumination Both to contaminated and uncontaminated "
"phenomena."

msgid "85532a222b394ac882ed0dfd3f1bb898"
msgstr "They abandon all contaminants And thus benefit both gods and humans."

msgid "7cec2cdb970146fe81df4fa2dd99feb1"
msgstr ""
"“Bodhisattvas constantly apply their knowledge Both to conditioned and "
"unconditioned phenomena."

msgid "21c65cbd73204f26bdbc84d99b44b336"
msgstr "They are thereby free from stains and without distorted vision."

msgid "a35bbe95252549baaa977941a26bc4db"
msgstr "Having attained flawlessness, they likewise engage in good conduct."

msgid "9732be4344c440ea92bfcfc22d384a2c"
msgstr ""
"“Bodhisattvas apply their unobscured knowledge To the factors of "
"purification and pollution."

msgid "4a832751dc2640ad8f51c98118ff6cae"
msgstr ""
"Thus they understand that the mind is luminous by nature And the ways in "
"which it becomes polluted."

msgid "9ff584b4285d4c3590e3acccc6710ea9"
msgstr ""
"“Bodhisattvas know how the state of nirvāṇa Is unborn and without "
"origination."

msgid "2f5bbdf3d9424874b13b196f15115e3d"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, in the Great Vehicle, The illuminations of phenomena are "
"infinite."

msgid "6433a0f887494e1ba1e5286c00ff8de1"
msgstr ""
"“Bodhisattvas pursue the knowledge of one with eight existences remaining "
"And the knowledge of a stream enterer. They pursue the knowledge of a once-"
"returner And the knowledge of a non-returner."

msgid "7ebb56f881f34686b0bd1fdddd266d02"
msgstr ""
"“They pursue the knowledge and accomplishments Of all the arhats and "
"pratyekabuddhas,"

msgid "c7be19e667de42d4a18834283844e84b"
msgstr ""
"Of all the world protectors and the bodhisattvas, Without a single "
"exception."

msgid "ce71532a12cf405d886eacdd55da40e7"
msgstr ""
"“Those heroes who Attain the fruitions, Who gain deliverance in the "
"imperturbable ultimate,"

msgid "7533c93e73f34c4dbaa5a76d64a04422"
msgstr ""
"And who disclose its cultivation embody the illumination of the truths."

msgid "fba03d03a7ae4b8fb2b83748ce5aa359"
msgstr ""
"“Since they have cultivated those truths, They enter a state of flawlessness"
" and attain the first fruition."

msgid "b5c60a7fa7ba4d9c8a1978d368de8620"
msgstr ""
"They also attain the second, the third, the fourth, And likewise the "
"fruition of pratyekabuddhahood."

msgid "019ca6c088394061bc676177df35d6bf"
msgstr ""
"“Those tigers of speech who through cultivation Attain acceptance And attain"
" the awakening of the victors Will illuminate those truths."

msgid "093defe6783a4aedb5fd73c234f601e6"
msgstr "“Bodhisattvas see all aspects of form With the divine eye."

msgid "8e3d10a3c862420e807c8b9a7fd8a8a8"
msgstr ""
"They perceive the sounds of the ten directions Through the discernment of "
"the divine ear."

msgid "7099c6a4960d48eaa043dbb935d80fe0"
msgstr ""
"“Through the illumination of the knowledge of previous existences, They "
"recall billions of eons."

msgid "ded05a892445413c9df0227c4bfe5ba2"
msgstr ""
"Through the illumination of the knowledge of luminosity, They have knowledge"
" of the mental conduct of others."

msgid "99cdf039c5dd4904af7c0b9cc12f50f9"
msgstr ""
"“Through the illumination of the knowledge of miracles, They move throughout"
" billions of buddhafields in the ten directions."

msgid "96d51efaef324389a6b15bf3c476f0f9"
msgstr "Their illumination of uncontaminated knowledge Is similar to space."

msgid "dd293997b93449d1bee296a020356b4b"
msgstr ""
"“Through the meritorious illumination of boundless superknowledge, "
"Bodhisattvas first approach beings,"

msgid "4b3634b3c24c4b028032e17fbc70dded"
msgstr ""
"And then, through dispassionate knowledge of them, They eliminate the doubts"
" of those beings."

msgid "c9df7b9e6c644642b748ee03c8cebb53"
msgstr ""
"“Yogic practitioners who apply themselves vigorously Thus gain the "
"illuminations of mindfulness, Intelligence, comprehension, phenomena, and "
"knowledge, The boundless illumination of truth, And the illumination of "
"superknowledge."

msgid "e42b8353dd114ea6ac7f6ddead10bfb3"
msgstr ""
"“Accomplishment culminates in wisdom and insight, Vast understanding and "
"boundless eloquence, Correct view and special insight, And total "
"imperturbability."

msgid "b3c3d19f68c14b98829c63a0e9851b36"
msgstr ""
"“Even though those powerful beings In whom these eight pure illuminations "
"are present Might not obtain awakening right now, They will nonetheless "
"perform buddha activities.”"

msgid "02668c8e0deb4c61b53c213abfb6460c"
msgstr "Then the Blessed One told Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja,"

msgid "4e29d323705846d689aab2130319d282"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, there are sixteen ways in which bodhisattvas give rise"
" to great bodhisattva compassion for sentient beings."

msgid "e88778eda83e444cad96217e35bfcee7"
msgstr "What are these sixteen ways?"

msgid "3e6b3164259c45098905410302fbda6f"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, bodhisattvas give rise to a bodhisattva’s great "
"compassion for sentient beings while thinking as follows:"

msgid "df92eef98ede4795a4367de11c4a7e13"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings are fettered by personalistic views, and they are "
"mixed up with various kinds of wrong views."

msgid "4381a73a3ce349588e9106a3315d72d1"
msgstr "To help them abandon all those views, I shall teach them the Dharma."

msgid "e40280095a3044f5ae77e00891feacbb"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings, due to misapprehension about what is actually the "
"case, perceive what is impermanent to be permanent, what is painful to be "
"pleasant, what is no self to be a self, and what is repulsive to be "
"attractive."

msgid "fe80c48106c94aceb89e00635b5780a7"
msgstr ""
"To help them abandon all misapprehensions, I shall teach them the Dharma."

msgid "ced1f948aa1a4f8d83ad1c180873f4d6"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings are stuck grasping onto I and mine, and they perceive "
"what is insubstantial to be substantial."

msgid "e46844ef5a8844ffb11dda7638f93d90"
msgstr ""
"To help them abandon grasping onto I and mine, I shall teach them the "
"Dharma."

msgid "dfc294c081c94cdd979debad071401d8"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings are obstructed by the five obstructions: they are "
"tormented by sharp pangs of desire, they are very aggressive, they are "
"attached to fogginess and sleep, they are excited and regretful toward "
"ignoble objects, and they are unable to reach certainty about the holy "
"Dharma."

msgid "aaea2ffec3b24ffaaf167877d72c6480"
msgstr "To help them abandon all obstructions, I shall teach them the Dharma."

msgid "da0a5c05b49846218b6f86b266fd2543"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings are bound by attachment to the six sense fields:"

msgid "fed5b71cacc74a4e87452f62d5572fda"
msgstr ""
"when they see form with their eyes, they cling to its marks and "
"characteristics, and when they hear sounds with their ears, experience "
"smells with their noses, experience tastes with their tongues, feel "
"sensations with their bodies, and notice phenomena with their mental "
"faculties, they cling to their marks and characteristics."

msgid "2bf5789f21814938858438f4247273cb"
msgstr ""
"To help them abandon attachment to the six sense fields, I shall teach them "
"the Dharma."

msgid "5477fa09f73f4e7695e1bf1bf1566abe"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings are overcome by pride, the pride of superiority, "
"excessive pride, the pride that thinks “I am,” manifest pride, the inverted "
"pride of self-abasement, and mistaken pride."

msgid "c61c9b29865e4e7cb559c997fc1d81b8"
msgstr ""
"Since they are conceited about themselves, they think “We are greater than "
"those who are inferior,” “We are greater than those who are our equals,” and"
" “We are even greater than those who are greater.”"

msgid "bd30192b28d64e5da0f7ad5bb59c7e3a"
msgstr ""
"They take their five aggregates, from form to consciousness, as constituting"
" I. They consider what has not been attained and think “I have attained it.”"

msgid "b878d8fcafbf4318b49ad326bc59b0e0"
msgstr ""
"They reflect upon themselves and think “We are superior.” And they believe "
"that their wrong views are correct."

msgid "2e30df76792c41b08dc575468e0ac171"
msgstr ""
"To help them abandon all forms of pride, I shall teach them the Dharma."

msgid "f04d6e4056cd481c8ce0519ba2fd6d49"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings have followed evil paths and are separated from the "
"noble path."

msgid "2028a551aa9648f6bb49347549d14328"
msgstr ""
"To help them abandon evil paths and find the noble path, I shall teach them "
"the Dharma."

msgid "cc084adfb1cf4c5d8c297661e22ef05d"
msgstr "“ ‘Alas, these beings are the slaves of craving."

msgid "b37f3d3f1e0c4c74a175a73f2e93a843"
msgstr "They are consumed by desire for wives, sons, and daughters."

msgid "5cf6f4d0ae1444c1abb2706804d84c9c"
msgstr "They have no independence or self-assurance."

msgid "a01f40eb99074ca7a0f3392ceee6352d"
msgstr ""
"To help them become independent, able to assert themselves, and dance with "
"joy, I shall teach them the Dharma."

msgid "6cc1732c789747a1ada5d8a45ec7ca45"
msgstr "“ ‘Alas, these beings are not in harmony with one another;"

msgid "6cbed0421f0a4ca58f2554305ad93fa9"
msgstr "they are full of anger, hatred, and ill will."

msgid "3ff0ea8d171c41d3b404ff80566d19af"
msgstr ""
"To help them abandon their anger, hatred, and ill will, I shall teach them "
"the Dharma."

msgid "73a90c1b9ebc4f2689e11d7cbb8ba28e"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings who are entangled with evil company and lack virtuous "
"friends commit evil deeds."

msgid "7a4da682e12e4e018b37c9d29b49116f"
msgstr ""
"In order for virtuous friends to take them on and to help them abandon evil "
"companions, I shall teach them the Dharma."

msgid "e0476ea015de4b329e4b68aa632ebb53"
msgstr "“ ‘Alas, these beings are overwhelmed by desire and attachment."

msgid "ea7dfee1f0004a4da3c61703a6e4b966"
msgstr ""
"They are discontent, and they are divorced from the state of the insight of "
"the noble ones."

msgid "b11472ec011847119e2b3285c030c187"
msgstr ""
"To help them abandon attachment and develop the knowledge of the noble ones,"
" I shall teach them the Dharma."

msgid "386b0a9d6b494854ac619920d7ef5d27"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings are entrenched in eternalistic and nihilistic views, "
"and they think that actions do not have consequences."

msgid "9c8e89ea5d154fa9b62597aa69923af4"
msgstr ""
"To guide them toward profound dependent arising and appropriate actions, I "
"shall teach them the Dharma."

msgid "5496ca8265e84005a805761d557a3d2d"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings who are blinded by ignorance and delusion cling to the"
" notions of a self, a being, a life, a living being, an individual, and a "
"person."

msgid "2d18df6a615a4c15b9df57d2ab85b119"
msgstr ""
"To help them purify the eye of noble insight and abandon all views, I shall "
"teach them the Dharma."

msgid "42dfa5d205db44c681f7296dbcdc7510"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings revel in saṃsāra and are captured by the executioner "
"of the five aggregates."

msgid "2c4a68ff0ff3420ca519335bc2c5c23f"
msgstr ""
"In order to extricate them from all the three realms, I shall teach them the"
" Dharma."

msgid "2005b3336a3148b29a010a487789fd9e"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings are tethered by Māra’s lasso and persist in cunning "
"and conceit."

msgid "47f76b7b345f445097fdf989e3861135"
msgstr ""
"In order that they become liberated from all the tethers of Māra’s lasso and"
" abandon cunning and conceit, I shall teach them the Dharma."

msgid "96aeea021a174330b344dd2b8271a2fc"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas, these beings have shut the gate to nirvāṇa and opened the gates to "
"the evil destinies."

msgid "48525252d53a440dacb2b0281df8c26e"
msgstr ""
"To help them open the gate to nirvāṇa and shut the gates to the evil "
"destinies, I shall teach them the Dharma.’"

msgid "0e33827e03d8416eaf921b56630e3fc5"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, great bodhisattva compassion for sentient beings "
"arises in these sixteen ways."

msgid "7f94ced448cc4d5386921f8bc72fa047"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, when bodhisattvas exert themselves in thirty-two "
"distinct bodhisattva activities, they become performers of excellent "
"conduct."

msgid "d723de1ccb2143379b833f36693e6a64"
msgstr "What are these thirty-two?"

msgid "f8a591754f5c40eda0364d9c421ee26e"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings go astray due to the sleep of delusion, while "
"they themselves are awakened through insight, bodhisattvas awaken beings "
"through insight."

msgid "b0282563e2474f4882cb601f781f5b0f"
msgstr "This is the first distinct bodhisattva act."

msgid "c65660d979454777a7d56f3f360b4c3f"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings aspire to the insignificant, while they "
"themselves aspire to the vast, bodhisattvas establish beings in the Great "
"Vehicle."

msgid "6656a015ef344386a0be150d2bf76942"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings desire what is not righteous, while they "
"themselves abide in what is righteous, bodhisattvas establish beings in the "
"desire for what is righteous."

msgid "e19b38c1615f440fac2754be723aa796"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing that the livelihoods of sentient beings are impure, while their own "
"livelihoods are pure, bodhisattvas connect beings to pure livelihoods."

msgid "ae45f71f7e724420b19d999c120491a2"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are sunk in views, while they establish "
"themselves in correct views, bodhisattvas establish beings in the correct "
"views of the noble ones."

msgid "c6df85cbd8dc4977bffd28ea92e52eb8"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing that sentient beings are ignorant and have amassed improper ways of "
"thinking, yet cognizant that they themselves abide by proper mental activity"
" that accords with reason, bodhisattvas establish beings in proper mental "
"activity that accords with reason."

msgid "cfde7f45d2d54affa0c98ce8a8f7801e"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings have taken a stand on the wrong teachings, while"
" they themselves have engaged the correct teachings, bodhisattvas teach "
"beings the Dharma so that beings may practice these correct teachings."

msgid "dac6f6a480734bc2aaae4d43567f7046"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing that sentient beings are stingy and possessive, while they "
"themselves have renounced all possessions, bodhisattvas connect beings with "
"the renunciation of all possessions."

msgid "22e1dcc7e23f498da6408a8dc33380a1"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings come to have evil characters and keep no moral "
"commitments, while they themselves are established in pure morality, "
"bodhisattvas establish beings in the commitments of morality."

msgid "3ab873c8f526498cb7612033584f3dfb"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings harbor ill will and are very aggressive, while "
"they themselves are established in the power of patience and love, "
"bodhisattvas establish beings in the power of patience and benevolence."

msgid "c0d61032cdb0424dbbf75207a7f39b92"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are lazy and not very diligent, while they "
"themselves are not lazy and apply themselves diligently, bodhisattvas "
"connect beings with applying themselves diligently."

msgid "0bb34655dbe74c68b584f4bfdfcf8e43"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are distracted and how their mindfulness is "
"weak, while they themselves have equipoise and are absorbed in "
"concentration, bodhisattvas establish beings in a state where they are not "
"distracted but are mindful and vigilant."

msgid "4d08fe32347641eeae437c49bc28f082"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings’ understanding is impaired and how they are "
"depraved and deluded, while they themselves are insightful and free of "
"delusion, bodhisattvas establish beings in great wisdom and freedom from "
"delusion."

msgid "a8612c4f98d145a3bba17dbf6196e104"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings have fallen into the unsuitable and thus commit "
"terrible deeds, while they themselves possess skillful means and perform "
"correct deeds, bodhisattvas establish beings in skillful means and the "
"performance of correct deeds."

msgid "b87c9c9eed7945eb9ddd332113ca7885"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are overpowered by afflictive emotions and how "
"their world thus consists in imagination, conceptualization, and "
"reification, while they themselves have turned away from all afflictive "
"emotions, bodhisattvas establish beings in the abandoning of all afflictive "
"emotions."

msgid "4c46fb0a6f0848f391e017edde774520"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are fettered by the shackles of personalistic "
"views and thus dwell in objectification, while they themselves have fully "
"understood these personalistic views and thus become free from being "
"fettered by objectification, bodhisattvas connect beings with fully "
"understanding personalistic views and freedom from objectification."

msgid "beabade3660348d4bb284348dfd88a29"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing that sentient beings are undisciplined, immodest and unrefined, "
"while they themselves are disciplined, modest, and refined, bodhisattvas "
"establish beings in discipline, modesty, and refinement."

msgid "a7eb9353c919434383b20913cb1b5c95"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings do not remember or acknowledge what has been "
"done for them and destroy their roots of virtue, while they themselves "
"remember and acknowledge what has been done for them and protect their roots"
" of virtue, bodhisattvas establish beings in remembering and acknowledging "
"what has been done for them and not letting their roots of virtue go to "
"waste."

msgid "513b7c38ca9f4967860c41b7f7c5c8bb"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings have fallen into the torrent and are under the "
"influence of the desire to sin, while they themselves have crossed over all "
"rivers, bodhisattvas connect beings to crossing over all rivers."

msgid "1d9654d80fa94974b9dfa3c2c6c43004"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings do not delight in and fail to comply with words "
"of advice, while they themselves delight in and comply with words of advice,"
" bodhisattvas establish beings in delighting in and complying with words of "
"advice."

msgid "6dc07f1572cc41c1889a9eca055e206c"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are destitute and cling to what is ignoble, "
"while they themselves are not destitute and dwell in deathless virtue, "
"bodhisattvas connect beings with freedom from clinging and abiding by the "
"roots of virtue."

msgid "e50e3f2788bd4ad4b907b2f913cc3929"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are poor and lack the wealth of the noble ones, "
"while they themselves do not lack the wealth of the noble ones and are "
"endowed with the seven riches, bodhisattvas establish beings in attaining "
"the wealth of the noble ones."

msgid "1e4963dde5f649c68f6a7bcc5896a3d4"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are constantly ill and ensnared by the venomous "
"snakes of the four elements, while they themselves are never ill and always "
"healthy, bodhisattvas establish beings in abandoning all forms of illness."

msgid "9fd9d4285bad43b596031f613c3aa292"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing that sentient beings are enveloped by the darkness of unknowing and "
"lack the illumination of wisdom, while they themselves have attained the "
"illumination of wisdom, bodhisattvas establish beings in the great "
"illumination of wisdom."

msgid "8a712816bf98453ebeda059426373ec9"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are bound by attachment to the three realms and "
"plunge into the five states of existence within the wheel of saṃsāra, while "
"knowing that they themselves are skilled in the full understanding of the "
"three realms, bodhisattvas establish beings in the skill of the full "
"understanding of the three realms."

msgid "6432195cd4a7451faaa152caaf7dc4bc"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings have embarked on wrong paths and diverged from "
"the right path, while they themselves are established on the right path, "
"bodhisattvas establish beings on the right path."

msgid "369bbfc745194773a6ddde39feeb9988"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are attached to their bodies and lives and fail "
"to perceive their faults, while they themselves pay no heed to their bodies "
"and lives and see their own inadequacies, bodhisattvas establish beings in "
"paying no attention to their bodies and lives and seeing their own "
"inadequacies."

msgid "c2a39f65d84645aa94bc6c25910e2ed6"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are separated from the Buddha, Dharma, and "
"Saṅgha, while they themselves are immersed in the unbroken lineage of the "
"Three Jewels, bodhisattvas lead beings into the unbroken lineage of the "
"Three Jewels."

msgid "4ffe60e521cb43a9ad222391a983806e"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings fall away from the excellent Dharma, while they "
"themselves persist in upholding the excellent Dharma, bodhisattvas establish"
" beings in upholding the excellent Dharma."

msgid "c0e50161bb2d4d15ace9be74a359a95b"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings live far from precious teachers and lack the six"
" recollections, while they themselves never give up the six recollections, "
"bodhisattvas establish beings in cultivating the six recollections."

msgid "bd1854fe6e2a47d49f862a36512610b2"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings are obscured by the veils of karma and "
"afflictive emotions, while they themselves are free from karma and "
"afflictive emotions, bodhisattvas establish beings in the freedom from karma"
" and afflictive emotions."

msgid "c0cc2ac234604f22b77850382577f222"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing how sentient beings possess all nonvirtuous qualities and have "
"abandoned all virtuous qualities, while they themselves have abandoned all "
"nonvirtuous qualities and possess all virtuous qualities, bodhisattvas "
"establish beings in the abandoning of all nonvirtuous qualities and the "
"perfection of all virtuous qualities."

msgid "67e7c85b13044e88b152f8a63fbb97cc"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, these thirty-two bodhisattva activities constitute the"
" preeminence of bodhisattvas."

msgid "1b556309e415485bab326e1f81c5dfd3"
msgstr ""
"Once bodhisattvas are established in these, they are agents of excellent "
"deeds."

msgid "0c82d235202f4849ac77b417d9f1676b"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, the conduct of bodhisattvas is immeasurable."

msgid "99c57a370bbf4676b43ecbc5c92b3783"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "1a1dfbc78dac43a1849e4197794fc2cc"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, as many possibilities of pollution as there are among "
"sentient beings, bodhisattvas can accomplish that many possibilities of "
"purification."

msgid "92f52afcf52a45cf80bae690c96303f9"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, even if all the sentient beings of world systems as "
"numerous as grains of sand in the river Ganges were situated in the śrāvaka "
"or pratyekabuddha vehicles, whatever the activity of all these beings, it "
"would not come close to even a hundredth of the activity of bodhisattvas who"
" have generated the first thought of awakening."

msgid "24563708b919425fa29e42fdc4fdf2e3"
msgstr ""
"It would not come close to even a thousandth, a hundred thousandth, a ten "
"millionth, a billionth, or any number, fraction, enumeration, analogy, or "
"comparison of it."

msgid "96e787080db94c67b52b94fb77faa35f"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "c239a23da817441b894ad8edeac16c87"
msgstr ""
"Śrāvakas and pratyekabuddhas are committed to abandoning the afflictive "
"emotions of their own mindstreams, but bodhisattvas are committed to "
"abandoning the afflictive emotions of all sentient beings."

msgid "612c4a588d0f4bd09a045565ba7e46bd"
msgstr ""
"In this way, son of noble family, compared to the activity of all beings and"
" the activity of śrāvakas and pratyekabuddhas, the activity of bodhisattvas "
"is said to be supreme."

msgid "fbff19261e914b09bed0c9e49dcd8595"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "f2d3892467f649fcba986ea393ff68d0"
msgstr ""
"The activity of immature ordinary beings is mistaken, and the activity of "
"all śrāvakas and pratyekabuddhas is limited, but the activity of "
"bodhisattvas yields qualities that are unmistaken and immeasurable."

msgid "f38f4bd0faaa4eb3be152f235821b19d"
msgstr ""
"It is because of this that bodhisattvas surpass all beings and all śrāvakas "
"and pratyekabuddhas.”"

msgid "f9b5d0bd5ab042d9a55acc56d497c5ac"
msgstr ""
"At this the bodhisattva Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja was content, pleased, delighted, "
"and overjoyed."

msgid "eff8fcdca1214b2ea7e33491f0e47782"
msgstr ""
"Feeling joyful and happy, he took delight in what was proclaimed by the "
"Blessed One."

msgid "2b534b456a544a90a6ed755473e62b32"
msgstr "He rejoiced, saying to the Blessed One,"

msgid "1e3b692279af4871a01f896e0f3886ae"
msgstr ""
"“Blessed One, these excellent descriptions the Tathāgata has given of the "
"bodhisattva ornaments, the bodhisattva illuminations, the great compassion "
"of bodhisattvas, and the conduct of bodhisattvas are marvelous!"

msgid "de48cde58d654b4390c7ddb818501fd6"
msgstr "“May the Blessed tathāgata, arhat, completely perfect Buddha teach."

msgid "1d18f8faa90c4c818132f963d0f3957a"
msgstr ""
"Blessed One, how does the great compassion of the blessed buddhas enter "
"sentient beings?"

msgid "08373f76cf034482b22d975e3d42b226"
msgstr ""
"What exactly are the aspects, characteristics, signs, foundation, and extent"
" of great tathāgata compassion?"

msgid "ef23d0db81bd488ab1c6cc34e1bbf363"
msgstr "How do blessed buddhas perform their activity?"

msgid "2dd0cd89ed9545fe962f1d4e1081ca1e"
msgstr ""
"What exactly are the aspects, characteristics, signs, foundation, and extent"
" of their activity?"

msgid "a08eed97e43c4083a7141ba9147399a4"
msgstr ""
"Blessed One! Please explain directly to us how the activity of the "
"omniscient, all-seeing tathāgatas manifests.”"

msgid "ab435d6816314733b850bac853ee2022"
msgstr "Then the Blessed One replied,"

msgid "5cfc24e5067e4c8ebbbf629e4c4d94d2"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, listen well and remember, and I will explain to you "
"briefly the engagement of great tathāgata compassion and tathāgata activity."

msgid "f137b6e72ba34dd2a1edebf76f71b452"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, I shall elucidate the statement that the great "
"compassion of blessed buddhas for sentient beings ‘neither arises nor "
"engages.’"

msgid "83601b03e54d4ce083ff31296165be8b"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "864c5972662d48bda7a2e0161a98acf2"
msgstr "The great compassion of blessed buddhas is constantly engaged."

msgid "66be49fda5874219aab718e3952b8ff8"
msgstr ""
"Since it is properly generated through training over innumerable eons, it is"
" neither engaged nor disengaged."

msgid "2ec297978a0c45af8be58a4841a3d0c0"
msgstr ""
"The great compassion of blessed buddhas is present for all sentient beings "
"without being activated."

msgid "01cfc63189044a84a4b5dd272caaf3d9"
msgstr ""
"As difficult as it was to obtain great tathāgata compassion, that is how "
"immeasurable, inconceivable, inexhaustible, and far reaching it is."

msgid "d6bbfec04574425380d402e975fd8bdd"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "30292f1fc05e483c9035714f7c24645f"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, as tathāgatas obtain awakening, their great compassion "
"extends to sentient beings."

msgid "10162164ea554920b508a2a071c6b124"
msgstr "Awakening is great compassion!"

msgid "bf174999befd4541b2c6d5d4ca57411f"
msgstr ""
"“How do tathāgatas attain such awakening? Tathāgatas attain awakening where "
"there is no root and no foundation."

msgid "4407dd7351b44c0cafa4fe7defd6712e"
msgstr "In this regard, what is the root? What is the foundation?"

msgid "19cd0cd62f91405999afe750d85ce52c"
msgstr "Personalism is the root and unreal imagining is the foundation."

msgid "d0ae932c9cd649c582ef4c29a1563c7e"
msgstr ""
"Tathāgatas understand these two to be the same because they are the same as "
"awakening."

msgid "26a521575ee24780b818ba18c4680b0e"
msgstr ""
"Consequently, it is said that tathāgatas are perfect and complete buddhas "
"whose awakening is without root and without foundation. Great tathāgata "
"compassion extends to beings as they think, ‘These sentient beings do not "
"comprehend these phenomena that are without root and without foundation. "
"They should comprehend them.’"

msgid "66642ff56aad4c909b5399fb02f96d1c"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, awakening is peaceful and tranquil."

msgid "0c1a061a411049b6a4940c9d2315f68d"
msgstr "In this regard, what is peacefulness? What is tranquility?"

msgid "5a7b6ce5e10f45d78e8139613fbe94e9"
msgstr "The inner world is peaceful."

msgid "b226214421be48dfb2642648f9362ccd"
msgstr "The outer world is tranquil."

msgid "cdf9afd6261f4afb922719649279093b"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "2791cba32d3a44c58cc4e607a54bdfd5"
msgstr "The eye is empty of self and what belongs to a self."

msgid "5a763734ae9d4fa480e570725db9f633"
msgstr "That is its nature."

msgid "670529c96d06401b8eed4ead8a0289f0"
msgstr ""
"The ear, the nose, the tongue, the body, and the mind are empty of self and "
"what belongs to a self."

msgid "0193ac8c709f420992554559c590f24f"
msgstr "That is their nature."

msgid "8adc59a8a9b14bbb87638e64d4891c41"
msgstr ""
"Because one understands the eye to be empty, one does not pursue form."

msgid "4fbcecfb8e6f4f0880cdff7b81cd3c82"
msgstr "Therefore it is said to be tranquil."

msgid "c68c18a4a48f4b5dbc58dc97ecf1ce02"
msgstr ""
"Because one understands the ear to be empty, one does not pursue sound."

msgid "caf5026c811e42c7a2e9aeb214cb7127"
msgstr "Therefore it is said to be tranquil."

msgid "d3242635eec34f8a860528fa3b6cae58"
msgstr ""
"Because one understands the nose to be empty, one does not pursue smell."

msgid "be678ef78c2943fdb00c103374654500"
msgstr "Therefore it is said to be tranquil."

msgid "f2c4cc2de5054c07aae100f04369cfd1"
msgstr ""
"Because one understands the tongue to be empty, one does not pursue taste."

msgid "4554b1dd3a6546f99eef7ab30778a8c2"
msgstr "Therefore it is said to be tranquil."

msgid "2469339ebbbc44d09c942abeffbeda57"
msgstr ""
"Because one understands the body to be empty, one does not pursue the "
"tangible."

msgid "507f7dd6c7ef41298ec04ce94f588269"
msgstr "Therefore it is said to be tranquil."

msgid "a65e1accd069475b97542687cf558236"
msgstr ""
"Because one understands the mind to be empty, one does not pursue mental "
"factors."

msgid "9f3a10a58eec460a84efa560efd6cb98"
msgstr "Therefore it is said to be tranquil."

msgid "1b607c968edc4c34a652626b2afe09ef"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘These "
"sentient beings do not comprehend peace and tranquility. They should "
"comprehend them.’"

msgid "b2a6d0f3fa144568931b1a0082e24085"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, because mind is naturally luminous, awakening is "
"naturally luminous."

msgid "5bc46094fe294c039b582cbef7201c7b"
msgstr "Why is it said to be naturally luminous?"

msgid "ce4e858a866a44ee8c595a06981431d3"
msgstr "Its nature is devoid of pollution."

msgid "f99303d4a1a04959bf34f607973ae6f8"
msgstr "It is equal to space."

msgid "3eb79ce0708344fab322f8be67e47c14"
msgstr "It is of the nature of space."

msgid "c440db5b54e84d498b656c51038254d0"
msgstr "It is established as being the same as space."

msgid "2780fc4172714ac7b5638db0356506bf"
msgstr "Because it is the same as space, it is sameness."

msgid "a69fa243b33041c998a5f730a75e6b12"
msgstr "Its nature is luminosity itself."

msgid "11bbfbf58fbb4d31bab1175020504ef2"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Since these "
"immature ordinary beings do not comprehend this natural luminosity, they "
"remain polluted by adventitious afflictive emotions."

msgid "b79a21855e38453abbda717a10ad4203"
msgstr "They should comprehend this luminous nature.’"

msgid "6122699f8b0c4a8a8390a8e7ebd5714a"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, awakening is without acceptance or rejection."

msgid "ea9b2cbcd435479db93748c7f235e61d"
msgstr "In this regard, what is the absence of acceptance?"

msgid "daadc05713894f58a0f9e2b75029f907"
msgstr "What is the absence of rejection?"

msgid "3abd71b907aa4fc0be9f838b9b22c383"
msgstr "Absence of acceptance means not clinging to any phenomenon."

msgid "b83cee573f1946eaa8f6b56144ad23d0"
msgstr "Absence of rejection means not rejecting any phenomenon."

msgid "ef16877d8064464aa681fd2090938734"
msgstr ""
"When tathāgatas enter the river of no acceptance and no rejection, they "
"truly see that suchness is without an ‘other side’ yet not without an ‘other"
" side,’ and thus they transcend these."

msgid "5af492dbb2ad4725825e3e274221f1f4"
msgstr ""
"In that way, tathāgatas attain complete and perfect awakening for which all "
"phenomena are beyond an ‘other side’ and the absence of an ‘other side.’"

msgid "855da58f1754418699b315fb18c38acd"
msgstr "Therefore they are called tathāgatas."

msgid "07817b592561470b95688922d7ba9f51"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘These "
"immature ordinary beings do not comprehend the absence of acceptance and the"
" absence of rejection. They should comprehend them.’"

msgid "d1a36ec8074c456dbec65ce28fe8fd65"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, awakening is without signs and without objective "
"reference."

msgid "3df144c8171648b682f4b054c753ad48"
msgstr "In this regard, what is meant by ‘without signs’?"

msgid "7cf86025a6ff40a98f563435d7a2a8ee"
msgstr "What is meant by ‘without objective reference’?"

msgid "6ca8ee16571048eeb5b24679f160e577"
msgstr ""
"A visual consciousness without an objective referent is without signs."

msgid "efd6e26c151c417c9b0226717d7f4e1e"
msgstr "Form that is unseen is without objective reference."

msgid "47110f214e7f422db4dd999986f58216"
msgstr ""
"An auditory consciousness without an objective reference is without signs."

msgid "e7fc2a0b5e624f689b826e992293e28c"
msgstr "Sound that is unheard is without objective reference."

msgid "51c5364474004b1db47c012d0599d0da"
msgstr ""
"An olfactory consciousness without an objective reference is without signs."

msgid "4515e516243f4a2b816ede70c6b4384a"
msgstr "Odor that is not perceived is without objective reference."

msgid "cb6f08da8c06439cbb8e1840a86f47cd"
msgstr ""
"A consciousness of taste without an objective reference is without signs."

msgid "cdd3148303c94f3d8447caf7f3a25a81"
msgstr "Flavor that is not perceived is without objective reference."

msgid "f13bc0afa3b34e9aa11fe5286cd8cc33"
msgstr ""
"A tactile consciousness without an objective reference is without signs."

msgid "18237def385e45dabb7e2f0a09907987"
msgstr "Touch that is not perceived is without objective reference."

msgid "b06fcaa00e8c4263ac95d7c86a3ab540"
msgstr ""
"A mental consciousness without an objective reference is without signs."

msgid "548689f7915e4848acc59137ed1ba237"
msgstr ""
"Mental factors that are not perceived are without objective reference."

msgid "902375d3b85342648da73b16350efab8"
msgstr ""
"Thus, the lack of attributes and objective references is the domain of the "
"noble ones."

msgid "ec97920556a14a7bb5e215782ad74957"
msgstr "What is the domain of the noble ones?"

msgid "eb166ae2f9ac40b59c443bf5a42cf4ad"
msgstr ""
"That which is not the domain of the three realms is the domain of the noble "
"ones."

msgid "5699a58dfb8a4780b08a92c4fe77ea2b"
msgstr "Thus, that which is not a domain is the domain of the noble ones."

msgid "4f56bb2f32134786bcfc9f3c9503dca4"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Immature "
"ordinary beings do not comprehend the domain of the noble ones. They should "
"comprehend it.’"

msgid "4424e2bccdb84267aa8b05b05f72d762"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, awakening is not the past, is not the future, and is "
"not the present."

msgid "e6d3dd1a2b1c4ef4934c0327e066f6ab"
msgstr ""
"It is the same throughout the three times, the termination of the triple "
"sphere."

msgid "962d9db62c144c7384312f4732b8dd11"
msgstr "In this regard, what is the termination of the triple sphere?"

msgid "bf273f86be3a4437b6fa9b88ce0608e8"
msgstr ""
"Mind does not engage with the past, consciousness does not pursue the "
"future, and mental activity does not engage with the present."

msgid "2ed43c63c1ee475c85d5a64422682846"
msgstr ""
"Since mind, mental activity, and consciousness do not abide, one does not "
"mull over the past, one does not give thought to the future, and one does "
"not proliferate the present."

msgid "0185a90f426945258e85bcc77a77fe9d"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Immature "
"ordinary beings do not comprehend the equality of the three times and the "
"purification of the triple sphere. They should comprehend them.’"

msgid "52f10f05852e4d77a508fb944b8dab3f"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, awakening is incorporeal and unconditioned."

msgid "d2d09746627045509425c58fd2c1b381"
msgstr ""
"In this regard, that which is incorporeal is not perceptible to visual "
"consciousness."

msgid "a0155fdbd846404bb699c8e444ffe10a"
msgstr ""
"It is not perceptible to auditory, olfactory, taste, tactile, or mental "
"consciousness."

msgid "fff30d7035c44ed091ecf7a8502fe886"
msgstr ""
"The unconditioned is that which is without origination, cessation, and "
"endurance."

msgid "c7bf7ef7078a404f9ffd25047fa25f5e"
msgstr "That is the unconditioned, free of these three characteristics."

msgid "09cceb67510d47b2aebe874d9fb3c2bb"
msgstr ""
"That which is conditioned should also be comprehended to be just like the "
"unconditioned."

msgid "2d41fdf27bc04802b586b0a1ad1ee216"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "d4a8981f347f4fbd84e67250fe1bad53"
msgstr "The nature of all phenomena is nonexistence."

msgid "9278589ae2254208a5d83171d3d280a6"
msgstr "That which is nonexistent is nondual."

msgid "831fc16f197749819676a80987b21ffa"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Immature "
"ordinary beings do not comprehend the incorporeal and unconditioned. They "
"should comprehend it.’"

msgid "755fd019524d4af090b4e2d9d737b510"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, what is called awakening is inseparable and abiding."

msgid "171f577ba74949f889edc79ec2c47cbc"
msgstr "In this regard, what abides?"

msgid "8fab2ebd6afc44fdbc2755411d98a079"
msgstr "What is inseparable?"

msgid "702e3c2b8f6c4033b672bc490d20a7df"
msgstr "Suchness abides."

msgid "2497509f49d94fd5bfa811d6c64c2a3e"
msgstr "Nonabiding is inseparable."

msgid "1bd5a0783d8644d9ade1e6a9e9c5bf9d"
msgstr "The realm of phenomena abides."

msgid "dd673cd61bbf4c54978a1d0d1e847bd1"
msgstr "Nondifferentiation is inseparable."

msgid "989310e3e13e41758e9e8c9f6f8d595f"
msgstr "The limit of reality abides."

msgid "13c124080fbc44709a17d3889baf6284"
msgstr "Immovability is inseparable."

msgid "40095a57150945cb99bdc18c089aac24"
msgstr "Emptiness abides."

msgid "03cce9aef85b4181b6914e65d8fe3363"
msgstr "Lack of objective reference is inseparable."

msgid "7a3030b21e754eb2959a83ef1a91dcfe"
msgstr "Signlessness abides."

msgid "3a8a395b7e4842968a3d9310f6fc494e"
msgstr "Nonconceptuality is inseparable."

msgid "71447e89771f49258cad624154f7a53a"
msgstr "Wishlessness abides."

msgid "05e15575608a4f2c8a9e87d1d0513d2d"
msgstr "Lack of making wishes is inseparable."

msgid "b8bf94ed127c43ce9640127f7f5812d9"
msgstr "The nonexistence of sentient beings abides."

msgid "f30c03dc12984c4d886b2c15128dc677"
msgstr "The essencelessness of sentient beings is inseparable."

msgid "b9cd05f76458437c809c0afdd111221b"
msgstr "Space abides."

msgid "942c5e6d63f34a628e43046edab3d80b"
msgstr "Lack of objective reference is inseparable."

msgid "c91fbec50936456eb35b7dc89420a4b5"
msgstr "Nonorigination abides."

msgid "afe228ec30524569b7f17743e5200bc5"
msgstr "Noncessation is inseparable."

msgid "56342824eaa5483c87e7d82ba81e1573"
msgstr "The unconditioned abides."

msgid "3a5b452fb3f5463492c14b0f484b358c"
msgstr "The absence of movement is inseparable."

msgid "27c9c254cd9c4d04ab36768c9416d027"
msgstr "Awakening abides."

msgid "01807063281b4bc79d3f7103963eb83c"
msgstr "Tranquility is inseparable."

msgid "1c32b80bc04c4f198be6f27324de66a3"
msgstr "Nirvāṇa abides."

msgid "d5036c7ef8514071902f63ab9b24c2e8"
msgstr "The absence of coming into being is inseparable."

msgid "bcc358f451cc4c5d8bc01621b3dce9ba"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Sentient "
"beings do not comprehend this inseparability and abiding. They should "
"comprehend it.’"

msgid "80844195f4f047b4a1a7e7476c08eddc"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, awakening is completely and perfectly awakened neither"
" by the body nor by the mind."

msgid "8b177419f43d4ab38047c700978f497b"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "f1441efd2f79415198808e28f56bbc7a"
msgstr "The body is inanimate, and the mind is like an illusion."

msgid "a4a02606a33f4521b15473ab45e9e975"
msgstr ""
"Those who comprehend the body and the mind to be like that may still talk "
"about awakening, using conventional language, but awakening cannot be "
"described as physical or mental, as a phenomenon or not, as genuine or not, "
"or as true or false."

msgid "77ca1706020240679f311206750f697f"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "b5b4b6ae47c44b25bf07fb98d0631141"
msgstr "Awakening cannot be described by means of any phenomenon."

msgid "5a0be4a2ebd34771805bfdd3f38fa8ae"
msgstr ""
"Awakening does not have a shape that can be described in conventional terms."

msgid "5aa7bc2f510542e6b975d2397a031af3"
msgstr ""
"Just as space has no shape and is indescribable, awakening likewise has no "
"shape and is indescribable."

msgid "12bda26cf3c642bfb39f6fd02f9865e2"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, no phenomena are describable if one has understood them "
"just as they are."

msgid "4519328a6a804ff9bff0a677bc78b71b"
msgstr "There are no words for phenomena."

msgid "fa4da32cfb114409889f81a68389337c"
msgstr "There are no phenomena that correspond to words."

msgid "ac59476f1cfc4b6dbb82dd5fe9520404"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Sentient "
"beings do not comprehend this aspect of the manner of phenomena. They should"
" comprehend it.’"

msgid "7f923498049b4e12bfe6a83af123f0d1"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, awakening is not apprehended and without a foundation."

msgid "004fbd73baf145a7bf19a20c7d6d8ebe"
msgstr ""
"In this regard, what is not apprehended? What is without a foundation?"

msgid "d90faf0ed3e34852bb82017e8594bb93"
msgstr "Understanding the eye is not apprehended."

msgid "631dd122128a47b1a2adc2974f6351b3"
msgstr "Form without objective reference is without a foundation."

msgid "5c1bcf66544e41168f7de5c688fd9761"
msgstr "Understanding the ear is not apprehended."

msgid "d895dae3527e47e9aecf25f1bea7b29b"
msgstr "Sound without objective reference is without a foundation."

msgid "1ca857552b194236993502cc34c9336e"
msgstr "Understanding the nose is not apprehended."

msgid "b642bb72098a45d3a7866aa5ef38d67d"
msgstr "Smell without objective reference is without a foundation."

msgid "a58d199f15744e5ebcbcb8a32a0abaaf"
msgstr "Understanding the tongue is not apprehended."

msgid "8890477463374802b639a5d31925d4a0"
msgstr "Flavor without objective reference is without a foundation."

msgid "e2cc9627fcce44839e5091e8580c32a5"
msgstr "Understanding the body is not apprehended."

msgid "5058c8d213f1443484b6bc5c675ce86c"
msgstr "Touch without objective reference is without a foundation."

msgid "8cacf62e264e420fb7444456ae0e9aca"
msgstr "Understanding mental cognition is not apprehended."

msgid "85ba0932ebea48df9028acd0c8d10afe"
msgstr "Mental factors without objective references are without a foundation."

msgid "3a391eb8831e483fb05ac8afa33324d5"
msgstr ""
"In that way, tathāgatas completely and perfectly awaken to awakening that is"
" not apprehended and without a foundation."

msgid "79d2237a12a14051a5f4c0527f6b9390"
msgstr ""
"“Having attained complete and perfect awakening, the eye is not apprehended,"
" form is not a foundation, and consciousness has nowhere to stand."

msgid "e4f6bc54b55943c8b5ed88df394a7d2b"
msgstr ""
"The ear is not apprehended, sounds are not a foundation, and consciousness "
"has nowhere to stand."

msgid "138ed7f67f16425ab0a94965afe46959"
msgstr ""
"The nose is not apprehended, smells are not a foundation, and consciousness "
"has nowhere to stand."

msgid "7bfe0802ae2540e8a0bb5073880c6d49"
msgstr ""
"The tongue is not apprehended, tastes are not a foundation, and "
"consciousness has nowhere to stand."

msgid "4e4490986ea74a7eb86606a051224488"
msgstr ""
"The body is not apprehended, tactile sensations are not a foundation, and "
"consciousness has nowhere to stand."

msgid "0b5bfeefc51a4251903027c2b7069c51"
msgstr ""
"The mind is not apprehended, phenomena are not a foundation, and "
"consciousness has nowhere to stand."

msgid "35987fe9789e4432b0008b4663ffe30e"
msgstr ""
"“Since consciousness has nowhere to stand, one deeply understands the "
"stations of the minds of all sentient beings."

msgid "bf850d9d94854dd49e7a31710d4e8785"
msgstr "What are the stations of the minds of sentient beings?"

msgid "5024c7c08a1f444580eabbe446e32d6a"
msgstr "There are four stations of the minds of sentient beings."

msgid "1264753766c143cf8e643029972c40eb"
msgstr "What are these four?"

msgid "99ffc2ed31b8469bbb12fac889667110"
msgstr "Form is a station of the minds of sentient beings."

msgid "e897ac5c30e3481186df6a5b4de17c42"
msgstr ""
"Likewise feeling, perception, and formations are stations of the minds of "
"sentient beings."

msgid "4d22492b41244af98b06e991a2f2f66c"
msgstr ""
"But tathāgatas know that even these stations of their minds are nowhere to "
"stand."

msgid "3e26bfc664a94a04890d91690df6a4e7"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Sentient "
"beings do not comprehend this limit of groundlessness. They should "
"comprehend it.’"

msgid "9964e601c8a24d7f8a8848ff1f39dd72"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, awakening is a designation for emptiness."

msgid "611bb63522b749d2bbf056e04316c823"
msgstr ""
"The emptiness of empty awakening is the emptiness of all empty phenomena."

msgid "a8931433b4944f858706a0eb12c113d4"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas completely and perfectly awaken by realizing that all those "
"phenomena are in truth emptiness."

msgid "424e4a970e3c49b1a0620c63037e7172"
msgstr ""
"Theirs is not an awakening brought about by making phenomena empty by means "
"of emptiness."

msgid "23d33c1058a4449cb697c922f6f88211"
msgstr ""
"What is called emptiness and what is called awakening are understood to be "
"one and the same."

msgid "cf035e732544416195a15de1d5865db0"
msgstr ""
"There is no division of emptiness and awakening into two categories at all."

msgid "74f978f166ca40d5abe44d3516042d15"
msgstr "“Why is that?"

msgid "0c9f32229f4c4dc580c171dab6693c3c"
msgstr "Phenomena are nondual;"

msgid "60ea94edc24f48249b5fdfdfb48e88c9"
msgstr "they cannot be separated into two."

msgid "0aae6eedf99948d0adc2f31778a86dcf"
msgstr "They lack attributes, names, and signs."

msgid "be33ca96eb5c45cb839a0575f5184e3d"
msgstr "They are without movement, immovable, and without origination."

msgid "797946b503a4444993bdd207ab461d4f"
msgstr ""
"Empty is a designation for what is devoid of clinging and apprehending."

msgid "28934627b4084efc873964d30933458c"
msgstr ""
"In this regard, ultimately, the phenomena that are referred to as empty are "
"without any objective reference whatsoever, but they are still called empty."

msgid "b5ce4f024d70481f97e8cd6d3efca6ec"
msgstr ""
"Just as we call space space even though space is actually indescribable, we "
"call what is empty empty even though emptiness is actually indescribable."

msgid "2709acb62bea47ad95970fae947c302a"
msgstr ""
"It is like this. This convention of using names to label what is nameless is"
" applied to all phenomena."

msgid "c316e990934f4937891a3b63e9878862"
msgstr "A name also does not inhere in the object or in a part of it."

msgid "97c102a7ea644348a7c5768eda2dc63c"
msgstr ""
"Just as names do not inhere in objects or in their parts, in the same way, "
"whatever phenomenon described by a given name also does not inhere in the "
"object or in part of it."

msgid "17652403204647c2b93bce3899992778"
msgstr "“In that way tathāgatas understand all these phenomena."

msgid "4b643ca03eb44435a46f5abaad05c67f"
msgstr ""
"They understand them to be primordially unborn, unceasing, without "
"attributes, devoid of mind, mental activity, and consciousness, and without "
"letters or sounds."

msgid "7321e354bfa74945a528af57d1cc5807"
msgstr "Insofar as they understand them, they are liberated."

msgid "0b0d45dc3259423e9f5be7b0813ea5b6"
msgstr "There is no bondage."

msgid "5ce3e4bb08c0441caab001b86a99bfaa"
msgstr "There is also no liberation."

msgid "8197f1a68afe41e4a8d6caaa9d8d0111"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Immature "
"ordinary beings do not comprehend this sameness. They should comprehend it.’"

msgid "22138c2d250d4f818c7c0d6b46ac4f81"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, awakening is similar to space."

msgid "4567700d16a24c02b9e3153bfeda0feb"
msgstr "Space itself is never the same, but it is also never not the same."

msgid "3ebaebe633ec423ca21045cd2ceaf0de"
msgstr "Awakening too is never the same, but it is also never not the same."

msgid "514ab9a8a88a4751a0d181aa66a0d2d4"
msgstr ""
"Since phenomena do not truly exist, one cannot say whether they are the same"
" or not the same."

msgid "443a5df2c6d24f64bf96fb60b734ffcc"
msgstr ""
"This is what tathāgatas realize when they fully awaken to the fact that all "
"phenomena are not the same and are not not the same."

msgid "eaa49bfa9ef34b29a33fb48046084a8b"
msgstr ""
"They fully awaken without making even the slightest phenomenon the same or "
"not the same."

msgid "d965b56af48a401c8f603a2d594342d8"
msgstr ""
"“They understand with correct wisdom exactly what these phenomena are like."

msgid "3d224e66a4be4568a3897a3cef6f5ea5"
msgstr "What is correct wisdom?"

msgid "b0c57122c9834ea8be76aa2a4f57aee5"
msgstr ""
"It is the understanding that all phenomena are without root, that they are "
"unborn and unceasing."

msgid "4d1e40ea372644858a8c25d9d09008d9"
msgstr "They arise out of the unarisen. Having arisen, they pass away."

msgid "779f1ff8ba6249e6b7754311816e8acc"
msgstr "They arise without a creator, and they pass away without a creator."

msgid "4e504c1f730444298da3392dd7a2eb18"
msgstr ""
"“In that way, though phenomena come to be through arising and perishing, "
"there is no coming to be whatsoever."

msgid "b9d735473e9d49e1a21cb24523b781d1"
msgstr ""
"It is said that ‘the tathāgatas teach the Dharma in order to cut off the "
"pathways of existence.’"

msgid "b16304fea9c549178fdfb34af18aa053"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Sentient "
"beings do not comprehend how to cut off the pathways of existence. They "
"should comprehend it.’"

msgid "522bb9b4b52e464f8e5a4b489399a4dd"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, awakening is a real ground."

msgid "b7ec7c9dc61f45f6b6536530dea8e097"
msgstr "What is a real ground?"

msgid "ce4b377a02e046d6a2bec80d0b35b21d"
msgstr "As is awakening, so is form, which does not transcend suchness."

msgid "1ee20b70815f4ff696d2e5a03bc190f3"
msgstr ""
"As is awakening, so are feeling, perception, formations, and consciousness, "
"which do not transcend suchness."

msgid "890f660a8ff54de991dc9a33a8d6add0"
msgstr ""
"As is awakening, so are the elements of earth, water, fire, and wind, which "
"do not transcend suchness."

msgid "6a74c3fa65f34ead86d32a91e4e49509"
msgstr ""
"As is awakening, so are the elements of eye, form, and visual consciousness,"
" which do not transcend suchness."

msgid "e4ce808aff0b406cb3b1cf1090a1cfb5"
msgstr ""
"As is awakening, so are the elements of ear, sound, and auditory "
"consciousness, which do not transcend suchness."

msgid "5802476b31c34ae9a85b1059167098c0"
msgstr ""
"As is awakening, so are the elements of nose, smell, and olfactory "
"consciousness, which do not transcend suchness."

msgid "9ad30622a7d3487dbd25e23d672a79a8"
msgstr ""
"As is awakening, so are the elements of tongue, taste, and gustatory "
"consciousness, which do not transcend suchness."

msgid "f70fe0fe209b406585b9763da2fd1b92"
msgstr ""
"As is awakening, so are the elements of body, tactile sensation, and tactile"
" consciousness, which do not transcend suchness."

msgid "0c522971cfee4e39b3e48baaa8d24c34"
msgstr ""
"As is awakening, so are the elements of mind, phenomena, and mental "
"consciousness, which do not transcend suchness."

msgid "de8dd28368ef493bbde6a1bce25cf44f"
msgstr "It is just these that are labeled as phenomena."

msgid "1eabd3b963a943759a73af2217434397"
msgstr ""
"In this regard, they are labeled as aggregates, elements, and sense fields."

msgid "a3fc54dc2d384aeeb748f1f3774612d0"
msgstr ""
"“It is to these as they really are that the tathāgatas are completely and "
"perfectly awakened, completely and perfectly awakened in an unmistaken "
"manner."

msgid "7a526f6b371945bca95440004da41ed5"
msgstr ""
"As these were before, so they are later, and so they are in the meantime."

msgid "2c6956e77e664b378be1e3b267a67e2f"
msgstr ""
"They do not arise in the beginning, they do not pass on in the end, and they"
" are devoid in the meantime."

msgid "f28df1d902374ffda8dda6a08900bc0d"
msgstr "This is a real ground."

msgid "7b5393109be049a8a9f265a58da6faeb"
msgstr "As one is, so are they all. As they all are, so is one."

msgid "54ed921bf2214caa87b9d31d91bca105"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas do not objectify the way things are in terms of one or many."

msgid "b87056ba5c9347b88d20fdb662f30061"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Immature "
"ordinary beings do not comprehend the real ground. They should comprehend "
"it.’"

msgid "9f3f517159244f90869f291cdde0361f"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, awakening consists in having penetrated the absence of"
" aspects through penetrating the aspects."

msgid "8b1fb2427a7b41e9ae59cda57fd4c0ba"
msgstr "In this regard, what are the aspects? What is the absence of aspects?"

msgid "b570ce467c7b47fd839185d554e3faa6"
msgstr "Aspects refers to taking up all virtuous factors."

msgid "7585a7294669473db381e4d97800d290"
msgstr "Absence of aspects refers to not objectifying any factor."

msgid "f5780321b75e45d096d4741f2cafa8a0"
msgstr "Aspects refers to the ground of the mind that is groundless."

msgid "450a29b2f18a47ef832b923300b6e408"
msgstr ""
"Absence of aspects refers to the gate of liberation, a meditative absorption"
" without signs."

msgid "a938764951a24b4bbff2c0464980a8f8"
msgstr ""
"Aspects refers to thinking about, evaluating, enumerating, and "
"discriminating phenomena."

msgid "aaa7373c9942474490a4fad14eba6533"
msgstr ""
"Absence of aspects refers to the complete transcendence of evaluation."

msgid "aa5a9119e7704a36b58c94d06034659a"
msgstr "What is the complete transcendence of evaluation?"

msgid "7ebfae4e4cd8403bbb5ad9f503b231b5"
msgstr "It is that in which there is no activity of consciousness."

msgid "c2ee42a5318340dd94f862aa2b83a889"
msgstr "Aspects refers to discriminating conditioned things."

msgid "5729bc22e5564445a999071f26015f86"
msgstr "Absence of aspects refers to realizing the unconditioned."

msgid "09953cf1da67416181c9ec20de4fcce6"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Immature "
"ordinary beings do not comprehend penetrating the aspects and the absence of"
" aspects. They should comprehend it.’"

msgid "ea1da94e29854688bbf3dae9c8b6e15f"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, awakening is the absence of contamination and the "
"absence of appropriation."

msgid "a8960e2983b447688196c39d10d5fe3e"
msgstr ""
"In this regard, what is the absence of contamination? What is the absence of"
" appropriation?"

msgid "415236158da14eadb691ca862f2c8211"
msgstr "Absence of contamination means freedom from the four contaminants:"

msgid "91cb7102af044abe8e84cc8cd8cf5d57"
msgstr ""
"freedom from the contaminant of desire, freedom from the contaminant of "
"becoming, freedom from the contaminant of ignorance, and freedom from the "
"contaminant of views."

msgid "b2e51f26fad748b8bfb8b849ad81df91"
msgstr ""
"Absence of appropriation refers to freedom from the four appropriations:"

msgid "a84000988d6b47959ad23b8182e966ef"
msgstr ""
"freedom from the appropriation of desire, freedom from the appropriation of "
"views, freedom from the appropriation of asserting a self, and freedom from "
"the appropriation of belief in the supremacy of one’s morality and "
"asceticism."

msgid "865bd27effb34897abcc27d36292c74c"
msgstr ""
"These four appropriations are darkened by ignorance and approached through "
"craving."

msgid "b29cbea3fb2540eea7b96c01cdf6de8a"
msgstr "Thinking ‘I am,’ they are appropriated through clinging."

msgid "02fdeb766b544694808da2710c749d02"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas understand the I to be the root of appropriation, and they "
"realize that purification of the self is the purification of sentient "
"beings."

msgid "3c2ab28c112d4a8793c79e42850c3db4"
msgstr ""
"The purification of the self and the purification of all sentient beings are"
" an inseparable nonduality."

msgid "2463a947168c4cadbdcead4524cb7dd2"
msgstr "Nonduality refers to nonarising."

msgid "20bd6a31d88d4888bf43789cfa9579d8"
msgstr ""
"Due to nonarising and noncessation, mind, mental activity, and consciousness"
" do not operate."

msgid "da7f84c9418f42d69ae7879e1d1c1968"
msgstr ""
"Where mind, mental activity, and consciousness do not operate, there is "
"absolutely none of the false imagining of incorrect mental activity."

msgid "9ffbe84b3f0c4f1e9df49a23efd1efee"
msgstr "“Someone with correct mental activity does not activate ignorance."

msgid "37e0ce342caa41b9af540fc1e502b9d4"
msgstr ""
"When ignorance does not arise, the twelve links of becoming do not arise."

msgid "220c9c95a88e457097556b2817b5e690"
msgstr "When the twelve links of becoming do not arise, there is no birth."

msgid "7ef9f1a1d6394cd39482ced832d3658f"
msgstr "That which is unborn is certain."

msgid "59b95608258b4fa8a2f27694258ae4c9"
msgstr "That which is certain is the definitive meaning."

msgid "497dcd8f1b9c4d2bbf51bb0b82c5ea14"
msgstr "That which is the definitive meaning is the ultimate."

msgid "cbade4c00496461babdf389ef8a34c3e"
msgstr "That which is ultimate means the reality devoid of a person."

msgid "324db8540d7646d4ae01a742e83bc6b7"
msgstr "The reality devoid of a person is inexpressible."

msgid "668c2113f1704316bbe55e91a5058557"
msgstr "The inexpressible is dependent arising."

msgid "f317a38877be401fa57c818de5b90f99"
msgstr "Dependent arising is the Dharma."

msgid "c2342ceda5c9438a88ecfe46eea19ad8"
msgstr "The Dharma is suchness."

msgid "60dba89c19bb4436a0a6df1324b8140e"
msgstr "Suchness is the tathāgata."

msgid "7c100396bf30469db982059eade11861"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, it is said that ‘whoever sees dependent arising sees the Dharma, "
"and whoever sees the Dharma sees the tathāgata.’"

msgid "ae759be5e71c451490ecd98f3ac9ae03"
msgstr ""
"When one searches, informed by suchness, one sees nothing whatsoever, and "
"that is how one sees."

msgid "5a9c35b3d0e941ddbdd340f0e9099c45"
msgstr "What is that ‘nothing whatsoever?’"

msgid "68f9626b5e624dd292698e5dab991929"
msgstr "The answer is ‘conceptual signs and objective references.’"

msgid "aae0c403b76f4c1fa35f2042eb94b3bc"
msgstr ""
"At the time when one sees without thought or objective reference, one sees "
"truly."

msgid "b172631507de47c6824a5f5be0ff1459"
msgstr ""
"In this manner, tathāgatas completely and perfectly awaken, by means of "
"sameness, to the sameness of all phenomena."

msgid "37364cd3f0bb4f87b2e8b1e2b406c2c4"
msgstr ""
"Great tathāgata compassion extends to beings with the thought, ‘Sentient "
"beings do not comprehend what is without contamination and appropriation. "
"They should comprehend it.’"

msgid "07f124ed3901480b934e598e190da4ff"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, awakening is pure, stainless, and without afflictive "
"emotions."

msgid "1a89d0db8d254b82857178cc072db692"
msgstr "In this regard, what is pure?"

msgid "3eff1bfbc7814ff5ad6d28b5198edc24"
msgstr "What is stainless?"

msgid "f426ad8b64044ef5816a41f570745cbe"
msgstr "What is without afflictive emotions?"

msgid "7efb433d4eab4b32b7d8fe78836d9ad9"
msgstr "Emptiness is pure."

msgid "ff3f09b1ae8e46f3a05b065fbae974db"
msgstr "Signlessness is stainless."

msgid "aefc22505ffe44ddb906608810b226ae"
msgstr "Wishlessness is without afflictive emotions."

msgid "0a631f84c817450fb205d07106fbb490"
msgstr "The unborn is pure."

msgid "8486b72bdd2e4df6be50304d659df863"
msgstr "Absence of conditioning is stainless."

msgid "93f052e6458b450daf8fece092f07484"
msgstr "Nonarising is without afflictive emotions."

msgid "be1506eb748e4713ab2383da4de87d20"
msgstr "The nature is pure."

msgid "6a7d27eefe294d91857dfe2b6b2f1922"
msgstr "Total purity is stainless."

msgid "7cf627fc24874700957c0c736f0702a2"
msgstr "Luminosity is without afflictive emotions."

msgid "6e53f98663444844aa9cc77d7de1c0e0"
msgstr "The absence of proliferation is pure."

msgid "a5a8246a7d3e465f84761110e589bba5"
msgstr "Non-proliferation is stainless."

msgid "71f4c534dd7b4f708215e0fdb97c581e"
msgstr "The pacification of proliferations is without afflictive emotions."

msgid "40b19a1249fb4a95923dd8bfbed84adb"
msgstr "Suchness is pure."

msgid "25f41d62a97e4def9702ca54dd73c183"
msgstr "The realm of phenomena is stainless."

msgid "a7f2736c96d1403fa87b3068b6a67be8"
msgstr "The limit of reality is without afflictive emotions."

msgid "988d5bc353a84ea8812bf93a351fae36"
msgstr "Space is pure."

msgid "658debda44d34701ad9deb96030a0c17"
msgstr "Space is stainless."

msgid "4046ea11123b474a80e9aaf690c193ca"
msgstr "Space is without afflictive emotions."

msgid "f89b0d40f6af4cc7a605d8beb8779979"
msgstr "Understanding inwardly is pure."

msgid "d09b0f3921c84c83800e438d1a8dd908"
msgstr "Not pursuing outwardly is stainless."

msgid "8e94085b417c4373a324cc14f18f54b1"
msgstr ""
"Not objectifying inwardly or outwardly is without afflictive emotions."

msgid "9ee1db478e09446994359e03d33f9a04"
msgstr "Understanding the aggregates is pure."

msgid "7bd285dddcbc4657a44ce5e525ca90c9"
msgstr "The essence of the elements is stainless."

msgid "34e2096b75eb436e8219a15bbe0ac729"
msgstr "Rejecting the sense fields is without afflictive emotions."

msgid "3f72018743934ab4b13eb124d2103b96"
msgstr "Understanding that the past is gone is pure."

msgid "d47d7800184448eab66685abbaf1588e"
msgstr "Understanding that the future has not yet arisen is stainless."

msgid "757c080d6dd542ab8d2d7dcec4ae2b12"
msgstr ""
"Understanding that the present is present as the realm of phenomena is "
"without afflictive emotions."

msgid "045c0a30a9324202b5cd458679d7cf1d"
msgstr ""
"“Therefore purity, stainlessness, and the absence of afflictive emotions are"
" actually united in the single state that is the state of peace."

msgid "71281f229dbe4b56ace992e28b54a270"
msgstr "Peace is peacefulness."

msgid "618df47edae4492cbaa73792b5cb231b"
msgstr "Peacefulness is what is called pacification."

msgid "a03cb8a18e7d4b75ab2e7bad0640e5e0"
msgstr ""
"Pacification is what is called the absence of signs by means of the act of "
"pacifying."

msgid "7b0f2924ba5740448da1552fdfc0265a"
msgstr "The absence of signs is what is called pacification."

msgid "0814cfda37614cb6b58e12e9a32272d5"
msgstr "Pacification is what is called intelligence."

msgid "de5787ada55e4b1e9e631bdc4f9c4aa9"
msgstr "“Therefore, son of noble family, as is space, so too is awakening."

msgid "da91c97838804e8cae980f3115ae293c"
msgstr "As is awakening, so too are all phenomena."

msgid "56b4ae8d58ec448ea8439eb1516a0559"
msgstr "As are all phenomena, so too are sentient beings."

msgid "fdd0ac8e0f6744109c69fb50103dd8c1"
msgstr "As are sentient beings, so too are the buddhafields."

msgid "677101dbee1e4bda862073036f1fa7c2"
msgstr "As are the buddhafields, so too is nirvāṇa."

msgid "9cf8922bfd644ae6b401b1e5b0e840e5"
msgstr ""
"Thus, all phenomena are said to be equal to nirvāṇa. Because they are "
"ultimate and final there are no remedies to apply."

msgid "8e68989b790a4b4cbddeb7888451de1f"
msgstr ""
"Because there are no remedies to apply, all phenomena are primordially pure,"
" primordially stainless, and primordially without afflictive emotions."

msgid "1f6bf5813f8c463d91ba9179d7ce1294"
msgstr ""
"Tathāgatas accordingly are completely and perfectly awakened to the reality "
"of all phenomena."

msgid "bee3dc8a52154abeb0ea3c717c00ef41"
msgstr ""
"After surveying the mass of sentient beings who are impure, who are not "
"stainless, and who possess afflictive emotions, they extend their great "
"compassion known as magical play to all sentient beings."

msgid "dfedf93c4ef24cc9b2ea278d26117a3d"
msgstr ""
"“Using his skillful means, the Tathāgata informed the gods of the Brahmā "
"realm that he would not turn the wheel of the Dharma without being requested"
" to do so."

msgid "0c13b200b3594a3d85937a43720fbc3e"
msgstr ""
"Then Top-Knotted Brahmā, surrounded and escorted by eight hundred thousand "
"gods of the Brahmā realm, instantly disappeared from the realm of Brahmā."

msgid "c03ee76a1fa24e658acc039df354dbb6"
msgstr ""
"He arrived in the presence of the Tathāgata and paid homage at the "
"Tathāgata’s feet."

msgid "6d909f7aae2246ab8779bf413ff6d571"
msgstr ""
"To ensure that the wheel of Dharma be set in motion, he supplicated the "
"Tathāgata:"

msgid "5747de8cde6842bab9b1a6ba6d5b464b"
msgstr ""
"‘May the Blessed One teach the Dharma! May the Sugata teach the Dharma!’"

msgid "7fc5b58f16024d9bb44ab3267ebc2535"
msgstr "He also supplicated the Tathāgata with the following words:"

msgid "d5e9041f7007429f9ce5bcf380c35e69"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Your Dharma, realized by buddha wisdom, Is peaceful and serene, pure and "
"immaculate, Unsullied and radiant, Inexpressible, soundless, and without "
"words."

msgid "6ce80defb8514521ba575c09777346d3"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘You endured great hardships of asceticism and austerity For millions of "
"eons To bring about the awakening of beings, confused and obscured By self-"
"satisfaction, from the deep sleep of delusion."

msgid "ec682c5b3eb44201b885b88fdda24f93"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Those entrusted with the lineage of the previous victors Realized this "
"supreme Dharma. On account of the many virtuous beings present herein,"

msgid "a063b8faabf04b189708057dd2368ac4"
msgstr "May the Tathāgata turn the wheel of the Dharma."

msgid "b693ff18e6cc4b32ae3dd78b2be3968e"
msgstr "“ ‘You have subjugated the hosts of Māra"

msgid "d8078d018d4849f7908ce117037bf12a"
msgstr "And opened the gate to the deathless."

msgid "3796b361f90b4327b8d9565a6703221e"
msgstr ""
"Great Leader, guide beings who have gone astray To the path of the noble "
"ones!"

msgid "ead38c9b1ce14529813b6acc723ddc8c"
msgstr "“ ‘Your unsurpassed buddha compassion"

msgid "3cbf7ffb02be43a184177722e9699868"
msgstr ""
"Benefits beings inconceivably. Teacher, I beg you, Please turn the wheel of "
"the supreme Dharma!"

msgid "c1d0476aaf2441ebbe10fe3b4d2c5c3a"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Blessed One, may you also turn the wheel of Dharma Just as the Victor "
"Krakucchanda, The Victor Kanakamuni, And the Tathāgata Kāśyapa have done."

msgid "c2ab8732fa1d4649a2c43b9f826be900"
msgstr "“ ‘Just as rainfall brings satisfaction"

msgid "93079425da4e4494871fd02de4fdb523"
msgstr "And causes medicinal plants to grow,"

msgid "f9fdde8337ca4d1c975d10ea52dbabed"
msgstr "So the clouds of your compassion encircle the world,"

msgid "756727a1b52f4c0b8e08c9c294463a73"
msgstr "And you, Tathāgata, let the rain of Dharma fall!"

msgid "c2ee0ba714b54bbdb7ecf3994cb46aa8"
msgstr "“ ‘As soon as a supreme guide is born,"

msgid "6f7f9a1ed5164550b4278208fa972aa0"
msgstr "He issues a sound in order to liberate beings."

msgid "d8518d0d2d424341b03561f23a1c819b"
msgstr ""
"Right now, please relieve the thirst of the yearning gods and humans With "
"the water of great Dharma.’"

msgid "4761fe4b695b4da282de8d239de661dc"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, the Tathāgata, aware of Top-Knotted Brahmā’s "
"supplication, proceeded with unrelinquishing great compassion to turn the "
"unsurpassed Dharma wheel in Deer Park in Rṣipatana near the town of "
"Vārāṇasī. In this world such a Dharma wheel had never been turned in "
"conformity with the Dharma before by any wandering ascetic, brahmin, god, "
"demon, or Brahmā himself. It was then that the word impermanence was "
"understood throughout the entire billionfold universe."

msgid "ab4b5016de6f4d7f982ec1066416772f"
msgstr "Kauṇḍinya was the first to fully know the Dharma."

msgid "4e1292bf19b949cd94beace3f47d379a"
msgstr "Then the Buddha, inspired, uttered the following:"

msgid "47defcb60269458f8294242f9530007a"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘That which is ineffable and profound, Beyond words and of definitive "
"meaning— Kauṇḍinya understood it,"

msgid "858c7911d7ba41e8a9a8963150aea883"
msgstr "So my effort has not been in vain!’"

msgid "50270b32219647c1be667b905a667090"
msgstr ""
"“By turning the wheel of the Dharma, the Tathāgata tamed innumerable and "
"unfathomably many sentient beings."

msgid "298dbac7a43b4851a5732f81895f1d87"
msgstr ""
"Through knowing this magical play of great tathāgata compassion, "
"immeasurable and innumerable sentient beings generated the thought of "
"awakening."

msgid "32d73d8c062a4809a01baee48b06df98"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, these sixteen kinds of great compassion of the blessed"
" buddhas are constantly spontaneously active and are never given up."

msgid "8bcdbaa0e4d24769bc9c9295367c001c"
msgstr ""
"Endowed with such great compassion, tathāgatas happily dwell among the "
"denizens in the great hell realms for the sake of each and every being, for "
"as many eons as there are grains of sand in the river Ganges."

msgid "4deaa6c19316472c80f1a524505d6ef8"
msgstr ""
"When they gaze at those to be tamed through the superior Dharma and Vinaya, "
"the tathāgatas are never discouraged, and their great compassion never "
"deteriorates."

msgid "68c7b6d8508b4dc6af37d52928710cce"
msgstr ""
"That is how the inconceivable great compassion of the blessed buddhas "
"extends to sentient beings."

msgid "d309f4f4af4848abb516dba473285006"
msgstr ""
"“The compassion of śrāvakas and pratyekabuddhas is compared to skin, the "
"compassion of bodhisattvas to flesh, and the great compassion of blessed "
"buddhas to bones and marrow."

msgid "74a9c7c2a74d464781176b73a6e70045"
msgstr "Śrāvaka compassion rejoices in buddha wisdom."

msgid "de7ee60854ca4d27b46cc9ccbac3c655"
msgstr "Bodhisattva compassion establishes bodhicitta."

msgid "8184d861c29649a397e44bab30de37dc"
msgstr "The great compassion of blessed buddhas predicts beings to awakening."

msgid "c102a2963f1c440c8df8a8601226fec7"
msgstr "The compassion of śrāvakas relies on love."

msgid "a1b65bdaade744d38d2957863d4be447"
msgstr "The compassion of bodhisattvas relies on bringing beings to maturity."

msgid "00d7cc5c52f84bddaa0523bf23a5f88c"
msgstr ""
"The great compassion of blessed buddhas relies on bringing them to full "
"maturity."

msgid "5dc159f89db541d49bc8783f6938a255"
msgstr "“The compassion of śrāvakas is discouraged by effort."

msgid "c6ec025e73714c12a9a8f966de09ad28"
msgstr "The compassion of bodhisattvas brings undertakings to completion."

msgid "8c2556267e684b1f9335a96565548914"
msgstr "The compassion of blessed buddhas brings success in all undertakings."

msgid "344f772d1e93474db074ce9fc3401849"
msgstr ""
"“Therefore, son of noble family, the great compassion of the blessed buddhas"
" is supreme because buddhas dwell for eons, hundreds of eons, thousands of "
"eons, or hundreds of thousands of eons in order to tame beings. For so long "
"as they do, they do not pass away into nirvāṇa."

msgid "4eaaa10d2e2d4bfd988d4eecd095f86e"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, you should understand this through this discourse."

msgid "172dff4dcae84611ae0b0fb679af88cc"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, in the past, innumerable beyond countless eons ago, in"
" an eon known as Most Fragrant, in a world realm known as Fragrant, there "
"appeared a tathāgata, an arhat, a completely and perfectly awakened buddha "
"known as Sandalwood Dwelling."

msgid "bee72386be6d4828b5b62a3447945ed7"
msgstr ""
"He was endowed with perfect knowledge and perfect conduct, a sugata, a world"
" knower, an unsurpassed charioteer of those to be tamed, a teacher of gods "
"and humans, a buddha, a blessed one."

msgid "105027f3fdb04831a5e25679ee781128"
msgstr ""
"The lifespan of the Blessed Tathāgata Sandalwood Dwelling reached sixteen "
"times eighty-four thousand years."

msgid "e03af6dd31ca43eea00918ee4b8a6c69"
msgstr ""
"His śrāvaka entourage consisted of sixteen times eighty-four thousand "
"śrāvakas."

msgid "02f5340b262e479da72a994a42629529"
msgstr ""
"“The sweet fragrance coming from one of the pores of his skin suffused the "
"billionfold universe with sweet-smelling fragrance."

msgid "ffe69501d8a34ce5a66bbe2a6c5c6b1d"
msgstr "No foul smell arose in that world."

msgid "86f8213de8264846922702a99c1c2611"
msgstr ""
"In that world, furthermore, the fences, trees, mountains, and material forms"
" that appeared were enveloped in the fragrance of that tathāgata."

msgid "a60e4d6fb77b440cb10f26bd80eb0f45"
msgstr "That is how it became known as Fragrant."

msgid "3405805bb61d4726b9e962f4c9a85f85"
msgstr ""
"“Through the fragrance of the Tathāgata, despicable physical, verbal, and "
"mental actions disappeared from the beings born in that realm."

msgid "2f73d5a64f5f44ffa4f043b4687e485b"
msgstr ""
"When they smelled that fragrance, those who went forth into the religious "
"life following the Dharma of that blessed one generated the four "
"concentrations."

msgid "4bc5570955e544febcce098eff3f28c7"
msgstr ""
"In that realm, ten thousand buddhas emerged simultaneously, all of them "
"named Sandalwood Dwelling."

msgid "fe2600f03bab49eb8aaff225ff6ee063"
msgstr "That is how the eon came to be called Most Fragrant."

msgid "e28819855ce448fbab76e2d3f47a3360"
msgstr ""
"“The Blessed Tathāgata Sandalwood Dwelling performed his buddha activity, "
"and at the time of passing into nirvāṇa he beheld the disposition of a being"
" who was trainable by a buddha and who was known as Trainable by Me."

msgid "e93610aabbad4dc5bdb49f0d21537be6"
msgstr ""
"The buddha saw with pure divine vision surpassing human sight that this one "
"being among the gods in the Sphere of neither Perception nor Nonperception "
"who had previously cultivated roots of virtue, who was devoted to the vast, "
"and who was tamable by a buddha would remain there for eighty-four thousand "
"eons."

msgid "184acd8c25cb4f58a086a40182b94cec"
msgstr ""
"Once he died and was reborn as a human, if he heard praise of the Great "
"Vehicle instead of enjoying sense desires, he would generate the thought of "
"unsurpassed perfect awakening and become someone who would not be turned "
"back from unsurpassed perfect awakening."

msgid "a62cbb96116949c38763da0236df937a"
msgstr ""
"“Then the Blessed Tathāgata Sandalwood Dwelling manifested great compassion "
"through his skill in means and said to the monks,"

msgid "0c7be947e9224faeb4ed0e57390877f6"
msgstr ""
"‘Monks! Since the time has come for me to pass into nirvāṇa, I will now pass"
" into nirvāṇa.’"

msgid "45f6f384b60e410ebae29af2b8edc2c2"
msgstr ""
"Thereupon the Blessed Tathāgata Sandalwood Dwelling entered the absorption "
"called indefatigable by seeing with great compassion and displayed passing "
"into nirvāṇa."

msgid "9b43851bd7634d39af4259fa77c2c151"
msgstr "“After passing into nirvāṇa, his relics were distributed."

msgid "1245c391964d45968f99b9f83ee2ac3a"
msgstr ""
"His sacred Dharma remained for eight times eighty-four thousand years."

msgid "dc3d6d36da034d8c9f25e3cf1a14f21f"
msgstr ""
"While his sacred Dharma was present, moreover, many beings received it, and "
"no counterfeit Dharma appeared."

msgid "60851018fc334ff781f83d64df35dcb8"
msgstr ""
"Through the cultivation of the power of meditative absorption and miraculous"
" blessing, that blessed one remained unmanifest for eighty-four thousand "
"eons."

msgid "9d277499ab7047bb88e40dd0b1fc0d13"
msgstr ""
"“Thus, when eighty-four thousand eons had passed, that being among the gods "
"in the Sphere of neither Perception nor Nonperception died and was reborn in"
" the human realm in the family of a merchant."

msgid "63e9fc4053594d66905f4307ca865742"
msgstr ""
"When he reached the age of eight, the Blessed Tathāgata Sandalwood Dwelling "
"rose from his absorption that had lasted eighty-four thousand eons."

msgid "36c109b55e54485193a325a74498706f"
msgstr ""
"He came before the youth in the form of a buddha, invisible to everyone else"
" except the youth."

msgid "c1753f8d902f4892b10babdc943c9aa7"
msgstr ""
"“This caused the youth to firmly make up his mind to generate the thought of"
" unsurpassed perfect awakening and not be turned back from unsurpassed "
"perfect awakening. The Buddha proceeded to teach the Dharma to the youth, "
"beginning with the Great Vehicle."

msgid "7b14078258814a7799bebf06a6d6c39f"
msgstr "He also delivered teachings about the faults of desire."

msgid "30b45f26f7b24a6c83a792312e96d36b"
msgstr ""
"The Blessed One understood the perfect special intention of the youth and "
"predicted that the youth would completely awaken to unsurpassed perfect "
"awakening after seventy-two times one hundred thousand countless eons."

msgid "cbc4ed90590d4e39962cb540afc1e0ef"
msgstr "He would emerge in the world as the Tathāgata Supreme Precious One."

msgid "9a634ed6e9ea47bf92ecc9e267055805"
msgstr "No human being but the youth himself heard this prophecy."

msgid "0e13e3fa51cd45f982aec840e5cd0637"
msgstr ""
"Twelve thousand gods who were worthy heard it and generated the thought of "
"unsurpassed perfect awakening."

msgid "d3519c77a84d455b9fad9616e463b9a4"
msgstr ""
"They also made an aspiration prayer saying, ‘When the Blessed Tathāgata "
"called Supreme Precious One finds awakening, may we be born in his "
"buddhafield at that time!’"

msgid "d11bb9d8ed2244c78d924dc21aafc055"
msgstr ""
"“In order for them all to be born into that buddhafield, the Blessed One "
"predicted, ‘The Tathāgata Supreme Precious One will predict your unsurpassed"
" perfect awakening!’"

msgid "eac1e4b3022e420e9d56abb819a97929"
msgstr ""
"Thereupon, the Blessed Tathāgata Sandalwood Dwelling, having prophesied "
"those bodhisattvas, completely passed into nirvāṇa, and the gods honored his"
" relics."

msgid "854d925718b24bf0ad88fa7241ab0f28"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, the blessed buddhas are endowed with such compassion, "
"which does not exist on the level of the śrāvakas or pratyekabuddhas."

msgid "0b21142d4f394bff9f1489ef17cdbf88"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, just as the blessed buddhas do not interrupt the "
"continuity of the lineage of the buddhas, likewise, the roots of virtue of "
"those who offer to the buddhas will also be uninterrupted until they pass "
"into nirvāṇa, because causes do not perish.”"

msgid "c8e84cc5a3a94fc5bd47742af47ac522"
msgstr ""
"When he had delivered this discourse on great tathāgata compassion, among "
"the assembly, as many beings as a third of the number of grains of sand in "
"the river Ganges generated the thought of unsurpassed perfect awakening."

msgid "acd3b2e3d80d4fafa512e7c95c89797d"
msgstr ""
"As many bodhisattvas as half the number of grains of sand in the river "
"Ganges attained willing acceptance."

msgid "03ce90fd87b149ffaf30c63a4cad6b9e"
msgstr ""
"And as many bodhisattvas as the number of grains of sand in the river Ganges"
" attained the sixteen kinds of great compassion."

msgid "4697e7cd43cd4b558a5fe97c3b1d0a0e"
msgstr ""
"They also attained acceptance of reality, which was endowed with the "
"empowerment of all the Buddha’s teachings."

msgid "fd040954142244429bbc858f9dcd8ff1"
msgstr ""
"At that time, all in the assembly who had heard this teaching became "
"content, pleased, delighted, and overjoyed."

msgid "ffc90f7ca1684a3babc7781e49ab43f1"
msgstr ""
"Feeling joyful and happy, everyone hailed the Blessed One with the words "
"“Very good!” and honored him with offerings both human and divine."

msgid "0bb57969dd654345a9ee6761633c6c55"
msgstr ""
"At that point, the Blessed One said to Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja, “Son of noble "
"family, you may ask, ‘What are the actions of the tathāgatas?’"

msgid "40f9e86e3ea74a33907a14a5d5b2f14d"
msgstr "There are thirty-two tathāgata actions. What are these actions?"

msgid "6f2306bf09d24cb88f071fada6ecfaa2"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas know with their unsurpassed wisdom and"
" in accordance with reality what is possible and what is impossible."

msgid "d03ecda7bf444399abd7bc587064e453"
msgstr ""
"You may ask, son of noble family, what is possible and what is impossible?"

msgid "c0bbc64b8c4b442c830e4c53ed7fd1a2"
msgstr ""
"That the maturation of wrongful conduct of body, speech, and mind will be "
"desirable, pleasant, delightful, or attractive is impossible."

msgid "e33b20ee5039459da4101a4aea712be5"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "7e0b438b70224df5b21585ecf90e7421"
msgstr ""
"That the maturation of good conduct of body, speech, and mind will be "
"desirable, pleasant, delightful, and attractive is possible."

msgid "65a5d173b87c41dbb22b30c2d30d879e"
msgstr "This will happen."

msgid "712607f13a3748058b43e8941b8fc04a"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, that one will attain great wealth through greediness, "
"be born as a god or human through flawed moral conduct, become beautiful "
"through ill will, attain realization through laziness, reach certainty "
"through mental distraction, or destroy the karmic traces through flawed "
"insight is impossible."

msgid "4a1dbcaa3f7d49e29c9d4ec129e08501"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "0653ee5d1f9140cea31d78456a7acc31"
msgstr ""
"That one will attain great wealth through generosity, be born as a god or "
"human through moral conduct, become beautiful through patience, attain "
"realization through perseverance, reach certainty through concentration, and"
" destroy all the karmic traces through insight is possible. This will "
"happen."

msgid "65cd74b37a2947cda76b46f77847df74"
msgstr ""
"“That the mind of someone who performs the acts of immediate retribution "
"will be at ease is impossible."

msgid "44b3a47d0e38473c8f59e411a27fa286"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "219e1ddd35cd419f84cbeebb7f8eba1d"
msgstr ""
"That the mind of someone with pure moral conduct will be at ease is "
"possible. This will happen."

msgid "a26ab0f3a88244589d0c895ff2aab655"
msgstr ""
"That one will attain willing acceptance while being involved with objective "
"references is impossible."

msgid "ea18bae27bfa46b788d9953cc57b8b1e"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "ca3890d614224667b2e9fefd95f37e1a"
msgstr ""
"That one will attain acceptance through devotion to emptiness is possible. "
"This will happen."

msgid "f75c3f6c284946228b0788c39fa72e37"
msgstr ""
"That the mind will become pliant while in a state of regret is impossible."

msgid "3f9f91ba540449869e2ad345ae819153"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "b1b5e5d19829406293148a3f7ee3caa0"
msgstr ""
"That a mind free of agitation will become pliant is possible. This will "
"happen."

msgid "02c725ac65094ae490ceb4c7f781a745"
msgstr ""
"That a universal monarch, Śakra, Brahmā, or a buddha will appear in the "
"world in a female body is impossible."

msgid "6fadd49fb8754840b55390e442bedbf8"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "071e91051b0a41c6b138e7835ba96c84"
msgstr ""
"That someone will appear in the world as a universal monarch, Śakra, Brahmā,"
" or a buddha after she has exchanged her female body is possible."

msgid "441e0847a5a6403183cf0adbddd4a4d0"
msgstr "This will happen."

msgid "a5ea65cfdaed449795eac24784a48959"
msgstr ""
"That someone who is not equal to the universal monarch will govern a kingdom"
" is impossible."

msgid "0573b049390046b08837977602edbc7f"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "824cbc9ee5fa41c4b77f92bf15dd6352"
msgstr ""
"That he who is equal to the universal monarch will govern a kingdom is "
"possible. This will happen."

msgid "a4a527491cf64bb985f7d85ba546b2dd"
msgstr ""
"“That a human being from the northern continent of Uttarakuru will descend "
"to lower destinies is impossible."

msgid "32c6efe0861042a2856d838c7988b8a0"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "c1a83789c9364826ada796cfff8af4a5"
msgstr ""
"That such a human will proceed to happy destinies is possible. This will "
"happen."

msgid "6216cbbb1524429e9acb5e3411ddd4a1"
msgstr ""
"That individuals who kill will enjoy long lives on account of their killing "
"and that they will attain the noble path on account of their wrong views and"
" the wrongful deeds based on them is impossible."

msgid "a040477c84ea4b69a2160880c3e266fa"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "774ade0439c34a35acc3383c9eaf8bd0"
msgstr ""
"That someone with a long life on account of abandoning killing will attain "
"the noble path through correct views is possible."

msgid "753b1ed8a6a14f75bbb35a912eb2104c"
msgstr "This will happen."

msgid "f745d79e5be349fe9484e65042af8390"
msgstr ""
"“That one will find deliverance without attaining the fruition of the eight "
"paths is impossible."

msgid "1e4f9530f2c148508250dd4c122fcc72"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "f61ae4a8e0574011bd14edf94473c9da"
msgstr ""
"That one will find deliverance once one has attained their fruition is "
"possible. This will happen."

msgid "a561078248fb43f2b1587764919211db"
msgstr ""
"That a stream enterer will actualize an eighth existence is impossible."

msgid "faa80dc22c4e4b4bb4a57fd7a4ab7473"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "25ca5938ac8b453e847733b539ff2efd"
msgstr ""
"That a stream enterer will enter a seventh existence even though there are "
"obstacles is possible."

msgid "de800da76a5241569a3117760154b698"
msgstr "That a once-returner will actualize a second existence is impossible."

msgid "7e302d92280f4347ad58d328d62942e5"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "24473464c29147c68e5a630384c8c102"
msgstr ""
"That a once-returner will reach the end of suffering after having returned "
"to this world is possible. This will happen."

msgid "fdd3a87afefd48c9a26ec35353636695"
msgstr "That a non-returner will return to this world is impossible."

msgid "776157879a3848c1b4c66f9e5d8107e8"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "6249399a9a4b4bfdb0ee6b2fe8d50baa"
msgstr ""
"That a non-returner will transcend suffering completely is possible. This "
"will happen."

msgid "bf453a860d754dc3b758e9b14f2a5025"
msgstr "That an arhat will enter a new existence is impossible."

msgid "a6fcb575a8cb41ec840b69786c9773f5"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "87eb009691c440919c06a12ade6d4f8e"
msgstr ""
"That an arhat will not enter a new existence is possible. This will happen."

msgid "4899d7884ba84365b6825f6daa210204"
msgstr ""
"“That a noble being will accept the instructions of another teacher is "
"impossible."

msgid "1e027b1184834d569249e9409ce75a40"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "bb23aadc2e284003b8caf869b04bd8bd"
msgstr "That such a being will have no other deity is possible."

msgid "179ac3adbf1b43c4912f74393b451d98"
msgstr ""
"That a bodhisattva who accepts the unborn nature of phenomena will regress "
"is impossible."

msgid "e3c35cf2e1c54180914274fb4e15a6f0"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "2121169fd6874c0280f9a1ed4b43bd9f"
msgstr ""
"That such a bodhisattva will awaken to complete and perfect awakening is "
"possible."

msgid "39b2076d589b497d83dc1cb8ddc2d3dc"
msgstr ""
"That a bodhisattva who dwells on the seat of awakening will arise without "
"completely and perfectly awakening is impossible."

msgid "b76f37b79406407c82ac5a801a412437"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "b8bad732b100401284565f1aca32d4f2"
msgstr ""
"That such a bodhisattva will arise as one awakened to complete and perfect "
"awakening is possible."

msgid "434593f627934808b44624efa40300da"
msgstr "“That karmic traces will appear for tathāgatas is impossible."

msgid "c71c485837b54bbaad65c94f64b10bd9"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "87de4090d0d64df1bbc13588dd809a6d"
msgstr ""
"That tathāgatas will have destroyed all karmic traces is possible. This will"
" happen."

msgid "46275f72ac154da18cec04b60fce8084"
msgstr "That the wisdom of tathāgatas will be obstructed is impossible."

msgid "97701c01e1044ffb89fbddd65956db0f"
msgstr "That the wisdom of tathāgatas will be unobstructed is possible."

msgid "8a16b35ead4c4a9f820d1442b2a78e53"
msgstr ""
"That the crown protuberances of tathāgatas will be visible is impossible."

msgid "c32c2a80d8444e109e1e5d1cfc902fe6"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "12d4db02b6754cc0a2062fbc913692e6"
msgstr ""
"That the crown protuberances of tathāgatas will be invisible is possible."

msgid "89ea38a19d174b3d89fb299e8c8688f8"
msgstr ""
"That one will know the activity of tathāgatas’ minds through means other "
"than the power of buddhas is impossible."

msgid "a2ae0a72e9b343458ac996cacb5f09a2"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "d53e781a619b4f6fa40cef2b31335800"
msgstr "That one will not know it is possible."

msgid "2c804b1ed6564d2487d5f3b22e8d4635"
msgstr ""
"That the minds of tathāgatas will not be in equipoise and will have "
"reference points is impossible."

msgid "11907cd3c7014e529ee7f161e27d05cc"
msgstr "That tathāgatas will be in constant equipoise is possible."

msgid "c72836202e8842109bae6035c4755af7"
msgstr "That untrue words will issue from tathāgatas is impossible."

msgid "2bed50a6e9514da6ba5cabf53d6ded87"
msgstr "That true words will issue is possible."

msgid "b851b7893d21431aaef8ba7e08d611b1"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, that deluded objective reference will exist for "
"tathāgatas is impossible."

msgid "3c5f2fca107a4fb0834130c0a1182be3"
msgstr "This will not happen."

msgid "9c6ffe7635e74719a599d3649378a0cb"
msgstr "That delusion will not exist for tathāgatas is possible."

msgid "74368b07e12e4b31b33d208f9e7da236"
msgstr "This will happen."

msgid "bedcd1b4c4654f6ebfae51a0adafe27f"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, words cannot illustrate the scope of the Tathāgata’s "
"power of knowing what is possible and what is impossible."

msgid "f328427cdd674eefba335b4c37df3bbd"
msgstr "It is perfect."

msgid "e137ec706ac949cf993de13d4ee070ef"
msgstr "It is unique and like no other."

msgid "ae247e3231d6479299c73c07cb752b25"
msgstr "About this the following is proclaimed:"

msgid "f5142ca45c114431a8ebb8711b5bcc04"
msgstr "“ ‘All earth may crumble,"

msgid "5e130c369df04c26ad71ca372c799907"
msgstr "The sky may tremble,"

msgid "c6118691524e4faea3000f32d8cc45a2"
msgstr "But for what the Buddha has explained not to be the case—"

msgid "ac23c9b906f8463896154504c6844696"
msgstr "That will never occur."

msgid "73c1d59fef314ac19e77f197d73d3049"
msgstr "“ ‘Beings may mold space Into five-colored form,"

msgid "ff1a1288a66d47939c4a13deea82f3ce"
msgstr "But for what the Buddha has explained not to be the case—"

msgid "f3d55426f984444880a914478bdbd24e"
msgstr "That will never occur."

msgid "b740fdfd08a842aba95f81d89e0050c7"
msgstr "To a lesser, middling, or supreme degree—"

msgid "7f5ad1bffebf4d39ad44f2fb590c029f"
msgstr "“ ‘All that the Buddha has explained to be the case"

msgid "a76451a20cc0465c94d8d77f61ea5f0a"
msgstr "There is no way that any of that Will turn out to be otherwise."

msgid "c6e7d01d5aaf46eea43352b50955ddfd"
msgstr "To a lesser, middling, or supreme degree—"

msgid "b81cc6fa78a44c9a937d078ad6ad3c58"
msgstr "“ ‘All that he has explained not to be the case"

msgid "919c45605d8245a4b0647d53cbc80e3b"
msgstr "There is no way that any of that Will turn out to be otherwise."

msgid "55711b6d548c4a398970eb11325e46f9"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘He who knows what is and what is not the case Continuously explains the "
"truth And the Dharma to creatures In accordance with their thoughts."

msgid "fbf3e1e63ccc4b0e9ae645cd1fd8dbae"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Other mendicants and brahmins Who rush around everywhere Do not know what"
" is and what is not the case. That is not so for the Buddha."

msgid "0a5e2c6e25dc47afab2d9ffe8daf1ea9"
msgstr "“ ‘When endowed with what is possible,"

msgid "bc25e64ee54d42869490eb366a868b43"
msgstr "The liberation of beings will multiply."

msgid "a98d2f8cf7b744df9c3e18f695aa55a3"
msgstr "The fully qualified Buddha Explains that precisely."

msgid "0acab7e1b745452190bd1e0e656c0723"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Toward beings who are not receptive, The Buddha remains in equanimity."

msgid "e7b9511e1c28441ca00857ceda2ef233"
msgstr "He waits for the right occasion, The time at which to liberate them."

msgid "1ececed0a17b4cb0a2386fb37c2ab789"
msgstr "“ ‘What liberates beings Is conduct beyond reproach."

msgid "13396799291e49158491708b8cc1f939"
msgstr ""
"That is the first liberating activity Of the supremely intelligent Buddha."

msgid "2dc5d4a882a344c1b4ff2ab46bce4337"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘His explanations of what is and what is not the case Are unfathomable and"
" innumerable."

msgid "b887d4249fcd4e04a6a509a934d8e1f5"
msgstr "This power of the great sage Is hard for adversaries to match.’"

msgid "0a8f2cdd04ae4f98887269cd3649105d"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, tathāgatas know skillfully and in accordance with "
"reality about past, present, and future actions as well as the basis, "
"causes, substance, and maturation of the actions undertaken."

msgid "fda9726270aa4dc08bd44e657bec6389"
msgstr "You may ask, how do they understand them?"

msgid "d9c449a7a060417bb7a9d46c6fc9a022"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, the tathāgatas know the actions undertaken in the past "
"that spring from virtuous causes, are free of anything nonvirtuous, and "
"will, in the future, engender what springs from virtuous causes."

msgid "219db4040bd649ecae8e6000af05fa7d"
msgstr ""
"They know the actions undertaken that spring from nonvirtuous causes, are "
"free of anything virtuous, and will, in the future, engender what springs "
"from nonvirtuous causes."

msgid "f910a96525384765987ad2c748085172"
msgstr ""
"They know in accordance with reality the actions undertaken that will become"
" the basis for something minor in the future, the actions undertaken that "
"will become the basis for something major in the future, the actions "
"undertaken that are the basis for something minor in the present that will "
"become the basis for something major in the future, and"

msgid "0ec4cd68689d433288ea5e901737c37b"
msgstr ""
"the actions undertaken that are the basis for something major in the present"
" that will become the basis for something minor in the future."

msgid "58dd7d0e6a674403b953d4cc6ef48108"
msgstr ""
"They know the actions undertaken that are the basis for something minor in "
"the present that will also become the basis for something minor in the "
"future."

msgid "9c77ff59b1b044d1bbf29a292869db4c"
msgstr ""
"They know the actions undertaken that are the basis for something major in "
"the present that will also become the basis for something major in the "
"future."

msgid "1f12d79c1eca440f895065ab45eb8496"
msgstr ""
"They know the actions undertaken that were a minor task in the past that "
"will become something major and turn into a great success in the future."

msgid "91f188c1e2d9486dbac7873580951caf"
msgstr ""
"They know the actions undertaken that require little exertion that may "
"nonetheless become of great significance."

msgid "dae4b079345f4db1be11d7f1007fe20c"
msgstr ""
"They also know the actions undertaken that require great exertion that may "
"nonetheless become of little significance."

msgid "42f54ebf97dc48e489999a7740b99777"
msgstr ""
"“They know the actions undertaken that will engender the cause of "
"śrāvakahood, the actions undertaken that will engender the cause of "
"pratyekabuddhahood, and the actions undertaken that will engender the cause "
"of buddhahood."

msgid "6b5bb2a3a66e4812b4024df60da26917"
msgstr ""
"They know the actions undertaken that are painful at present but will lead "
"to a blissful maturation in the future."

msgid "457b8e1ff29c4bd0ae0674b7a14acf37"
msgstr ""
"They know the actions undertaken that are blissful at present but will lead "
"to a painful maturation in the future."

msgid "660067caafb3441699ce9b3cf5831692"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas know the actions undertaken that are painful at present and "
"will also lead to a painful maturation in the future."

msgid "b362d743064242a48fae0f530ee40f10"
msgstr ""
"They know the actions undertaken that are blissful at present and will also "
"lead to a blissful maturation in the future."

msgid "7b09b1f351634f1c864399b21e666067"
msgstr ""
"“In these ways, son of noble family, the tathāgatas uniquely and "
"independently understand in accordance with reality all about beings’ "
"actions in the past, present, and future, their circumstances, and their "
"maturation."

msgid "0ec462c87cda4526b2b35e0f1e399e63"
msgstr "With this understanding they teach the Dharma accordingly."

msgid "f47742a06c2048638090197153fb4e48"
msgstr "This is the second tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "384ee79097e1419ebfa88a7a30579eea"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "694f9b1df1aa4bdfac49149f1a5526d1"
msgstr "“ ‘The tathāgatas are skilled in causes."

msgid "eaf16013825f4653ae6727b85dd4f6d9"
msgstr "They are endowed with the eye of knowing how actions mature."

msgid "c3fa584364924b07a99f2c8519674ccc"
msgstr "Not fettered by the three times,"

msgid "4b323dcd7fe24cc690ea97b8453e1718"
msgstr "They know the conduct of all sentient beings."

msgid "b2a2fb42bfe34cc7b9a6396de3b52497"
msgstr "Which causes engender bliss,"

msgid "d99199b8075443e5bbceeeeb2169a4d3"
msgstr "Comprising maturation as gods and humans,"

msgid "5b0ac39548b9471db442ee22a5ea5271"
msgstr "And which ones engender suffering."

msgid "fe55521f1c9c432da36486183b194558"
msgstr "“ ‘The sugatas know"

msgid "7c3b1e2aa8654295b98447f3c44cf462"
msgstr "Of virtuous and nonvirtuous actions,"

msgid "6e8bc5b5122e4ff1bcb1f1d4d5c7f3f7"
msgstr "The causes and the maturation"

msgid "2ec4a4d687774a52a364c219cf35ea69"
msgstr "“ ‘The sugatas know"

msgid "22c1781f9e60488c866de2a56adc5843"
msgstr "Like holding a precious jewel in their hands."

msgid "bec2f38316d24b1c9281667b18d7b56e"
msgstr "“ ‘Which actions arise from tiny causes"

msgid "5a4a6555a640433a9438215ad5592fbb"
msgstr "And engender immeasurable consequences,"

msgid "25101ab6dbb34c869ffbee8c4bace7be"
msgstr "However vast or tiny they may be—"

msgid "082f1f523ea34504bec3397173d8ac2c"
msgstr "The buddhas know them all exactly."

msgid "e2719fe010b3491a823a1ff387238247"
msgstr "What leads to the Śrāvaka Vehicle,"

msgid "d1e78b149fdb4da394a6ea038f4ef3ec"
msgstr "What leads to the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle,"

msgid "8c0bc83f679b41d8934c849b497ad424"
msgstr "And the causes of a victor."

msgid "09423f5bb4e2466999b2485e72617653"
msgstr "“ ‘The sugatas know all about"

msgid "aadfcec1adc44b96b4efc7916c30740d"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘They know which causes are painful now But will later engender bliss;"

msgid "b4dbc77fe09040d6a0b3dc5546d1db03"
msgstr "Which causes are blissful now But will later engender pain;"

msgid "24441f4f45ad4687b68c84c047dbcc56"
msgstr "“ ‘Which causes are painful now and will be painful later;"

msgid "b32d9cc1f6db4af1bb21e231754a146f"
msgstr "And which causes are blissful now and will be blissful later."

msgid "322d31b12b064360a92b8750a6f6ff02"
msgstr "The sugatas thus know the true nature of actions"

msgid "b43e100d663d479c998d76c9abf36866"
msgstr "By all beings of the three times,"

msgid "b66cd32d671d4bcaace0fb1d9235cfe8"
msgstr ""
"In accordance with their causes. “ ‘With their unique buddha wisdom Of "
"actions and the causes for their engagement"

msgid "23f9bddff76d40b1b5634f60734810f4"
msgstr "The victors always know this just as it is.’"

msgid "8476403cb43c459688bf58a6e58a1ba6"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas know in accordance with reality the "
"many and various inclinations of other beings and individuals."

msgid "7386ef0bdbc643c5ae1d863ec606af8f"
msgstr ""
"You may ask, how do they know in accordance with reality the many and "
"various inclinations of other beings and individuals?"

msgid "3d3d21630c8c4e728eb2a1b51707fe22"
msgstr ""
"They know which individuals are established in attachment and inclined "
"toward aversion, which individuals are established in aversion and inclined "
"toward attachment, and which individuals are established in delusion and "
"inclined toward attachment, aversion, and delusion."

msgid "0708f79f5e9c4cedbf7923d365cbb938"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas know which individuals are established in virtue and inclined"
" toward virtue, which individuals whose engagement is minor are inclined "
"with a vast intention, and which individuals whose engagement is vast are "
"inclined with a minor intention."

msgid "36624a31ee48431e95e27087c6826dd6"
msgstr ""
"They know which inclinations will transform minor engagements into major "
"ones and which inclinations will transform superior engagements into minor "
"ones."

msgid "94f127ff20134a8e8e9382ee118f3914"
msgstr ""
"They know in accordance with reality which inclinations lead to acquiring a "
"determined disposition that is destined for error, which inclinations remain"
" undetermined, which inclinations lead to acquiring a disposition that is "
"destined for truth, and which inclinations lead to attaining liberation in "
"the case of one destined for truth."

msgid "adeab7ccf730434893bdcb245a98dc26"
msgstr ""
"They know which inclinations will lead beyond the desire realm, which will "
"lead beyond the form realm, and which will lead beyond the third realm."

msgid "6b2fd85d4d9f44d3be71acbd1c31905b"
msgstr ""
"They know which inclinations will suppress something major through relying "
"on something minor and which inclinations will transform something major "
"into something minor."

msgid "c988f24efa4c4ea0a9aa29cd68f04629"
msgstr ""
"They know which inclinations will bring about the attainment of varying "
"kinds of corresponding birth, appearance, and means of livelihood."

msgid "ccaa4e457eda4c83be804b11595688bc"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas know which inclinations will lead to downfall from the peak "
"of existence and which inclinations will lead to the attainment of "
"liberation."

msgid "46fb33e5cc5a4f8da6794ff25dae497a"
msgstr "With this understanding they teach the Dharma accordingly."

msgid "d94474eda0d54665b051e4e0fd8ae6df"
msgstr "This is the third tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "294de5b15609404aabe1c8aeec4ce318"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "68424e4c7a1b4d80a27c27559f0611d4"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘With their limitless intelligence, the tathāgatas know the entire range"

msgid "37300a7dd25b4acdbba9feea29a70be6"
msgstr "Of the world’s various and manifold inclinations."

msgid "dcf1f6d619cf4f30b2022a9638978c56"
msgstr ""
"The buddhas know well which inclinations are caused by aversion and instill "
"attachment"

msgid "f5a3b0910f454312abddcb7f966ef1d9"
msgstr "And which ones instill aversion and incline toward delusion."

msgid "1965439840b545f4926cd547a7a8b548"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘With minds established in delusion, beings may engage in virtue or "
"attachment."

msgid "23e90e2f1d954f0f96f4877385a482ef"
msgstr ""
"Whichever is the case, it may be with minor engagement but a vast "
"inclination."

msgid "3d51795e23c246639718346d5b13c690"
msgstr ""
"Even when there is vast intent and vast engagement, Inclination may "
"transform it into something minor."

msgid "cbee82972e9949c888824b9b64307eb5"
msgstr "This the sugatas know."

msgid "6816d7cd6a1e46b0b93fd2c10d8813c4"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The buddhas know which inclinations will transform a being’s minor "
"engagement into something vast"

msgid "1e4381208b0d434b9aceb137b351793e"
msgstr "And a being’s vast intelligence into something minor."

msgid "cf09103927e44c47b68345428032b156"
msgstr "They know which inclinations are destined for error,"

msgid "e07336c0c63c4141a6037e9a44783ed6"
msgstr "Which for the truth, and which for liberation from the three realms."

msgid "08abb82668bf4fb8b136cf416a9b56cf"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The victors know well which inclinations bring about which births, "
"appearances, And means of livelihood of all sentient beings of all the three"
" times,"

msgid "8b61a77ed5204948a7798be2e0fba80f"
msgstr ""
"Which bring downfall from the peak of existence, and which bring liberation."

msgid "c9fa35d3c9f84d59b91473cfd178a253"
msgstr ""
"With this knowledge they teach the Dharma—such is said to be the activity of"
" the sugatas.’"

msgid "dcd21e3840a34aeea43c37d54af8b3dd"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas know, in accordance with reality, the "
"worlds that are comprised of many and various elements."

msgid "24e2fecd13e940ceb804c7eca63e235c"
msgstr "You may ask, how do they know them?"

msgid "5e3df38067734ff3bd4f5911a3b5fa98"
msgstr ""
"They know, in accordance with reality, which elements accumulate mundane "
"virtuous conditioning, which elements accumulate nonvirtuous conditioning, "
"which elements accumulate neutral conditioning, and which elements establish"
" one in the element of deliverance."

msgid "3ee39b7fad494aabb6b39be91fcfa68b"
msgstr ""
"“They know the element of the eye, the element of form, and the element of "
"visual consciousness."

msgid "eb3e1fa1d5544dd3beee2501a5e27b49"
msgstr "How do they know them?"

msgid "0541012530f943a6a646695b7059c4e2"
msgstr ""
"They know them to be an inner emptiness, an outer emptiness, and an inner "
"and outer emptiness, respectively."

msgid "ceb160672a4243a78f941b6cbb70c8cd"
msgstr ""
"They know the element of the ear, the element of sound, and the element of "
"auditory consciousness."

msgid "a4d4e8ae84ff4a81a4265743504f0588"
msgstr "How do they know them?"

msgid "f21cb4b29e1043f8a32b9685d6b04f1a"
msgstr ""
"They know them to be an inner emptiness, an outer emptiness, and an inner "
"and outer emptiness, respectively."

msgid "d7e5a006e7404d33800cfd37a0f63ede"
msgstr ""
"They know the element of the nose, the element of smell, and the element of "
"olfactory consciousness."

msgid "86ba3c212cc442daa45dd6cc83ef9abe"
msgstr "How do they know them?"

msgid "488ba879cc3347258326675d595d9202"
msgstr ""
"They know them to be an inner emptiness, an outer emptiness, and an inner "
"and outer emptiness, respectively."

msgid "a8022b00e59847299fcd36a925e16435"
msgstr ""
"They know the element of the tongue, the element of taste, and the element "
"of the consciousness of taste."

msgid "1b4c75fc6fb94431a98b503c1ae6d412"
msgstr "How do they know them?"

msgid "fe840e048a8e42b1a2cf17a6823fce9b"
msgstr ""
"They know them to be an inner emptiness, an outer emptiness, and an inner "
"and outer emptiness, respectively."

msgid "a073dbf4546743f280c775128c1f2e73"
msgstr ""
"They know the element of the body, the element of the tactile, and the "
"element of tactile consciousness."

msgid "b738ebd16b1f4761b11df0d9c510ae4e"
msgstr "How do they know them?"

msgid "ac9b6b71a3934837ba037f5a0b6cc18d"
msgstr ""
"They know them to be an inner emptiness, an outer emptiness, and an inner "
"and outer emptiness, respectively."

msgid "2830b1f11ac94313baab73815de013a6"
msgstr ""
"They know the element of the mind, the element of phenomena, and the element"
" of mental consciousness."

msgid "50de7229873641dcbf2efafddbcc8428"
msgstr "How do they know them?"

msgid "5350061b3efe4661975ea7840bcc4507"
msgstr ""
"They know them to be an inner emptiness, an outer emptiness, and an inner "
"and outer emptiness, respectively."

msgid "6b9f494e287142439638b52394e1731b"
msgstr "They know the elements of earth, water, fire, and wind."

msgid "3d4998e7c43948af8f9f3d7be3cee7d5"
msgstr "How do they know them?"

msgid "f4b37662a1da48b2985a0e382fbd2a94"
msgstr "They know them to be just like the element of space."

msgid "f5fd080dd7a347a49ef66bd572a02bfc"
msgstr "“They know the desire realm, the form realm, and the formless realm."

msgid "fc5dc9871b7142cdb5f70e8bd8f4266b"
msgstr "How do they know them?"

msgid "a86ae15b8e0b47ed94181c7e1e9d5fa9"
msgstr "They know them to originate in false imagining."

msgid "8c34c8e6e1774106a255fcb3c2110191"
msgstr ""
"They know conditioned elements to be fabricated and unconditioned elements "
"to be unfabricated."

msgid "a577152b19004473a5af8259bbeead48"
msgstr ""
"They know that the elements of pollution are characterized by adventitious "
"afflictive emotion and that the elements of purification are characterized "
"by natural luminosity."

msgid "2efba8108b47409bb48d1ca2425c2362"
msgstr ""
"They know that the realm of saṃsāra is characterized by incorrect ignorance "
"and that the sphere of nirvāṇa is characterized by correct knowing."

msgid "6b3f47b5e21e4ad9a12e03f7b177e4cf"
msgstr ""
"“In this way, the tathāgatas fully understand which elements establish the "
"world, which elements fully establish it, which elements facilitate, and "
"which elements obstruct."

msgid "13b87c4835ca45469668d32b44e702db"
msgstr ""
"They know which elements belong to engagement, which belong to reflection, "
"which belong to determination, and which elements are supports."

msgid "df2b07a334ee4b80a575564640fde345"
msgstr "With this understanding they teach the Dharma accordingly."

msgid "cf1085b8d5ad432bb1c6bad366841e7b"
msgstr "This is the fourth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "f6fccacda9bf4903b25cc6e42fd2424f"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "7ae65293c45341ceb74830f2dfdedb24"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The lions among humans are skilled in the ways of all the elements."

msgid "7a71a23e2c9d4f669daa93bd3d49e542"
msgstr "Which elements are engaged where and in what ways"

msgid "2b9003f733674b43a8cb95c8fe72c628"
msgstr "And which elements are the source of extensive virtue."

msgid "fd3e7af8b46a4b88a03cc2a612be8231"
msgstr "“ ‘With their great insight, the sugatas know these elements:"

msgid "69c8f3616e1e45f0aff7776c10560f08"
msgstr "The experiences that propel merit, nonmerit, and neutrality,"

msgid "5dc82bc50c1c460e99997a7d150cddc7"
msgstr "And the element of peace that brings the attainment of deliverance"

msgid "bc507969b5a046eb856ee5c65eb6e9e1"
msgstr "And that, when established, brings liberation from the elements."

msgid "50998b5447ef4222ba41e4675a2c4016"
msgstr "The sugatas know without exception"

msgid "67a0318d2eaa4c67810a5cb43731b86c"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Knowing the elements of the eye, form, and mind to be naturally empty Is "
"the essential conduct of the victors."

msgid "1ea65652ba1245f8b9e7766d4ccabbde"
msgstr "Likewise, the elements of the ear, nose, tongue, and body,"

msgid "cba7db81e5d44f7085b1ee04015e4a25"
msgstr ""
"And the elements of the mind and phenomena, are known to be perpetually "
"empty."

msgid "31dc2d68cbd34a81a1eb2cfae92d6806"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The lions among humans know The elements of water, fire, earth, and air "
"to be like space."

msgid "2855e287c304497daebc5d640bb4696d"
msgstr ""
"They know without exception that the realms of desire, form, and "
"formlessness Emerge from conceptuality."

msgid "cfedb7b7c99c4f798d4db0de9d39eb63"
msgstr "“ ‘The victors know the elements of pollution to lack a true nature."

msgid "0d7b9c60324245b998661c3f61c15a07"
msgstr ""
"The sugatas know the elements of purification to be like this as well."

msgid "6317a3cdb40149eeb9c19173265927b6"
msgstr "The unskillful go on creating saṃsāra,"

msgid "d90678415a864d03a06f54cae5bf7e85"
msgstr "While nirvāṇa lacks the three characteristics of the conditioned."

msgid "6c9e58609b3a4863967c88472b56cc48"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Some elements are characterized by being engaged through nonvirtue,"

msgid "571988c0429d4cf4a2972e548c962f38"
msgstr "While others terminate all forms of engagement by means of virtue."

msgid "ebac28bd16ea42a78270926332099721"
msgstr ""
"Though the buddhas understand this world comprised of various and manifold "
"elements,"

msgid "ce5241e2ed9446b8ae1547664ac12773"
msgstr "They are not conceited, thinking, “I know!”"

msgid "bb4dc65071df4f84839b490a7788e3ce"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘These lions among humans fully understand the elements, Which are "
"limitless like space."

msgid "f42ee2686b574b7bb3d6a04291654716"
msgstr "The sacred wisdom of the victors is unobstructed—"

msgid "c178f8b170a64a1e807c790b4098c063"
msgstr "Beings are unable to fathom its range."

msgid "c5e62c284a4544d3b03ffc7b6b5e0a4f"
msgstr "“ ‘This is the fourth activity of the pure protectors."

msgid "814dc1f3486441a19f4bc61a1ab1a919"
msgstr "They know the procedure in terms of the elements for taming beings."

msgid "888a17910ceb460abf9f3b150487ce23"
msgstr ""
"In the process of taming them, through the proper performance of acts,"

msgid "65e450d961214f60aeb5bad333d2fd88"
msgstr "Even though there exist myriad delusions, these never occur to them.’"

msgid "7eb72918cfbd42a08ba337c343923cf9"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas know, in accordance with reality, the "
"levels of the faculties of other beings and individuals."

msgid "9bf84423cad847cb8d7738319ae2d1ee"
msgstr "You may ask, how do they know them in accordance with reality?"

msgid "be8b3bc5d9dd4fda8a32f94042e34216"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, they know, in accordance with reality, which beings are"
" less gifted."

msgid "92444a9118a343cb8df49f7e6a0c0525"
msgstr ""
"Likewise, they know whose faculties are average, whose are sharp, whose are "
"extraordinary, and whose are poor."

msgid "997406129d0b4d2a9e65540d3dda71dc"
msgstr ""
"“They know how consummate attachment, aversion, and delusion arise from the "
"dominant influence of conceptuality."

msgid "7c6c9a96d2cf4d9d9effe9f125545b98"
msgstr ""
"They know how contrived attachment, aversion, and delusion arise from the "
"dominant influence of conceptuality."

msgid "1d95dcc5abff4fdaaa3f5844a224af15"
msgstr ""
"They know how perverted attachment, aversion, and delusion arise from the "
"dominant influence of conceptuality."

msgid "9263988eff354db8ad3509fd562165f0"
msgstr ""
"They know how destructive attachment, aversion, and delusion arise from the "
"dominant influence of conceptuality."

msgid "790d6277c6b54e11a8da292daad93c86"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas know comprehensively how, from the dominant influence of "
"conceptuality, some faculties originate from virtuous causes, some from "
"nonvirtuous causes, some from neutral causes, and others from the causes of "
"deliverance."

msgid "a9241587a00b47e89c06536ee741cf39"
msgstr ""
"“Moreover, son of noble family, the tathāgatas know the sense faculties of "
"the eyes, ears, nose, tongue, body, and mind."

msgid "e243f9878bb847c1a86016e036735bb5"
msgstr "They know the male faculty, the female faculty, and the vital force."

msgid "4bb3f24664d7423dbec9d834387c3641"
msgstr ""
"They understand the propensity for physical pleasure and pain, mental joy "
"and grief, and equanimity."

msgid "f3a5157f9f174aac91ff515e799cf08c"
msgstr ""
"They know the spiritual faculties of faith, vigor, mindfulness, absorption, "
"and insight."

msgid "ccbeae7875ae495cad4e436908dad397"
msgstr ""
"They know the faculty that changes unknowing into omniscience, the faculty "
"of omniscience, and the faculty endowed with omniscience."

msgid "089b7b5763334a5dba0837bb9f6fe9d7"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas understand which capacity caused by the sense power of the "
"eyes will transform into a sense power for the ear, rather than into a sense"
" power for the nose, tongue, or body."

msgid "05359339c83c411392078f7a2e804042"
msgstr ""
"They understand which capacity caused by the sense power of the ear will "
"transform into a sense power for the nose, which capacity caused by the "
"sense power of the nose will transform into a sense power for the tongue, "
"which capacity caused by the sense power of the tongue will transform into a"
" sense power for the body, and which capacity caused by the sense power of "
"the body will transform into a sense power for the eye."

msgid "70a951bbaaf04e8b8e69f5929ef53684"
msgstr ""
"“To people who are capable of generosity and who apply themselves to moral "
"conduct, the tathāgatas, understanding the range of capacities, give "
"discourses on generosity."

msgid "557357de0942442d93a36272acb4ceeb"
msgstr ""
"To people who are capable of moral conduct and who apply themselves to "
"generosity, the tathāgatas, understanding the range of capacities, give "
"discourses on moral conduct."

msgid "379e0a88d8de4330ac86514ea3711a27"
msgstr ""
"To people who have the capacity for patience and who apply themselves to "
"vigor, the tathāgatas, understanding the range of capacities, give "
"discourses on patience."

msgid "bfa3e8ee025d4bb7bdb4b131136c6ef7"
msgstr ""
"To people who are capable of vigor and who apply themselves to patience, the"
" tathāgatas, understanding the range of capacities, give discourses on "
"vigor."

msgid "1b72f0a03eaa4c0e842d3777abb4beac"
msgstr ""
"To people who have the capacity for concentration and who apply themselves "
"to insight, the tathāgatas, understanding the range of capacities, give "
"discourses on concentration."

msgid "7a28919c07c54057a5f8fa2980ad1898"
msgstr ""
"To people who have the capacity for insight and who apply themselves to "
"concentration, the tathāgatas, understanding the range of capacities, give "
"discourses on insight."

msgid "2864e2f59723421fa29fff13977eadee"
msgstr "Likewise, all factors of awakening should be comprehended in detail."

msgid "ba0b54ccb90444adb44524f12caab712"
msgstr ""
"“To people who have the capacity for the Śrāvaka Vehicle but apply "
"themselves to the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle, the tathāgatas, understanding the "
"range of capacities, give discourses on the Śrāvaka Vehicle."

msgid "39dc130b46ce4fccba7ae4c21683bd45"
msgstr ""
"To people who have the capacity for the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle but apply "
"themselves to the Śrāvaka Vehicle, the tathāgatas, understanding the range "
"of capacities, give discourses on the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle."

msgid "25028ce7e09942ff94fd66324259f797"
msgstr ""
"To people who have the capacity for the Great Vehicle but apply themselves "
"to the Śrāvaka Vehicle and the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle, the tathāgatas, "
"understanding the range of capacities, give discourses on the Great Vehicle."

msgid "a1565506dcc841cf93f49fc9ca71abdf"
msgstr ""
"To people of the highest capacity who apply themselves to the Great Vehicle,"
" the tathāgatas, understanding the range of capacities, give the final "
"discourses."

msgid "ed61c14778e947f589bc254bdd5c48c1"
msgstr ""
"“When the tathāgatas know that those who are subject to a lack of fortune "
"and who appear unfortunate are not receptive, they remain in equanimity."

msgid "e26e3eb3cc0440f294a34af8b223fc21"
msgstr ""
"When the tathāgatas know that those who have the power of good fortune and "
"who appear fortunate are worthy, they teach them the Dharma as they are "
"venerated by them."

msgid "52cea3c760f74493b43e3467815324cc"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, in this way the tathāgatas know the developed and the "
"undeveloped capacities of all sentient beings."

msgid "f599beb245f844dda12d69c45e3c85d6"
msgstr ""
"They know the capacities that have not yet emerged as well as those that "
"have emerged."

msgid "794cdedc56c34a8899924e1650e5be70"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas know in accordance with reality the capacities of beings, "
"their aspects, their applications, their intentions, the causes from which "
"they arise, their conditions, their reference points, their concordant "
"causes, and their limits."

msgid "5e5ec5c0294745c3960e1823a7774c3d"
msgstr "This is the fifth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "141f4bd137bf489fa55b9ecc9ef77044"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "d5fb2a493ed44f528154213f4d320519"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘With transcendent knowledge of faculties, they are wise regarding the "
"intentions of beings."

msgid "fa089f85b2434521b3b7f6f6902df289"
msgstr ""
"The victors know well how beings’ conduct accords with their faculties."

msgid "dfe4ed53a23e40b693179fd469a8d886"
msgstr ""
"The victors know the methods for those of exceptional, average, or poor "
"faculties."

msgid "de94f9474ff04d82a612326e69baaf98"
msgstr "Their incomparable deeds for liberating beings are outstanding."

msgid "5b381fd643be4fb6966d885e60f0519c"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘They know the faculties by which afflictive emotions are consummated, "
"contrived, Accumulated, and perverted."

msgid "58ad2648161e465382bfad223af71dbf"
msgstr ""
"They know the faculties of destructive afflictive emotions and those of "
"virtue, Those that are neutral, those that are nonvirtuous, and those that "
"are liberating."

msgid "5a182be302cd430f88cb413d7f000b2a"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘They understand the sense faculties from the eye to the mind, the male "
"and female faculties, The vital force, the propensities for pleasure and "
"pain, joy, grief, and equanimity, The spiritual faculties of faith, vigor, "
"mindfulness, insight, and one-pointedness, The method for the faculties for "
"omniscience and for making all known, and the faculty for liberation."

msgid "3e7b2c55e14d47e5ba4aa2255c4880d7"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘They know what occurs due to the cause of the eye and is made present to "
"the ear rather than to the nose and the tongue,"

msgid "baa7cef5d3ac43fcae559be2b3fbfa31"
msgstr ""
"And what occurs due to causes up to the body and in turn is present to the "
"eye."

msgid "5ad7e4eadd734002a1a7f9ca3c525efd"
msgstr ""
"To people with the capacity for generosity who exemplify moral conduct they "
"give talks on generosity."

msgid "6f55c5cf678641c4b55d471d2f6c9353"
msgstr ""
"To people with the capacity for moral conduct who exemplify generosity they "
"give talks on moral conduct."

msgid "c779f400ee694c27b37255705399919f"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘To people with the capacity for patience who exemplify vigor they give "
"talks on patience."

msgid "203ff63f5b1648418682304619950b91"
msgstr ""
"To people with the capacity for vigor who exemplify patience they give talks"
" on vigor."

msgid "cd847798ffbf4e0ea722fe0ad858ad14"
msgstr ""
"To people with the capacity for concentration who exemplify insight they "
"give talks on concentration."

msgid "106a4feab7124a4f959259ac2f276120"
msgstr ""
"To people with the capacity for insight who exemplify concentration they "
"give talks on insight."

msgid "05de4a7922d44792ae19095e97c3b7e5"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘To people who have the capacity for the Śrāvaka Vehicle but apply "
"themselves to the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle"

msgid "d6435fe486eb42b98ef65c7e4d738755"
msgstr ""
"They will give discourses on śrāvakas but cease those about pratyekabuddhas."

msgid "5f7000007750416ca0e4a177a7847570"
msgstr ""
"To those whose capacity is definitely for the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle but who"
" apply themselves to words They teach the methods and faculties suited to "
"the Dharma of the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle."

msgid "60056578bcb345d2b66fc7280a67cd3e"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘To those whose capacity is definitely for the Great Vehicle but who "
"resort to something inferior"

msgid "5feddd6f70b9443ca973d13b594799bf"
msgstr ""
"They discourse on the transcendent perfections of the victors who abide in "
"great compassion."

msgid "aaa6b3453a1a44a1b60fbd654866fe65"
msgstr ""
"Knowing who is ready and who is not, victors teach the former and are "
"equanimous toward the latter."

msgid "6e3e6fecb4bd45b2bc1724ec7c7400cb"
msgstr ""
"Through the ten strengths they know which capacities have developed and "
"which have not."

msgid "16bd5e3421a04242a3a8fc52383fafc7"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘They know the form of conduct of peoples’ capacities and how it is "
"applied,"

msgid "f0690e246ebb4a4393edacbed3515a32"
msgstr ""
"Likewise their intentions and what their circumstances and their causes are,"

msgid "2adc5e0001de4966ac3cb9b73000a453"
msgstr ""
"And likewise their reference points, their limits, and their corresponding "
"causes."

msgid "38eadf4b8af04d7dbf69891cbe0f05a1"
msgstr ""
"Knowing with spontaneous wisdom, their buddha activity of teaching is "
"unerring.’"

msgid "65e46d0d1d8a4392a347731b62e4d588"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas know in accordance with reality the "
"paths that lead to all destinies."

msgid "0ead1f5595a14adca3ab8658884f7253"
msgstr "You may ask, how do they know them?"

msgid "92fee923850e47bbb96c348f5dd343fb"
msgstr "They know the beings who are destined for truth."

msgid "2b6cf3e9c36e4883904bfb9e5c4af73f"
msgstr ""
"They know the beings who are undetermined and the beings who are destined "
"for error."

msgid "36f57c0b42de4555a94bfbe43099dc2a"
msgstr "They know the beings who are determined."

msgid "9fb743f334c74ed881c4ca9a68d50e5b"
msgstr ""
"Whether the tathāgatas teach the Dharma to them or not, those beings who "
"have causal capacity and excellent prior engagement, who understand through "
"mere outlines and whose intelligence is sharp, are destined to become "
"liberated."

msgid "558d781ece8a4296bef80ca0da7d7b8a"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas understand their causal capacity, and, in order to accelerate"
" their liberation, they teach them the Dharma accordingly."

msgid "12e133ae364945c2836a7d328083d2ea"
msgstr "“They know the beings who are undetermined."

msgid "624c28bb00a04ed3a87202a7912b239f"
msgstr ""
"If they meet an agreeable teaching and instruction, beings who are swayed by"
" conditions and characterized by having to mature will become liberated. But"
" if they do not, then they will not become liberated."

msgid "a4341738c78d4c3ea65d40f614827e6d"
msgstr "To them the tathāgatas deliver discourses on causes and conditions."

msgid "0216f5b121f44ee5ad708157e0ff8301"
msgstr ""
"In this way, once they have heard the Dharma from the tathāgatas, they apply"
" themselves accordingly and attain the result."

msgid "3e965b018b99483c86218594a3debf5e"
msgstr "It is for their sake that the blessed buddhas appear."

msgid "25e972d9d9d84331bdf39fccceb6a8de"
msgstr "“They know the beings who are destined for error."

msgid "ec5b26a234884e13acab2f84698fb8b2"
msgstr ""
"Whether they teach the Dharma to them or not, those beings who have not "
"purified themselves, who are narrow minded, foolish, and unreceptive, are "
"not destined for liberation."

msgid "6dddbeefbe0144788e0622688eca6795"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas are aware that they are not receptive and thus remain "
"equanimous toward them."

msgid "98129589eef34adba1eaa3eb6de0e3ff"
msgstr "It is for their sake that the bodhisattvas don their armor."

msgid "70c5e3f2db974b0eb5846b1e34ea8e81"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, the tathāgatas know the three paths of attachment."

msgid "72471ff3915c4a009e4788260617f037"
msgstr "What are the three?"

msgid "727afd0c0550411c9c5db30a5c3df674"
msgstr ""
"They are the path of attachment arising from attraction, the path of "
"attachment arising from clinging, and the path of attachment arising from "
"previous causes."

msgid "df25c80dba3549788d942a848a3df206"
msgstr "They know the three paths of aversion:"

msgid "137ed9c747894e3da0ea34e0680601c6"
msgstr ""
"the path of aversion arising from the cause of anger, the path of aversion "
"arising from unfulfilled wishes, and the path of aversion arising from "
"preexisting latent tendencies."

msgid "2ffa7af5ab754128bf2a5b2e879998b0"
msgstr "They know the three paths of delusion:"

msgid "c621cd51e8bd40a294369bdde582b0e6"
msgstr ""
"the path of delusion arising from the cause of ignorance, the path of "
"delusion arising from the cause of personalistic false views, and the path "
"of delusion arising from the cause of doubt."

msgid "058c78e8907c48e7a852edea4c6e9030"
msgstr "All these the tathāgatas know."

msgid "05e93667c90a417484138fc105c24408"
msgstr ""
"“Moreover, son of noble family, the tathāgatas know the difficult paths that"
" swiftly lead to the superknowledges for those with sharp faculties and the "
"difficult paths that slowly lead to the superknowledges for those with dull "
"faculties."

msgid "ece7093485b847509bca8175eb61d65f"
msgstr ""
"They know the easy paths that swiftly lead to the superknowledges for those "
"with sharp faculties and the difficult paths that swiftly lead to the "
"superknowledges for those with dull faculties."

msgid "cc2b82afeb6a4bed8519522fa3434b73"
msgstr ""
"They know the paths that very slowly lead to the superknowledges because of "
"beings’ loss of focus and the slower paths that may nonetheless swiftly lead"
" to the superknowledges because their continuities are uninterrupted."

msgid "1f13e70be38a4ddc8f39fe95007e71f4"
msgstr ""
"They know the swift paths that may nonetheless lead slowly to the "
"superknowledges on account of falling short of final relief and the slow "
"paths that nonetheless lead swiftly to the superknowledges on account of one"
" not being attached to such paths."

msgid "87d62005d3df426a8773c9f83310982e"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgatas know that there are paths where it is not the power of "
"meditation but the power of discrimination that is brought to perfection."

msgid "fae1e8299d5d4b268d561db142970a80"
msgstr ""
"They know that there are paths where it is not the power of discrimination "
"but the power of meditation that is brought to perfection."

msgid "4a70e48d9ba447b5ad538d63c7e1b107"
msgstr ""
"They know that there are paths where neither the power of meditation nor the"
" power of discrimination is brought to perfection."

msgid "3d88205185804e4f8668adf1f0707d13"
msgstr ""
"They know that there are paths where both the power of discrimination and "
"the power of meditation are brought to perfection."

msgid "4be35a4b4dcd4c5a97a77350cad1b0c9"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgatas know that there are paths with excellent intention but "
"without excellent application."

msgid "55b0cce2f9534b748d8788d63521ca1b"
msgstr ""
"They know that there are paths without excellent intention but with "
"excellent application."

msgid "4e3fefce810c42d38fb8f83e554775d3"
msgstr ""
"They know that there are paths without excellent intention or application. "
"They know that there are paths with both excellent intention and "
"application."

msgid "5534b04d889d4604b4c25ca261a76bb4"
msgstr ""
"“There are paths where it is neither the speech nor the mind but the body "
"that is purified."

msgid "b3d5a4b86612454c9703ea3a3081a90b"
msgstr ""
"There are paths where it is neither the body nor the mind but the speech "
"that is purified."

msgid "fd73cd5ca6824bf595362a9151fa7bbd"
msgstr "There are paths where the body, speech, and mind are all purified."

msgid "268a41e926914c4faa14283497e5fe48"
msgstr ""
"There are paths where neither the body nor the speech nor the mind are "
"purified."

msgid "51dcf4994ce84f448f3dd16376762255"
msgstr ""
"“In this way, the vision of a tathāgata’s wisdom enters, without "
"obstruction, the full extent of the paths that arise from the causes of the "
"engagements of all sentient beings and from the causes of error."

msgid "34060eb464434032b2a62716ea85b6d8"
msgstr "This is the sixth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "5c6e89e8597e4383b74ee389800f0021"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "e60c1316fdf443b680a6da8681a981e2"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The sugatas know all the paths and the beings who are destined and have "
"the cause."

msgid "1324446c0d1a405f97f571a465d36ed3"
msgstr ""
"These teachers know the endless kinds of afflictive elements of those "
"characterized as undetermined and as having to mature, Those who are "
"unreceptive and harbor wrong views, and those beset by three kinds of "
"attachment, three kinds of aversion, and the associated ignorance, As well "
"as the causes and conditions for such paths."

msgid "02c8748d98564c89848aa8b8f5d486a0"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The protectors of the world understand the paths that are difficult for "
"the sharp ones and at the same time slow for those of feeble capacity, And "
"the paths that are easy for the sharp ones and at the same time slow for the"
" others."

msgid "81149f0ab6b9446daececc02c9a16e54"
msgstr ""
"there are paths that are slow for the slow witted and at the same time slow "
"for the sharp and pure ones."

msgid "ad39b115079c4c61b3d4534d333ec312"
msgstr ""
"There are paths that are swift for the slow ones and at the same time very "
"swift for those not attached to them."

msgid "36a2b2cd6e9c42e9b846b7027e875ca9"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘There are paths of meditation that generate discrimination and those that"
" do not."

msgid "bebe7e4a72ef4a7fbda4fb06d02629db"
msgstr ""
"There are those that generate meditation and those that generate both due to"
" having outstanding application."

msgid "9a84d45a71364e4c9d0f52772797aa4e"
msgstr ""
"There are paths that purify intention but not application, And there are the"
" paths that engage in both."

msgid "2aea403965f74fc0be7759c3742cd1fd"
msgstr "The buddhas, the all-seeing great beings, know that"

msgid "306e2e6aee144c3fb15fd98d8c3254ce"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘There are paths that purify the body but not the speech or the mind,"

msgid "cc60efe2d71248b6942635fad28f87ca"
msgstr "Some that purify speech and the body but never the mind,"

msgid "a2b7f6dae6f243468703cb01cdfd1bc4"
msgstr "And some that purify the mind but never speech."

msgid "a6200665457545e2b43018cd4e3ce6e2"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘There are some that purify speech and the mind but never the body, And "
"some that purify both body and mind."

msgid "5eac9c37cd8940fe895de48ab165b263"
msgstr "As for how they engage or refrain,"

msgid "469422d094e64d02bf7bcf2e633f7f19"
msgstr ""
"This knowledge born of seeing wisdom and the mind is the sixth outstanding "
"sugata activity.’"

msgid "723c2ac3d11d4e86a0dba17dee215ffa"
msgstr ""
" “Moreover, son of noble family, the tathāgatas know in accordance with "
"reality the process of pollution, purification, and emergence through "
"concentration, liberation, absorption, and meditation."

msgid "ec49186b2e134f6caf84689cfdfc8c43"
msgstr "You may ask, how do they know it?"

msgid "1a5d2d6fb3b84042930a8b3ba8c13998"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas know the causes and conditions for the arising of sentient "
"beings’ pollution."

msgid "106826f37b3b4be1adf9df1d6afae666"
msgstr ""
"They know the causes and conditions for sentient beings’ purification."

msgid "bc7d0e3b9aab44859bab386382762005"
msgstr "What are causes? What are conditions?"

msgid "f7707f35601c437088595696a422eac9"
msgstr "The cause of sentient beings’ pollution is improper mental activity."

msgid "2a3736cb4e10439e894e7fef47a27e32"
msgstr "The condition for sentient beings’ pollution is ignorance."

msgid "dc53f14b2bdf4cb0b57024f46b7b2296"
msgstr "Ignorance is a cause and formations are conditions."

msgid "9d7a4457f97242b3842edf50d4761229"
msgstr "The formations are causes and consciousness is a condition."

msgid "9519ea46a624495bb80ddb43d6a288ea"
msgstr "Consciousness is a cause and name and form are conditions."

msgid "6c187c6fde5c41dda7c4b4fcd9a4787d"
msgstr "Name and form are causes and the six sense fields are conditions."

msgid "0540a2cfa4184f24a13c64acbff63e54"
msgstr "The six sense fields are causes and contact is a condition."

msgid "942d34c42cf44066bd78ce697fef5a33"
msgstr "Contact is a cause and sensation is a condition."

msgid "f474b48dcd5d433b8940220f4aa965e6"
msgstr "Sensation is a cause and craving is a condition."

msgid "60d2daa45207478696c8418a7e91fb80"
msgstr "Craving is a cause and appropriation is a condition."

msgid "7446a8fe63f84208aa77d5344c53cb77"
msgstr "Appropriation is a cause and becoming is a condition."

msgid "356c914a70154183b3fee65736c5bc8e"
msgstr "Becoming is a cause and birth is a condition."

msgid "04a2e7bca70148b4bea1e13c16cd22bc"
msgstr "Birth is a cause and old age and death are conditions."

msgid "d0d275fd475e45c2be6493a7d1f9b851"
msgstr "Old age and death are causes and afflictive emotions are conditions."

msgid "14dfb7310f1b462bbc43977478db77a5"
msgstr "Afflictive emotions are causes and actions are conditions."

msgid "73baeb2a327548f294337f7fc5f36b85"
msgstr "Views are causes and craving is a condition."

msgid "cc42a335ccde45f4bb68d84a603d54b3"
msgstr "Latent tendencies are causes and their activations are conditions."

msgid "ee1feb970e0943ea8c9c9a35796e8a44"
msgstr "These are the causes and conditions of beings’ pollution."

msgid "a9baf07f11014f56b44a1d50f67392a5"
msgstr ""
"“What are the causes and conditions for sentient beings’ purification?"

msgid "97fd6f4a1a5a4fc1a806683c9c4de3b5"
msgstr ""
"There are two causes or two conditions for sentient beings’ purification."

msgid "3e0555331158401c8511a4b83d71e50f"
msgstr "What are these two?"

msgid "5dcd7af3675045df91be9b6bd3730739"
msgstr ""
"Another’s words to be followed and one’s own correct mental activity form a "
"pair."

msgid "20ee15632de34aeab18b62aa7ff8066b"
msgstr ""
"One-pointed tranquil abiding and skill in special insight also form a pair "
"of causes or conditions."

msgid "0f16b1e940814ebdba08bfccd9b29d24"
msgstr ""
"The same applies as well as to knowing that there is no coming and knowing "
"that there is no going, realizing nonorigination and reaching certainty, "
"actualizing liberation through virtuous conduct and knowledge, cultivating "
"the gates to liberation and knowing what is naturally liberated, and knowing"
" contamination and knowing nonorigination."

msgid "68b8eef013da45d7a3255beb7c191f41"
msgstr ""
"Finally, the pair consisting of realizing the truth and attaining the truth "
"is a pair of causes or conditions for beings’ purification."

msgid "9551df704df0443f83d6b9101c7181da"
msgstr "All these the tathāgatas know."

msgid "b609141600444293882ee0029d7dfe0a"
msgstr ""
"“Moreover, son of noble family, the perceptions of pollution are "
"immeasurable, and the perceptions of their purification are equally "
"immeasurable."

msgid "db142c8bd1a94df597b43e6ad56cf624"
msgstr ""
"By discriminating in accordance with reality, the perceptions of pollution "
"are replaced by those of their purification."

msgid "1c41e5a72af3463198a9bea1531a54c6"
msgstr ""
"But by grasping with excessive pride, the perceptions of purification may be"
" replaced by those of pollution."

msgid "aaa5f58253604686bb46e84ed9649f9a"
msgstr ""
"Thus, through nonsequential enumerations, one enters the wisdom of the "
"tathāgatas."

msgid "de995753c0e34f48ae6e66ec2cc14ad8"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, endowed with such wisdom, the tathāgatas are detached "
"from desires and sinful nonvirtuous factors, possess applied and sustained "
"thought, and are joyful and blissful through detachment."

msgid "d56b5048961a4d878cfc75d4f77c0b26"
msgstr ""
"Attaining the first concentration, the tathāgatas emerge from cessation."

msgid "7adda9bf2646493496d5a491f8eb833a"
msgstr "Attaining cessation, they emerge from the first concentration."

msgid "2553b5f6634148d4ab38417c2db9016b"
msgstr ""
"They have attainments that follow the sequence of the eight liberations and "
"attainments that do not."

msgid "76c2aec14feb4b5283659b601b034580"
msgstr "They also have attainments in a nonsequential order."

msgid "56a65076e15749fa9042be7e2c562fe2"
msgstr ""
"Although absorption is revealed as attainment and attainment is revealed as "
"absorption, there is no blending at all within the tathāgatas’ absorption."

msgid "9edcbd9ba4dc48deb0a8cba8bb78ff92"
msgstr ""
"For them there is no attainment in absorption in terms of objective "
"reference points."

msgid "edc08091646947d39420c2f9efba5e24"
msgstr "A single tathāgata absorption accomplishes all absorptions."

msgid "a19b062e019b46cbbb07dff9cd673a32"
msgstr ""
"Without emerging from a single absorption, the tathāgatas attain all "
"absorptions, but for them there is no fluctuation from one mental moment to "
"another."

msgid "ab0f9c0a50954904af93b149c67c73b9"
msgstr "For the tathāgatas, a mind outside of equipoise does not exist."

msgid "c36f48225d8048d8829147c9cf32b66f"
msgstr "No one is able to witness a tathāgata absorption."

msgid "d25626c6c8c84095bd6dd6839c469c7f"
msgstr ""
"A śrāvaka absorption is surpassed by a pratyekabuddha absorption. This is in"
" turn surpassed by the bodhisattva absorption, which is in turn surpassed by"
" the tathāgata absorption, which is unsurpassed."

msgid "30a3cb9251464e62940fd42da9c4f722"
msgstr "Due to that the tathāgata wisdom penetrates unchallenged."

msgid "20f0a139a57441f38684fce892b37689"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgatas know the instructions and guidance by which śrāvakas "
"cultivate their meditative absorptions."

msgid "b755e54a99fa4a50b50de14df12f21e7"
msgstr ""
"Likewise, they know those by which pratyekabuddhas and bodhisattvas "
"cultivate theirs."

msgid "04753562879b4f7e9405e09bf991d275"
msgstr "Understanding these, they instruct and guide beings accordingly."

msgid "451fed23613a4f11b6d10a9c74393e06"
msgstr "This is the seventh tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "8ee2cea13c914112a8891e6a74f14619"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "e0578e1e6adc4665ba84d93d91205854"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Through their naturally occurring wisdom, The victors know all the causes"
" and conditions for beings’ pollution."

msgid "baeb65de651d42fe92c856f283dc06ef"
msgstr ""
"Likewise, the Dharma lords know the causes and conditions Of purification "
"engendered by striving."

msgid "da25133ac79946b7a288aa7bd8930135"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The cause is what is improper, and the condition is ignorance. The cause "
"is ignorance, and the condition is the formations."

msgid "54cfb8c039c745aaaf66b5fa11bfa8db"
msgstr ""
"Consciousness, name and form, and the six sense faculties Are all causes and"
" conditions for wandering through the stages of existence."

msgid "98393e54272742ca8c894d801d0deb0a"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘It is taught that afflictive emotions are causes and actions are "
"conditions,"

msgid "4827e9bc7d5e4ecdb7bef1d68dc43c96"
msgstr "Views are causes and craving the condition."

msgid "0644d5ca032049019a9a1b88f52bbe2f"
msgstr "Entanglements and their latent tendencies are causes for this."

msgid "b8e9920fe92747bb90d95e2e184ab6d3"
msgstr "People subject to these causes are conditioned like that."

msgid "e8a3ce93293e452082eabaea8fcf096e"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘There are different pairs of causes or conditions for beings’ "
"purification."

msgid "878922dac48e4cf7bb4f60b41f4f6138"
msgstr ""
"Hearing the agreeable sound of the Dharma from another and, having heard it,"
" Correctly realizing phenomena to be inherently empty"

msgid "f73d5359cc8b4c0fabe8af909be608b0"
msgstr "Liberates them from the ocean of existence."

msgid "84346fe6b9d9411891295088ef1fc064"
msgstr "“ ‘Uniting tranquil abiding and special insight,"

msgid "59d48d47777b4ebfa37cccca0e015a28"
msgstr "Meditating without any coming or going,"

msgid "bddbacbf4a8f40ffa1a64453d3ca9d83"
msgstr "Where there is no birth, no death, transference, or thought,"

msgid "e475e708bcc142e09389748ff13c0636"
msgstr "And reaching the immaculate, one becomes purified."

msgid "12e76a4534e7479ba4d2c90cd45c4f79"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Endowed with virtuous conduct and threefold knowledge, there is "
"relaxation."

msgid "18c01e57db734848be48f581688eb5fe"
msgstr "Becoming heedful, one cultivates the three gates of liberation."

msgid "3ccfd3a47e2642fd977f7bc26e0473a9"
msgstr "One knows depletion and nonorigination and attains the truth."

msgid "b4aac5f34c7c4798b34548e4869d63b8"
msgstr ""
"These are the causes and conditions that direct one onto the path of "
"purification."

msgid "ce13feb512714602b484df2b3e9cdef5"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Attaining the first concentration, The victors reach cessation and emerge"
" accordingly with mindfulness."

msgid "81fe12c2eea641739e814bc575a34b1c"
msgstr ""
"The Dharma kings attain the eight liberations In sequence, out of sequence, "
"and in nonsequential order."

msgid "6e3cfcf182e3487ca53677eb7c41cb11"
msgstr "“ ‘The incomparable abide in a state of equality,"

msgid "f9b9ad9458d4465b982a70b7fbbfdb84"
msgstr "Displaying countless absorptions from a single absorption."

msgid "3b71f0a6bcf84a3fb882beee9231c1e3"
msgstr ""
"Their minds are not mixed up in this, and they have no thoughts about "
"phenomena."

msgid "e97d98971963455c856881f7290c41e2"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, for the victors, their minds are never not in meditative "
"equipoise."

msgid "5aa6967dd09b4dd5bf7726a501ec8c84"
msgstr ""
"All the millions of śrāvaka and pratyekabuddha absorptions And the "
"absorptions of bodhisattvas."

msgid "c7504da7f90b4c5a8f63a0f25f57a31b"
msgstr "“ ‘A sugata’s absorption surpasses"

msgid "6c54eee7e13345458f5567bb7dde8aef"
msgstr ""
"Knowing and being skilled in their instructions is the activity of the "
"sugatas.’"

msgid "dd9f0ea10eaf4780a3616e5c00cdfaf3"
msgstr ""
" “Moreover, son of noble family, the tathāgatas can recollect their own and "
"other beings’ and other individuals’ various former existences."

msgid "4c2db763ea7b4359bc25c59ec5dc4e87"
msgstr ""
"They can recollect one or two, three or four, five or ten, twenty, thirty, "
"forty, or fifty previous births."

msgid "cdee73a5046745d8b0aed48d335df6ab"
msgstr ""
"They can recollect one hundred or one thousand, one hundred thousand, or "
"billions of births."

msgid "42c51c6dc84c4783abcab31e5a90c643"
msgstr ""
"They can recollect the eon of world destruction, the eon of world formation,"
" and the eon of both destruction and formation."

msgid "fb374b889d8a4872b5150ad65b1cb4cc"
msgstr ""
"They can recollect many eons of destruction, many eons of formation, or many"
" eons of destruction and formation."

msgid "a53b118bc8bd41c482a533777559bd87"
msgstr "“ ‘These beings went by this or that name."

msgid "a4fb530f791540c59d5027f517d336f6"
msgstr ""
"I was born there with that name, in that clan, in that family lineage, "
"eating that food, with that complexion and that shape."

msgid "7b74d366132646b4a9ff572a4e704644"
msgstr ""
"I lived there during that period and experienced those joys and those "
"sorrows."

msgid "0877c8b2d30a4bb9a1ebf3b69c64606f"
msgstr ""
"Then, after I died and transmigrated from there, I was reborn as another "
"being."

msgid "065a15ccff7c46fa823ca65bf6976dc1"
msgstr ""
"Then, after I died and transmigrated from there, I was born here in this "
"form, in this area, from this region.’"

msgid "4d91be8a415e434aa3ccc5ff1614a282"
msgstr ""
"Thus they recollect their own and other beings’ various former existences."

msgid "bc77e79439324343a72feee8e155f0f2"
msgstr "“They recollect the former existences of a being."

msgid "f76775bb359d455190ba38d513cfb8b6"
msgstr ""
"How and through which prior causes a given being was born—the tathāgatas "
"know such prior causes."

msgid "9e9cb18a02a74d62b48878f89ac1aecb"
msgstr "Knowing these, they teach the Dharma accordingly."

msgid "b65f067cdfbb43d2aaa469ddf11cfb6b"
msgstr "“The tathāgatas know the movements of the minds of all past beings."

msgid "33667035fb6d471fb69e3146ff19e058"
msgstr ""
"They know that following a given objective reference, there arises a mind "
"having such an objective reference, that it has arisen due to the given "
"objective reference, and that it ceases when this objective reference is "
"incomplete."

msgid "5efb2ab9680c493cabd75824c59dda4f"
msgstr ""
"The mind of a single being thus exists as an ongoing continuum, in which a "
"given mind occurs following another. Even if one were to speak for as many "
"eons as there are grains of sand in the river Ganges, it would be difficult "
"to explain this with words."

msgid "97343b8ea9a34daea5ea9b40a332e2bb"
msgstr ""
"“In this way, the tathāgatas know the ongoing continuums of the individual "
"minds of all sentient beings."

msgid "ff92b51d03bb445e93b8c988f321e14b"
msgstr ""
"Even if the tathāgatas were to explain this until the end of time on the "
"basis of rational analysis, their wisdom would not reach its limit."

msgid "fef6c3526d784fd996bb5002e27554f8"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgata knowledge that recollects previous existences is "
"inconceivable, unequaled, and immeasurable."

msgid "63992f76f47e42bda52eac3427a9c07b"
msgstr "Its scope is not easy to explain."

msgid "a39bdd1a331d4dacbca211780d0d13db"
msgstr ""
"“Having become buddhas, the supreme leaders, the tathāgatas remind beings,"

msgid "80db5e2357f54546b90d97b1fbdb76fa"
msgstr ""
"‘Hey sentient beings! Roots of virtue generate either buddhahood, "
"śrāvakahood, or pratyekabuddhahood!"

msgid "0abc56b1d9af465a8359623128c1a061"
msgstr "Remember that! Remember!’"

msgid "1138834067064777ad11f5498350e3e7"
msgstr ""
"In this way, through the power of the buddhas, they also become mindful."

msgid "40e820ff136645ed868a2ddbd49e167b"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgatas teach them the Dharma in such a way that on account of the "
"roots of virtue they observe in those beings, they will ensure that, "
"whichever vehicle these beings take, they do not turn back from liberation."

msgid "1e874bb1b97348d89a4560e439929e9f"
msgstr "This is the eighth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "74b87ff988fc43eea83948739358ee2c"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "3f4746e0ed0d4240b5b0ba4e9560fd1a"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The lamps of the world recollect without obstruction Countlessly many "
"past existences— Their own and others’—"

msgid "f64ec505063d4630b74311b53994e08d"
msgstr "Like Indian gooseberries resting in the palm of one’s hand."

msgid "cb55a7b9a18c4a97a1a1e5437c47d6d3"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Migrating through the transference of death From a lifetime with a "
"certain name, clan, and complexion, with certain thoughts, And having "
"reappeared as another being through a given cause, They teach the Dharma "
"with knowledge of this temporal process."

msgid "50b32e6b7f9a474da7ef50e0604567cf"
msgstr ""
"All about the minds of transmigrators and the factors arising from the mind,"
" The past, endless and unimpeded, And what gives rise to any given state of "
"mind."

msgid "c7bf199a4e524752abc2e901ae86a252"
msgstr "“ ‘The victors know with their great wisdom"

msgid "62fa12b8a4634433a77005e30a57a1e1"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The sugatas understand What constitute the prior and earlier mind states "
"of a single being. Even if they were to explain them for as many eons As "
"there are grains of sand in the river Ganges, there would be no end to it."

msgid "f5ab71fd64004947bb7207d6322ed22d"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Even if they taught The countlessly many prior activities forever, Their "
"unequaled wisdom would not be exhausted."

msgid "34774b9fec4b46d4b341d48337a11704"
msgstr "That is what the ocean of sugata wisdom is like."

msgid "96d7592cd6544ecfaea84f1d7631557f"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Those beings of virtuous intent Who have shown respect to the victors in "
"the past"

msgid "31037878658e469aaed1086eadb22616"
msgstr ""
"Are made mindful of their previous virtue By the strength of the buddhas’ "
"miraculous power."

msgid "ad22d2a259f54d2caf4be519d7a35038"
msgstr "“ ‘Mindful of their previous virtue Due to the power of the buddhas,"

msgid "c2686de7420c4ff49b88cb2ef895ea19"
msgstr ""
"And mindfully abiding in the three vehicles, They do not turn away from the "
"virtuous path of liberation."

msgid "595e019be846420f8e1abd52a85511f2"
msgstr ""
"Of the limitless sugatas who appeared in the past. “ ‘No sentient being can "
"conceive"

msgid "d37ca6e3151d466ca1502f6faa8a18a9"
msgstr ""
"The endless taming of sentient beings Is the eighth activity of great "
"beings.’"

msgid "9addd832fee84ddfa52dae63afee2507"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, with their pure divine vision, which surpasses that "
"of humans, the tathāgatas observe beings dying, transmigrating, and taking "
"birth. They observe their migrations into happy or sad destinies, their "
"goodness or wickedness, their beautiful or ugly complexions."

msgid "768c9c6b0c9c431a848e260fd6177817"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Alas! Regarding those sentient beings who have acted badly either "
"physically, verbally, or mentally, who have denigrated the nobles ones, and "
"who have held wrong views, once their bodies fail and they die they will be "
"born as hell beings, falling into lower realms and miserable destinies "
"because they took up actions based on their wrong views."

msgid "f03ca6ab0ae645f980915ab618d5ec44"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Regarding those sentient beings who have acted virtuously either "
"physically, verbally, or mentally, who have not denigrated the noble ones, "
"and who have held correct views, once their bodies fail and they die they "
"will be born among gods in the higher realms and blissful destinies because "
"they took up correct views.’"

msgid "faa562ae33d645c290e5c4bb4a3d9d7c"
msgstr "Thus tathāgatas know how beings migrate due to actions."

msgid "ec5ca5bd1ad74211995b00053552faf5"
msgstr "“The divine tathāgata vision is like this:"

msgid "5ecd32a46ed64c9a87862230fee80220"
msgstr ""
"It observes the destruction and formation of the worlds of the ten "
"directions, all those that appear as fields in the limitless, innumerable, "
"and incalculable buddhafields reaching to the end of space, the limitless "
"realm of phenomena."

msgid "a6d4edbf1b964123933ba736c267fb15"
msgstr ""
"It observes the death, transmigration, and rebirth of all those beings who "
"appear and the death, conception, and rebirth of all those bodhisattvas who "
"appear."

msgid "76705c330b334b3e83358d42f8a7fa7a"
msgstr ""
"It observes the buddhas who appear attaining complete and perfect "
"buddhahood, turning the wheel of Dharma, relinquishing the physical body, "
"and entering into parinirvāṇa."

msgid "1adee21821f6422eb255e63a3278aa8b"
msgstr ""
"It observes the śrāvakas who appear becoming free and entering parinirvāṇa."

msgid "78cd7b928fd049259d1773cb7b29892f"
msgstr ""
"And it observes the pratyekabuddhas who appear displaying miracles and "
"purifying gifts."

msgid "8ffad14f75b049329f3dafe6fedf88aa"
msgstr ""
"“Beings who do not appear and who are invisible for the five non-Buddhist "
"superknowledges, for śrāvakas, for pratyekabuddhas, and for "
"bodhisattvas—even they are visible to the divine tathāgata vision."

msgid "632d73ac1b6f441282863bc0d672b35a"
msgstr ""
"“Furthermore, those beings who are invisible in Jambudvīpa are visible to "
"the tathāgatas. The gods and humans of the world realms of the vast "
"trichiliocosm do not see them."

msgid "a6b2360380864d24a9c6d2e854124a88"
msgstr "The realms of such invisible beings are limitless."

msgid "89a8e5ce00054694ae4807ddf79d3f77"
msgstr ""
"“The divine tathāgata vision scans the realms of beings in all buddhafields,"
" asking, ‘Who are the beings to be tamed by the buddhas?’"

msgid "5ed810b3e4ef40228b142d03136b7e02"
msgstr ""
"For as many kinds of beings to be tamed by the buddhas as exist, that many "
"tathāgatas abide in their presence. Even as they tame these beings, other "
"beings remain unaware of this."

msgid "a69cde23d7dd416db9cacb81d3febc56"
msgstr "This is the ninth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "d9addb472d9540f3a5a6c79e14ed11cd"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "25a69cc420d54874ac3445caa6d5953f"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The divine vision of tathāgatas is unstained and luminous, Purified, "
"limitless, meritorious, and splendid."

msgid "7055d9954991444d9d953dec95b1ab8f"
msgstr ""
"It beholds the attributes throughout all the fields of the ten directions—"

msgid "4024a3524fe0479f9554a94b706f1f70"
msgstr "All that appears, will appear, and has appeared."

msgid "fcece24c8e4f49eeb611b0c94f84b0bd"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘There the victors observe beings—whether they have form or not, Whether "
"they exist in happy or miserable destinies, whether they are excellent, "
"average, or inferior, And whether they are evildoers migrating toward the "
"miserable existences Or the meritorious and karmically fortunate in the "
"higher realms."

msgid "4a40a876f64a476d87afd9e4f8339855"
msgstr ""
"Bodhisattvas engaged in their conduct in all the fields, Entering the womb, "
"appearing, proceeding toward the tree of awakening, And taming Māra while "
"seated in front of the tree of awakening."

msgid "4ba1f3c430bd4c2ead3504657305afb2"
msgstr "“ ‘The divine vision of the all-seeing buddhas beholds"

msgid "f02e59903eda4048895ea038f94c8692"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The victors observe buddhas who are Dharma kings, who awaken to supreme "
"awakening, Who turn the wheel of the Dharma, and who liberate gods and "
"humans, Discarding the physical form of a victor after performing supreme "
"buddha deeds And demonstrating nirvāṇa."

msgid "598a12f593544cefb8ddde0486be8d0b"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The victors observe those who hear the guiding Dharma and apply "
"themselves correctly, Becoming noble, cool, and free of illness and reaching"
" a state of peace; Hearing the Dharma, they think, “I will also cross the "
"ocean of existence And arrive at the state of transcendent bliss.”"

msgid "5c7a7efd8e4041698838b754697245af"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The tathāgatas’ pure and unstained divine vision Observes all beings "
"present in very subtle bodies As well as the endless masses of beings "
"invisible to the divine vision Of guhyakas, śrāvakas, pratyekabuddhas, and "
"bodhisattvas."

msgid "f53bb882f9e24fd7aa70e696df595526"
msgstr "“ ‘The victors observe the subtle realms of beings in Jambudvīpa,"

msgid "b36f692d4897446ba9e7318437950f61"
msgstr ""
"Those whom the various beings, god or human, in the great many "
"trichiliocosms do not see."

msgid "757c3fde4b274d6fbec5885fa805a3bb"
msgstr ""
"They know the endless cycling of the mass of beings through vast destinies, "
"Yet beings do not have any conception of their all-encompassing vision."

msgid "6d857644436f4ea3b193fed26d15a437"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Even though the world protectors teach the supreme Dharma Before those "
"tathāgatas’ trainees who have sharp faculties, Beings in other crowds do not"
" see the tathāgatas at all."

msgid "607f1db3cb9d4279a67b07cde04a585e"
msgstr "This is the activity of the power of the guides’ divine vision.’"

msgid "8e20172dfc654cca8872f7d134655743"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas have accomplished perfection. Through "
"their own superknowledge they have actualized the nonexistence of "
"contaminants and the liberation of their minds: ‘Due to the depletion of all"
" contaminants, rebirth has come to an end. I have relied on pure conduct and"
" done what had to be done, and I will not know any other existence after "
"this one.’"

msgid "a3f56654aaa840e182e6c4a3a19c082b"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgata knowledge of the depletion of contaminants is pure, "
"stainless, completely pure, luminous, and destroys all karmic traces."

msgid "41a63b6f90a74f38ad52972a9c0db232"
msgstr ""
"The śrāvaka depletion of contaminants is limited and does not destroy the "
"karmic traces."

msgid "6627f971aaec43bab20aa3ed538cb556"
msgstr ""
"The pratyekabuddha depletion of contaminants is also limited and is lacking "
"in great compassion and courage."

msgid "935a61798dc74919af5ea07b65d17767"
msgstr "“The tathāgata depletion of contaminants is supreme in every respect."

msgid "3faa252dd992407c8cc77c6596d29116"
msgstr "It destroys all karmic traces."

msgid "205c486015c04ba188759f60a9bfebfe"
msgstr "It is sustained by great compassion."

msgid "e95e9b577c4546af87e86895ad4b9d95"
msgstr "It is not lacking in fearlessness or courage."

msgid "d9093a6a73da4a11b2a9840da3f958a5"
msgstr "It is unsurpassed in all worlds."

msgid "2dcf7723886b48bf8b448cd1394a5ccf"
msgstr "It consists of a single mental moment."

msgid "26d1b8a5feb7460594bed2e4d475519c"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "55b1711602bf4c158669ad55c0a378c4"
msgstr ""
"For the tathāgatas, there are no karmic traces of actions, afflictive "
"emotions, or deluded conduct."

msgid "fc96605fc37749b0a22c351eb1a6969c"
msgstr ""
"To illustrate, since space is pure by nature, it is impossible for dust "
"particles and smoke to coexist with it."

msgid "fdb81a5b33f14b2dade18e9a5f4cac48"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, it is impossible for the tathāgata knowledge of the "
"depletion of contaminants to coexist with the karmic traces of actions or "
"afflictive emotions."

msgid "f0e8a6b903b6411e822b80605bac9e1e"
msgstr ""
"Thus, as soon as the knowledge of the depletion of contaminants is present, "
"they teach the Dharma to afflicted and grasping sentient beings so that they"
" in turn will give up their grasping, and so that their defilements will be "
"depleted:"

msgid "e4432f5fe9334649877065caf16e7cdc"
msgstr ""
"‘Alas, you sentient beings who come to be through unreal conceptualization, "
"you should understand contaminants and grasping in accordance with reality!’"

msgid "a5b00348eebe4b4a9b83acb3f21bb701"
msgstr ""
"In this manner, the tathāgatas make them know in accordance with reality "
"that contaminants are not real."

msgid "0740334aad224055b7bb5d0587df2e80"
msgstr "And having known that, they do not cling to any phenomenon."

msgid "e5957b1bab974e88b80fdec6684b80c1"
msgstr "Due to their lack of clinging, they pass completely beyond sorrow."

msgid "e1fa485bdf304108ad12a47565ece3d6"
msgstr ""
"In this way, they teach the Dharma through well-conceived illustrations."

msgid "fe69e9d11e7f49dfac5ba7e771dc245b"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, this is the tenth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "fb35e76f2cda4c9e9d3b14cae1cec490"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "64b0ea1f8975450f991556eacd674394"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The guides’ knowledge of the depletion of contaminants Is exceedingly "
"vast, unobscured, and limitless."

msgid "f3d5ab22d4ed4664adb00459e19773b2"
msgstr ""
"Through the strength of the ten strengths, The peace of supreme awakening is"
" realized and fully discerned."

msgid "a6e79706921045f3bae5b6b4ea0d2b10"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The śrāvakas’ knowledge of the depletion of contaminants Does not destroy"
" karmic traces and is limited."

msgid "06ad90bd04354ecc9febbdf1dee8109c"
msgstr ""
"But the knowledge of the supreme guides, excellent among humans, Destroys "
"karmic traces and is unlimited."

msgid "2f73aa779d464fecb35330afa5e1c0db"
msgstr "“ ‘Likewise, for pratyekabuddhas who reach their awakening"

msgid "5e0a27ed38b44dc0b3a01250981cae18"
msgstr "With no great compassion or courage,"

msgid "297de04dcb644a059427af2d61ddbfa5"
msgstr "Once their contaminants have been completely depleted,"

msgid "1c80ffd68ae142fb95382c4f0106b4fa"
msgstr "Their great compassion and courage will also be limitless."

msgid "d708aa7fb6cb4a9fa0de3beceba3bb31"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Once the buddha knowledge of the depletion of contaminants is present, "
"They come to know that the contaminants of beings are unreal."

msgid "a002597a219e4d2f90b4d20e85ef1a97"
msgstr ""
"By not knowing this crucial point, Those sentient beings get it all wrong."

msgid "cc5c1e21b6aa4dc7a0cb91edaadf1db7"
msgstr "“ ‘The victors engendered inexhaustible compassion toward them,"

msgid "310da40671a34ad2802f4eea662159d8"
msgstr "Teaching that phenomena are impermanent, empty, and selfless:"

msgid "ac7d37ba4fba409da790dd09d24a1fb2"
msgstr "“Understand these phenomena to be unreal and illusory"

msgid "1c6493e9c53e40eaae984e496236f177"
msgstr "And truly attain supreme peace!”"

msgid "a130254e2c9345d1be1c31bdb9e8a089"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Even though there are no creatures, Individuals, human beings, humankind,"
" or agents of actions, All these beings cling to what is completely wrong—"

msgid "536538626cc14538bdaa98304b3be4b9"
msgstr "Thus the teachers who engender compassion explain liberation."

msgid "b5730118db66402dbb592108a812107d"
msgstr "“ ‘The sugatas never grow weary."

msgid "d13665f6fae14a76bc9a0fb2ad323fb8"
msgstr "Knowing reality, they are never wrong."

msgid "acbbdc3fea2f4645ab1440c5de9d28a7"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, the victors are always diligently engaged, Teaching the Dharma to"
" benefit beings."

msgid "0ca5b2b779b644ebae33d16b46a999ec"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Subduing opponents completely Is an action in line with the victory of "
"possessing the ten strengths."

msgid "e68f592b806949e1ba753c2886a9b8fb"
msgstr ""
"Dwelling in the power of possessing the ten strengths, They fully turn the "
"incomparable noble wheel.’"

msgid "d5b204597baa49db82ff60dce5708265"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas dwell in the tathāgatas’ four types of"
" fearlessness."

msgid "4f5f677b602140968d1653f64b7b05cb"
msgstr ""
"No one in the world with its gods can reasonably reprove the tathāgatas, "
"saying, ‘You have not become completely and perfectly awakened regarding "
"phenomena,’ in response to their proclamation, ‘We perform awakened deeds "
"and have become completely and perfectly awakened.’"

msgid "fa6c5658b14e436cae84cec776acf031"
msgstr ""
"“Why is it that tathāgatas declare that they are completely and perfectly "
"awakened?"

msgid "7c3d844331ec4aeb9d243a1351a83f7a"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas are completely and perfectly awakened to the fact that all "
"phenomena are equal."

msgid "d1cfccff3e4f464dba72137fe1fbd4a1"
msgstr ""
"They are completely and perfectly awakened to the fact that the phenomena of"
" ordinary people, those engaged in learning, those in a state of no more "
"learning, pratyekabuddhas, bodhisattvas, and buddhas are all equal."

msgid "a2122292f7394ddbbc91357f1c99410c"
msgstr ""
"They are completely and perfectly awakened to the fact that mundane, "
"supramundane, flawed, unflawed, contaminated, uncontaminated, conditioned, "
"and unconditioned phenomena are all equal."

msgid "eb33743a822947bdaf27944b8ddfdc6e"
msgstr "“How are they equal?"

msgid "1fb24c9f49f74fcf847efc43ee7e5ee4"
msgstr "In terms of the essential view, they are equal in their emptiness."

msgid "08204a56b0844448b3353bf81db8cc1b"
msgstr "In terms of the essential sign, they are equal in being signless."

msgid "60cd5b3df6884b7f80f3d0ad491fc424"
msgstr ""
"In terms of the essential nature of the three realms, they are equal in "
"being wishless."

msgid "4cec8a6172eb4034b4bf098d259df6a9"
msgstr ""
"In terms of the essential nature of birth, they are equal in being unborn."

msgid "5d77ab889ad444aaa12c6ca313bbc03e"
msgstr ""
"In terms of the essential nature of conditioning, they are equal being "
"without conditioning."

msgid "333393fd53224df995c213fc07a9341d"
msgstr ""
"In terms of the essential nature of origination, they are equal in being "
"without origination."

msgid "d64c24812c94495b8d9e3d46c75505e7"
msgstr ""
"In terms of the essential nature of the substratum consciousness, they are "
"equal in having no substratum consciousness."

msgid "256df3cc059246eeaafd00222eacfd93"
msgstr ""
"In terms of the essential nature of the three times, they are equal in "
"accordance with reality."

msgid "eb8612aa5a4e4b7a8967dff9f5b16ccd"
msgstr ""
"In terms of the essential nature of ignorance, becoming, and craving, they "
"are equal in being knowledge and liberation."

msgid "07a67116795b44a7ab561882ab012176"
msgstr ""
"In terms of the essential nature of saṃsāra, they are equal in being "
"nirvāṇa."

msgid "efb57b3eb6e54fee9b012725ed3bb3cb"
msgstr ""
"Thus, the tathāgatas are completely and perfectly awakened to the equality "
"of all phenomena, and that is why they declare, ‘We are completely and "
"perfectly awakened.’"

msgid "1356070d8aed42d68a1c27e1e03c5292"
msgstr ""
"“Just as the tathāgatas have become completely and perfectly awakened with "
"regard to those phenomena, in the same way they abide in great compassion."

msgid "c0f44b0edc134c22bbc71f0ab62319a3"
msgstr ""
"They teach other people and beings by means of various Dharmas, discourses, "
"and circumstances."

msgid "b15650a9cb0d4f70ad6a0128192a631d"
msgstr "Their Dharma arises for the sake of eliminating created suffering."

msgid "7fd0aa82294f411e95d54219f565433c"
msgstr ""
"“This tathāgata fearlessness overpowers and annuls allegations such as ‘They"
" say they are teachers when they are not’ and ‘They say they are completely "
"and perfectly awakened when they are not.’"

msgid "cdc42c346ae046279fbe16bd9e5269f2"
msgstr "This is the eleventh tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "bb5e544be3cb496a96e646d2e595eed6"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "6f247d0999504fdb8a5d97d49d8cacdf"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The spontaneously arisen ones Have realized all phenomena to be equal."

msgid "09af89b7d9314e11b4599c22765c1995"
msgstr "Therefore they are completely and perfectly awakened."

msgid "d0a81d436d0749bb8fe9136583ca94e3"
msgstr "The tathāgatas see equality."

msgid "7ce86fbdf9bf42ceb70bfc2180f3f88c"
msgstr "“ ‘The phenomena of ordinary people,"

msgid "dd2027f0972645ce8d41287f780778ef"
msgstr "The phenomena of those engaged in learning or no more learning,"

msgid "87f6c7b5a83643008c6ffeff6b926a4c"
msgstr "And the phenomena of pratyekabuddhas"

msgid "ed4d76810aa148819969ec276ab72442"
msgstr "Are all equal to the phenomena of buddhas."

msgid "15068eb79d6d4a3db59584ffb3ea9dfa"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The mundane and, likewise, The supramundane, As well as virtue and "
"nonvirtue, Are similar and equal to nirvāṇa."

msgid "8967c5142f644cfbbe926f5f42bf718e"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Empty, signless, Wishless, unborn, And unconditioned, They are all seen "
"to be equal."

msgid "e60328033c7e4f858033cfd596415e86"
msgstr "“ ‘Having realized those, They teach beings with compassion."

msgid "947b9feedbed4b4e86a01bf33444bf90"
msgstr "Therefore beings are liberated."

msgid "4af94040c8494bd7bbb4d677452c921b"
msgstr "This is the supreme activity of the capable ones.’"

msgid "8b00c27f11054269bc3fb2ee3f92fdb2"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, no one in the world with its gods can reasonably "
"reprove the tathāgatas, saying, ‘You have not eliminated those contaminants’"
" in response to their proclamation, ‘We have eliminated contaminants.’"

msgid "5f2369458df149978bf4d5c2996c1ef2"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgatas’ depletion of contaminants occurs in the following manner:"

msgid "466e8ed99e5f4ea29823b70dba80215b"
msgstr ""
"Since the minds of tathāgatas are freed from the contaminants of desire, "
"they have destroyed all karmic traces that partake of attachment."

msgid "1eb26bc6c56b41c8b14e7b74fb7f7dbf"
msgstr ""
"Since the minds of tathāgatas are freed from the contaminants of becoming, "
"they have destroyed all karmic traces that partake of anger."

msgid "bda7f08ba422454f849cef2066e8bca4"
msgstr ""
"Since the minds of tathāgatas are freed from the contaminant of ignorance, "
"they have destroyed all karmic traces that partake of delusion."

msgid "183b4a4d0a8541fda94af6ea9a1366cc"
msgstr ""
"Since the minds of tathāgatas are freed from the contaminants of views, they"
" have destroyed all karmic traces that partake of afflictive emotion."

msgid "bd09a338ab6b4350b7742ded4bc8c29b"
msgstr ""
"“Therefore, from a conventional worldly point of view, the tathāgatas are "
"said to have depleted the contaminants."

msgid "26aa407c5fe04c5388f4dc5bac4a13dc"
msgstr ""
"However, ultimately, from the perspective of the insight and wisdom of the "
"noble ones, phenomena that are to be known, abandoned, cultivated, or "
"realized are never established."

msgid "1e18c1281fc6485081e290eafb2b444f"
msgstr "“Why is that?"

msgid "7aebf1513b1747bf86f2dbe0401b0c19"
msgstr "The ‘depleted’ are never not depleted."

msgid "f01cc92215f549e0be16a58ae7918f01"
msgstr ""
"They are totally depleted, but they are not ‘depleted by means of an "
"antidote.’"

msgid "f3b9e30f29d142ddaed5f49ab00ba3a8"
msgstr "Their depletion accords with reality."

msgid "07a00c8adf7749c5b05b1a2c2ae0add8"
msgstr ""
"That depletion that accords with reality is devoid of anything depleted."

msgid "19e9a45557314863ab4e6df6b8161b4a"
msgstr ""
"That which is devoid of anything anywhere depleted is called unconditioned."

msgid "a5ff75e5dc664d5594423dab917dfe5b"
msgstr ""
"The unconditioned is unborn, does not endure, and does not deteriorate."

msgid "2886456d4dfb42198b12226aebfb6dfc"
msgstr ""
"“Therefore, whether tathāgatas appear or not, that which is the nature of "
"reality and the realm of phenomena prevails."

msgid "7b0ea09ab374415d92fb4d87ce6090ce"
msgstr ""
"Just as the realm of phenomena prevails, in the same way wisdom prevails "
"within it."

msgid "091ea83543e74a64bd96ee6d23f1a205"
msgstr ""
"Just as it is without engagement or withdrawal, wisdom prevails in the same "
"manner."

msgid "791c36210b8c4bd5ac95403f76f4b154"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgatas, who, in accordance with the way of the Dharma, do not "
"objectify the contaminants or their abandonment, are settled in great "
"compassion and teach the Dharma to sentient beings so that they may abandon "
"their contaminants."

msgid "d6664aaabb6141eab964dae2841a8173"
msgstr "This is the twelfth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "ac421dae2f4243f193fc5429c54fa5c8"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "1cac83e8386d4e868a768b28fa32432f"
msgstr "“ ‘The victors have abandoned the contaminants of desire,"

msgid "7b4ff97e77674c3f95bd758dad3771aa"
msgstr "Thus they have no further karmic traces of attachment."

msgid "c2c73e4d5fbc4ae98704d622793a37ca"
msgstr "The lords of humans are freed from all further becoming,"

msgid "9cb2263838cc4e64bffe93ede5573afd"
msgstr "Thus all faults without exception are cut off."

msgid "e9f596cbb16646edb6145e259abb7baf"
msgstr "“ ‘The sugatas are established in knowledge of all kinds,"

msgid "c72a33ac6d5d469b95d2cf3e2ca499e3"
msgstr "Thus they are free of any residual delusion."

msgid "afa49c1bf63f402e9c18d0e0924c7ba9"
msgstr "The lions among humans are free from any view,"

msgid "17402d20ebca4efa95b84e35536db3be"
msgstr ""
"Thus they are without any karmic traces that partake of afflictive emotions."

msgid "4466b704ab994409ae29868a041e6cc8"
msgstr "“ ‘In order that all attain the depletion of contaminants,"

msgid "b6beb2319dfd49a08851259a2fa41230"
msgstr "The victorious ones teach the Dharma at the conventional level."

msgid "8763edf63bcb4eaaba77adf5d24eb6d5"
msgstr "Phenomena that increase or are depleted"

msgid "dc8988d6ce0645218e68b511de07cb28"
msgstr "Do not exist ultimately."

msgid "42dec39537884e7498dfaf85d856dc6d"
msgstr "“ ‘For them, depletion is not depletion by means of an antidote,"

msgid "f38456e7973c4c398c510705ab720d57"
msgstr "Because there was already depletion before that depletion was taught."

msgid "7816755fd7ad440bb1b8106f8780ad69"
msgstr "That which is depleted is unconditioned"

msgid "b911c174c9774dff8e2259ab91e2bac5"
msgstr ""
"And is therefore not something that possesses the three characteristics."

msgid "8581c4bc164b42d78d66c965127e2760"
msgstr "“ ‘The realm of phenomena endures without change."

msgid "65a18acf9bbb4056a37ff8f3e2f8aa67"
msgstr "With perfected faculties phenomena are known."

msgid "86fd7b64df764d6da80b84f08e72c0df"
msgstr "Knowing them, they teach the Dharma accordingly."

msgid "2496976d58de4efca7644143a6228343"
msgstr "This is the twelfth activity of the victors.’"

msgid "4498feaeceea409f9acafa85f61a7f2d"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas know in accordance with reality which "
"obstructing factors obstruct. No one in the world with its gods is able to "
"reasonably reprove the tathāgatas, saying, ‘Those factors do not obstruct.’"

msgid "822511fbaaf24fffab9a34812966af21"
msgstr "What are the obstructing factors?"

msgid "e31530dcb83445be88851ccdebc7d5b0"
msgstr "There is one [obstructing factor]: a mind that lacks faith."

msgid "98ba1c5792ce4dba8801be29bbf0a652"
msgstr "There are two [obstructing factors]: immodesty and impropriety."

msgid "8e50b154144040c8b3994cda431a2d2a"
msgstr ""
"There are three [obstructing factors]: misconduct of body, speech, and mind."

msgid "0b373375e768432185f2f1d85b9d9a7c"
msgstr ""
"There are four [obstructing factors]: going wrong because of desire, "
"aversion, delusion, or fear."

msgid "adba2f0b68b1490d993f8f832ce95a65"
msgstr ""
"There are five [obstructing factors]: killing, stealing, sexual misconduct, "
"lying, and consuming intoxicants."

msgid "e4e03d8d28974aa1a5ab71377c469598"
msgstr ""
"There are six [obstructing factors]: irreverence toward the Buddha, the "
"Dharma, and the Saṅgha and irreverence toward the training, meditative "
"absorption, and the meditation cushion."

msgid "79ffb816e0884da4aa743bddc629e575"
msgstr ""
"There are seven [obstructing factors]: ordinary pride, the pride of "
"superiority, excessive pride, the pride that thinks ‘I am,’ manifest pride, "
"the inverted pride of self-abasement, and mistaken pride."

msgid "6850f495d0f04ef387d87d771cc49a79"
msgstr ""
"There are eight [obstructing factors]: wrong view, wrong intention, wrong "
"speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and"
" wrong absorption."

msgid "e595124af5144067bc4cec22eca023df"
msgstr "There are nine [obstructing factors]:"

msgid "e843ca6da69c496c977344b20b4c536c"
msgstr ""
"giving rise to miserable states of mind such as ‘I was harmed,” ‘I am being "
"harmed,’ or ‘I will be harmed’;"

msgid "d569c0adc7274a338dad142456f8121a"
msgstr ""
"giving rise to miserable states of mind such as ‘My friends were harmed,’ "
"‘They are being harmed,’ or ‘They will be harmed’;"

msgid "7f5e8c9c553443c78c96d6934e8b431e"
msgstr ""
"and giving rise to miserable states of mind such as ‘Those who are not my "
"friends have benefited,’ ‘They are benefitting,’ or ‘They will benefit.’"

msgid "2fcea0b0a7e14c06aa230bc351e78912"
msgstr "There are ten [obstructing factors]:"

msgid "0485fdc13fbe46d49d8c80649fbee4fa"
msgstr ""
"the ways of the ten nonvirtuous actions of killing, stealing, and sexual "
"misconduct, lying, slander, harsh words, and idle chatter, and covetousness,"
" maliciousness, and wrong views."

msgid "abf6a8cda2eb4167936eb9e5a09e798d"
msgstr ""
"“Tathāgatas know the following to be obstructing factors: becoming engrossed"
" in the taste of factors that are entangled with incorrect mental activity, "
"being mistaken, being ensnared by obscurations, and being disordered by "
"clinging to existence and to views, as well as any physical, verbal, or "
"mental acts encumbered by the aggregates."

msgid "edb1b2e14b624d589c63a50d01807b4f"
msgstr ""
"Declaring, ‘These are obstructing factors,’ they teach them as such, in "
"accordance with reality."

msgid "480bee07a64c4770ae8bb99935d22726"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas teach the Dharma in order that these obstructing factors are "
"pacified, calmed, and abandoned."

msgid "b09388cab17c48ab9b24dc75ffb96186"
msgstr "This is the thirteenth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "4dfaf02efa4a4b548ee473dff8ee8996"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "688f36f678e44b78945a8975f02a4bee"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Those who rely on factors realized by the victors as obstructing Will not"
" attain liberation:"

msgid "88bf20c4371f4a42a619865a125c3f0c"
msgstr "Discarding devotion"

msgid "5b24986e79dc49d6895554e3ea4e3d65"
msgstr "And lacking the slightest modesty or propriety,"

msgid "d8fd3facc13649d099e69b34f92bb62d"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Likewise having no restraint whatsoever In body, speech, and mind, Having"
" desire, aversion, and delusion, Killing and destroying the property of "
"others,"

msgid "14bb35b42c8b4ad293373671cb717856"
msgstr "“ ‘Taking another’s wife, lying, or consuming intoxicants,"

msgid "56a5728d238f4d45b8d9fa686f0779c9"
msgstr ""
"Lacking the six kinds of reverence and having the seven kinds of pride, And "
"engaging in the eight kinds of misdeeds— These all obstruct the path to "
"liberation."

msgid "da7dbf5a2f434d178f07407ce81dda1d"
msgstr "“ ‘The miserable states of mind said to be ninefold,"

msgid "7b3c1bd99a1b489ea6a90121e86a0fef"
msgstr "The ways of the ten nonvirtuous actions—"

msgid "389cb3cb117f472a935f7a5be22d717c"
msgstr "For those who lack any propriety,"

msgid "bd1e07e6a26f4862a2b96c4027d17828"
msgstr "There will never be superknowledge or liberation."

msgid "91278c52ae8c4fc59bb644337ef5c648"
msgstr "“ ‘To those who are encumbered by being mistaken,"

msgid "2c6add8060774478a7c88fea983af095"
msgstr "Who cling to extremes and hold on to what is unreal,"

msgid "872a1dc396d848c0bebf174609652b7f"
msgstr ""
"The victorious lords teach out of benevolence So that these beings may know "
"and abandon those factors.’"

msgid "c9e305d2f3bb4a8ea81222e4248cde6e"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas know, in accordance with reality, the "
"noble path of deliverance as a noble path of deliverance, which eliminates "
"created suffering. Beings will be delivered if they rely on it, and no one "
"in the world with its gods is able to reasonably reprove the tathāgatas, "
"saying, ‘This is not a path of deliverance.’"

msgid "041a43c115e64d0698327e601051d75f"
msgstr "What, then, is the path of deliverance?"

msgid "ce77bf0773a14f40881658f203360405"
msgstr ""
"It is the single path for sentient beings to travel that leads to "
"purification."

msgid "8293df811e7147958fa4e24555a68715"
msgstr ""
"“There are two factors of the path of deliverance: tranquil abiding and "
"special insight."

msgid "781bc8774aae482cb8805afa1028e3b5"
msgstr "There are three: emptiness, signlessness, and wishlessness."

msgid "82c49a67a3174b22a71a6e6df63ed9c9"
msgstr ""
"There are four factors of the path of deliverance: mindfulness of body, "
"mindfulness of feeling, mindfulness of mind, and mindfulness of phenomena."

msgid "b3e1f40a19da41ffadf976b370e4e494"
msgstr ""
"There are applications of mindfulness of the body where one contemplates "
"what is inside the body, what is on the outside of the body, and both "
"together."

msgid "7588408088874ef381557316e5e6f6b8"
msgstr ""
"There are applications of mindfulness of sensation where one contemplates "
"inner sensations, outer sensations, and both together."

msgid "4a2e2938b26447709a0bc278afad872c"
msgstr ""
"There are applications of mindfulness of mind where one contemplates the "
"introverted mind, the extroverted mind, and both together."

msgid "83d55e17aa164850b1d7ebc4210ae294"
msgstr ""
"Finally, there are applications of mindfulness of phenomena where one "
"contemplates inner factors, outer factors, and both together."

msgid "5987c9c385c8422889ee76761de09e4d"
msgstr ""
"There are five factors of the path of deliverance: the spiritual faculties "
"of faith, vigor, mindfulness, meditative absorption, and insight."

msgid "2cf59978620e446694a9ac924e7b68c9"
msgstr ""
"There are six factors of the path of deliverance: the recollection of the "
"Buddha, the Dharma, the Saṅgha, renunciation, morality, and the gods."

msgid "55c391ae0d7f41788e0ae8c27c09d138"
msgstr ""
"There are seven factors of the path of deliverance: the factors of "
"awakening, which are correct mindfulness, correct investigation of "
"phenomena, correct vigor, correct joy, correct pliancy, correct meditative "
"absorption, and the factor of awakening that is correct equanimity."

msgid "a0027793b1a147e0a740734ddd827d8d"
msgstr ""
"There are eight factors of the path of deliverance: correct view, correct "
"intention, correct speech, correct action, correct livelihood, correct "
"effort, correct mindfulness, and correct meditative absorption."

msgid "b33cfc5c494f4675a053eab634d4e7ec"
msgstr ""
"There are nine factors of the path of deliverance: the first, second, third,"
" and fourth concentrations, the attainments of the absorptions of infinite "
"space, consciousness, nothingness, and neither perception nor nonperception,"
" and the attainment of the cessation of perception and feeling."

msgid "482921ee0ee74c3c9f5a132a78fcda9f"
msgstr "There are ten factors of the path of deliverance."

msgid "2bfb454ad31f4521811ff395ea23ced3"
msgstr "What are they?"

msgid "975f09a07fc244389c86392b5a194156"
msgstr "They are the ways of the ten virtuous actions."

msgid "2508d2138dcb4c458e89af9c625b1dfd"
msgstr "What are these?"

msgid "c0ea47e9fee2438daa23deb5846a5ab6"
msgstr ""
"They are giving up killing, stealing, sexual misconduct, lying, slander, "
"harsh words, idle chatter, covetousness, maliciousness, and wrong views."

msgid "66db1fade416470aa73f20f5508ee43e"
msgstr "These are the ten factors that constitute the path of deliverance."

msgid "18250b1b79cc41f287a36da13f7ffe32"
msgstr ""
"“Thus, the virtuous factors of awakening, whether they belong to the "
"category of moral conduct, meditative absorption, or insight, or whether "
"they belong to the category of liberation, the insight of liberating wisdom,"
" or the noble truths, are said to constitute the path of deliverance."

msgid "bdae66d0d4e64c71889aaad04bd9c5c4"
msgstr "“Moreover, the path of deliverance is to be correctly accomplished."

msgid "e2688e5ec7734e73807f340777494428"
msgstr ""
"Correct accomplishment is the absence of the factors of accumulating or not "
"accumulating, accepting or rejecting, and appropriating or abandoning."

msgid "2beb0ba1d2fb44a6b66a9b665070b80f"
msgstr "Why?"

msgid "09cc7de3029046fcb0a565bc122c8cfe"
msgstr "The correct approach is not to engage the mind in duality."

msgid "c89c8266204846768357de7897cead14"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing with wisdom all phenomena in a nondual manner and in accordance with"
" reality is the path of deliverance."

msgid "610d6861339f4f83b8c69568105b7825"
msgstr "The tathāgatas teach this path of deliverance to sentient beings."

msgid "cef328e5a4394df39bddf26ef0d9eba5"
msgstr ""
"When they rely on it, sentient beings are delivered, since created suffering"
" is truly eliminated."

msgid "36a549d51d414f9abecd424acd0a8021"
msgstr "This is the fourteenth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "d4e578fe5a81412d9fc44f50af6335e1"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "e46173d1acc44596a369f9fb5ce2bb5c"
msgstr "“ ‘Those who have been purified will gain immeasurable bliss."

msgid "4dbd9b15a4ec4c67a71da43f95f7e205"
msgstr "If people rely on this path, they will experience peace."

msgid "aad2faa65aa44aa1a24891861b417b6e"
msgstr "The victors know all."

msgid "b3b34fa82f5340a289623b2de99e16aa"
msgstr ""
"Learning and knowing by themselves, they teach the Dharma that leads to "
"immortality."

msgid "1578140fc4ee48d182688c1d0c13171c"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘If they attend to the virtues conducive to awakening, which are praised "
"by the victors,"

msgid "ad87977e9bcd4ca2b4d461ffaaeb81f6"
msgstr "All the many virtuous factors that there are,"

msgid "7d2f7e71f363450aa77ac863da0b7340"
msgstr ""
"There is no way for the intelligent Not to be liberated—so the Sugata has "
"explained."

msgid "f32c1fd528bb470fa9eb40a36a655475"
msgstr "“ ‘Those who are skilled in the true Dharma"

msgid "2b796ed4f03d4b9cb7e95547295afa52"
msgstr "Will pacify the mass of afflictive emotions accordingly."

msgid "9c68d92ea3954055990ce434a632aeb0"
msgstr "Without clinging to non-Dharma or even to Dharma,"

msgid "3ffee0e2159642d7bba0f01d8648c888"
msgstr "They will reach the peace of liberation that is free from all ills."

msgid "7da438a3ef7943b6b3ce2e16c9b1b0aa"
msgstr "“ ‘Those who are skilled in the support consider that phenomena"

msgid "2ec3c81dc2804884bd683a924ec98a1b"
msgstr "Are deceptive and fake and are like space—"

msgid "e17077e8698742e08a46b06157a97453"
msgstr "They are like illusory forms and dreams."

msgid "19b7619416454276809e144ddf8742dc"
msgstr "Thus they are liberated from the ocean of existence."

msgid "0ea96cc9493b40b68dd03959724ae249"
msgstr "“ ‘The activity of the kings of sages, the capable ones,"

msgid "4801cafcb0c74e9d8940df66cac2d606"
msgstr "Once they have generated compassion,"

msgid "ac533195905d44e7af69daf24f3dc7ba"
msgstr "Serves to liberate crazed beings from the wheel of existence."

msgid "a9e9e22541d44058ab67f1096e88c4ca"
msgstr "Therefore they are uncorrupted.’"

msgid "9007fef5ab4843278c146698d790f5db"
msgstr ""
" “Moreover, son of noble family, the tathāgatas are without bodily faults "
"that could be reasonably objected to, such as the bodily faults that the "
"immature or even the learned may possess."

msgid "d4da93aa15c243e4a15d8d684e61fa30"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "0726a4c754114c01b14c0826a96ed0bf"
msgstr "The physical activity of the blessed buddhas is faultless."

msgid "ea86d54256074f37b3cf7276ecdd0063"
msgstr ""
"They display beautiful comportment as they survey the world and behold their"
" surroundings, when they bend and stretch their limbs, as they wear the "
"religious garments consisting of the upper Dharma robe, the outer robe, and "
"the lower robe, and as they hold the alms bowl. The soles of their feet do "
"not touch the ground as they come and go, walk and stand, and sit and "
"recline, or as they enter and depart houses, towns, and hamlets."

msgid "29a626c671d84e61b0e1555c5a225942"
msgstr ""
"Instead, the tathāgatas’ feet step on thousand-spoked wheels that appear out"
" of the ground, and on the lotus flowers with sweet fragrance that emerge."

msgid "2fd98f5d250a47fa9eae964fb5ce92b6"
msgstr ""
"Those sentient beings, born as animals, who touch the tathāgatas’ footprints"
" experience bliss for a week."

msgid "33dca4d72ff640719f1fd6939c937463"
msgstr ""
"After death, they will be reborn in the happy destinies of the higher "
"realms."

msgid "562620559fb0491d99f179f415ef84db"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas’ religious garments do not actually touch their bodies by "
"four finger lengths, but even so, a fierce wind will fail to make them "
"disheveled."

msgid "8050f796b8544ccd893e57085ebf774c"
msgstr ""
"The radiance of their bodies arouses bliss in sentient beings as far as the "
"lowest hell."

msgid "7167aee07a8a455c80027af35d11f0b1"
msgstr "Therefore, the bodies of the tathāgatas are said to be faultless."

msgid "44f9dc755bcd43979b254f70d5c8348e"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, the tathāgatas are without verbal faults that could be"
" reasonably objected to, such as the verbal faults that the immature or even"
" the learned may possess."

msgid "bbb4a080688145568581d8a758da1b1e"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "758a2a7fe73547379ec239c87adf4e89"
msgstr ""
"Because, son of noble family, their speech is timely, poetic, correct, and "
"truthful, and they act accordingly."

msgid "86b6019590e14f8495234ec9ba116470"
msgstr "Their words are precisely defined and satisfy all sentient beings."

msgid "703794af09d94d0c8ae3becd27df0626"
msgstr "They are not repetitive."

msgid "703562111f6249158cb16704510f0184"
msgstr "They are adorned with beautiful phrases and meaning."

msgid "73639549b75d49d99a610b1e76359b57"
msgstr ""
"A single instant of expression satisfies the minds of all sentient beings."

msgid "77a981109ed440d9a16adb6bc77cd53e"
msgstr "Therefore, the speech of the tathāgatas is said to be faultless."

msgid "752ec15b7f69433ebf4e6be986a82b52"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, the tathāgatas are without mental faults that could be"
" reasonably objected to, such as the mental faults that the immature or even"
" the learned may possess."

msgid "3d6e87c989d649f0a7e688ffd22cc4e3"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "dd605af8e1cd410c99b78d8ea78f063b"
msgstr ""
"Because even though they perform all the buddha deeds without abandoning the"
" state of equipoise, the tathāgatas apply their unattached vision of wisdom "
"to all phenomena without abandoning the mind in equipoise."

msgid "4a14fc67f4664a95a20a082c2d271484"
msgstr "Therefore, the tathāgata mind is said to be faultless."

msgid "fbdd25f8cf53492984454428e65364a2"
msgstr ""
"Just as their mind is faultless, they teach the Dharma accordingly to beings"
" in order to dispel all their faults."

msgid "0660a5c1db41409f80a6429e2c6286f8"
msgstr "This is the fifteenth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "925ea79b75d945609dd33713988759bd"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "010c09986bcd4417bd98ef50dae04ef2"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The guides of beings are without the slightest Physical, verbal, or "
"mental faults."

msgid "3b892bdc14324b6f86a3ddf2aa27ec70"
msgstr "The world protectors are without wrongdoing."

msgid "805a64aa0f6346dbb381a46a6ad133ba"
msgstr "They look faultlessly at all the ways to benefit beings."

msgid "cf26ead7dc2b4a15a0830ac03293896f"
msgstr "“ ‘Thus the victors are without the slightest fault,"

msgid "c2088fb8c1e945af8a7aefe4a9da4ee9"
msgstr "And they teach the supreme Dharma of peace to beings."

msgid "369fd0099c6e433b9c50d91a2c60190e"
msgstr "The complete abandonment of all those faults"

msgid "db1ea70749664e83877adb46665d7506"
msgstr "Is the fifteenth activity of the victors.’"

msgid "125c40b92b7643768a97bbe93197d3a8"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas have no noisy kinds of speech that "
"could lead to conflict, such as the noisy speech of Māra, the class of "
"māras, or the non-Buddhists."

msgid "64833a0f31d84ab8b1bb9801efdc2904"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "5f3c516c7da441ae8cc73683e66f2d2c"
msgstr "Because the tathāgatas do not speak noisily or raucously."

msgid "880a37bb19da4479bc55a06cf614aa64"
msgstr "And why is that?"

msgid "132dc949b20947ce8f124ac0c789c8f7"
msgstr "Because they are free of attachment and anger."

msgid "7106a5e5e777473b9a2de30fa902dcee"
msgstr ""
"They do not become elated when all beings revere them, nor do they become "
"disheartened if no beings revere them."

msgid "9a7671172bcd498a9e09116098049c96"
msgstr ""
"They do not babble regretfully about tasks that were difficult or could not "
"be completed."

msgid "2b9793e3a67d40ac8d68cd54ca9c75ad"
msgstr ""
"“Tathāgatas do not dispute about anything in the world; they do not grumble."

msgid "30b3163c02b94d37ab907c4e80c64152"
msgstr "They abide in the absence of afflictive emotions."

msgid "b50afebe9b4e4036a4ad2dfb73e01c0d"
msgstr ""
"They are not possessive, they do not cling to or appropriate anything, and "
"they are free from all bonds, so they do not speak noisily."

msgid "4d9ef737d9fd44ad81e044ec9f49f4df"
msgstr ""
"Just as their speech is not noisy, they teach the Dharma accordingly, so "
"that all the noisy speech of all sentient beings will be abandoned."

msgid "7555460ad8a3442eb6698bf41a47157d"
msgstr "This is the sixteenth activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "be2e9dc81a234bf8b116123e603e6a13"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "664b9fcdd4014b8e880f0461719dfaef"
msgstr "“ ‘When hearing praise, they are not elated."

msgid "4db972692e254661bd825547e4c7583f"
msgstr "When hearing blame, they are not disheartened."

msgid "91e38d9051324898921acaf7159ceeb0"
msgstr "They have no attachment or anger."

msgid "2e37bee470fa4fa1b0c9cdb01beead1c"
msgstr "They do not belittle previous actions that were well performed."

msgid "bc885d04bcc64a42be7b2b3c537bab6f"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The victors constantly cultivate the absence of afflictive emotions."

msgid "7073679614b740edaf0ac1bb4ca40a14"
msgstr "They lack possessiveness, clinging, or bonds."

msgid "9dd50ededd6442108dc801e3c39903d7"
msgstr "They teach in accord with their manner of abiding."

msgid "1cbdb09c7d664c7e933999e405823a7f"
msgstr "That is the excellence of the path on which one sees the truth.’"

msgid "ae8beb28e66a4e1ba1a9e41de6e8b78f"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas do not suffer from forgetfulness that "
"could lead to confusion about any phenomena."

msgid "19698b2e8bc343d69d7786c3d4b1a744"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "8256d73db61c4d4985541d7450881ffc"
msgstr ""
"Because none of the concentrations, liberations, absorptions, or meditative "
"attainments of the tathāgatas are marred by forgetfulness."

msgid "caa0a0c2b7f54e14aae89aea8ea0fa7e"
msgstr ""
"When the tathāgatas observe the activity and movement of the minds of all "
"sentient beings and teach the Dharma that is suitable for each, they do not "
"suffer from forgetfulness."

msgid "e721b27dccc44661b9a8f5c21ae682b1"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas do not suffer from forgetfulness regarding the "
"discriminations of meaning, phenomena, etymologies, and eloquence."

msgid "802730a8c41c4b5a832bccd253c06a95"
msgstr ""
"They do not suffer from forgetfulness in their unattached vision of wisdom "
"of the past, present, and future."

msgid "28a7a606cb7246bcbe86b987842bf6dc"
msgstr ""
"“Just as the tathāgatas do not suffer from forgetfulness themselves, they "
"teach the Dharma accordingly, so that no sentient beings will suffer from "
"forgetfulness."

msgid "e5b89c12ec0e4291add2dca50ea4d34c"
msgstr "This is the seventeenth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "5492d7c5a2904f9cbe16f535d76be83a"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "b58f35f85a5a45efaf1e0dfd39b46820"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The guides do not suffer from forgetfulness regarding phenomena Or in "
"their wisdom, liberations, or fields of activity."

msgid "1747b6a228d9494f99f918279bf03cc4"
msgstr "They teach the dharmas that correspond to mentalities,"

msgid "82130049a8d0456f826f4a27ef7a7719"
msgstr "Since the activity in the minds of sentient beings is endless."

msgid "57f22245e49d412d94f31f5c1b923f09"
msgstr "“ ‘Their discriminating knowledge is not marred by forgetfulness."

msgid "83fea625271b46bfb1efe427bacebd98"
msgstr "Their wisdom is unobscured with respect to the three times."

msgid "4e64b62a041d48ec85d3572070fdf748"
msgstr ""
"Just as they are without forgetfulness, so do they teach the Dharma "
"accordingly."

msgid "7107ada49bb44842b5e0f3a7d555a483"
msgstr "This is the activity of supreme beings.’"

msgid "60eedc14ca524a8caa9f014d551456a1"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the minds of the tathāgatas are never not in "
"equipoise."

msgid "b2e2750ee17c4bd2abed365f9c17ef89"
msgstr ""
"Whether they walk, stand, sit, or recline, whether they eat, speak, or "
"remain silent, they are constantly in equipoise, attain the supremely "
"profound absorption, and practice an unobscured type of concentration."

msgid "feb8c5d5315e48dab11dcbec60d7d74c"
msgstr ""
"Without the blessing of the tathāgatas, no one among beings, whether in "
"equipoise or not, is able to observe the mind of the tathāgatas."

msgid "2ad66a3989864230a0898b2a00bf1633"
msgstr ""
"“Just as the tathāgatas are constantly in equipoise, they teach the Dharma "
"accordingly, in order that sentient beings will not become distracted from "
"their absorptions."

msgid "4728226736e748ee9c43a37a684ba9bd"
msgstr "This is the eighteenth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "46308c01cb1641cdbedd19e47dbc3a76"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "deb35603ead9423fbade4df8c6289ea2"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Whether standing, sitting, lying down, or moving about, The buddhas are "
"without a mind that is not in equipoise."

msgid "a2649ddbdc2b470ea79e59dc3bfd2220"
msgstr ""
"Whether sitting silently, speaking, or eating, The victors are never seen to"
" waver in their equipoise."

msgid "9654eb287620431abaea95389e4ed4ea"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘There is no one in the ten directions Who can know the mind of a sugata "
"in equipoise."

msgid "0744f0bcea3049068d4463002801df01"
msgstr ""
"Just as they are in equipoise, so do they continuously teach the dharmas to "
"beings."

msgid "e136c950f7614a1da00ce54223c49bd9"
msgstr "That is the activity of the victors.’"

msgid "7acccad72fd94ff9887313a35097c93b"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas are free from perceptions of "
"difference of the type that would lead the mind into a state of imbalance."

msgid "a98361a621be4997ae2d661a696f8c1e"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "307a842093954ee8ac5985c8286b4f98"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas are free from perceptions of difference regarding the fields,"
" since the fields are inexhaustible like space;"

msgid "a317e9f416ed4fb886729878e30b0ec8"
msgstr ""
"they are free from perceptions of difference regarding sentient beings, "
"since they are by nature without a self;"

msgid "23d466d7c86547c0915f48da3758390a"
msgstr ""
"they are free from perceptions of difference regarding the buddhafields, "
"since they know the realm of phenomena to be a state of unadulterated "
"equality;"

msgid "34ed58e2b10f4c4fbed707677697ea87"
msgstr ""
"and they are free from perceptions of difference regarding phenomena, since "
"the nature of reality is free from attachment."

msgid "5c146b9e96314331b707bf1cede658de"
msgstr ""
"“Tathāgatas do not favor those who observe moral conduct or feel anger "
"toward those who transgress moral conduct."

msgid "693db75306c64b4eb4641aa9fc193444"
msgstr ""
"They do not reward those who do good or return harm to those who have done "
"harm."

msgid "88cf124b689248f2b608002e73f1dfa0"
msgstr ""
"They are not indifferent to those who are worthy of training, nor do they "
"condemn those who are stuck in error."

msgid "2152d93708ce4811a4ee4741f8b8dbfc"
msgstr "The tathāgatas abide in sameness regarding all phenomena."

msgid "610c6db547694f24a9a41d8dca187016"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, the tathāgatas are said to be without any perceptions of "
"difference."

msgid "d53c083a1b5640bd9f935d0fac597321"
msgstr ""
"“Just as the tathāgatas are free of perceptions of difference, they teach "
"the Dharma accordingly in order that all sentient beings may abandon "
"perceptions of difference."

msgid "3b99353ed33f4766834a63ffe2e1b0a9"
msgstr "This is the nineteenth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "fff687d503464b399277c39fe913b186"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "4fcc08dc39d74342bdf5a56cf63f2913"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The sugatas are free of perceptions of difference Regarding fields, "
"sentient beings, or phenomena."

msgid "b9e3d65dfba44e44ba5c02c0b33f4f67"
msgstr ""
"Because they abide in sameness, The greatly renowned never have perceptions "
"of difference."

msgid "6ae1fab1d50942f69d4faae18ca8b0d0"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The minds of superior humans are the same Whether beings observe moral "
"conduct or faultless conduct, Or whether they are ready to be tamed or "
"difficult to tame."

msgid "9bd1d95bbcb342dda2eda9f162d6b4a8"
msgstr "They liberate those who apprehend difference.’"

msgid "0a9e6564f89a4a4394ff43f04541bc57"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the equanimity of the tathāgatas is not due to a lack"
" of discernment."

msgid "4f5883016aa04b8aac04981ca7135d7c"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "d96aa0ace1ae42b98465180070b86a62"
msgstr ""
"Because the equanimity of the tathāgatas comprises cultivation of the path, "
"not a lack of its cultivation."

msgid "b64e6e2a5fb04415b13c3cdd5ca06759"
msgstr "It is the cultivation of body, mind, and moral conduct."

msgid "6cbd91ed5bde435483168cc864aeb09b"
msgstr ""
"The equanimity of the tathāgatas comprises the cultivation of insight, not a"
" lack of its cultivation."

msgid "da582660cfcf4c03bffaf313a3304a8e"
msgstr ""
"It is endowed with insight, not with delusion. It transcends the world; it "
"does not descend into the mundane."

msgid "7b2b15a24814478faec3b0b72498d699"
msgstr ""
"It constitutes the deliverance of a noble one, not the nondeliverance of "
"someone who is not a noble one."

msgid "cf03c13bd3684f0695b6c83e27a6dfc6"
msgstr ""
"“The equanimity of tathāgatas involves turning the wheel of the Dharma. It "
"is not without great compassion for beings."

msgid "601c15d6e1574326bf3740997cece307"
msgstr "It is realized of its own accord without relying on a remedy."

msgid "5edf81bf43ef4956ab96899b41c39d61"
msgstr "It is not an elated state of mind or a depressed state of mind."

msgid "d39e0860435c46118dc0fb41e02dbd4d"
msgstr "It is an unwavering state without objectification."

msgid "82b5706bed84402c987899e36b8f7536"
msgstr "It transcends conceptualization and conceptual exclusion."

msgid "d69fe13c664747eb880205274f727780"
msgstr "It is aware of the occasion and timely."

msgid "11b59f7bf3184b758fbc79d4532b071c"
msgstr ""
"It does not waver. It is not intentional, discriminative, or analytical. It "
"is not an accomplishment. It is indefinable. It is genuine."

msgid "d15ca18080c64215af89f5b4bfe9f5fe"
msgstr "It is just that: suchness—unique suchness."

msgid "53f73e311f8847d5a6bb13cf3932cf13"
msgstr ""
"“Through the perfection of such great equanimity the tathāgatas teach the "
"Dharma accordingly, so that all sentient beings may perfect such equanimity."

msgid "482554150cf94d8eb18dc350d5accc2e"
msgstr "This is the twentieth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "40cd7c855b054f01a092451b39acb031"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "3811be39228f4da198ffddc636e6a2e0"
msgstr "“ ‘Since the supreme path of excellent conduct has been cultivated,"

msgid "584ad8f4924f433984c7ab256114cffb"
msgstr "Their equanimity is not due to lack of discernment."

msgid "a9bd5fdb16f6465aae2369f91c402418"
msgstr ""
"The supreme beings fully cultivated body, mind, Moral conduct, insight, and "
"truth."

msgid "d237cbd183be479298cbbc8a72b330e9"
msgstr "“ ‘The victors lack attachment or anger."

msgid "0f4a6fe6e7074ba48f37fe8bffd63f9e"
msgstr "Without discrimination, analysis, or accomplishment,"

msgid "c4462a6a843e42448d7c8d881e639ce1"
msgstr "Their equanimity is genuine and unique."

msgid "66f92ab06fe2491996a9cd25bf4a5403"
msgstr "Still, they teach all beings.’"

msgid "279a9500c5b240fc92be6920a0922ac5"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the zeal of the tathāgatas does not deteriorate."

msgid "57585d96b3e545e6bc9608581415614b"
msgstr "What kind of zeal is it?"

msgid "8cd114fd840b4b18ad134bbf4f64318c"
msgstr "It is the zeal for virtuous factors."

msgid "4b10cc62ca404e80a1a83b75690d1d17"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "0172e672c0854e3e80fba5bded08ae84"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas’ zeal for great love and great compassion does not "
"deteriorate."

msgid "729484fda2b94620b080b417e71206bd"
msgstr ""
"Their zeal for teaching the Dharma and for taming and ripening beings does "
"not deteriorate."

msgid "4b9f33ca482d4a3f8b438c553033d8f4"
msgstr "Their zeal for solitude does not deteriorate."

msgid "e6bac3b0bd444a57b2e81eb9ac26be01"
msgstr ""
"Their zeal for engaging sentient beings in embracing awakening does not "
"deteriorate."

msgid "27cb15e3c6054a21965bfe6d5e293d9a"
msgstr ""
"Their zeal for the unbroken continuity of the lineage of the Three Jewels "
"does not deteriorate."

msgid "998182efefa8411db1377c8d7e8e7471"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgatas are not driven by zeal, but, rather, their zeal is preceded "
"by wisdom."

msgid "a3969baf2e1e4b24a9da878840fe9419"
msgstr ""
"That is why it is said that the zeal of the tathāgatas does not deteriorate."

msgid "02b2848f79594f458472ff7e899b7577"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas teach the Dharma so that the unsurpassed zeal of all sentient"
" beings may be perfected."

msgid "4a875d5369be49a98bef58527ab886e1"
msgstr "This is the twenty-first tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "ae34b94fef8c4937972df785d3d9141a"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "37ca1d2a392b4b6384df53070ab0160f"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The zeal of the victors is a constant wish for and delight in virtuous "
"factors."

msgid "a16ec0aeea2c46b694b9d6d0ad11d114"
msgstr ""
"They bestow the Dharma of love and compassion in order to liberate beings."

msgid "861b06bfedd74d24bc3b5cab53a6b8d6"
msgstr ""
"Their longing to mature beings and to delight in forest groves does not "
"deteriorate."

msgid "8eceedb590d0447eb1a65a8b146cc994"
msgstr ""
"They cause many to embrace awakening and do not disrupt the continuity of "
"the lineage of the Three Jewels."

msgid "2bbfb23af1a840c99007f2a8a0d9cb4c"
msgstr "“ ‘They are not driven by attachment, aversion, fear, or delusion."

msgid "9d3effb6200f496ea47fc2f4438cb00c"
msgstr ""
"Exceptionally skilled, they realize all factors that are produced by "
"knowledge."

msgid "97df6631312f414cb61beadcc855cd52"
msgstr "Observing lazy beings who lack zeal, the victors motivate them."

msgid "19707e71b7694376af3e866aa3fb31f3"
msgstr ""
"With unequaled knowledge they understand the zealous actions of beings.’"

msgid "e81e6e7266f04b06b324245a8f34ca5b"
msgstr " “Son of noble family, the vigor of tathāgatas does not deteriorate."

msgid "36a2fa2ba9d240a2987ced67c88661ef"
msgstr "The vigor of the tathāgatas is as follows:"

msgid "557142be491e4ecfbd71d358b3d92122"
msgstr ""
"It is a vigor that does not forsake beings to be tamed or disdain those who "
"listen to the Dharma."

msgid "564b2f0f359444829f1d52d2f982d5d3"
msgstr ""
"When the tathāgatas discover audiences receptive to the Dharma, who do not "
"tire of listening to the Dharma even for an eon, the tathāgatas will teach "
"the Dharma, uninterrupted by meals and without stirring, even for an eon."

msgid "f94081a0ac574aa0a370d86cdd9c1ad7"
msgstr ""
"For the sake of just a single being to be tamed by the buddhas, the "
"tathāgatas, in their concern for beings, will travel beyond as many "
"buddhafields as the number of grains of sand of the river Ganges."

msgid "44def5d251404945a3a4d513006c61fe"
msgstr "They will not become physically, verbally, or mentally weary."

msgid "0b3cfaa1fece46bc9034f01ec15c7ee1"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgatas have made their minds pliant, roused vigor, and spoken in "
"praise of vigor."

msgid "0f7a3a5542b946f8b1060ab002c34d7e"
msgstr ""
"The vigor through which sentient beings, by correctly applying themselves to"
" it, will attain noble liberation—that is the vigor commended to them."

msgid "f42358d428de4203a5352b1b18bcf5b8"
msgstr "This is the twenty-second tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "0bc0bd25b10547fd8f4b862fefcf53e5"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "c9874bef1bee405aa00ccbc57bfd8dab"
msgstr "Through which the lions among humans became noble beings."

msgid "70f58a2bb7a243b4bf81cdec758a6d49"
msgstr "“ ‘They continually praise that powerful vigor"

msgid "0f43f1911da84b5d92719c97e9f93493"
msgstr "That powerful vigor does not deteriorate at all."

msgid "79e911c8146b4dcc9fa901432a8ecf0f"
msgstr "Once an audience is found, the Dharma is taught."

msgid "83fb41cb508b4ad2bc0a5d51ccf30137"
msgstr "“ ‘The vigor of the sugatas never rests."

msgid "0996f9743f37460198859d18cc60732f"
msgstr "It is without physical, verbal, or mental weariness."

msgid "f2bf13b3ce5e4fcc88e0d73173e0b2ae"
msgstr "Just as this spontaneous vigor is completely free of sin,"

msgid "5e5c8ab7c3654c65908ba2062de22eb7"
msgstr "So are beings, having purified their minds, stablished in it.’"

msgid "7dc086994fa1492d8b4e90b22e80bc34"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the mindfulness of tathāgatas does not deteriorate in"
" any respect or in any way whatsoever."

msgid "68f52a2e77bc496ea094bcfd887151f7"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "4cd0d1f05d3c467db51e2d91d78633d8"
msgstr "Because the tathāgatas are not forgetful."

msgid "bddf6cae91eb48558a8f51a02ae94a22"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, as soon as tathāgatas awaken into unsurpassed, perfect "
"awakening, they behold the mindstreams of all sentient beings of the past, "
"present, and future. Still, they are not forgetful at all."

msgid "49ef78a4de9347b3befde16616a3d984"
msgstr ""
"Although they know the conduct of beings in accordance with reality, the "
"tathāgatas do not let go of their wisdom regarding it."

msgid "53af43b003014f12baa88c2cbe69d03d"
msgstr ""
"The mindfulness of tathāgatas does not deteriorate when they assign beings "
"to three groups, engage with their faculties and mentalities, and behold "
"their conduct."

msgid "4518aa123e074c2fb8c694fdd5bffe78"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas’ teaching of the Dharma to beings happens without activating "
"their recollection, without intention or analysis."

msgid "c048485ad498418c95c8d852435a5228"
msgstr "Even while teaching, their mindfulness does not deteriorate."

msgid "adb3d38490f245e1afab125c5d8156f6"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "6ca1dd3f729f4491bfb72af3b023c5de"
msgstr "Because the mindfulness of tathāgatas does not deteriorate."

msgid "f99a460916a34ab7b6716f0d9759a21e"
msgstr ""
"Just as they are mindful and without forgetfulness, they teach the Dharma to"
" beings accordingly."

msgid "400c56702a02478aafd5c1e63fda312f"
msgstr "This is the twenty-third tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "65655dbfb4df4cf7be2bff7890365d5a"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "0a32c961ebf24515a8654e6b1ee6225f"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The mindfulness of the teachers does not deteriorate in the slightest."

msgid "0d7196dad94640af8f339ea38319dbc1"
msgstr "The mindfulness of the victors is effortless."

msgid "3c3d9ebed4b54e27a47c1a74e487478c"
msgstr "When the victors awaken into awakening,"

msgid "10f49d80422c433185c33fbfd8409e15"
msgstr "They know the minds of all beings without exception."

msgid "72a9960935ed49f9bb9efddcce9037d0"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The thoughts, faculties, and conduct of beings Are not to be cognized "
"consequently."

msgid "e9ec916f32a64cd5bc60f8ee42e4e1f6"
msgstr ""
"Remaining in order to act spontaneously, The victorious lords teach beings "
"the Dharma.’"

msgid "6b5ed8cafea849d4824685c3ac217e65"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the meditative absorption of the tathāgatas does not "
"deteriorate."

msgid "fd61e774cf2747b782f9d300126a74b3"
msgstr ""
"It is the sameness of all phenomena, the fact that all phenomena are not not"
" the same, and all phenomena as they really are."

msgid "4734dee8b5514735bb0a973ce598dc61"
msgstr "Why does the meditative absorption of the tathāgatas not deteriorate?"

msgid "6581219d3c0e47d5ad2722c307b6afba"
msgstr "What is equal to suchness is equal to absorption."

msgid "fd64ede7aa2842c491086d0c72931fae"
msgstr "What is equal to absorption is equal to the tathāgatas."

msgid "1e878277384f4be9b44f7f2404a88b5c"
msgstr "That is why it is called equipoise."

msgid "ee619c7aa8044c279f78e101808cb5ba"
msgstr ""
"“What is equal to the extreme of attachment is equal to the extreme of the "
"lack of attachment."

msgid "423367459eac49a291e198c3f7c5817e"
msgstr ""
"What is equal to the extreme of aversion is equal to the extreme of the lack"
" of aversion."

msgid "ad01aa4244cf440c93ea7e67df39b9a5"
msgstr ""
"What is equal to the extreme of delusion is equal to the extreme of the lack"
" of delusion."

msgid "b8640dd5b0e649b0853a22bd8217df2c"
msgstr ""
"What is equal to the extreme of the conditioned is equal to the extreme of "
"the unconditioned."

msgid "66f0bfa06d5942cfa3fdbc86f04ae8e0"
msgstr ""
"What is equal to the extreme of saṃsāra is equal to the extreme of nirvāṇa."

msgid "eeaefe38236d47bf9e7d250c04784408"
msgstr "Having settled evenly in these types of sameness is called equipoise."

msgid "5838c9f690cc432d9ddeb39889938ed4"
msgstr "Because the absorption of the tathāgatas is without deterioration."

msgid "f6181254222e4a409fcfce1c46e1c79c"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "451f44c3522349588ff27e9a6e90ef9f"
msgstr "Because there is no deterioration in that sameness."

msgid "be23e9898d4d4aeeb1dfe133a7f3d27a"
msgstr "There is no deterioration at all."

msgid "26c831f53c944e9392ad46e7186e8690"
msgstr ""
"“The absorption of the tathāgatas does not involve the eyes, ear, nose, "
"tongue, body, or mind, even though the tathāgatas have complete faculties."

msgid "e9550d6ea2a041e5917c93f89126c2a7"
msgstr ""
"Their absorption does not settle in the earth element, in the water element,"
" in the fire element, or in the wind element."

msgid "f6217aeca13d4738bb9fb13a59574176"
msgstr ""
"It does not settle in the desire realm, in the form realm, or in the "
"formless realm."

msgid "acf13fe9e05a4cbc82a43a882afb2272"
msgstr "It is not settled in this world or in the world beyond."

msgid "05724158b1d8482ca667bd49d36ff08e"
msgstr "Since it does not settle, there is no deterioration."

msgid "569971d57b7849a7852dc56abb784d94"
msgstr ""
"That is why it is said that the absorption of the tathāgatas is without "
"deterioration."

msgid "952fa32f565048fe8d9314b6dd90b2dc"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas teach the Dharma so that all sentient beings may also attain "
"absorption."

msgid "1e460e45b3524b3ab7b43f297a2f168a"
msgstr "This is the twenty-fourth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "1b2352f7cec74a33aa9247e39b5dfa02"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "6137eabfba814efba726bf428352b5c8"
msgstr "“ ‘The buddhas are constantly in equipoise."

msgid "8cee14120b634d5c8fbe990450ee8858"
msgstr "Their absorption does not deteriorate."

msgid "1a5cb74bd7094e3b90efb295ddb73db8"
msgstr "The equality of all phenomena."

msgid "c06d809c25cc402ab46dc4b969d9fbec"
msgstr "The buddhas are settled evenly in equality,"

msgid "46306baeed86460c94cebae47f118815"
msgstr ""
"In the earth, water, fire, or air element, Or in the realms of desire, form,"
" or formlessness. “ ‘The concentration of the victors is not settled"

msgid "2f8656d451c443a5bf34f9a39d49c324"
msgstr "Therefore, their absorption is without deterioration.’"

msgid "2315b317b39f488aa32cc79fd081f207"
msgstr ""
" “Furthermore, son of noble family, the insight of the tathāgatas is without"
" deterioration."

msgid "9eb9c784eb5d4662b5f5b7ca047c4581"
msgstr "What kind of insight is it?"

msgid "edcf903b48594c74be74453279fe1b26"
msgstr ""
"It is a thorough knowledge of all phenomena, a knowledge that does not "
"depend on anything else."

msgid "cb6fd7b6ef8a49aca6b138208ced735f"
msgstr ""
"They know how to teach the Dharma correctly to other beings and individuals."

msgid "aef7ec75ed2f41408a091a4f1dcbbae2"
msgstr ""
"They are skilled in correct discrimination and know how to analyze words."

msgid "3a55235565e04bcf914e4e6544c3857a"
msgstr ""
"They know how to teach so that the usage of a single word will prevail for a"
" hundred thousand eons."

msgid "cf319f7d80b443d1b3a5f818221a3117"
msgstr ""
"They know how to eradicate doubts in accordance with the manner of the "
"question."

msgid "0f8c28ac0f4e40eea19f65e14f63379f"
msgstr "They know how to be totally without attachment."

msgid "ff4eb2ff9ef74ff4b42daaa3d3cecc09"
msgstr "They know how to teach the arrangement of the three vehicles."

msgid "56ce92e8283b435599ddd18caef6f3f5"
msgstr ""
"They know entirely the eighty-four thousand types of mental conduct of "
"beings."

msgid "86b4fafa4bb1497da9b976387293793f"
msgstr ""
"They know how to teach the eighty-four thousand divisions of Dharma, each as"
" is appropriate."

msgid "384a30c6fffa433dab2768623e0d5d38"
msgstr ""
"In this way, the insight of the tathāgatas has been shown to be limitless, "
"infinite, inexhaustible, and immeasurable."

msgid "1df0e40be6954549ab787751c055b818"
msgstr ""
"“Just as the tathāgatas are without deterioration and thoroughly without "
"deterioration, so they teach the Dharma so that the insight of all sentient "
"beings will be inexhaustible."

msgid "43ac4f12159f456999e55db691d5eb6e"
msgstr "This is the twenty-fifth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "e4f597a182bd4681a8cfb7bc1334b5b3"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "45b0752cd73a477ba08a0124ed2f0e24"
msgstr "“ ‘With insight that perceives all aspects directly,"

msgid "d7932741be9e4292a08c7bbf5043b7ba"
msgstr "The masters of correct discrimination have gone beyond."

msgid "cc3cf135c75c47929c99776e33cf9452"
msgstr ""
"They teach the Dharma to beings, naturally responding to their thinking."

msgid "4576cac4fb224d2bbdd978442f98d8e9"
msgstr "In a single syllable or word, limitless words are contained."

msgid "2c52a105499f47e9a4ee7b828160bd39"
msgstr "“ ‘Aware of the infinite conduct of beings,"

msgid "47934c3d0e744c1b8fbfc3505c59642e"
msgstr "They teach the eighty-four thousand Dharmas accordingly."

msgid "1339f8f8ecfb4ecf8d08a7c8d1c51798"
msgstr "The insight of the sugatas never deteriorates."

msgid "8dabca51d49c457aa16a008bb2c38cb2"
msgstr ""
"This activity of the ten strengths sets them apart from other beings.’"

msgid "7a34f71c40864165805e69c5a34d7d00"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the liberation of the tathāgatas is without "
"deterioration."

msgid "294b021f5a4a4c4488f17b088347a0e0"
msgstr "What is the liberation of the tathāgatas?"

msgid "78d7e6db0a6a4121b77f6f82a947c64c"
msgstr "The liberation of śrāvakas conforms to words."

msgid "f9b17e11e0b74f17990ef072d70526e4"
msgstr ""
"The liberation of pratyekabuddhas consists of their comprehension of "
"conditions."

msgid "d617a011fcde4087a3a47f65f88629b6"
msgstr ""
"The liberation of buddhas is called liberation because it is free of all "
"attachment and apprehending."

msgid "e58c8d0cb65944d09c41c1f6720e6cc2"
msgstr ""
"They are not tied to the past, they are not projected into the future, and "
"they do not abide in the present."

msgid "cf3c787d71c84298868d7b06035b7f62"
msgstr ""
"They are free from apprehending the eye and form as two, and from "
"apprehending the ear and sound, the nose and smell, the tongue and taste, "
"the body and tactile objects, and the mind and mental factors as two."

msgid "7ef9b9b1933a41149c6ddb6a4ba59be8"
msgstr "They are free from apprehending and grasping."

msgid "84df00458e3d4945a168ecc861205441"
msgstr "Likewise, they know the luminous nature of the mind."

msgid "3f9cf7fec08a484a859b1258a9f4bb31"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, they are called complete and perfect buddhas who have gained "
"unsurpassed complete and perfect awakening through a single mental moment of"
" insight."

msgid "eb3d43bbda3c4c799f563d08ae42f9ed"
msgstr ""
"“Just as the tathāgatas have attained complete and perfect buddhahood, so "
"they teach the Dharma to other beings and individuals."

msgid "b33bcce3cc2e4c189e4f5addb32341fb"
msgstr "This is the twenty-sixth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "bd957e91bd4f441b8f60efb992a85370"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "c8901556e09d4ab4af8b49dd046a1bf3"
msgstr "“ ‘The liberation of śrāvakas conforms to words."

msgid "27de7362134e47b0b9e01c531bda388d"
msgstr "That of pratyekabuddhas concerns dependent arising."

msgid "8015c6285f39432dbde2ca93f09470f2"
msgstr "The liberation of the irreproachable buddhas"

msgid "d8a1409566404ad69f70da7eafed8ea5"
msgstr "Transcends attachment and is immaculate like space."

msgid "0cdaba83d8d04627a0eed1f208b8981b"
msgstr "“ ‘Their minds were not bound in the past;"

msgid "5e0bc625d319411c980b4c005083480b"
msgstr "Their mindstreams are naturally free."

msgid "16acb303853948bcb015f87bb9f91a37"
msgstr "Just as they are free, they know."

msgid "a92df22f980e4b938e8bcacac18c7032"
msgstr "Knowing, their liberation never deteriorates.’"

msgid "bf8a7dd1303e410699f764ae1589c301"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, all physical activities of the tathāgatas are "
"preceded and accompanied by wisdom."

msgid "9b96a8ca38364e9fb47958159a354479"
msgstr ""
"They tame sentient beings while they gaze, speak, remain silent, or eat."

msgid "d6bfe5d1c7d54d8b9d6c78dc8be846d4"
msgstr "They tame them through their conduct."

msgid "ec9046e4f20f41f19906d2a81a3aff97"
msgstr ""
"They tame beings by means of their major marks and minor signs and by means "
"of their invisible crown protuberance."

msgid "2d95335c099449529db38d162392fcc4"
msgstr "They tame beings merely by their gaze and by emitting light."

msgid "dd64a32a3cda4e29b5fc621d06c62e01"
msgstr ""
"They tame them as they walk about and while arriving at or departing from "
"cities."

msgid "0b2c36e4c9554cc9a0645986de121413"
msgstr ""
"There is no manner of conduct of the blessed buddhas that does not tame "
"sentient beings."

msgid "28896f757baf44f4af288f8ad63f403f"
msgstr ""
"That is why all physical activities of the tathāgatas are said to be "
"preceded and accompanied by wisdom."

msgid "f62b8dbf83ea4d3dbaaf2663f45d3cf5"
msgstr "This is the twenty-seventh tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "6bad8571307b49c6adc2adbb4c64f5c8"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "df664c2d7b6844eb97c99ea18b3eb85e"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The buddhas apply themselves to taming beings By displaying their conduct"
" as guides As they walk about, arrive, and depart And by means of their "
"major marks, minor signs, and crown protuberance."

msgid "2dd8da913dfb4463bb4c79855cc7fb4a"
msgstr "“ ‘The moment the guides emit their light,"

msgid "960674a23c594422801ffc7dcbf32777"
msgstr "Many beings experience bliss."

msgid "dbca9e791e06405bb408479a00e62b77"
msgstr "Touched by the light, they are tamed."

msgid "8f17d7d051b54cc3a53f212d4724d070"
msgstr "This is the activity of venerable beings.’"

msgid "65b457143b5c4a9db32ce47db1c5e3a6"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, all verbal activities of the tathāgatas are preceded "
"and accompanied by wisdom."

msgid "1a4944db97174cf78b321dfbb1800b19"
msgstr "Why is that so?"

msgid "7ac49fa0c0c04827b67907351ae96197"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas teach dharmas that give results, they communicate "
"continuously, and the words they articulate are clearly defined."

msgid "f94d3559300f4d5ca598eb559c118baf"
msgstr "The speech of the tathāgatas makes everything known."

msgid "04e09ff0f29f48a3b9fd13f198fd6904"
msgstr "It generates cognition."

msgid "ffe5a3c6b8cd416f8b6bb4812b0453dd"
msgstr "It is neither lofty nor sordid."

msgid "be0b97e38f464c759eb3f2e51a2c6b64"
msgstr "It is not crooked, unclear, or dishonest."

msgid "ed18c2f2745742b88be101d9397cc5a1"
msgstr "It is not rough, harsh, or distorted."

msgid "d5b4d1bdc0064879857c86abac99dd7e"
msgstr "It is soft, pleasing, and flexible."

msgid "970a5aafea9d40429f5343c8a9f77f1d"
msgstr "It is not inane or prattling, nor is it frantic, hasty, or hurried."

msgid "b26db673d47949beb5d21805a515b510"
msgstr "It is distinct, and the words are clearly defined."

msgid "3107ada6a95e4399bff8b5601815bdda"
msgstr "It is joyous, melodious, and lucid."

msgid "a80ad011687d4538902168dd64f42870"
msgstr "It is unimpeded, perfect, and pleasant."

msgid "12f473b95e874b64bd7899cc403c49ac"
msgstr "It is relevant, renowned, honorable, and beautiful."

msgid "bff998ebdd86460280c55eb316a28f73"
msgstr "It is flawless, impeccable, and pliant."

msgid "e0ce40eade4740a8bca9635e2f823b80"
msgstr "It is stainless, immaculate, and unambiguous."

msgid "7f8ae00ab7c94bf184de8409bbb8413e"
msgstr "It is intelligible, unimpeded, and liberating."

msgid "2cbd8a6e4fb24194ac574d7825d351a0"
msgstr "It is illuminating and straightforward."

msgid "7618081c70e14b1bb6f4d36227edda4d"
msgstr "It is not inferior, disordered, or stammering."

msgid "ab9cdacd42df4e1089223035a091d2d5"
msgstr "It generates bliss, physical well being, and mental delight."

msgid "78c936c27dc84745aede7d1ecce114ca"
msgstr "It pacifies attachment, subdues aversion, and dispels delusion."

msgid "b8c8d7ec4ef440b48fdd5fe499a2884f"
msgstr "It overcomes demons, eliminates evil, and subjugates opponents."

msgid "f05b2972fe874b3c862603713e7e1286"
msgstr "It generates consciousness."

msgid "530236da3bcf4ae3929c106854f22c5d"
msgstr "It sounds like a drum."

msgid "9e545c1f22f547d8b8892f4b2aa316d3"
msgstr "It delights the wise."

msgid "ae2a82b1ce1c4c66a0add17defadc3e4"
msgstr "It sings like a kalaviṅka bird, Śakra, and Brahmā."

msgid "821f5acc2f47431eae346025ea348859"
msgstr "It sounds like ocean waves and thunder."

msgid "7ebc429dd48440c68911abf68547a796"
msgstr "It resonates like the earth."

msgid "61ac258560124d3a88bbd711f393c525"
msgstr "It sounds like a crane, like the calls of a peacock and a cuckoo."

msgid "bada4ca6332844eb9c6c4747d458f254"
msgstr ""
"It sounds like the jīvañjīvaka bird, like the king of geese, and like the "
"king of beasts."

msgid "c1f0fe7d1fe2408a8cc1b161ab4d53aa"
msgstr "It sounds like a vīṇā, the three-stringed vīṇā, and drums."

msgid "17cc7a818aba4bcbab2313a85b2922a6"
msgstr "It sounds like a flute, a conch, and cymbals."

msgid "706e5d5e03ec4c16b748684dc8088eb1"
msgstr "It is informative, instructive, and lucid."

msgid "b5c9d1c7c6f64838a8ad71e280018ff1"
msgstr "It is charming, worth listening to, and profound."

msgid "9cbc6879b55245cabd5e2d102f8e77a0"
msgstr "It is not false."

msgid "07d347fbd541455a8fdcd36bd7347790"
msgstr "It is melodious and generates roots of virtue."

msgid "c406d6a8fce64cd6b670ec0507bce580"
msgstr "Its words and expressions are not degenerate but clearly defined."

msgid "06e085ad280e437e97a387a25ec381bc"
msgstr "It is meaningful and endowed with Dharma."

msgid "78304512c1dc4ef0a739aff8c24629ff"
msgstr "It is timely, always relevant, and appropriate."

msgid "38cf0d6f35b04b80af39b34f52204922"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgatas teach while knowing whose faculties are excellent and whose "
"are not."

msgid "4e6681005aea445689f4e9e3eea530fe"
msgstr ""
"Their speech is embellished by generosity, purified by moral conduct, "
"correctly accomplished through patience, made pliant through vigor, made "
"flexible through concentration, and investigated with insight."

msgid "cc458a684eef4c8a8e52215499c69617"
msgstr "It is taken up with love and undiscouraged because of compassion."

msgid "9f03281f3d644f8a85b9ec72c28fcdf3"
msgstr "It is joyful and radiant."

msgid "8d3d0e05c9ef471aaad446071d6f2688"
msgstr "It discerns with equanimity."

msgid "5a1acd9b13d24ee0a178bcce8a89c687"
msgstr "It establishes the three vehicles."

msgid "8f2dec1c34a442a2a8f0115bac2b03c7"
msgstr "It is the unbroken lineage of the Three Jewels."

msgid "9cf74521119548fa962b12b57747b487"
msgstr "It differentiates the three groups."

msgid "8f3fc5ef4fe64933b912de2f5fd48333"
msgstr "It trains through the three gates of liberation."

msgid "937297faab4146248e4061ec001a8be1"
msgstr "It is entirely suffused by the truth and wisdom."

msgid "9608aa71bc104a1c9b0db8f75f217034"
msgstr "It is not criticized by the wise but praised by the noble ones."

msgid "453c2410c0d047ffb7798947d7d9146a"
msgstr "It reaches to the limits of space and is supreme in all respects."

msgid "0649b9db596e4e2b9e78520179786db3"
msgstr "Son of noble family, the speech of the tathāgatas is like that."

msgid "b7e0a28aa9c7449b888339b69f167b99"
msgstr ""
"That is why all verbal activities of the tathāgatas are said to be preceded "
"and accompanied by wisdom."

msgid "8163f80d266d44d3b906d054867ba5fa"
msgstr "This is the twenty-eighth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "247833b006384aa6acafc6459ca3abbf"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "4fcdd78badc84902b0d161ae5245b4ce"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Their incomparable speech is lucid and stainless with all its splendid "
"qualities."

msgid "73a4e04d061e4465ada51ac598d62482"
msgstr ""
"It radiates throughout a thousand fields, and from a single act of speech "
"many discourses resound."

msgid "86137f1637c946818ea1ccbad32ab7d9"
msgstr ""
"Some people hear the Śrāvaka Vehicle and others the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle."

msgid "07b3bf66100d4f48a647f1d297b22e8a"
msgstr ""
"According to what they have heard, the buddhas, the great beings, Guide "
"their minds toward the corresponding awakening."

msgid "e860db8be6b04165a9cd4f6080971785"
msgstr "“ ‘Their terminology is neither disjointed nor contradictory."

msgid "3a268802b06442c69080d5bcd39010bb"
msgstr "They teach the Dharma without any concepts in their minds."

msgid "da8f2468a71d4e3dbcb79a98f3e6fdfc"
msgstr "Like an echo, which resounds exactly and effortlessly,"

msgid "0d85d32123404178a5ba234dde27964d"
msgstr "The speech of noble beings resonates and satisfies ordinary beings.’"

msgid "08b5c1951041421c8d223c60e1bb220b"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, furthermore, the entire range of the tathāgatas’ "
"mental activity is preceded and accompanied by wisdom."

msgid "d2a62325aa354ee1b85a5df6f869b1ac"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "47849ace36c34cbf8e568bf9eb34c96a"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas are inexpressible in terms of mind, mental activity, or "
"consciousness."

msgid "069ba60eed6a4a338e9fd2aa0f81915e"
msgstr "They are distinguished by wisdom."

msgid "f35b3de115cc44bd8433731d77b72fc8"
msgstr "They are the sovereigns of wisdom."

msgid "46fad76f40434dfc9ace7c96f007200c"
msgstr ""
"The wisdom of the tathāgatas conforms with the minds of all sentient beings."

msgid "2158d8d0af9540c8b0664c3cdf1a5cdc"
msgstr "It engages with the mental activity of all sentient beings."

msgid "5af2f2c23ff240a498b1bda9cd802a2b"
msgstr "It knows the consciousness of all sentient beings."

msgid "be0635626e3548f8b3a6ab6d15b04262"
msgstr "It has resolved all phenomena."

msgid "0e6ae8cad4ec46f0ab38408d96d54205"
msgstr "In all its absorptions, it does not depend on anything else."

msgid "dd00d579f5b945e3b5f50318bc722fb2"
msgstr "It completely transcends objectification."

msgid "29d91a29ec7a42f19b955fb25231d3f5"
msgstr "It is free from conditioned arising."

msgid "0ef6460b277342f5a8cddbd365cf81b4"
msgstr "It has eliminated the three existences."

msgid "7ea178f477624881906843f2e5f09f9c"
msgstr "It has completely transcended any degree of pride."

msgid "4e312897dab7419491244eed30c00138"
msgstr "It is free of all the works of Māra."

msgid "54c51a996e7448faa0860f5bb381d75d"
msgstr "It is not constrained by any deception or pretense."

msgid "4f574d7b1a0c479a95a005c78de95961"
msgstr "It has eschewed clinging to I and mine."

msgid "efc3d612b2f34409a39273da919fe42a"
msgstr ""
"It is free of the faulty vision and darkness of ignorance and delusion."

msgid "1105e51b4109457486b24375a181cbf2"
msgstr "It has completely cultivated the branches of the path."

msgid "703c3a2165fc4526bf5fe8e9d8ffca46"
msgstr "It is nonconceptual like space."

msgid "081f9475cac34496a2d65bc13c7f6eea"
msgstr "It is inseparable from the realm of phenomena."

msgid "97e0989f6a524c7487a508ad25a68115"
msgstr ""
"This is how the tathāgatas’ mental activity is preceded and accompanied by "
"wisdom."

msgid "a30244f32d854a71b6c9bb05d8cdf8a0"
msgstr "This is the twenty-ninth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "bdd79d31e8b948d7b9bfd3787f26d8dc"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "90902a94f12647c582c548db76d3d9de"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The victorious lords of humans cannot be fathomed by mind or thought."

msgid "f609fc4ba5134c7b8f8844dde1e65ba1"
msgstr "Pure wisdom purifies the acts of all the guides."

msgid "ffb89524731f4ca3b1ec94343c24d6db"
msgstr "Sugata wisdom engages equally with the thoughts of all beings,"

msgid "4ebe892dd1cf438c914766dc240e2ea3"
msgstr "While being by nature the realm of phenomena."

msgid "0e45bdfd382d4bf4b39d9b25de5983db"
msgstr "“ ‘It is endowed with all types of concentrations and absorptions."

msgid "e1e95e31e4c14084a5f2b4842c4d7f4a"
msgstr "It is not stirred by any conceptuality of mind or mental activity."

msgid "e2ecc471f3824538ad4f803f3178e474"
msgstr "It is free from Māra’s domain and transcends all of Māra’s works."

msgid "f288e023cb714b78a2a1e3c5ee3dd70f"
msgstr "It uniform, immaculate, and changeless, having the nature of space.’"

msgid "a3bc476381d54f98be294faf7fc3608b"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas’ vision of wisdom has unattached and "
"unobstructed access to the past."

msgid "22a976d97aef4fa59f24051a62c0aaaa"
msgstr "How is that?"

msgid "28aeb406357e4a29affbe22520f26a2c"
msgstr ""
"They know numerically the entire range of buddhafields that have appeared "
"and disappeared in the past."

msgid "e303f534caac419bb08295b178bc9b22"
msgstr ""
"They know each and every blade of grass, each bush, herb, and forest in "
"those buddhafields."

msgid "99992df23d734e6f80b6c5419f3832d9"
msgstr ""
"They know each and every gathering of creatures designated as beings in "
"those buddhafields."

msgid "ebae292d831d4a11bd10a602d46d307a"
msgstr "They know each and every type of conduct of those beings."

msgid "0b4e9c8eac8a45fa8285e782cc7c3999"
msgstr ""
"They know each and every buddha that has emerged in those buddhafields."

msgid "5f057e36e4f241cb88e26830ca427a37"
msgstr "They know each and every dharma taught and expressed by each buddha."

msgid "9598637ea8ef4cbb95905787259c6b24"
msgstr ""
"They know each and every being tamed in the Śrāvaka Vehicle and the "
"Pratyekabuddha Vehicle, as well as those tamed in the Great Vehicle."

msgid "6aa5920608e54bb4b19ffc69321a6d81"
msgstr ""
"They know all the distinguishing features of the buddhafields, the different"
" monastic congregations, and the range of lifespans, as well as the "
"different categories of Dharma."

msgid "8b27416fb181473ead1132a9f8fc5090"
msgstr ""
"They know of each inhalation and exhalation and of the enjoyment of "
"excellent food."

msgid "002c320698fa4f6096785a960cc245af"
msgstr ""
"“The tathāgatas know the forms of all past beings, their deaths, and their "
"rebirths."

msgid "a9a1b1eb2bb14e6a86e30418a64ddfe9"
msgstr ""
"They know their various faculties, activities, and mentalities. They know "
"their mindstreams."

msgid "f567102cb2fb416b9510f91d9c0bd642"
msgstr ""
"They know numerically each and every mental state that has arisen based on a"
" previous mental state, both through direct and indirect cognition."

msgid "0820750a874642dd8b87c1704c619567"
msgstr "They also observe the past mindstreams of previous tathāgatas."

msgid "7c489f8803b642f9b913a1bff83bb95f"
msgstr ""
"With such wisdom, the tathāgatas teach the Dharma to beings continuously in "
"accordance with their ways of thinking."

msgid "585928abb30a4b64981d21a4b8757eba"
msgstr "This is the thirtieth tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "da947e93b47441189f35d10f68b533ba"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "a7ff3237eb1248b88c8f746e04854233"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘With regard to the fields, beings, and Dharma taught, Buddha wisdom is "
"unattached and immeasurable."

msgid "15d76077ae46491ab59c832dcadb5f41"
msgstr "The number of beings liberated by the guides"

msgid "4d33a366f33b4947982c04ada80abb1f"
msgstr "And the number of monastic congregations in the fields,"

msgid "c798da315a31465ea96ced8dfccd153c"
msgstr "“ ‘The thoughts and faculties of beings,"

msgid "20903312ebf54c5595accb786d87a189"
msgstr "Their grades of physical form, speech, and mind,"

msgid "b1de46b91b5145928979ac713bba6bc3"
msgstr "Their names and behavior and all past events—"

msgid "9566251ceeb94bdb91e674f42a5e0f51"
msgstr "These the perfect buddhas behold and realize.’"

msgid "9ad089cf1c0f4898a000e4fa2ee83747"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, the tathāgatas’ vision of wisdom has unattached and "
"unobstructed access to the future."

msgid "b86d561197ef422288c8d5f67ca20e35"
msgstr "How is that?"

msgid "c67ee7d9cbfc46e29a32b952a63e2c40"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas know each and every being, Dharma, and field that will arise "
"and cease in the future, its arising and disappearance."

msgid "b7b3ce6c8442431f965c2f21a93b8930"
msgstr ""
"They know each and every destruction by fire or water of the eons to come, "
"each and every buddhafield that will come into being, the total amount of "
"earth in those buddhafields, each and every particle of dust, blade of "
"grass, bush, herb, and forest, and each and every constellation of stars."

msgid "fd9ffa3710074742bf8a680699b09470"
msgstr ""
"“They know each and every buddha that will appear in each of those infinite "
"buddhafields, each and every śrāvaka, pratyekabuddha, and bodhisattva, each "
"and every enjoyment of excellent food, and each and every instance of "
"inhalation, exhalation, walking, sitting, and conduct."

msgid "d372667fef8a42d495104b468124bf26"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas know each and every being in those infinite realms who will "
"be liberated by means of the Śrāvaka Vehicle, the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle, "
"and the Great Vehicle."

msgid "0dd116a5af8e43a6adcb58bda9729124"
msgstr ""
"They know the lifespan of each and every being in each of those infinite "
"fields, as well as each and every mind and mental event to come."

msgid "8c27be23ef914701b21441b5628b874b"
msgstr ""
"Moreover, they teach the Dharma to beings while observing the future, "
"without the future mindstream of tathāgatas being interrupted."

msgid "c5d728e278f84e3f95aa4bfc6b156671"
msgstr "This is the thirty-first tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "25e2c325f0d540aebcc0db703d1ce85d"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "6bbefb80f860482ca6dc2eff685ce0fa"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘With their stainless vision, The buddhas are fully aware Of any event "
"that will appear and disappear in the future, As well as each and every "
"victor throughout the buddhafields."

msgid "cc4bb3c0d9c6417b9803aaf8416916e4"
msgstr "“ ‘As they set their sights upon future events,"

msgid "7813d1abdd3843529d943b4a7b796c0b"
msgstr "Their minds are never distracted."

msgid "726d08afbe094d088db4433272795635"
msgstr "They teach beings the Dharma accordingly."

msgid "977402ed1237460d82a16b2847fc693d"
msgstr "This is the liberating activity of the supreme beings.’"

msgid "1de0b62176e743d4972c36f5e6370acb"
msgstr ""
" “Furthermore, son of noble family, the tathāgatas’ vision of wisdom has "
"unattached and unobstructed access to the present."

msgid "41611516ee534237b8958800622f4770"
msgstr "How is that?"

msgid "64fedf6590ce4179a7f7c9ba63889950"
msgstr ""
"The tathāgatas know in a threefold manner the number of all the present "
"buddhafields in the ten directions."

msgid "b333b3fd710d4e0d842ad51aca250c5b"
msgstr ""
"They know all the present buddhas, all of the present bodhisattvas, all of "
"the present śrāvakas, and all of the present pratyekabuddhas."

msgid "bc387dc8a9ba4b0f8f69648b408a48fe"
msgstr "“They know all the present constellations of stars."

msgid "bd13237e2a4a4954b5a627eff009e1fc"
msgstr "They know the present blades of grass, bushes, herbs, and forests."

msgid "8df02876a38544308c454e463c0c8894"
msgstr ""
"They know numerically all the dust particles of the earth element being "
"crushed into pieces right now in the ten directions."

msgid "fd9357cb6a2e4fd491f9456793fa3625"
msgstr ""
"They know numerically all the minutest drops of the water element in the ten"
" directions."

msgid "b8e568f3c3b24ee4981b6aea5668ba6a"
msgstr ""
"They know numerically all the sparks of the fire element flickering in the "
"ten directions."

msgid "b3de7797fe2f48c3a4f082108fd1e8cb"
msgstr ""
"They know numerically all the gusts of wind forming in the ten directions."

msgid "c729c1af751f4fd18ae5d3831281644b"
msgstr ""
"They know numerically all the minutest extensions of space in the ten "
"directions."

msgid "6ff6f3495cca4e66b1bca2360ab75cc8"
msgstr "“They know the three aspects of the realms of beings in the present:"

msgid "d497e931cee74f2b957bf9931880543c"
msgstr ""
"They know the realms of beings currently dwelling in hell, the causes of "
"their birth, and the causes of their liberation."

msgid "1da81f970d134ace9fa7007e874a237d"
msgstr ""
"They know the realms of beings currently reborn as animals, the causes of "
"their birth, and the causes of their liberation."

msgid "efc4a0ee7e2946e28e8eb4405477a615"
msgstr ""
"They know the realms of beings currently in the world of Yama, the causes of"
" their birth, and the causes of their liberation."

msgid "99465ae371174e5abd435233a8c8f7f0"
msgstr ""
"They know the realms of beings who have become human, the causes of their "
"birth, and the causes of their liberation."

msgid "de9684fee5d3440dae837681d4309e47"
msgstr ""
"They know the realms of beings who are currently gods, the causes of their "
"birth, and the causes of their liberation."

msgid "8cf5b19758674cce8bb09c1fdc8fc5b2"
msgstr ""
"They know the mindstreams of present sentient beings, their afflictive "
"emotions, and their lack of afflictive emotions."

msgid "15936680577c4a418e453143c78a9987"
msgstr ""
"They know the faculties of present beings fit to be tamed and those who are "
"not fit to be tamed."

msgid "17cf1721885b4d809c425caa0a8f1310"
msgstr ""
"“Even though the tathāgatas know in this manner, they have no consciousness "
"that pursues dualities, and they teach the Dharma to beings in order to "
"introduce them to nonduality."

msgid "746e4bfb253240a3a26fa9584aeafd78"
msgstr "This is the thirty-second tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas."

msgid "3be1dc2bf17f4a789e36abed07fd344a"
msgstr "About this it has been proclaimed:"

msgid "bb3574d9fb63439ea1ff167de9252666"
msgstr "“ ‘The sphere of activity of the victors is infinite."

msgid "0f80de920e494a4892d36b878894e5e3"
msgstr "It is immeasurable, unfathomable, and inconceivable,"

msgid "c7924ea78bb248138c8970bb17f52a03"
msgstr "Equal to space and beyond compare."

msgid "11f8ab7a183b41989c1002d201d2fb7f"
msgstr "No one is capable of knowing it."

msgid "1dddce7584804d8dbf90ff6282af755a"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The victors know fully Each and every action performed by beings In the "
"present moment, throughout the ten directions."

msgid "3c23665a483f4ccc8f7226214a9a40d4"
msgstr "This is the supreme activity of the spontaneously arisen ones.’"

msgid "702bfcbff6534bbc81d86c29cac2ad46"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, these are the thirty-two tathāgata activities."

msgid "ee225e708efe428e97ed24594c0ef20e"
msgstr "With these the tathāgatas tame the masses of beings."

msgid "d9b843ca5c51496ebe5141f1fd175e16"
msgstr ""
"Even though the tathāgata activities are immeasurable, they are presented in"
" abbreviated form in order to guide beings."

msgid "019ff291d24c48e281311abb566a9753"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, the tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas is "
"immeasurable."

msgid "69a90946188b4952a185397c2d6ebecf"
msgstr "It is inconceivable."

msgid "da65697d8b6948629fe00722c7b87302"
msgstr ""
"It remains unknowable to the whole world, indescribable by language, and "
"hard for others to achieve."

msgid "6a395ea9ad4e40c490b853d6cb7a34a8"
msgstr ""
"It exists unceasingly in all buddhafields, conforms equally to all buddhas, "
"and completely transcends all efforts."

msgid "353c382fc638449ba923e6f1efda5e01"
msgstr "It is nonconceptual since it is equal to space."

msgid "9dce65d26c0e48e193927abab98b357b"
msgstr ""
"Since it is the action of the realm of phenomena, it does not act in a "
"differentiated way."

msgid "339deb9aecbd4b53afe148aacdb83c8d"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "94127562bf3549e2ae6f8a3ca7e71577"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, the blessed buddhas do not appear in order to deliver "
"differentiated discourses."

msgid "5baf386bc3e64132b1b60bd3918a975b"
msgstr ""
"Nor, indeed, do they appear in order to deliver discourses that "
"differentiate beings, buddhafields, dharmas, intentions, liberations, or "
"types of nirvāṇa."

msgid "590651f52a7b483994fca78063739ffd"
msgstr ""
"Rather, upon attaining complete and perfect buddhahood, the tathāgatas—who "
"are of one taste with the realm of phenomena, who are unobstructed, and who "
"provide opportunity to all beings—set in motion the unobstructed wheel of "
"the Dharma—the irreversible wheel of the Dharma—so that beings may "
"comprehend the Dharma."

msgid "af912635f84241489b4afe248a253134"
msgstr ""
"“Consider, son of noble family, the analogy of an expert jeweler who knows "
"the procedure for purifying gems."

msgid "0c1f80f4cfdb49cca0ff907e737bc518"
msgstr ""
"He picks out a rough gem from a mine and rinses it in a strong soda "
"solution."

msgid "8c28d508291742658e13153677b917ef"
msgstr ""
"He then polishes it with a cloth made of black hair. But his efforts do not "
"stop there."

msgid "1ce1024e13034263a6bc439b36d375ba"
msgstr ""
"Next he rinses the gem in a strong quicksilver solution and polishes it with"
" sawdust and woolen cloth."

msgid "47f21ddb37db4fb3bd74d2686f0d6c17"
msgstr "But his efforts do not stop there."

msgid "463527275874442e971b83ef0a446a73"
msgstr ""
"Finally he rinses it in a great purifying liquid and polishes it with the "
"finest cotton."

msgid "a7341a8c49c94baaadbf9063d3976dbd"
msgstr ""
"Once he has polished it and separated it from the lesser quartz, it may "
"thenceforth be called beryl."

msgid "a3c6bedd4dfc4882b3fd33f80e1ac9f2"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, son of noble family, when the tathāgatas know the masses "
"of completely impure beings, they cause beings who delight in saṃsāra to "
"experience revulsion through discourses on impermanence, suffering, no self,"
" and unattractiveness, which provoke revulsion."

msgid "20788f4bf6d94a2f848693feb617e0ae"
msgstr ""
"Then, they cause them to enter the Dharma and Vinaya of the noble ones."

msgid "6921ac316e9f42f29c21d8ad0a6cfcbc"
msgstr "But the efforts of the tathāgatas do not stop there."

msgid "dcf40c39fb854b3ab55d21d81b6b9389"
msgstr ""
"Next, they cause beings to comprehend the way of the tathāgatas through "
"discourses on emptiness, signlessness, and wishlessness."

msgid "75c95af9393a49ddb96c89360f87ef83"
msgstr "But the efforts of the tathāgatas do not stop there."

msgid "b429a5bd8ef349ed8f75eeae6a92d49d"
msgstr ""
"Finally, they guide beings into the domain of the tathāgatas through "
"discourses known as The Irreversible Wheel of the Dharma and The "
"Purification of the Triple Sphere."

msgid "617ebab2fc5c48ab88e1a84d1d4d8037"
msgstr ""
"Once beings with their various causes and natures have entered equality, "
"they comprehend the true nature of the tathāgatas and may thenceforth be "
"called unsurpassed recipients of generosity."

msgid "6486f29a12684ec0b62ab3c24ba38bfc"
msgstr ""
"“Therefore, son of noble family, you should understand by way of this "
"exposition that tathāgata activity is inconceivable, universally applicable,"
" flawless in every way, and attuned with the three times, and that it "
"constitutes the unbroken continuity of the lineage of the Three Jewels."

msgid "e5c9190045d143fd8ad950b116fbe91d"
msgstr "The tathāgatas abide in inconceivable tathāgata activity."

msgid "6e795f0fc42c479e8c7196b70ac0cfc6"
msgstr "They do not discard their space-like bodies."

msgid "48ac393e7846437f94caee6153d93769"
msgstr "They teach in all buddhafields."

msgid "72e9754fa5d3446d8b4464400fd27d9a"
msgstr "They do not eschew words that communicate the inexpressible Dharma."

msgid "6ce0e5b259214883b7e05bdc9b35533d"
msgstr ""
"Rather, they teach the Dharma to sentient being by causing them to "
"understand how things really are."

msgid "756602563c2449d7b1fc5ed0390dae16"
msgstr ""
"They know the minds of all beings to be without objectification, and they "
"know the thoughts in their minds."

msgid "84ada54942b645259a5ba24fe55d6177"
msgstr ""
"The blessed buddhas appear in order to purify the bodhisattva intention."

msgid "21122c853bae4fed88794a465bed8b40"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, this unceasing and uninterrupted continuity, this "
"unbroken continuity, this unbroken continuity of discourses that prophesy "
"bodhisattvas constitutes the tathāgata activity of the tathāgatas.”"

msgid "1de1a102ba1540c6912d03e79bb92f49"
msgstr ""
"When this exposition of tathāgata activity had been delivered, the "
"unfathomable, innumerable, and uncountable buddhafields of the ten "
"directions shook six times."

msgid "4d4fc1533f124676beb7e08ce48641e1"
msgstr "They shone brightly and were sprinkled with flower petals."

msgid "a89f1f88835543dbb8eaaf110bd9f8c7"
msgstr ""
"When each and every one of the radiant and resplendent gods, nāgas, yakṣas, "
"gandharvas, asuras, garuḍas, kiṃnaras, mahoragas, humans, nonhumans, monks "
"and nuns, and male and female lay practitioners who had assembled in the "
"pavilion Jeweled Array heard the present Dharma discourse explaining "
"tathāgata activity, they all grew content, pleased, and delighted."

msgid "df5640e4a72c418690625ccb46a63e1b"
msgstr ""
"As an act of worship to the Tathāgata, they offered flowers, fragrance, "
"incense, garlands, lotions, powders, religious robes, canopies, victory "
"banners, and various types of draped banners."

msgid "192dd9f0682e43e2918a17bdb28a70f0"
msgstr ""
"They played cymbals and other musical instruments and sang melodious songs "
"in veneration of the blessed ones."

msgid "a8b70a902a8a45e09d0f99deec21990b"
msgstr "They scattered flowers over the crown of his head."

msgid "d76423cc691f466cbfe5e68785b0b9d2"
msgstr ""
"They sprinkled spherical ornaments, earrings, armlets, jewel necklaces, "
"pearl necklaces, crescent-shaped adornments, muslin ornaments, mongoose "
"decorations, rings, bangles, decorations shaped like the leaves of a tala "
"tree, ornaments interwoven with flowers, shoulder ornaments, anklets, long "
"necklaces, head ornaments, hand jewelry, and ornaments for the ears and "
"feet."

msgid "9d3300b7050142068f08344388a6f44a"
msgstr ""
"The assembly also spread out precious stones of beryl, gold from the Jambu "
"River, precious stones of emerald, red gems, sapphires, fire-colored gems, "
"gems with brilliant light, and multicolored gems."

msgid "553f226cef9743ea9b7a5ebf5a826553"
msgstr ""
"They scattered gold and silver dust as well as fragrant aloe powder, "
"incense, sandalwood powder, benzoin powder, red sandalwood powder, and lotus"
" powder."

msgid "8685f0ae62f04cd2b6897f473d2af08e"
msgstr ""
"They tossed celestial flowers, including different kinds of mandārava "
"flowers, mahāmandārava flowers, coral-tree flowers, mañjūṣaka flowers, "
"mahāmañjūṣaka flowers, roca flowers, mahāroca flowers, sthala flowers, "
"mahāsthala flowers, cakra flowers, stainless cakra flowers, hundred-petaled "
"lotus flowers, thousand-petaled lotus flowers, hundred-thousand-petaled "
"lotus flowers, bright flowers, sweet-smelling flowers, exceedingly beautiful"
" flowers, flowers resembling starlight, luminous flowers, multicolored "
"flowers, and other similar flowers."

msgid "acef0cb1615f463a90301c23c60b167b"
msgstr ""
"They proceeded to scatter water-borne flowers, such as the blue lotus, "
"lotus, water lily, and white lotus."

msgid "0edcb7944cef4052be9b6cdead4c5238"
msgstr ""
"They scattered soil-grown flowers, such as jasmine flowers, pariṣaka "
"flowers, flowers from the harimantha tree, magnolia flowers, aśoka flowers, "
"dhanuskari flowers, pāṭala flowers, and flowers from the mucilinda tree."

msgid "67e68cfbe81c445a8ff1462cef21b3cd"
msgstr ""
"Finally, they played all kinds of musical instruments and drums, including "
"small drums, flutes, bass drums, conches, kettle drums, gongs, and cymbals."

msgid "e619e32491d9435ba0fdffa581755680"
msgstr "They sang different kinds of melodious songs."

msgid "4ce448631dfe4a9e85fcac0a19f33b91"
msgstr ""
"They rained down showers of incense, powders, jewelry, ornaments, pearl "
"necklaces, and fine garments, along with the sounds of cymbals large and "
"small."

msgid "4a995633d9b64ed98f6199692fe64968"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattvas who had gathered from the various worlds of the ten "
"directions rose into the sky above them and, as an act of worship to the "
"Blessed One, sacrificed their own bodies."

msgid "c8ce8a5e592e4217b475a8c54eee5af5"
msgstr ""
"As soon as they had done so, they bedecked the entire pavilion Jeweled Array"
" from the sky."

msgid "bfac953d06e248b787dd74c112edd17e"
msgstr ""
"It became embellished with many pearl necklaces arrayed as latticework of "
"dangling jewels, decorated with checkered designs, carefully arranged, "
"adorned with a net of small and large bells, and embellished with lotus "
"flowers made of jewels."

msgid "177da2b76aaa415ea14af7baaf0d0afe"
msgstr ""
"From each individual pearl of those necklaces, unfathomably innumerable "
"bodhisattva bodies emerged."

msgid "c38f4e35e9c54dfc9719872592cb2cdc"
msgstr ""
"They circumambulated the Blessed One seven times and sat down on lion "
"thrones of lotus flowers with jeweled designs."

msgid "5deb761c106b48eb9a52e04c14474a57"
msgstr ""
"As an act of worship to this Dharma discourse, immeasurably many blessed "
"buddhas from the immeasurably many buddhafields of the ten directions sent "
"forth into the world realm Endurance arrays of offerings, accomplished by "
"each tathāgata, known as free-flowing utterances lasting for eons."

msgid "193a102a35964e4eb7500a7073b3c620"
msgstr ""
"Through the power of the Buddha these arrays arrived in this world realm "
"Endurance and beautified the pavilion Jeweled Array with supreme "
"embellishment."

msgid "8e8fc53f37b84c4982a91a0bb1a2a079"
msgstr ""
"From among this retinue, immeasurably many beings generated the mind of "
"unsurpassed, complete and perfect awakening, and immeasurably many "
"bodhisattvas attained acceptance of the nonorigination of phenomena."

msgid "e3741fc90af64255bd97a838a038479b"
msgstr ""
"At that point, the Blessed One surveyed the entire bodhisattva assembly with"
" his elephantine gaze and said the following:"

msgid "a10c39afbee44c0c822feb280c7c9d12"
msgstr ""
"“This inconceivable array of ornaments offered by you, noble beings, which "
"is blessed by the bodhisattva’s meditative absorption and bestowed by the "
"tathāgatas, is not constructed, is not disorderly, does not grow old, and "
"does not deteriorate."

msgid "6924e797e17a41eaaedbae8a3416a348"
msgstr ""
"Sixteen years after the Tathāgata Maitreya reaches perfect buddhahood, and "
"while he resides in the pavilion Jeweled Array, when this Dharma discourse "
"of the Great Assembly chapter from The Gateway to Unobstructed Deliverance "
"through the Bodhisattva Way of Life is taught in detail, and a congregation "
"of bodhisattvas endowed with teachings and all qualities assembles, who will"
" delight in making these offerings to the Tathāgata Maitreya as well as to "
"all the tathāgatas of this Good Eon?”"

msgid "c5ea9aee78244835b66b8999fa72d914"
msgstr ""
"Thereupon, a bodhisattva named Sovereign of the Magical Display of All "
"Phenomena, seated amidst the assembled retinue, rose from his lotus seat, "
"placed his right knee in the heart of the lotus, joined his palms together, "
"and bowed toward the Blessed One."

msgid "b6f8eaa4f40c45de804d77ecc0244af2"
msgstr ""
"He supplicated the Blessed One and said, “Blessed One, I will delight in "
"offering this array of ornaments, which is not constructed, is not "
"disorderly, does not grow old, and does not deteriorate, to the Tathāgata "
"Maitreya, as well as to all those other tathāgata, arhat, completely and "
"perfectly awakened buddhas of the Good Eon who are not present here.”"

msgid "bb7679805ed540e3a12f82984f369337"
msgstr ""
"At that time, a being called Magical Display of Māra, hailing from the four-"
"continent world system Susthita and seated in that very retinue, asked the "
"bodhisattva Sovereign of the Magical Display of All Phenomena,"

msgid "cf01a8e002b840c68e53c0bbf890f6d7"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, how long can any receptacle of yours preserve this "
"array and keep it from getting old?”"

msgid "7aa63723ab6244b4a2774f6f9b217409"
msgstr "The bodhisattva replied,"

msgid "ce7783af2683487d9f2b47e631cc508e"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, every receptacle is fragile and liable to break."

msgid "d824975a34e7459285efec12686a05a3"
msgstr ""
"Only space is indestructible and not liable to break. Therefore, the "
"receptacle of space is the best of all."

msgid "f7909c4e284d4af1abe9c2e933912f47"
msgstr ""
"My friend, look at my body without closing your eyes, and you will see a "
"great receptacle.”"

msgid "a43911db9ca64d089167a62dfa73c9b0"
msgstr ""
"Magical Display of Māra gazed at the body of the bodhisattva with his eyes "
"wide open."

msgid "ad5434fbf89f4156b54c6dd372d97c89"
msgstr ""
"He saw a world sphere called Appearance of the Sovereign of Water in the "
"maṇḍala at the navel center of the bodhisattva’s body and asked,"

msgid "f077547e3941429eb9d80845a335b225"
msgstr ""
"“Why is that world sphere called Appearance as the Sovereign of Water?”"

msgid "191f73b6236c49f6b8e24521cf9e1e95"
msgstr "“Because it is full of water. It looks just like an ocean."

msgid "6f0fb19bcf3a4867b63a774407eba400"
msgstr ""
"In that sphere lives a tathāgata known as Glory of Precious Blue Lotus."

msgid "500853bf03354ee2bb71fd96dd0896a8"
msgstr "He dwells there and teaches the Dharma to passing bodhisattvas."

msgid "2b0504e6ddb24422a4a20aeabe7a4bbe"
msgstr ""
"From that vast reservoir of water emerges a lotus with jeweled designs on "
"which are seated a blessed one and bodhisattvas.”"

msgid "64289bbb83444e569370e5e96e378ad9"
msgstr ""
"Magical Display of Māra joined his palms together to salute the bodhisattva,"
" who asked him,"

msgid "eee69e0ece0442de88e47592e67fd694"
msgstr "“My friend, do you see the receptacle of the bodhisattvas?”"

msgid "66906348c12f440b947f7a3f2b860a0e"
msgstr "He replied, “Yes, I see it."

msgid "6e47f20dd53046f497e753f953dc99c5"
msgstr ""
"Noble being, with such a receptacle as this, will you be able to preserve a "
"great jeweled design without it wasting away or getting old for billions of "
"eons?”"

msgid "1673a7d6b2f947a39efb3522e0e11ccf"
msgstr ""
"At that point, Magical Display of Māra saluted the Blessed One and said,"

msgid "1fa3ef20a8e54f70852f89c80014b904"
msgstr "“Blessed One, I have never seen this noble person before."

msgid "894f81b088b649d0b0e58a67e160b0a0"
msgstr ""
"Since I have never heard this Dharma discourse either, I wonder now, how "
"will I pass quickly beyond sorrow by means of the Śrāvaka Vehicle?"

msgid "e6c5e6c8bc964531aba4d1f7ff900ed7"
msgstr ""
"Now that I have heard this discourse and witnessed the miraculous power of "
"the bodhisattva called Magical Display of All Phenomena, I will generate "
"with determination the mind of unsurpassed, complete and perfect awakening."

msgid "d6b934c82fa545ddb4a33e5e93d0744c"
msgstr ""
"Blessed One, even beings who burn in hell for as many eons as there are "
"grains of sand in the river Ganges will eventually awaken to unsurpassed, "
"complete and perfect awakening. Therefore, I will never give up such "
"unsurpassed, complete and perfect awakening!”"

msgid "2f10c402661b4323bb0a39405d932d45"
msgstr "The Blessed One replied, “Excellent!"

msgid "36c507dc601c4d5f89dd0411f5e7a68a"
msgstr ""
"It is excellent that you, O noble being, now wear the armor of unsurpassed, "
"complete and perfect awakening and possess the blessing of miraculous "
"power.”"

msgid "637c32f147ca4790ab88617265f01703"
msgstr ""
"At that point a bodhisattva called Siṃhaketu, who was also present in the "
"assembled retinue, said to Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja,"

msgid "54e6b9b5bf4d450f8e9d5fc9008871a4"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, when bodhisattvas are established in dhāraṇīs, they "
"retain all that the buddhas say, and when they teach the Dharma it becomes "
"inexhaustible."

msgid "1800283620d24294946b8f8c458430dc"
msgstr ""
"Explaining it carefully, they satisfy all beings. What are the bodhisattva "
"dhāraṇīs?”"

msgid "80d9f6c468294aaca69b7dc89fb06429"
msgstr "Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja replied,"

msgid "4f6f4b4d23794a61acb14a6d37831bde"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, when bodhisattvas are established in dhāraṇīs, they "
"retain all that the blessed buddhas say, and when they teach the Dharma it "
"becomes inexhaustible."

msgid "e4bbce067466468caede6e8f55508a22"
msgstr "Since they explain it carefully, they satisfy all beings."

msgid "cbb310f8bc964edc9e342f16dc3be9fb"
msgstr "The bodhisattva dhāraṇīs are eight:"

msgid "6a32326f321643a280132676b4a74369"
msgstr ""
"the  pure melody dhāraṇī,  inexhaustible basket dhāraṇī,  limitless "
"enfoldment dhāraṇī,  ocean mudrā dhāraṇī,  lotus array dhāraṇī,  entering "
"the gate of nonattachment dhāraṇī,  entering ascertainment by discriminating"
" knowledge dhāraṇī, and  blessing of the buddha ornaments dhāraṇī."

msgid "c07807c32b8442048c05030befa8e646"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, these are the eight bodhisattva dhāraṇīs."

msgid "cc7b4f8e4f0646c8bf55f2757091dfd4"
msgstr ""
"Once bodhisattvas are established in these dhāraṇīs, they retain all that "
"the buddhas say,"

msgid "9339d94bf8744c2e85a7015055c78883"
msgstr "and when they teach the Dharma it becomes inexhaustible."

msgid "261768b9912e447690904a3cda12bea5"
msgstr "Since they explain it carefully, they satisfy all beings.”"

msgid "9bde3418d3dc4e5bb1ddce83a892cd6e"
msgstr "Then Siṃhaketu entreated Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja,"

msgid "f653a8ec82fa4b9c8f68d3bd39dbc0a0"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, be eloquent and teach the introduction to the detailed"
" classification of these dhāraṇīs that lead to zeal, in order that the "
"bodhisattvas who hear this introduction will attain these dhāraṇīs.”"

msgid "b559823f931e450b8fd90f807bcd7fe2"
msgstr "Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja replied,"

msgid "6e75f7fc256d4401aac01ba42b8d280c"
msgstr ""
"“For that reason, son of noble family, listen carefully and keep in mind the"
" introduction to the detailed classification of these dhāraṇīs that I will "
"now explain to you."

msgid "9fe7404f5f8040609c6f9ab6b5133428"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may ask, ‘What is the pure melody dhāraṇī?’"

msgid "d46e1bf654cd4d2db030605ca3bf730c"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, when established in this bodhisattva dhāraṇī, since it "
"is a completely pure gateway for entering nonattachment, one firmly abides "
"with a mind that is centered."

msgid "d6d026cc79b746d895b120514e704470"
msgstr ""
"After one has gained certainty due to the blessings of the Dharma teaching, "
"as one teaches the Dharma the melody of the Dharma generates understanding "
"in a single buddhafield."

msgid "b8e76c635284412f8170699e0d6e1f35"
msgstr ""
"The melody generates understanding in two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, "
"thirty, forty, fifty, or one hundred buddhafields."

msgid "a9f67c7bc28348e08b97714e8993d582"
msgstr ""
"It generates understanding in one thousand buddhafields, in ten, twenty, "
"thirty, forty, fifty, or up to one hundred thousand buddhafields."

msgid "210ed357642f4903b107770d778abfb2"
msgstr "Its melody creates understanding in billions of buddhafields."

msgid "a83090f6d9dc48f6a8a3d71901d6b2d0"
msgstr "It magically creates a lion throne that reaches as high as one krośa."

msgid "c5301b25ae3b4f6a998c91759643df53"
msgstr "One sits down on it and teaches the Dharma."

msgid "21f659b9fd3d4de58b7d1f9085097c43"
msgstr ""
"Likewise, in order to satisfy the interests of devoted beings, one magically"
" creates a lion throne that reaches as high as half a yojana, a full yojana,"
" Mount Meru, or the Brahmā realm."

msgid "e43e63c22c43489eabf6f25694af7b05"
msgstr "One sits down on it and teaches the Dharma."

msgid "72abf7e7d4f249df91f4be1a5ce6b532"
msgstr ""
"“While seated on the lion throne, all the buddhas of the ten directions "
"appear."

msgid "5c35610d24304b1193500475d72548fd"
msgstr "One hears all the dharmas that the blessed buddhas explain."

msgid "c111f3a289e3479ba327cfa9fcd7cd81"
msgstr ""
"Having heard them, one retains all of them through the power of dhāraṇī and "
"does not forget them."

msgid "da5738d0309445b5ab143adce07be765"
msgstr ""
"Such dharmas cause one to experience the meaning of each of the dharmas."

msgid "ead2ee73905a4b5190d332ada0d860bd"
msgstr ""
"Listening to other dharmas does not prevent one from teaching the Dharma."

msgid "ddcaab60985e42baaba00cd678d6ce18"
msgstr ""
"Teaching the Dharma does not prevent one from listening to the Dharma."

msgid "57e28208909e4007995efe0903f04397"
msgstr ""
"By engaging in the sound of a single syllable, one engages in the sounds of "
"all syllables."

msgid "2ba18ff3a5c045c78667b5cf310d381d"
msgstr ""
"Thus, by uttering the first letter a, infinite doors to the Dharma are "
"expressed."

msgid "4933211923ff446fb97aa72681100f68"
msgstr ""
"“All phenomena are without coming because they never come, unmoving because "
"they never depart, nonabiding because they are never present, natureless "
"because they are primordially pure, rootless because they are primordially "
"unborn, limitless because they never occur, and without depletion because "
"they are never in motion."

msgid "9c8c6e8b3eb642bc87c2183c8bd71e81"
msgstr ""
"All phenomena are unborn because they are without conditioning, nonarising "
"because they have no creator, without origination because they are unmoving,"
" without discord because they are reciprocally intertwined, unceasing "
"because they are without agency, unmoving because they are wishless, free of"
" elaboration because they are unthinkable and nonconceptual, inexpressible "
"because they have engaged all sound, unutterable because they are soundless,"
" indemonstrable because they do not endure in any form, unconstructed "
"because they are unthinkable, without conceit because they are "
"unestablished, unconceited because they undeceiving, and imperceptible "
"because they are equal to space."

msgid "04d668f9c2eb44c6a40755eab4e15cac"
msgstr ""
"“All phenomena are beyond conventional terms because they have no means of "
"expression, without arising because they do not abide in any object, unborn "
"because they do not abide in any place, primordially pure because they lack "
"afflictive emotions, without self because they lack a nature of their own, "
"without sentient beings because they are primordially pure, without life "
"because of the absence of faculties, without individuality because they are "
"aimless, and primordially empty because of inner peace."

msgid "761c390cc9064d25bfb5a3eda3f7d141"
msgstr ""
"“All phenomena are beyond conceptual signs because they are without "
"limitations, wishless because they lack grasping, without conditioning "
"because they are unconditioned, unconditioned because they completely "
"transcend presence and absence, exceptional because they do not rely on "
"anything external, without acceptance because they are without "
"appropriation, without rejection because they are without abandonment, "
"natureless because they are without bodies, lacking aspects because they are"
" pure, actionless because they lack an agent, without maturation because "
"they lack transmigration, and without anguish because of the absence of any "
"seeds."

msgid "3d436a525dff4b90bb580b1289457f16"
msgstr ""
"“All phenomena are signless because of the absence of apprehending, without "
"wrong acts because they are not bound, unbound because they are not "
"established, unestablished because they are not created, uncontaminated "
"because they are not subject to contamination, unoriginated because they are"
" primordially without origin, clear because they lack remedies, lacking "
"remedies because they lack differentiated aspects, without materiality "
"because they do not originate from the great elements, lacking feeling "
"because of the absence of feeling, lacking perception because they "
"completely transcend the pathways of perception, lacking formations because "
"they are free of craving, and lacking consciousness because of the absence "
"of discriminating knowledge."

msgid "ad0e5eb75e6f47fdac8843d283b85d3c"
msgstr ""
"“All phenomena lack elements because they are like the space element, "
"without guidance because they completely transcend the path of objects, "
"without objects because they are unmoving, without desire because they are "
"not falsely imagined, without form because they are without engagement, not "
"formless because they are not determined, not disordered because they are "
"devoid of disorder, inconceivable because they cannot be apprehended, "
"without mental activity because they are indivisible into duality, "
"unapprehendable because they completely transcend the path of objects, "
"without a substratum because they are impermanent, noneternal because they "
"are not in disharmony with a support, nameless because they lack conceptual "
"signs, unmixed because there is no relative continuity, without foundation "
"because they are foundationless, inexpressible because they have nothing to "
"regret, lacking regret because they are free of sin, without karmic traces "
"because they are stainless, stainless because they are primordially pure, "
"and primordially pure because of the absence of afflictive emotions."

msgid "f17f995477434b0fa47727cb9f8dcf0b"
msgstr ""
"“All phenomena are without afflictive emotions because they lack support, "
"without support because they lack deception, without deception because they "
"enter nonattachment, entering into nonattachment because they are "
"unobscured, unobscured because they are like space, like space because they "
"are without conceptuality, immaterial because they are motionless, "
"indemonstrable because they do not appear, nonappearing because they are "
"free of appearance, without similarity on account of lacking dissimilarity, "
"without dissimilarity because they are like space, without darkness because "
"they lack luminosity, without appearance because they are beyond remedies, "
"beyond contemptibility because they are beyond wrongdoing, and beyond "
"contemptibility because they do not perform actions."

msgid "d74f9a41022d44229c0896e565ec8d95"
msgstr ""
"All phenomena are not in accordance with reality because they are deceptive "
"fictions."

msgid "018d165fd1774ee7a4aa7dc08604da34"
msgstr "They lack differentiation because they are primordially present."

msgid "1b4b6043c5814c3e9da6eb9891dabf1d"
msgstr ""
"“All phenomena lack spectators because they are formless, are without an "
"audience because they are soundless;"

msgid "b711d2b637f14321a62bef901414e2d5"
msgstr ""
"they are without a perceiver of smell because they are odorless, without a "
"perceiver of taste because they are without taste, without a perceiver of "
"touch because they are intangible, without a perceiving consciousness "
"because they are not phenomena, and without objectification because they are"
" beyond mind, mental activity, and consciousness;"

msgid "eb807df0d2a948ea9e77c72f406e6144"
msgstr ""
"and they are inconceivable because they are like awakening, and they have "
"primordially transcended sorrow because they are primordially unborn."

msgid "991ee86f98e64135a796df732d03dfbe"
msgstr ""
"“In this way, son of noble family, as the bodhisattvas utter the primary "
"letter a, because they have attained the pure melody dhāraṇī their teaching "
"of the Dharma goes on for an eon or more without the sound of the letter a "
"ever being lost."

msgid "2814cdf9ffd542b78374e2de99722e42"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, any letter among all the letters used to teach the Dharma "
"will not dissipate."

msgid "c062fb8df942460da2ae6b6dabd0e0ae"
msgstr "They teach the Dharma, in word and meaning, unceasingly."

msgid "fd814a521ee14eb5ab25473550d4334e"
msgstr ""
"“With regard to bodhisattvas established in this dhāraṇī, their bodies are "
"pure due to their behavior, their speech is pure due to their eloquence, and"
" their minds are pure due to their cultivation of love."

msgid "4dae3ae3afda425d9e46a22c7a41e8f7"
msgstr ""
"Their generosity is pure due to the absence of miserliness in making gifts "
"of the Dharma and material wealth. Their morality is pure because there is "
"no degeneration in their discipline."

msgid "0c411dc7ee714eaeb14790921c332c2b"
msgstr "Their patience is pure due to the absence of animosity."

msgid "339a6f948a5e42c0b9a68f306e694411"
msgstr "Their vigor is pure due to their performance of virtuous actions."

msgid "77156af5d4164042b0c6778c186ec184"
msgstr "Their concentration is pure because they are unattached."

msgid "289d8953e7864732a60e4c04c0523498"
msgstr ""
"Their insight is pure because the light of their wisdom is without darkness."

msgid "fe159cc5df6d43e8a302e5f435be5f9a"
msgstr "Their behavior is pure due to an absence of contemptible acts."

msgid "d9a430189d554d47b34c171a4879ac5d"
msgstr "“Their eyes are pure due to the purity of their divine vision."

msgid "acce83863350400ab72cadae748de104"
msgstr ""
"Their ears are pure due to attaining the divine ear and listening to the "
"Dharma discourses of all the tathāgatas."

msgid "6be46b09a5794b8d94735d9122c9aa46"
msgstr ""
"Their noses are pure because they perceive the fragrance of the tathāgatas’ "
"discipline."

msgid "a3780943b7e14285927a424bc3a405ee"
msgstr ""
"Their tongues are pure due to an absence of thirst for delicious taste."

msgid "95571ef8245c48b4ba55f7eb01d894b7"
msgstr ""
"Their bodies are pure because they are born miraculously and unstained by "
"the impurities of a womb."

msgid "0c974cbd873e494ba28514ec9c56d4cb"
msgstr ""
"Their minds are pure because they are skilled in distinguishing phenomena."

msgid "6d64ed34fbed436e943c9f8eeaecf48a"
msgstr "“For them, form is pure because they are well adorned by signs."

msgid "d4befceda81542f7b692ee34f8096ee8"
msgstr "Sound is pure because they articulate pleasing speech."

msgid "0c6e3cb12d4043d7b3c9409e6d2e50bc"
msgstr ""
"Scent is pure because they are draped in the fragrance of discipline, "
"learning, and generosity."

msgid "b5071ec929054740ac9512d7aea8dee5"
msgstr ""
"Taste is pure because they have attained the supreme taste, the sign of a "
"great being."

msgid "d05ec72fd9fe48c2a3c3dcda27c31c5f"
msgstr "Touch is pure because they have attained smooth and pliant limbs."

msgid "c37d1c302e094cc194326c7cc02febac"
msgstr ""
"Phenomena are pure because they have attained the illumination of the "
"Dharma."

msgid "9f5f753124b844cea4232ce12d644fe0"
msgstr ""
"Likewise, their mindfulness is pure because they have not forgotten the "
"dharmas they have heard, their intelligence is pure because they have "
"completely transcended the works of Māra, and their realization is pure "
"because they have internalized the realization of the profound Dharma."

msgid "cfa52b8bc34a4948849473a3d01afa5c"
msgstr ""
"“Bodhisattvas established in this dhāraṇī pervade with light as many "
"buddhafields as have understood its sound."

msgid "5b53bf57767e4b08b20f95c66c7a638f"
msgstr ""
"That is to say, due to the attainment of the exceptional uniqueness of this "
"very dhāraṇī, this light causes the Dharma taught by all the buddhas of the "
"ten directions to manifest."

msgid "7618f8d352a3452790e7be7e6f73e36e"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, this pure melody dhāraṇī is introduced only concisely "
"here."

msgid "5ac277ce2e9b4acf9f49ecb7dd006149"
msgstr "The teaching on this dhāraṇī of pure melody is immeasurable."

msgid "ee30ab2bb8bd48fc9643d32769b40524"
msgstr "It is inconceivable in terms of the categories of language."

msgid "716e344798bf4f9ca4b5824a7394f79e"
msgstr "It is limitless in terms of instructions."

msgid "95dc825de97a4489a4c077c206099516"
msgstr "It is immeasurable in terms of lacking all doubt."

msgid "f833f8cb411c485498b707aceb7192d7"
msgstr "It is infinite in terms of explanation."

msgid "b7d01970d5b84af99a31aa60af777a8c"
msgstr "It is without attachment in terms of engagement."

msgid "3a4d93d47d274024a3efde9ff3baaca4"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may then ask, ‘What is the inexhaustible basket "
"dhāraṇī?’"

msgid "69460a47822a47299e5a8c1968d3e48b"
msgstr ""
"It is the inexhaustible teaching of the dhāraṇī. The following teachings are"
" inexhaustible:"

msgid "3a14524a56b949789aa4959c5ce7c0bb"
msgstr "The teaching on impermanence says, ‘Form is impermanent.’"

msgid "1daf8b3f3bde4664bd1dbbfc7f4e648a"
msgstr "The teaching on suffering says, ‘Form is suffering.’"

msgid "245053c674984318845af7a33d03f701"
msgstr "The teaching on the lack of self says, ‘Form is without self.’"

msgid "27319fa0f3c9420a8a6abc5091127264"
msgstr "The teaching on peace says, ‘Form is peace.’"

msgid "65a43fe5abfb4ed2a9bbf5b71b97f4ff"
msgstr "The teaching on voidness says, ‘Form is void.’"

msgid "9be961e049504c71bb0c551fea17627e"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on likeness to a water bubble says, ‘Form is like a water "
"bubble.’"

msgid "d63b9670eb494eaaa8298eea0d37edd1"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on likeness to an illusion says, ‘Form is like an illusion.’"

msgid "573d470edbac43bd8d2922d909abdbf5"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on likeness to a hallucination says, ‘Form is like a "
"hallucination.’"

msgid "67f5bf9c29b7472499eb23a0b2cb2d86"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on likeness to the moon’s reflection in water says, ‘Form is "
"like the moon’s reflection in water.’"

msgid "25fcaa6e60a44db094230959fc429c8e"
msgstr "The teaching on likeness to a dream says, ‘Form is like a dream.’"

msgid "cdc7ebda6a4a411ab5db252a53931ac3"
msgstr "The teaching on likeness to an echo says, ‘Form is like an echo.’"

msgid "ebe5b0aeebaa4be2835b728dcdbca0d7"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on likeness to an optical illusion says, ‘Form is like an "
"optical illusion.’"

msgid "24178d0761eb4dd0b7c46cfe2c995ee4"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on likeness to a reflection says, ‘Form is like a reflection.’"

msgid "5036960ce6d14f1cac4ae029ac2933ec"
msgstr "The teaching on the lack of a nature says, ‘Form is natureless.’"

msgid "14f6e1e2cdb542c8a69c1e2f444935f0"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the lack of substantiality says, ‘Form is insubstantial.’"

msgid "2d1ad6eef56c4ef3835cd39daba03d4f"
msgstr "The teaching on the lack of a ground says, ‘Form is groundless.’"

msgid "70d338e36ec845128d5005f2519a946b"
msgstr "“The teaching on emptiness says, ‘Form is empty.’"

msgid "cb8d86d7e3ac4188920397af70ad3b4c"
msgstr "The teaching on signlessness says, ‘Form lacks conceptual signs.’"

msgid "fe8de62709fe42939f19bf5ea0b9ecfe"
msgstr "The teaching on wishlessness says, ‘Form lacks wishfulness.’"

msgid "0c40965f49054894bf31c28eee52277e"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the lack of conditioning says, ‘Form lack conditioning.’"

msgid "a13af0207f0a402fab3d3f98fe862708"
msgstr "The teaching on nonarising says, ‘Form is unarisen.’"

msgid "b8498f55c2f9426697a9d6f54454db19"
msgstr "The teaching on the lack of birth says, ‘Form is without arising.’"

msgid "37cd4120ca71423b85c85a1b899b38dc"
msgstr ""
"“The teaching on the lack of a nature in the beginning says, ‘Form is "
"natureless in the beginning.’"

msgid "228c835d727545f58bf7d5ec25105d21"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the lack of a nature in the end says, ‘Form is natureless in"
" the end.’"

msgid "86ecd71b8bea4425a618af1816a0d74c"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the lack of a nature in the meantime says, ‘Form is "
"natureless in the meantime.’"

msgid "5ee30e9bab6f4f8c8f7ff0a7ca5918fb"
msgstr "“The teaching on peace says, ‘Form is peace.’"

msgid "38797910cb7c42ab80ad39b63b3a63cb"
msgstr "The teaching on pacification says, ‘Form is pacified.’"

msgid "2198cdcbcd984bea9c9b04dd1a1cac20"
msgstr "The teaching on the absence of movement says, ‘Form is unmoving.’"

msgid "0052951e0fad47ed8016b997ce383785"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the absence of elaboration says, ‘Form is without "
"elaboration.’"

msgid "5d008e6625b54b84abb0f2270cf56c7b"
msgstr "The teaching on inconceivability says, ‘Form is inconceivable.’"

msgid "5943b256db3a4116b53cd396dc0ad486"
msgstr "The teaching on being incomparable says, ‘Form is incomparable.’"

msgid "8ea4033e1e614dc18081704b4909c9f3"
msgstr "“The teaching on the lack of a self says, ‘Form is devoid of a self.’"

msgid "9700d49158f44eeb911f24dd2b4618b1"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the lack of sentient beings says, ‘Form is devoid of "
"sentient beings.’"

msgid "5dbe7448ffec4197be280ea08e4b7359"
msgstr "The teaching on life says, ‘Form is devoid of life.’"

msgid "942f11caecf2466ca8daa2bb84063902"
msgstr "The teaching on vitality says, ‘Form is devoid of vitality.’"

msgid "292c6423bda345aba2dbc7fa67455c4d"
msgstr "The teaching on individuals says, ‘Form is devoid of individuals.’"

msgid "e0e746eca6484e31b101ebb5c3a0db52"
msgstr "The teaching on the inanimate says, ‘Form is inanimate.’"

msgid "f9cee18b6dcb4ef38bd38bca64c9c9b5"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the absence of mobility says, ‘Form is devoid of mobility.’"

msgid "9e2197888c5a4292933c8791a5716b9a"
msgstr "The teaching on the lack of agency says, ‘Form is devoid of agency.’"

msgid "b2bab485e33b4d98b1a8f24ded7e5b9a"
msgstr ""
"“The teaching on likeness to grass, walls, trees, dirt, and optical "
"illusions says, ‘Forms are like grass, walls, trees, dirt, and optical "
"illusions.’"

msgid "543fce424ca049efb1b2ee88b7297608"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on having the character of being established says, ‘Form has "
"the character of being established.’"

msgid "10cd1f28c1824e4fbc0742ccb3835183"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on coming about from the four great elements says, ‘Form comes "
"about from the four great elements.’"

msgid "fdd0f7af9cbc407ca59ba198118e7bf7"
msgstr "The teaching on the absence of sound says, ‘Form is soundless.’"

msgid "0a3f581c61d04cd8a1fca5948b2f4bff"
msgstr "The teaching on noncognition says, ‘Form is not cognition.’"

msgid "f5d0d92346a14c2b88057e1ff32d54c5"
msgstr "The teaching on being inexpressible says, ‘Form is inexpressible.’"

msgid "825015f2d87f486b9e9a873d3c389d55"
msgstr "The teaching on inherent purity says, ‘Form is inherently pure.’"

msgid "131309ab11a34333b945d620ee3e5afb"
msgstr "The teaching on dependent arising says, ‘Form is dependently arisen.’"

msgid "8c17bdaeddcd4732946d95a7dadbc37c"
msgstr ""
"“The teaching on the absence of annihilation says, ‘Form is without "
"annihilation.’"

msgid "60e3ba7579e848c68b24b15335028a44"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the absence of permanence says, ‘Form has no permanence.’"

msgid "23c57d06ea2d4da4a8de5d50fa092ec7"
msgstr "The teaching on the absence of a creator says, ‘Form has no creator.’"

msgid "12dbe707c6ff4792958d58214b1b18fa"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the absence of an experiencer says, ‘Form has no "
"experiencer.’"

msgid "aea23e5062f9444ca351e32d6df7792f"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on being produced by the maturation of actions says, ‘Form has "
"been produced by the maturation of actions.’"

msgid "83e8f334f3a7417fa70306102592805c"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on being equal to the realm of phenomena says, ‘Form is equal "
"to the realm of phenomena.’"

msgid "c1bc0ed0b12d4a5f98f497ee639f84b2"
msgstr "The teaching on abiding in suchness says, ‘Form abides in suchness.’"

msgid "5c58aca665a448eb83229ea91794f46e"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on abiding at the limit of reality says, ‘Form abides at the "
"limit of reality.’"

msgid "b07f29612a364280935b35493229e5e3"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the absence of mineness says, ‘Form has nothing that is "
"mine.’"

msgid "2a9756d234ee442ebc1945424e486f9e"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the absence of apprehending says, ‘Form is without "
"apprehending.’"

msgid "d005515fd9c8449094bdc7494824b1a4"
msgstr "The teaching on being endless says, ‘Form is endless.’"

msgid "a56fa37921344b6b8daa30b3a4a71697"
msgstr "“The teaching on being inconceivable says, ‘Form is inconceivable.’"

msgid "742e97febbcd4d338efe76bffaf0d4a5"
msgstr "The teaching on being incomparable says, ‘Form is incomparable.’"

msgid "d999f984e13d4d0aa5b91e1d4fe27450"
msgstr "The teaching on immeasurability says, ‘Form is immeasurable.’"

msgid "c964a5e7a58147b1b075ff5b46d1aee4"
msgstr "The teaching on infinity says, ‘Form is infinite.’"

msgid "0fc0e883c94f482e8dbbe1a113a3c92a"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the nature of awakening says, ‘Form is of the nature of "
"awakening.’"

msgid "2522845d48a849c0a011e544ff9ee688"
msgstr "The teaching on equality with space says, ‘Form is equal to space.’"

msgid "64fe1a2c8d81449f8feed8b44d395b63"
msgstr ""
"The teaching on the nature of nirvāṇa says, ‘Form is of the nature of "
"nirvāṇa.’ These teachings are all inexhaustible."

msgid "75c7da10d8a74015acb87977ec62d0c4"
msgstr ""
"“Similarly, by engaging in uttering a single sound, inexhaustible teachings "
"are extensively applied to all that can be known, including all phenomena, "
"that is, the aggregates, the elements, the sense fields, the collections of "
"names, the collections of terms, and the collections of letters."

msgid "9252fe8772594760945dfa771174abe2"
msgstr ""
"The knowledge for expressing what is inexhaustible among this basket of a "
"body arisen from the four great elements, the knowledge for entering into "
"the inexhaustible Dharma discourses that are a basket of jewels, and the "
"inexhaustible knowledge of the teachings are called the inexhaustible basket"
" dhāraṇī."

msgid "429ff180674146ac8f9dbf71e0e8bfe5"
msgstr ""
"Through the teaching of a mere introduction, the inexhaustible basket is "
"uttered for an eon or more."

msgid "ceb37def385049bdaf9c65fa2339923c"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may then ask, ‘What is the limitless enfoldment "
"dhāraṇī?’"

msgid "e8deac5b60144a71a76a57eb8c101356"
msgstr "The ‘limits’ are nihilism and eternalism."

msgid "734b098b16b344d98186dce8012fc93d"
msgstr "The ‘enfoldment’ is the twelve links of dependent arising:"

msgid "8e3370910c4f4a03a36ec59c64a23c89"
msgstr "Conditioned by ignorance, formations occur."

msgid "d9b7e9c637ef4f7b8f27b8266ef7d0ed"
msgstr "Conditioned by formations, consciousness occurs."

msgid "4dcbbfed446a4c7f9dce142879c83f9d"
msgstr "Conditioned by consciousness, name and form occur."

msgid "4e4b4374622b4e508d30a9f2b71822ef"
msgstr "Conditioned by name and form, the six sense fields occur."

msgid "4bf636a99ef04a5da3bd989224f04f2e"
msgstr "Conditioned by the six sense fields, contact occurs."

msgid "a31355acd6f54408b28e721bdb1af868"
msgstr "Conditioned by contact, sensation occurs."

msgid "67ed4a556c0a4a58b6dabbffa1d9431f"
msgstr "Conditioned by sensation, craving occurs."

msgid "71204593d9c642c3acfea72743f1491b"
msgstr "Conditioned by craving, appropriation occurs."

msgid "845695147c114f168578010e380007e9"
msgstr "Conditioned by appropriation, becoming occurs."

msgid "d1237436d7ca453b88ea09446e75eca4"
msgstr "Conditioned by becoming, birth occurs."

msgid "2eca10c650034e99b626a6c4e6876b21"
msgstr ""
"Conditioned by birth, there occur old age, death, sorrow, lamentation, "
"suffering, unhappiness, and chaos."

msgid "105cae7023204fb595bcb0debe68559e"
msgstr "In that manner, nothing but this great heap of sorrow occurs."

msgid "0d8f853c26b64effa4e04393fdbd5f37"
msgstr ""
"The infinite intent of the formula, the infinite doors to its expositions, "
"and its infinite introductions provide knowledge of the limitless enfoldment"
" dhāraṇī."

msgid "0cd9d596ea0d4e9a92e5ccc1ce0ac676"
msgstr ""
"“The ‘limits’ are birth and cessation, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is beyond birth "
"and cessation."

msgid "cae4304797024e16aa00871c1f6f3282"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are pollution and purification, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is natural"
" purity."

msgid "c5d60496d1204428ae12ca076e84d6f5"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are discursive signs and elaborations, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is "
"their lack of origination."

msgid "b4605f7cfffa4a1f87c16a70f9c22f61"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are thoughts and conceptualization, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is "
"beyond thoughts and conceptualization."

msgid "b6240c450bcb4947a561431983b6059e"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are causes and views, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is comprehension of "
"causes and views."

msgid "41b956c4835a40b18dda4e40057482ca"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are name and form, whereas ‘enfoldment’ does not form cognitive"
" representations."

msgid "b4b280ad991b4e778efa4d296f0977a1"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are the conditioned and the unconditioned, whereas ‘enfoldment’"
" consists in the purity of all three spheres of agent, act, and object."

msgid "9e9ebb88dee04bf7b958376da6ed6e68"
msgstr ""
"“The ‘limits’ are inner and outer, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is not based on "
"consciousness."

msgid "006b32a512b743e6a8e8b55a6973dfde"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are karma and maturation, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is beyond karma "
"and maturation."

msgid "e5c85412519246cfa20feace42d6fc4e"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are virtue and nonvirtue, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is beyond "
"conditioning."

msgid "2ae392058d854558aa77ead8a9c5f12c"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are having or lacking culpability, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is "
"without duality."

msgid "0d283d17a9524c1aaef80e27f60dad73"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are karma and afflictive emotions, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is "
"natural luminosity."

msgid "afe9f0e3edc14d28993f1dd9cb775d88"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are self and no self, whereas ‘enfoldment’ is complete purity."

msgid "2e473c59081b4b8cb1ea439570cb1d4d"
msgstr ""
"The ‘limits’ are saṃsāra and nirvāṇa, whereas ‘enfoldment’ means that all "
"phenomena are thoroughly transcendent by nature."

msgid "a979ef7bb248434085505902d41e7c4e"
msgstr ""
"“Therefore, son of noble family, the teaching on limitlessness is boundless."

msgid "a901653dfe3a4e5a9deb889d9434e713"
msgstr "The teaching on enfoldment is boundless."

msgid "b9b19bb75cdf403a8cde97bd94c0ba50"
msgstr ""
"Since bodhisattvas established in this limitless enfoldment dhāraṇī are "
"aligned with limitlessness and are aligned with enfoldment, even if they "
"were to teach the Dharma for limitless hundreds of thousands of eons, they "
"would not reach the end of the wisdom that retains meanings and syllables."

msgid "8a4a6f8d32fb4cf991f878bb503e0503"
msgstr ""
"This is the introduction to the limitless enfoldment dhāraṇī, the "
"corresponding Dharma, the attendant realization of the illumination of "
"wisdom, and the corresponding realization of unclouded wisdom with regard to"
" this pure gateway."

msgid "741c8e33c0a14c8b87df8205016b1919"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may then ask, ‘What is the ocean mudrā dhāraṇī?’"

msgid "39038b80ba5c4f97b377ccfb663d3ba2"
msgstr "It is as follows:"

msgid "053cc110d3814423a04fe5521ad70d44"
msgstr ""
"To give an analogy, all that appears in the world realm of the four great "
"continents comprises appearances in the form of beings, mountains, and "
"trees;"

msgid "37084cc919434cc7a88789c644e7b249"
msgstr "grasses, bushes, medicinal herbs, forests, and harvests;"

msgid "b1ffbe210bbf495db21c2776438553d3"
msgstr "the moon, the sun, the stars, gems, clouds, fire, and lightning;"

msgid "9e535d04d7db4e7b878381dbca3ee808"
msgstr ""
"the layouts of cities, towns, and hamlets; palaces and riches; parks, "
"springs, ponds, sprouts, and fountains; and all resources or objects of "
"enjoyment, whether inferior, average, or supreme."

msgid "b31481ab36d5467aa4e5d5fca3e40b0b"
msgstr ""
"“Since all these forms of appearance are sealed by the great ocean in a "
"manner that is not too little, not too much, and not excessive, the ocean is"
" known to be great."

msgid "19541fe4ccdc4d4e994d68b9a3e26fb4"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, for bodhisattvas who are established in the ocean mudrā"
" dhāraṇī, it is like a seal that seals the bodies of all sentient beings, "
"the speech of all sentient beings, and the minds of all sentient beings."

msgid "c07db020cbd0401799f909dd89e44124"
msgstr ""
"To whatever extent these bodhisattvas engage in the liberating activity of "
"speech in promulgating the Dharma of the blessed buddhas of the ten "
"directions, it is as if they mark things with a seal by way of such "
"utterance."

msgid "166df76ce4024307bf8cd2522a563456"
msgstr ""
"Anything that bodhisattvas may express, which bears the seal of the "
"Tathāgata, the seal of nonconceptuality, teaches everyone the seal of the "
"Tathāgata, the seal of nonconceptuality, without recourse to any extraneous "
"means."

msgid "1cef431a2b8f4601b79a3e2880c7c278"
msgstr "“Thus, the teaching concerning their seals is as follows."

msgid "725565991f324b73983e74bda314c28e"
msgstr "A is the seal of the unconditioned."

msgid "2c73ac144b9c48148740b697d93051a1"
msgstr ""
"Ra is the seal of the attainment of freedom from desire regarding any "
"phenomenon."

msgid "f452d1bac9bf42269aa48aff604b6831"
msgstr "Pa is the seal of teachings on the ultimate."

msgid "a25973afebd747689690dfe1d25207d3"
msgstr "Tsa is the seal of pure vision."

msgid "96fa661d82b3423cb23ec577cbdeac68"
msgstr "Na is the seal of the knowledge of all name and form."

msgid "00fe4682a77d4431b059af2d4c664540"
msgstr "La is the seal of extrication from the vines of craving."

msgid "3514724667d3430c8f49166257fd2fed"
msgstr "Da is the seal of the pure ten strengths."

msgid "f562d0ca12444da4b1a4a095360112e7"
msgstr "Ba is the seal of the pure factors of awakening and strengths."

msgid "58f6414a76f1446ea2613ecc04576261"
msgstr "Ḍa is the seal of freedom from upset and agony."

msgid "857a910c8cc74cdaa80863b264056a5f"
msgstr "Ṣa is the seal of attaining the six kinds of superknowledge."

msgid "957454027e514802b43e5815fd47a4db"
msgstr "Ba is the seal of abandoning the left-hand path."

msgid "37af68f446b7411eb91d0405f07445ab"
msgstr "Ta is the seal of the teaching on suchness."

msgid "4ad0a54bde2e4721a15e92f041c205f1"
msgstr "Ya is the seal that accords with the way things are."

msgid "91dc0ede04f449b8a202fb467e5b2735"
msgstr "Sta is the seal of freedom from the afflictive emotion of arrogance."

msgid "f996a639b20148ac96739654135f207c"
msgstr "Ka is the seal of freedom from doubt."

msgid "a8ea30ba8f4544618bf243b152f86089"
msgstr "Sa is the seal of teaching truth."

msgid "b29edfbc8dfb4065ab2ddbc7864e9901"
msgstr "Ma is the seal of the pure path."

msgid "cb9587362f6748319ab04a402fd2e70a"
msgstr "Ga is the seal of entry into the profound."

msgid "e0de5cfdc6244a718e0f318def4b931e"
msgstr "Sṭha is the seal of demonstrating power and might."

msgid "6bd720c643cd4841bf15ed3f17ba0e02"
msgstr "Dza is the seal of transcending old age and death."

msgid "3b08ed9716f741b3b6d13400db8be9de"
msgstr "Shwa is the seal of abandoning the hazards of wild animals."

msgid "725538eaeae141b5b469d9d02f58afa4"
msgstr "Dha is the seal of the stainless realm of phenomena."

msgid "d1cd32d0241d4c2896a15bd5925d0068"
msgstr "Sha is the seal of the perfection of tranquil abiding."

msgid "80c589d449a044ad9028e53615cd5020"
msgstr "Kha is the seal of the basic nature of imperishable space."

msgid "450d6e1458914a8689734c1e775239b6"
msgstr "Kṣha is the seal of knowledge of the perishable and of the unborn."

msgid "076b58e760ca4aae85dc125a47041ab8"
msgstr "Su is the seal of abandoning the obscuration of dullness."

msgid "4328d35227f74df1953b5d2e7aee7be5"
msgstr "Sa is the seal of gaining omniscience for all sentient beings."

msgid "1ba84dfe4e8b4279a2d330b419fce245"
msgstr "Hwa is the seal of abandoning dharmas that facilitate degeneration."

msgid "e3b48e03bca840fbb5045b334720b3a0"
msgstr "Bha is the seal of gaining realization of existence and nonexistence."

msgid "cf05a7c4c865488283e179482f9d5702"
msgstr ""
"Tsha is the seal of relinquishing attachment, aversion, fear, and stupidity."

msgid "3183dbce8f8d43ba922a373feff804c1"
msgstr "Sma is the seal of mindfulness, alertness, and nonforgetfulness."

msgid "8c112c1953794182b0e9fc4ac658f38d"
msgstr "Hwa is the seal of summoning."

msgid "6cc80a32a1c946a8b2b8b335ffe0a23d"
msgstr "Sa is the seal of rejecting all afflictive emotions."

msgid "43d18873dfa64b31bd924445522292f2"
msgstr ""
"Gha is the seal of eliminating opacity, distorted vision, and ignorance."

msgid "27e46042332345758f43de06e478403f"
msgstr "Ṭha is the seal of reaching the ultimate."

msgid "15f7231554d74befb39ffb7a9f16a311"
msgstr "Ṇa is the seal of gaining realization of excellent qualities."

msgid "df4defc3f7a9418f865c90c68d2c765f"
msgstr "Pha is the seal of attaining the result."

msgid "db49005b94f64569aa599603ad92a669"
msgstr "Ska is the seal of gaining comprehension of the aggregates."

msgid "fe6ce9d1a70b404aab3e6af194081259"
msgstr "Dzwa is the seal of eradicating contagious diseases."

msgid "01dba69d08fd4f48866af074013da43e"
msgstr ""
"Shtsa is the seal of directly and perfectly awakening wondrous marvelous "
"qualities."

msgid "81497115b07949b29d35a7323e19206c"
msgstr ""
"Ba is the seal of reaching the end of the path and arriving in nirvāṇa."

msgid "0394b04d380a4e198aac3b93debebacd"
msgstr "La is the seal of the infinitude of syllables."

msgid "1af9659c958c45fe95d9cea5591f980e"
msgstr ""
"“In this way, son of noble family, bodhisattvas, in as many ways as there "
"are, comprehend the teaching of the seals represented by all these syllables"
" used to teach the Dharma."

msgid "39c337920658412e854694a8c94ba9e0"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, this introduces the gateway of the ocean mudrā dhāraṇī."

msgid "47380645f1e74361a7891f99432cfa8a"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may then ask, ‘What is the dhāraṇī called lotus "
"array?’"

msgid "1f8fc5530bf942b7969855d7ff44a674"
msgstr ""
"Regarding bodhisattvas who are established in this dhāraṇī, wherever and in "
"whichever assembly they choose to teach the Dharma, various beautiful lotus "
"seats will blossom forth."

msgid "89f5f725ab5847f5b3e851faf70e6d1f"
msgstr ""
"As soon as they sit down on their lotus seats, a rain of lotus flowers will "
"shower from the sky,"

msgid "4960859ce80e4a518bb36734f57cd789"
msgstr ""
"and various kinds of doctrinal teachings will issue forth from them: "
"profound discourses, variegated discourses, illustrative discourses, "
"expositions, melodic verses, prophecies, metered verses, praises, ethical "
"narratives, ancient narratives, past life accounts, epic stories, and "
"authoritative explications will manifest in this way."

msgid "60f5c5a73c204cae93dc4e8addbbc212"
msgstr ""
"“The reverberation of Dharma emanating from the lotus flowers alleviates "
"suffering."

msgid "07436eb8b72e40a88706a958c3f9aca1"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattvas remain neutral and silent without abandoning resting in "
"equipoise."

msgid "86d047611ede411e9e5202d497459ba0"
msgstr ""
"The deliverance issuing from the manifested lotus flowers alleviates "
"suffering and instigates the buddha activities."

msgid "3014fb7b55cc42aa9967a016f5f5263e"
msgstr ""
"“Light rays burst forth from each and every pore of the bodhisattvas’ "
"bodies."

msgid "091b7512757e43b5b7a81f55c79bc203"
msgstr ""
"Lotus flowers blossom from these light rays, and more bodhisattva forms "
"emerge from these lotus flowers."

msgid "f6bbeade491f4e9bb6a7cd7652067842"
msgstr ""
"These disperse into the vast, immeasurable world realms in the ten "
"directions and perform buddha activities."

msgid "d4ee7ec11da846fcb78bffea8dfe6da3"
msgstr "This is the introduction to the gateway of the lotus array dhāraṇī."

msgid "3c874c3ccec841b7b456dd2d444a81ec"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may then ask, ‘What is the entering the gate of "
"nonattachment dhāraṇī?’"

msgid "2036fa6334264e0f857a1c742b568c29"
msgstr ""
"It consists in not being attached to a single teaching and not being "
"attached to two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight, nine, or ten "
"teachings."

msgid "d9c676c1b3fe43afa1c2af992b2b4acc"
msgstr ""
"It consists in not being attached to twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, sixty, "
"seventy, eighty, ninety, or a hundred teachings."

msgid "abde84e8800c45b295e0a95764faca5c"
msgstr ""
"It consists in not being attached to a thousand, a hundred thousand, ten "
"million, ten thousand million, or a hundred thousand million teachings. It "
"consists in not being attached to a quadrillion, one hundred quadrillion, "
"ten quintillion, immeasurable, innumerable, an incomparable number of, or an"
" unfathomable number of teachings."

msgid "1020f4d831d94b2e99ce3f2c5f81f50e"
msgstr ""
"“It consists in not being attached to a number of teachings as vast as the "
"number of grains of sand in the river Ganges, as vast as the number of "
"particles in Jambudvīpa, as vast as the number of atoms of the four "
"continents, as vast as the number of atoms in twenty, thirty, forty, or "
"fifty trichiliocosms or in a buddhafield."

msgid "2c9dbb56afa841c9867503f135b41057"
msgstr ""
"It consists in not being attached to the number of teachings ranging from a "
"number as vast as the number of grains of sand in the river Ganges in a "
"single buddhafield to a number as vast as the quantity of atoms in all the "
"buddhafields."

msgid "d448b72ccbe245f1b5b7450976e38137"
msgstr ""
"“In this way, son of noble family, one teaches the gateways to the Dharma "
"and their teachings, commencing with any gateway up to as many as the number"
" of atoms in all buddhafields, through a single presentation, through two, "
"three, four, five, six, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, or fifty teachings, or "
"through hundreds, thousands, or a limitless number of teachings."

msgid "a4838e744160418cac5789d62b4dae14"
msgstr ""
"Although one teaches using lexical imputations and associations and using "
"precisely defined words, meanings, and syllables, one will be neither "
"attached nor interrupted."

msgid "d42cdc8ce9eb41c49ad058e08a9dde78"
msgstr "This is the dhāraṇī called entering the gate of nonattachment."

msgid "2f7029e8e0514c06bad0a25f93610fa7"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may ask, ‘What is the dhāraṇī called entering "
"ascertainment by discriminating knowledge?’"

msgid "840473424c9245e8830424c90b90b773"
msgstr "One knows meaning, phenomena, etymologies, and eloquence."

msgid "1ca86ae8ad2f477883b5504fd9890268"
msgstr ""
"When all sentient beings of the eastern direction gather around one who has "
"attained these kinds of knowledge, they inquire—each in their own "
"language—about the mastery of meanings."

msgid "3607f2d5f719420582d29831e72c29bd"
msgstr ""
"Beings of the southern direction inquire about the mastery of phenomena."

msgid "de963f57f4384ae1aa52e7c6831017c1"
msgstr ""
"Beings of the western direction inquire about the mastery of etymology."

msgid "c74e22eaa9144a95b30f5d693d7c8fd3"
msgstr ""
"And beings of the northern direction inquire about the mastery of eloquence."
" When this occurs, the bodhisattvas’ vocal deeds will be correspondingly "
"immense."

msgid "38666e7c07b749d9bbf3e60c9fbc70cd"
msgstr ""
"They will speak and employ various languages at the same time, without "
"forgetting any and without their minds becoming distracted."

msgid "4e932e96624541ab98e597d827fdc9b4"
msgstr "Knowing how to use languages, they adapt to all languages."

msgid "e54cac276f364db480a27cb50676ce97"
msgstr ""
"By one moment of utterance, they bring knowledge that satisfies the minds of"
" all sentient beings."

msgid "382b7f73c16b4fdb83e8b6b87e769bae"
msgstr ""
"This is the dhāraṇī called entering ascertainment by discriminating "
"knowledge."

msgid "9da601ae75b14de691c16697c0b076d0"
msgstr ""
" “Son of noble family, you may ask, ‘What is the dhāraṇī called blessing of "
"the buddha ornaments?’"

msgid "66d656df01eb4b119fd1c691d2f0cc0e"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, for bodhisattvas who have attained this dhāraṇī, the "
"form of the Tathāgata, golden in color with a body adorned with the "
"auspicious marks and signs and seated on a great Dharma seat in the center "
"of a large circle of attendants, will manifest right above the crowns of "
"their heads."

msgid "28219ae8c0a54a73a1f60d0a6174b09b"
msgstr "The Tathāgata’s form places its right hand on top of their heads."

msgid "b69f1ec5801a4a6daefff0218651bf48"
msgstr ""
"As soon as it touches them, they are endowed with the activities of body, "
"speech, and mind adorned by buddha ornaments."

msgid "d2f0ce0b81264aadbc1b514bfe22ea22"
msgstr ""
"Endowed with such qualities they can engage the mental dispositions of any "
"audience and thereby teach the Dharma in a manner suited to each individual."

msgid "5e94ad316c714fed93e0dbcc51caac64"
msgstr ""
"“However long they wish to teach the Dharma uninterruptedly without "
"nourishment—whether it is for a day or two, three or four days, a week, a "
"fortnight, a month, a season, or the course of a year, or even for a hundred"
" years, a thousand years, or a hundred thousand years—because they are "
"sustained by the blessings of the tathāgatas, whose gateways of Dharma are "
"inexhaustible in number, they do not grow weary either physically or "
"mentally."

msgid "ad2004ef2b7e4f3ca8a17ac89b9af976"
msgstr "“They possess four kinds of great knowledge."

msgid "27b518e333f04aee9dcff43b05397952"
msgstr "You may ask, ‘Which four?’"

msgid "452df64c0fda4efb97aea10ca22950cd"
msgstr ""
"They know how to distinguish the dispositions and words of sentient beings, "
"they know the inexhaustible four types of discriminating knowledge, they "
"know how to delineate the vehicles, and they know how to teach the Dharma in"
" accordance with each individual."

msgid "848075ae8fd34334ac408240b541f787"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, this is known as the concise introduction to the "
"gateway of the blessing of the buddha ornaments dhāraṇī."

msgid "58228279c684410792a28321ce6806b8"
msgstr ""
"This dhāraṇī is inexhaustible, continues endlessly, embodies the scope of "
"the tathāgatas, and is a boundless teaching."

msgid "8e435694a10c44308286c4a79d2ca803"
msgstr "“Son of noble family, these are the eight bodhisattva dhāraṇīs."

msgid "34148609c3e14d2597de2f421a94efc8"
msgstr ""
"Bodhisattvas who are established in these dhāraṇīs retain what all the "
"buddhas say and uphold the Dharma they teach."

msgid "2674b498dc734717ab0cc96c37fe5153"
msgstr "Since they explain it carefully, they make all beings happy.”"

msgid "61de4989c279475e9c3e3022581e8b7d"
msgstr "Then Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja spoke these verses:"

msgid "8bd3e18e8fc141f09beeb4ceb96fc89e"
msgstr ""
" “While those in this vehicle who have attained The eight dhāraṇīs taught by"
" the sugatas"

msgid "1263154740294dcb925a1e19c911fae0"
msgstr ""
"May explain a vast number of sūtras without barrier, They are not hampered "
"regarding any meanings or syllables."

msgid "f3da85e0634f4dd7a324b571437a8a69"
msgstr ""
"“Delightful, melodious, and attractive melodies Foster understanding in vast"
" numbers of buddhafields."

msgid "7306d30b995f48d2b43a2087e8b36cfb"
msgstr "Hearing it, sentient beings progress toward nirvāṇa."

msgid "5c223553aa5043f893ca7ac738591aff"
msgstr "The pure melody dhāraṇī is limitless."

msgid "94fe83eef9894756a1e87cb2f7a5ac16"
msgstr " “While learned and wise ones who know all linguistic forms"

msgid "b101577c0ac04c0a88ee353fbd6039a7"
msgstr "May teach for many eons, they do not run out of Dharma."

msgid "1ee08836396948d984d27fdb1c4b2336"
msgstr "As they pronounce a single basic word, it becomes inexhaustible."

msgid "fcb08e0bab234046942b6680bacf61b8"
msgstr "This is the dhāraṇī of the inexhaustible basket."

msgid "dba712e07722453c9db910a557aac2e1"
msgstr ""
" “Wise ones who attain the dhāraṇī, whose positive determination has reached"
" the limit of reality,"

msgid "535b4c437ac14b3ebca3734ac2105271"
msgstr "Are intent on the teachings that are authentic and appropriate."

msgid "4e3d7b00e68a44469d2b301aad7bbfe9"
msgstr "These leaders have abandoned and thus purified all extreme beliefs,"

msgid "6dea163979fb484ca31dca7e19c9626f"
msgstr "Yet they do not become stuck in the middle."

msgid "4e02a68fa3844cea954a0911267b610c"
msgstr ""
" “When they have attained the great ocean mudrā, Having discussed it and "
"described the inconceivable seals,"

msgid "aef24cc92ae84262be95b9eb9a670153"
msgstr ""
"All the forms in the four continents Possess the great ocean that is "
"nonconceptuality."

msgid "b4fe3bdfc9d54853ab0c18d422b81260"
msgstr " “When great beings teach the Dharma to an audience,"

msgid "2ef76fe264ee4440aa666cb774007208"
msgstr ""
"A vast shower of lotus flowers falls from the sky And a multitude of "
"teachings manifest from them."

msgid "c5756a94d9f7401bb4e2559092b5175b"
msgstr "This is the pure lotus array dhāraṇī."

msgid "cbc5cb6d562d49a6ae2f61ef71277ea0"
msgstr " “When they have attained the nonattachment dhāraṇī,"

msgid "f40f090ca66c45f4ac2da98ccf579d01"
msgstr ""
"They have no attachment in speaking, whether expressing a single word Or "
"two, three, four, five, a million, A hundred thousand million, or an endless"
" number of words."

msgid "d0d26731df984df2a2bcdaeaabdecd05"
msgstr ""
" “When they have attained the dhāraṇī that transcends doubt And are "
"requested by the multitudes of beings of the ten directions, Then, regarding"
" the entire range of meaning, phenomena, etymology, and eloquence, All the "
"doubts of these beings are dispelled, and their anxieties disappear."

msgid "e236b7bd17564109b6e5a642a21bd76e"
msgstr ""
" “When they have attained the dhāraṇī of the buddhas’ magical display, And "
"this great brilliant one is seated on his throne, The Buddha places his "
"right hand upon their heads And they become just as eloquent as the Victor "
"himself."

msgid "d55c1af27e144c70be5638c2e8013054"
msgstr "“When they have attained these dhāraṇīs,"

msgid "4b2fe65060944a28b5aba788b5575679"
msgstr "Their qualities become inconceivable and endless."

msgid "bb3c1f5804a14a9ea76562ffd8fd3288"
msgstr ""
"Even if they were described for eons ten million times the extent of Ganges,"
" Since they express tribute to the supreme leader, there would be no end."

msgid "482a3713f243444183f5004170d40914"
msgstr ""
"Their knowledge will engage the three realms equally. “When they have "
"attained the supreme dhāraṇīs,"

msgid "024187fa026b42dab34c16c5caab1e5c"
msgstr "They rise above the three existences like lotuses."

msgid "50cc2df2d8ff41adaff2610863e32f44"
msgstr "They are unshaken by any object, just like Mount Meru."

msgid "acdd391184b0420b8eaa4035eb8dd583"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They behave in a way that "
"leaves all worldliness behind."

msgid "69d25696cb9e48e085c358001e475c66"
msgstr ""
"When they address gatherings of non-Buddhists to quell them, They are "
"without fear of the audience, like a lion."

msgid "74c181b3f5b0433297586cc1cf0182ac"
msgstr "“Like earth, the dhāraṇīs make virtues grow."

msgid "57784a0d7da147b5ac2f80e8f6172467"
msgstr "Like water, they rinse away stains."

msgid "0c6e2709193f474bbb6509f98cb076e4"
msgstr "Like fire, they incinerate arrogance and conceptualization."

msgid "921202edafe84e66ba11d9190e5acc47"
msgstr "Like air, they are unobstructed by directions."

msgid "7890506d307e48599367b537d90070fd"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, Their knowledge and faculties"
" are unagitated when they speak."

msgid "8f8758e36f1646adaf6ca6e1744b11f3"
msgstr ""
"They bring liberation to beings like medicine, And, wishing to help them, "
"they dispense the diuretic of Dharma."

msgid "f89e3e2cc15e40db8ba5babeae079524"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, Throngs of beings never tire "
"of gazing at them."

msgid "807d8b46d02b48618abdf9e062aa650a"
msgstr ""
"Like the moon, and with pure training in virtues, Their mental equanimity "
"emits a steady brilliant light."

msgid "c743b533015e4fe491a6403fb4b6811e"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They dry up each and every "
"existence of beings."

msgid "b90b63b6ba024857951c5aa8471f47e0"
msgstr ""
"Like the sun, and generating light that dispels darkness, They wake the "
"slumbering beings in the three existences."

msgid "6a34be214cd34999bbaba144122db3a1"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, There is not the slightest "
"clinging to anything."

msgid "22fea7da986f426cb2faae3b828b203b"
msgstr ""
"Like a king, and being great world rulers like Vaiśravaṇa, They display the "
"riches of the teachings."

msgid "f15ca583f217400f9e1cef1ea0829a06"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They resemble nāgas, mindful "
"of great miracles."

msgid "294f3938f0964c129d3bbecec78caea5"
msgstr "When clouds billow and lightning appears in the sky,"

msgid "63bf064da7ce46a98fbd7df9636d401b"
msgstr "They rain down showers of Dharma in order to bring peace."

msgid "787362eabb7344d982fa65b0139436cc"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, All audiences will gaze upon "
"their faces as supreme leaders."

msgid "16fb06349b654007912da6ffbab2b1ee"
msgstr ""
"Having a supreme form like Śakra, not a mediocre one, The wise ones consider"
" the Dharmas and aims pertaining to beings."

msgid "6b24c2bb6aa7467d83c2e094d990de04"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They meditate on the pure "
"abodes of Brahmā."

msgid "9371563982434f999457df6a6f1963a2"
msgstr "Like Brahmā, their equipoise is compassionate."

msgid "aaf42d46af694ea3869294d1dac0fa91"
msgstr "Outshining all the worlds, they meditate."

msgid "21c913f01b874ad5b824dd2e9964ca57"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They venerate the many "
"buddhas of the ten directions."

msgid "92564fa55674430da0fb19eb6af18c37"
msgstr "They never regresses from the five types of superknowledge."

msgid "9e27f30ab124487394ac548c471edf7d"
msgstr ""
"They traverse inconceivable hundreds of buddhafields through pure space."

msgid "420264d3d215403181f9ebfb5a9c5bbd"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, It will not be before long "
"before they attain buddha qualities."

msgid "9be49704fd7646c086b6848e3bb2b496"
msgstr "The victors of the directions will express their approval of this"

msgid "9e2cc4a43369457daa9c9b462e7dcbc0"
msgstr "And praise them like their only gifted child."

msgid "a8112ff9c8694798bbf7186b380b8170"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, Their eloquence is like a "
"well-strung rosary."

msgid "a86a98bb28e04e7fb2d5a944d0508c63"
msgstr "When they elucidate the many profound and varied sūtras,"

msgid "beb8ce72f77444a1b5fa4e8d585c1c30"
msgstr "Their eloquence is vast, expansive, and inexhaustible."

msgid "d88b311b47f14268be86569a65fda0f1"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They are neither arrogant, "
"deceitful, nor proud."

msgid "a04f79ff461c46a5b04c39515a8d4da2"
msgstr ""
"They are mindful and intelligent, and they possesses the realization of the "
"wise ones."

msgid "00a30f805e3f47858e3b6d85e9929d34"
msgstr "The scope of their infinite knowledge is like the sky."

msgid "44195061e4224aceb6d53904c78f052e"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, All their faulty conditioning"
" is terminated."

msgid "eda00e48d7ed45d9a10333779a1bb998"
msgstr "Insight, wisdom, and skill is united,"

msgid "2619a451c7944abc918ac833f3c45adb"
msgstr "And love and compassion are likewise united."

msgid "c92d8b485c8f42af9bc9937b866c9b1c"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, There is not the slightest "
"agitation when they speak."

msgid "59fda2c6282b4e599c02b7aa0b202a24"
msgstr ""
"Great beings know the languages of ordinary beings, And their behaviors, "
"capacities, and inclinations as well."

msgid "d2d768f861604ea198e752c647a77789"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They attain special insight "
"into the Dharma and attain virtue, mindfulness, Miracles, abandonment, the "
"spiritual faculties, the five strengths, The factors of awakening, and "
"likewise the supreme path of tranquil abiding."

msgid "dbcc617189cc4f72820856a9ba437c80"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They realize the sugata "
"domain by themselves, Thoroughly perfect the perfections, And become "
"intelligent and skilled in the means of attraction."

msgid "a9e6fdc5efaf4024b73114e2e3fa7281"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, There will never be even the "
"slightest confusion."

msgid "3052b7e693e74a4eb22fb0907be00e6f"
msgstr "They will be determined but not intoxicated by peace or calm."

msgid "5b59e5be9e8f498284c1fa69a41c2af3"
msgstr "They will be disciplined and settled in conduct."

msgid "97c87297433e43e484f84da47b4e20ca"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They are present upon a lotus"
" flower in the presence of the Sugata."

msgid "420eace351514d59b0dbf308c4480999"
msgstr ""
"Their bodies will be nonsubstantial, arisen by the force of the Dharma"

msgid "47e27777c525443bbd539e7b00661df7"
msgstr "And unstained by the impurities of the womb."

msgid "4c815625382f430fbd152227ff46d068"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They are consecrated by all "
"the victors as proponents of the Dharma."

msgid "d5f0a2b845284ecb8b759f8b221f16a8"
msgstr ""
"Whatever physical, verbal, and mental actions they perform Will benefit "
"beings since they are done with omniscience."

msgid "3964f0c3c4454e7ba09a6801150d451a"
msgstr ""
"“When they have attained the supreme dhāraṇīs, They are endlessly applauded "
"when they speak."

msgid "be617bb2485a4fbbb0fddb19cfa9b0f6"
msgstr ""
"Even though the knowledge of the guide of all beings expands, Their praise "
"remains inconceivable for many eons.”"

msgid "41f6d83f02b94aeb955bb6d82a7dd484"
msgstr ""
"At this time, the Blessed One expressed his approval to the bodhisattva "
"mahāsattva Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja:"

msgid "06a02ec7983740369f0c2e4c7dfc6b08"
msgstr ""
"“Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja, it is excellent that you have explained this dhāraṇī "
"teaching so well, that you have assumed responsibility for these teachings, "
"and that you were motivated to request the profound words on the dhāraṇī "
"gateway from previous tathāgatas."

msgid "75720f3876ac4301a8baf3b882d9059b"
msgstr "It is very good!"

msgid "d7fbee257ade4842894a38d8e6df9db7"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja, you should also know what has transpired by "
"way of the following discourse."

msgid "a286431f117c40048164c303c75a0ef7"
msgstr ""
"“Once, in times past, inconceivably many eons ago, during the eon "
"Illuminating, in a world called Stainless, a tathāgata, a buddha, a blessed "
"one known as Stainless Illumination appeared in the world."

msgid "b5ab68134c4f47a7918813af9faa2692"
msgstr "The world Stainless was pure like lapis lazuli."

msgid "55d08c7eb6184bbc8e88b62451ef265c"
msgstr ""
"It was like a mirror wiped completely free of dust and was as smooth as the "
"palm of a hand."

msgid "42b11661533c4a489888465b81edaef5"
msgstr ""
"In that world grew fruit trees of the seven precious substances with jeweled"
" branches, leaves, flowers, and fruits."

msgid "3d082a05ef3741258e613ecd0c1a4f59"
msgstr ""
"There were many different beautiful lotus flowers the size of chariot wheels"
" made of gold extracted from the Jambu River."

msgid "bb057e3bf34344f2ad677204b651fc27"
msgstr ""
"“In that world divine and human beings enjoyed themselves in opulent "
"multistoried mansions."

msgid "085455e9702249fbb5505f1781c93a12"
msgstr "Food and drink appeared at the mere thought of it."

msgid "19a59ba8ff3f4546997cb566cf7836d5"
msgstr ""
"The amusements enjoyed by these divine and human beings resembled the "
"amusements enjoyed by the gods of the Para­nirmitavaśavartin heaven."

msgid "421d5f8ae08e4fbe96a8c9decd082101"
msgstr ""
"These divine and human beings had only a modicum of attachment, aversion, "
"and delusion. They were handsome and refined."

msgid "c58b6c07b38a43708da2adb2619e3cb1"
msgstr "“This world had neither sun nor moon."

msgid "3546f888aebd4fcd8eababf2d4107e38"
msgstr ""
"The Blessed Tathāgata Stainless Illumination lit up the entire buddhafield "
"with a glow that emanated from his body."

msgid "e569d1017a064282a193b0551cff1545"
msgstr ""
"The world even lacked names for day and night; the closing of the lotus "
"flowers marked nighttime and their opening marked daytime."

msgid "2a2700beacae4e288a8989064a5524fa"
msgstr ""
"“This tathāgata’s bodhisattva saṅgha comprised countless ordained "
"bodhisattvas in a state of equipoise."

msgid "eb76fe9fa9db4e24b28c98f469db54b8"
msgstr ""
"There were innumerable householders who had embarked on unsurpassed perfect "
"awakening."

msgid "9ce4c091561f4fa49e8224aa6ed7a639"
msgstr "Here, no vehicles except the Great Vehicle were disseminated."

msgid "21b276efad8f49dcacaf5bc6da9538f4"
msgstr ""
"The Blessed One taught the pure irreversible sermon, and his lifespan lasted"
" half an eon."

msgid "54f3fda9188347e0911dfadcff7a42ff"
msgstr "It was a world in which people did not grow old or die."

msgid "ad4ee9425b0940c6b41f5b7bcefc1f16"
msgstr ""
"In this buddhafield, those who dwelled in multistoried houses located on the"
" ground were considered ‘human’ beings, while those who dwelled in "
"multistoried houses located in the sky were considered ‘divine’ beings. "
"Other than that, there was no distinction between the divine and the human "
"beings in terms of their complexions or enjoyments."

msgid "8afa39072a03410085d0b295b595e432"
msgstr ""
"“In that world there were no kings, except for the blessed, unsurpassed "
"Dharma king."

msgid "c0441f663a2b4e959e8e635a904cb3c9"
msgstr ""
"In that world, there was no one except for the divine and human beings who "
"performed acts of worship to that tathāgata."

msgid "77a1a32a238a496581e021ec8cf62a60"
msgstr ""
"There were no gods except for those who aspired to listen to the Dharma."

msgid "5e49da348cb143bf9a2ca70212c48ad8"
msgstr ""
"There were no other teachers. No one kowtowed to others, performed "
"superfluous deeds, or thought of anything else."

msgid "5a4875b1f1024d218927b55a139d34b4"
msgstr ""
"“In this world no one was designated ‘a woman.’ Among its beings, no one was"
" designated ‘a sinner,’ and no one was designated ‘a transgressor of the "
"training.’"

msgid "bc978024ef2944589668b01df553e944"
msgstr "There were only those who trained in the three precepts."

msgid "9392389c5466439795a3c626f4540062"
msgstr "What are the three precepts?"

msgid "ea4da168c69f4bbe870e5d31a8f93770"
msgstr ""
"They are the precepts of advanced morality, advanced contemplation, and "
"advanced insight."

msgid "9e78045c45d2483f920cafbdcd753900"
msgstr "“What is the precept of advanced morality?"

msgid "3d34f08d765c4a6e8a1caf2f2e800c7f"
msgstr ""
"It consists in not forsaking the mind of omniscience and in abandoning "
"everything conditioned."

msgid "fb64c009d4ad46de8b47c20d16531dcf"
msgstr "What is the precept of advanced contemplation?"

msgid "7fff192ed7094d7b850613acf6855426"
msgstr ""
"It consists in attaining advanced understanding through settling in "
"absorption."

msgid "eaf1507f994f4e319427ad2c99ba0153"
msgstr "What is the precept of advanced insight?"

msgid "e411d605fa9a4dfa8f72c50eafd1cdfb"
msgstr ""
"It consists in attaining discriminating knowledge through being established "
"in the perfection of insight."

msgid "2615a14beb0d4c0a85a7cee8b1631750"
msgstr ""
"“Those bodhisattvas engaged in precepts like these without prior scriptural "
"transmission."

msgid "c9418413eecd455a905e811104d16596"
msgstr "This world realm was pure in this way."

msgid "cf31eea872d340d6a70f8ff8bdfc968c"
msgstr "The doctrinal exposition of this blessed one was pure in this way."

msgid "d10a823e7bdd4cdeb99d92bc31dca93a"
msgstr ""
"“At that time, a bodhisattva known as Glorious Light was present in the "
"retinue that had gathered."

msgid "83a3c791a99e43d5a03e2fdc0870c9c0"
msgstr "He rose from his seat and asked the Tathāgata,"

msgid "489226ecc11042e2a79f8f2fe533ea2f"
msgstr ""
"‘Blessed One, if one speaks of retaining dhāraṇī, what is the dhāraṇī in "
"which the blessed bodhisattvas are established so that everything taught by "
"all the blessed buddhas is upheld, the Dharma does not fade away once it has"
" been taught, and all sentient beings are satisfied through its eloquent "
"explanation?’"

msgid "3d32f3706567491c924cce83626934cc"
msgstr "“That blessed one replied,"

msgid "5577b27473ac4e68ada9776512ec2ad7"
msgstr ""
"‘Son of noble family, it is good that you thought to ask the Tathāgata about"
" this point. There is a dhāraṇī called jewel lamp."

msgid "a55e71ca01bb4b9594a2511e09e8455d"
msgstr ""
"Bodhisattvas who are established in this dhāraṇī retain all the buddha "
"teachings and appease all sentient beings through eloquent explanation.’"

msgid "fb54e1fad440403eaea0233130e67816"
msgstr "“Then Glorious Light requested the Tathāgata,"

msgid "bc82c839281b46559df98cd4cd5b7490"
msgstr ""
"‘Blessed One, please introduce the jewel lamp dhāraṇī so that we may "
"practice accordingly what we hear and so that we may attain this dhāraṇī.’"

msgid "64db957ccabf4094b71da67d8a066c2f"
msgstr "In reply the Tathāgata uttered the following verses:"

msgid "6811c1a6e0de452396132ab02766f175"
msgstr "“ ‘Freed from the dregs of afflictive emotions,"

msgid "311f29a08dab4b7a84f2709d13a0eb66"
msgstr "Stainless and purged of all defilements,"

msgid "7839b5e978964b1a9ebb280ff81bbf24"
msgstr "The mind is stainless and perpetually pure."

msgid "e7e86d3cfff943f88b06ee56936d48ca"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "b40084423ad044739ccf5f945dd013ed"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Through body, verbal expressions, and mind, One is luminous, stainless, "
"and free of blemish like the moon."

msgid "ffb0d62c4c5f4a01a0d9e8ba6e950cfa"
msgstr ""
"One has a loving intent and mental equanimity. Such is the jewel lamp "
"dhāraṇī."

msgid "a70c8084020f4ab2a8f5f284a33e1732"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Released from dualistic views And freed from all thoughts and "
"conceptualizing, One comprehends all conceptions."

msgid "327f35d784d74dd1abafa18d4e99ba9f"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "2808761bf8bc426db9af6c9d8f75cf9c"
msgstr "“ ‘Engaged in mindfulness, intelligence, and understanding"

msgid "342bf716584348db9b3074880d31f538"
msgstr "And endowed with qualities and vast insight,"

msgid "031dd5c582bb402a991aea381af69297"
msgstr "One is pure and stainless like the center of the sky."

msgid "27d0889e773442a987ab0f9a506abb96"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "15307d6b23554b40905a18162e4eea16"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The Three Jewels are an unbroken continuity. One is freed from the three "
"existences, the three stains having been relinquished,"

msgid "1c96952eb54c4f6bb87f20844afe26aa"
msgstr "And the duality of a doubting dualistic mind is terminated."

msgid "621cca95fe9e44438841d2de1316c025"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "264c9737e7134daaa917e49ab86aa0e0"
msgstr "“ ‘Desire, aversion, and ignorance conquered,"

msgid "85e32a5b58ed462091bf915da7ad49ea"
msgstr ""
"One is endowed with all qualities, the dregs of degenerate times left "
"behind,"

msgid "3a8e0df50f1f4c979c2255b149c29b7f"
msgstr ""
"And the visual distortion of obstructing afflictive emotions is removed."

msgid "68c1f4473bfa4fe99772179c471abd8d"
msgstr "Such is the supreme jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "14aeca672c2347bcbfde22afe350917f"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘One having become immersed in all languages, As many as there are in the "
"worlds, The lowest, the mediocre, and the highest,"

msgid "ae10498864b44949add6393407cfa372"
msgstr "The jewel lamp dhāraṇī remains unsullied."

msgid "50f6521736144876887bf5437a2a4cfd"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Endowed with profound teachings And with infinite and multifarious words "
"and syllables,"

msgid "ee34e4791c6d441387c2b1f15361534b"
msgstr "One is without failure for oneself or others."

msgid "0cbb8418b17348fab9ba4ac4362a116d"
msgstr "Such is this dhāraṇī that is endowed with nonduality."

msgid "fd50a863c18d4865a9ff43a54e9b02ef"
msgstr "“ ‘The four types of discriminating knowledge are attained,"

msgid "4577ddb005954a19a3201f78eaf0607b"
msgstr "The four bases of miraculous powers are established,"

msgid "f95592fb0d53472e82f4a1179685dcdd"
msgstr "And the four concentrations are embodied."

msgid "f73624910031424eadc57b87e4af058e"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "71645510d4134209b8c6f15f160bc791"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Being the system of teachings of the ultimate meaning, And possessing the"
" four abodes of Brahmā and the means of attraction,"

msgid "479a3b370faf43dcb718653706687465"
msgstr "One sets in motion the five kinds of superknowledge."

msgid "ee4b4d6153a04120a794e405a1e0fd28"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "ac9465e5ceeb4d35a1d6772447b53413"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Being established in the applications of mindfulness And in harmony with "
"the correct exertions,"

msgid "7dc04b2243804369aef07cb971d6c728"
msgstr "One activates the four bases of miraculous powers."

msgid "c4cc3d6f83854539bbc806bc7318c421"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "4a31f40b257f480a845b4e091656e32f"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Endowed with the five spiritual faculties And established with five "
"strengths,"

msgid "b5c8f560b76646c4a354b904ecfbb677"
msgstr "One is endowed with the factors of awakening, an unwavering force."

msgid "e05ea00e840444bfbb343ab286ee4aee"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "422a5d32579e4e63ace6894432848a22"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Motivated by the eightfold path, Supreme tranquil abiding and special "
"insight are united, And one is motivated by awareness and liberation."

msgid "0579422a0d9a43d0ace5b503e5861a86"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "8a25587c1ff440fb8494f73b19c13a1d"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘One being endowed with the spiritual levels to be mastered And in harmony"
" with the unifying path of freedom, All faults are totally abandoned."

msgid "ec9c8e6754e149eba80a59b10b407e9b"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "77f26bf9e5d449eb903e9182ce7f75d2"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘One sheds light on all worlds Like the luminous orbs of the sun and the "
"moon, Which are pure and eye opening."

msgid "4a8e26efc5d540bbaf18578a7fdddc30"
msgstr "Such is the jewel lamp dhāraṇī."

msgid "971f3e96eec847e5bba7c16a03e4679e"
msgstr "“ ‘Here the pure divine eye is without visual distortion,"

msgid "767919b038824190a044efc32ca72a32"
msgstr ""
"And the eyes of supreme insight are pure. Here, the eyes of Dharma are "
"likewise pure,"

msgid "8f87b67e9d6e44f686718bd05e2b693d"
msgstr "And the authentic vision of the Victor is pure."

msgid "344b35a4118440578e2379f37b8357ad"
msgstr "“ ‘Here the māra of afflictive emotions is purified,"

msgid "6d03bd5e1bb64099a7b6f6ce52c2484f"
msgstr "And the māra of aggregates is purified."

msgid "73e114038e124ab1aec257cd349e9d88"
msgstr ""
"Here the māra of the Lord of Death is purified, And here the māra of "
"sectarianism is also conquered."

msgid "8fee951cc2ba45f7b8de3d413dbfa7f8"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘One who abides in this dhāraṇī May travel to many different realms,"

msgid "657b4410abb84702afb8286d0b990fba"
msgstr "Behold vast numbers of buddhas, And listen to the highest Dharma."

msgid "c59e11724a904246b5a2796ecc68d584"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Hearing extensive teachings, One retains them through the power of "
"mindful dhāraṇī."

msgid "ece409c36a944c6cb1226e04df4c7cbb"
msgstr ""
"One even manages to retain the meanings and syllables And thereby teach all "
"beings."

msgid "fac72a256f604569b67269c8d1268d9b"
msgstr "“ ‘When classified by way of causes and conditions,"

msgid "06f628df1eac41daa2d3d483ce213771"
msgstr "Mind is understood to disintegrate moment by moment."

msgid "6e071d0dc14a489bb25d9902a05b06f2"
msgstr ""
"Attaining knowledge of how phenomena are classified, One abides in this "
"dhāraṇī."

msgid "4afb359e89434504afaaf4855aeb88ee"
msgstr "“ ‘One attains eloquence and is unobstructed in threefold awareness."

msgid "d52308c49c1d4cc6a4c201a53ba26de7"
msgstr "One attains purification of the three eyes"

msgid "e195756b10584365baa8bbf22319418c"
msgstr "And the goal of the three liberations."

msgid "e0fc6d12d3ff4a7f90b470fa496392ae"
msgstr "Here, one is endowed with attainment of dhāraṇīs."

msgid "d6e7169c1d624f2a987619f2cf741115"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Although the exegesis of the many dhāraṇīs Is unfathomable and boundless,"
" Having attained this excellent dhāraṇī, They are all mastered."

msgid "e0815c9e32834564ac55a2076259ff66"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘One enters the infinite concentrations and liberations, Equipoises and "
"absorptions, The playful expressions of superknowledge, And the infinite "
"dhāraṇīs."

msgid "d9900a202d434159af16c697a05bbd34"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Just as rivers, lakes, and ponds Flow into the vast and endless ocean "
"through limitless channels,"

msgid "186c262892624dd9bfb0b91cd9464e6b"
msgstr ""
"Those who uphold this dhāraṇī Pass through gateways of infinite teachings."

msgid "a901ce411cbc4b388f721f8bd96d6d54"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Engaging in countless languages, One masters them all through boundless "
"understanding."

msgid "b278297807924fa58c2446da32335594"
msgstr "For those who proclaim this dhāraṇī, Merit will never be exhausted."

msgid "c73738f4d1fa42dab82c6260a32c6dbf"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Those who attain this dhāraṇī Will hold a supreme, flawless jewel in "
"their hands."

msgid "48f89c4a2ad24ab5a0eabb8614b3cf3e"
msgstr "Their bodies, names, families, Clans, and births will be pure."

msgid "374c977b18f346d0807cf251b0cd3a6a"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The engagement in profound methods, The acceptance of nonarising, And the"
" levels of understanding the unoriginated and irreversible Are definitively "
"taught to be this dhāraṇī."

msgid "df75730edcef4667bb770b8e9dd2942c"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘When all bodhisattvas who seek Unsurpassed supreme awakening Have "
"attained this dhāraṇī, The highest awakening will not be hard to find."

msgid "9359f4f0226e4c2b824050da71514bcb"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Once the sugatas of the ten directions, Who teach Dharma to benefit and "
"delight people, Have attained the excellence of this dhāraṇī,"

msgid "fb285d031b794dd5b126ba720f0f5d43"
msgstr "Their eloquence will be uninterrupted."

msgid "d678b60c4ed246dbba57076dc7810e7e"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘When those who have attained this dhāraṇī Understand the joys, "
"aspirations, and thoughts of beings, They will teach them the fruition that "
"is ever-present,"

msgid "d1b48789db3740238244e5888bd3bd2a"
msgstr "And thus bring satisfaction to vast numbers of beings."

msgid "98b4cc9c9d234371b70e987da21d0d00"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘Brave ones abiding in this dhāraṇī Turn the wheel of the sacred Dharma"

msgid "c49ea6c63f304419be900a2626623503"
msgstr ""
"And thus free beings from their sundry forms of suffering, Setting them in "
"the excellent vehicle."

msgid "238116a1ba3f4ee798cb95ab5f4e208a"
msgstr ""
"“ ‘The great sages may, for many eons, Praise and extoll its qualities, But "
"they will not manage to express The full extent of its qualities.’"

msgid "8644b1d37deb4ebe96d53ee31e1889ec"
msgstr ""
"“As the Blessed Tathāgata Stainless Illumination gave this dhāraṇī teaching,"
" thirty-two thousand bodhisattvas within the great bodhisattva assembly "
"attained the dhāraṇī, among them the bodhisattva mahāsattva Glorious Light."

msgid "de82c97b264c4c269d87c65892c2a545"
msgstr ""
"Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja, you may reflect or wonder, doubt, or regard with "
"skepticism whether the bodhisattva of this period known as Glorious Light "
"was someone else, but you should not!"

msgid "b57acd6d510842448d87f806a37aa87d"
msgstr "Why not?"

msgid "2c3ab48c2e244f4da6535ac19c325fe6"
msgstr ""
"Because really you yourself were the bodhisattva of that period known as "
"Glorious Light!"

msgid "d0781993dca04fdf935a7b8b627ed2bc"
msgstr ""
"Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja, you have requested countless tathāgatas since time "
"immemorial for this analysis of dhāraṇī."

msgid "5c2d22aea0a744b68847f53ae5aa1011"
msgstr "You have made such an inquiry."

msgid "d153ed9a7aa8409aaf5a3094988fecf4"
msgstr ""
"“That is why you again have made a request to the Tathāgata and have "
"fearlessly delivered this dhāraṇī analysis."

msgid "b0e250ab84964628aeccdf2a17d8c4a1"
msgstr ""
"Since you have realized this Dharma with your all-seeing intelligence, with "
"this discourse I declare you to be supreme among bodhisattvas endowed with "
"mindfulness and among the bodhisattvas who have attained dhāraṇī.”"

msgid "fd2baba570374baca2f5fb4ff7b10bde"
msgstr ""
"At this point, a bodhisattva known as Prajñākūṭa, who was present in that "
"assembly, asked,"

msgid "d03d54e78aad42c7901c716f889bea31"
msgstr "“How, Blessed One, do bodhisattvas attain this jewel lamp dhāraṇī?"

msgid "081b1abea5c24d1487041c033106e59a"
msgstr "And having attained it, how do they avoid losing it?"

msgid "c78dfcf3176a4798a6d7ad0f616888b7"
msgstr ""
"And having generated the power of the dhāraṇī, how do they sustain all "
"sentient beings?”"

msgid "4ee07e3204604490838f4af35620a125"
msgstr "The Blessed One replied,"

msgid "bfe45233d4f74accb05ed33d67799cd4"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, when bodhisattvas abide by the sources of insight and "
"perform the functions of insight, they will attain this dhāraṇī."

msgid "a9966525f6354eeeb45f22b4c5c356e1"
msgstr "There is no doubt about it."

msgid "064d5279194b459e89b51afea059ca76"
msgstr "They will nurture all beings.”"

msgid "124e6aeac95c488b882289a5fbf7744d"
msgstr "Prajñākūṭa asked in turn,"

msgid "d62e1db522b045a78aa3d87e7ad31e86"
msgstr ""
"“Blessed One, what are the sources and functions of insight? Please explain "
"it to me.”"

msgid "7d414e76e15145c3bfb8bce56eabf4ae"
msgstr "The Blessed One replied,"

msgid "368e12da62a14bcb9dc6bb738581308b"
msgstr ""
"“Because of your request, son of noble family, listen carefully and bear in "
"mind what I tell you. These are the sources of insight and their "
"corresponding functions:"

msgid "539b6c4f08594a70aed8ba418776cab6"
msgstr ""
"Son of noble family, listening to teachings not yet heard is a source of "
"insight."

msgid "8ff652f9081e450fbf156e8871fac515"
msgstr "Its function is to teach others the Dharma one has heard in detail."

msgid "556fc087379840fca907f3d41f90b255"
msgstr "Investigation is a source of insight."

msgid "f0d29cdee0c2408d8f1d3f361e2206a7"
msgstr "Its function is to teach others what one has investigated."

msgid "ad695a9173d844d88a68b223c0122893"
msgstr "Proper discernment is a source of insight."

msgid "684d2da5f2f2465789cae55fc3fc2c40"
msgstr "Its function is to establish beings in what is appropriate."

msgid "c74879263f834f62a07e2a3a4f6d2b3b"
msgstr "Application is a source of insight."

msgid "1ec812ba56a44f33b75ff7948ea656f0"
msgstr "Its function is to accomplish."

msgid "f9b516a6e0864d8e9c1de23c7168696c"
msgstr "Thinking decisively about mind is a source of insight."

msgid "9a09f6a6f7f24eecb52006be4108ea9a"
msgstr "Its function is to teach decisive thinking about mind."

msgid "538dbbe48258480cb2265f9a3eac6f62"
msgstr "Dwelling in solitude is a source of insight."

msgid "e6988d72a21a410c84553fb3d7391831"
msgstr "Its function is to know how to isolate body and mind."

msgid "0c3de7f26aec4ff2adc16ad690510a61"
msgstr "Delighting in solitude is a source of insight."

msgid "dd4d0ea7f454487d9a06765d7d8b5e34"
msgstr "Its function is to accomplish a solitary path."

msgid "ba4914d82995402d842962bf94e4b11a"
msgstr ""
"Cultivating tranquil abiding and special insight is a source of insight."

msgid "94f58cc7f8ff4e97b4e33ac7baae0f32"
msgstr "Its function is to attain awareness and liberation."

msgid "9d029312bb0c4e488c844592fc859140"
msgstr "Cultivating the three liberations is a source of insight."

msgid "5bb9904df82a4b469f730647123ac88f"
msgstr "Its function is to realize threefold awareness."

msgid "346d1fc738ac4a019a5f337e555c9fdc"
msgstr "Cultivating the application of mindfulness is a source of insight."

msgid "40a4b763aca942e29ac57dd2e0ee380a"
msgstr "Its function is the absence of mindfulness and mental activity."

msgid "6a016071bd9e456c81598a1b51d79de0"
msgstr "Cultivating abandonment is a source of insight."

msgid "09476ada492c4fe99ff2257c7092a739"
msgstr "Its function is to know all phenomena to be naturally abandoned."

msgid "4bcd1ee06b494eae8deb75556c03b9d4"
msgstr "Cultivating the bases of miraculous powers is a source of insight."

msgid "206c739ae7d54b2bb3940c38c76582a1"
msgstr "Its function is to attain miraculous power without manifestation."

msgid "07414aaf4e3145e294ef712d38cdc342"
msgstr "Confidence with faithful devotion is a source of insight."

msgid "55044b0142dd43ba811d19efb84db016"
msgstr "Its function is to transcend all attachments."

msgid "6502e494b4a749f78ffbc6d09636f645"
msgstr "Dauntlessness is a source of insight."

msgid "a0120e2b63794a57b1234a34138e8091"
msgstr "Its function is to be well trained in body and mind."

msgid "211b8c7b0d6d44b0b31640d9bdd57cb2"
msgstr "Mindfulness and introspection are sources of knowledge."

msgid "88048573a5234f24a621bdaa9aff698a"
msgstr "Their function is to attend to what is to be recollected."

msgid "19ba3a078a31415b83131e85ee8fa5d7"
msgstr ""
"Gaining realization in the levels of meditative absorption is a source of "
"insight."

msgid "3dbe06ab7f25460fbc2cdfb943d5aea9"
msgstr "Its function is to attain constant presence in equipoise."

msgid "2aedfc5977b648fc9e5c69409d57b4c8"
msgstr "“Relying on the faculty of insight is itself a source of insight."

msgid "a3a22932c43a41c595eee205f02f7c48"
msgstr "Its function is to know which faculties are best and which are not."

msgid "52aa0944e2434712a8318e92faa98dcc"
msgstr "Knowing the five strengths is a source of insight."

msgid "1edae859d2c04247a98cb7b55fc1089f"
msgstr "Its function is not to be crushed by evil and afflictive emotions."

msgid "e975a089dda744ed976fa0f2ac385098"
msgstr ""
"Harmoniously accepting the factors of awakening is a source of insight."

msgid "3452fa806b7c4389ae07bc7907a3909c"
msgstr "Its function is to harmoniously realize the nature of all phenomena."

msgid "60ebe1dc55cb41e780354ba988db172b"
msgstr "Practicing the branches of the path is a source of insight."

msgid "b1013d076b45466b969e431b04add4ed"
msgstr ""
"Its function is not to be partisan toward Dharma or non-Dharma by "
"understanding that all teachings are like rafts."

msgid "1a6b2b7485ba4beb9141dabb8641451e"
msgstr ""
"Familiarizing oneself with suffering and its origin, cessation, and the path"
" is a source of insight."

msgid "f161bdd16aed4129ace5db0a706fd7be"
msgstr "Its function is to actualize cessation."

msgid "b33acb47735c4323b04fac55d00eb2d3"
msgstr "“Mastering the sūtras of provisional meaning is a source of insight."

msgid "3565e690410c4059b30294e89aa53677"
msgstr "Its function is to rely on the sūtras of definitive meaning."

msgid "c29788dcacaf43619132e37984de376e"
msgstr "Retaining everything that one has learned is a source of insight."

msgid "7015c47198de43099261c2f2efcf8c6c"
msgstr "Its function is to rely on the meaning."

msgid "3ac297e22abe429fa46e80e818d894f0"
msgstr "Investigating consciousness is a source of insight."

msgid "c6b8b065d0ef402eb528e869d48167f7"
msgstr "Its function is to rely on wisdom."

msgid "4fbdfb2bd2df4d3894d6bb1e306399d9"
msgstr "Not clinging to the words of an individual is a source of insight."

msgid "12eff104b0544b4e86a7853b0d191ab3"
msgstr "Its function is to rely on the nature of reality."

msgid "8e37c3255d7c4edcbf62cba7452f4828"
msgstr ""
"“Discerning that all karmic formations are impermanent is a source of "
"insight."

msgid "e1e997326f154f51a8d57007f6196a8f"
msgstr "Its function is to know fundamental nonorigination."

msgid "488828ad834c49dfa5bfcbb94846aefb"
msgstr ""
"Comprehending analytically that all formations are painful is a source of "
"insight."

msgid "f88e2288b5cf4630ab3f1c201f942d66"
msgstr ""
"Its function is to know that all phenomena are not actually conditioned."

msgid "e9ad6ebe97f8463b8023ea43588120eb"
msgstr "Discerning that phenomena are selfless is a source of insight."

msgid "d9288e4bfe4e4ff48184418deb8172d9"
msgstr "Its function is to know that beings are primordially pure."

msgid "911ad4604ae7409a976bd4bb5175f579"
msgstr "Discerning that nirvāṇa is peace is a source of insight."

msgid "21e4c14efe1941e3a942c7105eb2aa6e"
msgstr "Its function is to know that all phenomena are nirvāṇa by nature."

msgid "cc8349ebc25549398fb7278064d34f48"
msgstr "“Being unintimidated when one hears the truth is a source of insight."

msgid "630362f298cd42968f50fc8d077b4b90"
msgstr "Its function is to have special awareness of the truth."

msgid "2096bc6189db4ed78eaea8f4fb0b624a"
msgstr ""
"Being unintimidated when one hears of the nature of reality is a source of "
"insight."

msgid "e947844c4bb44ff2b49c8d39f5482320"
msgstr "Its function is to have special awareness of all phenomena."

msgid "08ff6f1a422b4d48b5697bd62615c2c1"
msgstr "Being unintimidated by any etymologies is a source of insight."

msgid "c4a86bba83c14ef29cb6c18c925c274b"
msgstr "Its function is to have special awareness of etymologies."

msgid "ef130d1c632c459d93c4ce34480f38e6"
msgstr ""
"Being unintimidated when one hears the Buddha’s eloquence is a source of "
"insight."

msgid "208f09361013447e8f91c29a2964d216"
msgstr "Its function is to have special awareness of eloquence."

msgid "d16981db81d646908f9e83230e8ac04f"
msgstr "Feeling love toward beings and phenomena is a source of insight."

msgid "d58f3c6c246c43e9a0f623d73645949e"
msgstr "Its function is to experience nonreferential love."

msgid "db76ee0725c44c59a4678a9a93404f63"
msgstr ""
"Acting compassionately toward oneself and others is a source of insight."

msgid "81386fbe362b44dfa8f5740b778fad66"
msgstr ""
"Its function is to experience great compassion that dissolves duality."

msgid "feaf8f83d8354e7397a188091df84536"
msgstr ""
"“Delighting in cultivating supreme joy when attending to the Dharma is a "
"source of insight."

msgid "dc2781a2887e42cf982a549de0f29b8f"
msgstr "Its function is to be without acceptance and rejection."

msgid "83ff125f45f54518b93a8b5a91f75fec"
msgstr ""
"Being impartial, free from attachment or aversion, is a source of insight."

msgid "f22ff9c7993e4236b55e5f06cd75ecf9"
msgstr "Its function is to be free from duality."

msgid "a209ce43c85f44d8ab6db86e2900e574"
msgstr "Recollecting the Buddha is a source of insight."

msgid "f2b994940097489c9737aec5049a736b"
msgstr "Its function is to know dharmakāya."

msgid "508e6b6da2704fa4883f450306488681"
msgstr "Recollecting the Dharma is a source of insight."

msgid "cd9c5eb756024076b67c09a4e45bf5d9"
msgstr "Its function is to know the nature of reality beyond attachment."

msgid "d93ed4320bc44b0ca876e04606ebe735"
msgstr "Recollecting the Saṅgha is a source of insight."

msgid "c4d7dfba7e7a4bf78ffa7ede5872cf84"
msgstr "Its function is to comprehend it analytically as being unconditioned."

msgid "f6004bc972fb46bfa177e6f93020e443"
msgstr "Recollecting generosity is a source of insight."

msgid "61281152f1c34b1592a87be19bc34c9f"
msgstr "Its function is to let go of all afflictive emotions."

msgid "5a41b518fdbb424597f07d8dee31942d"
msgstr "Recollecting moral conduct is a source of insight."

msgid "531932d074c34b5987990d6ea6023927"
msgstr ""
"Its function is to know that moral conduct is not actually something to be "
"accumulated."

msgid "ece925b51ddc4b738ce67130fbe3d142"
msgstr "Recollecting the gods is a source of insight."

msgid "8aecaf8753c04defa9912bb77cf5e6c7"
msgstr "Its function is the pure nature of reality."

msgid "0ee75b8197444b74aa2ccb36ad048910"
msgstr "“Comprehending what one has learned is a source of insight."

msgid "e160e524a9294cf8886eacae06e5e54c"
msgstr "Its function is to comprehend all worlds."

msgid "b9f5dece97bc436eb69003d39646a2b9"
msgstr "Performing deeds to be done is a source of insight."

msgid "77b48c386f5d46ada92cbf5b546a6604"
msgstr "Its function is to know the maturation of actions to be nonexistent."

msgid "4eeaf53bb821433585931b289d82ee8f"
msgstr "Being without pride is a source of insight."

msgid "897665cedf9d4a9e9f73f86ab5fd80c5"
msgstr "Its function is to attain great wisdom."

msgid "c9b18a016ef8459181b9145439086aaa"
msgstr "Benefiting oneself is a source of insight."

msgid "f2a89b15c49c4e6e8a7ef9665e7d9d42"
msgstr "Its function is to benefit both oneself and others."

msgid "d18c788ff0e74d569e2c1ed8c65549a5"
msgstr ""
"Upholding the eighty-four thousand Dharma teachings is a source of insight."

msgid "153239033fd74756b00ff8cb30ca6efa"
msgstr "Its function is to know the eighty-four thousand Dharma teachings."

msgid "86b7c345a3c04853ab8f8b9bbe72a0ec"
msgstr "Knowing Dharma teachings is a source of insight."

msgid "1daa9b51142543a3b610cb326572e4c5"
msgstr "Its function is to teach Dharma successfully."

msgid "f00d5677012245bdb7660624f975abc9"
msgstr "Inspiring beings to embrace awakening is a source of insight."

msgid "3535a0484286414fa5d266dad0f7b185"
msgstr ""
"Its function is to place beings on the level of nonregression through the "
"perfection of insight and skillful means."

msgid "4e257e5d039b497084217d9aeb53218e"
msgstr ""
"Being apprehensive of any birth as a being in worldly existence is a source "
"of insight."

msgid "ccd6b83cb91b4d0abb82535523b81df9"
msgstr "Its function is to be born according to one’s intentions."

msgid "4a9ac583124441c88ff8d0cbde1a3b2e"
msgstr "Acceptance that accords with language is a source of insight."

msgid "95d2d27bf1424af589a4e1806d85e5c5"
msgstr "Its function is acceptance that rises from cultivation."

msgid "de4fc388c85c4cb98561ecf8649a1181"
msgstr "“Understanding decay is a source of insight."

msgid "1d8523fe75bc4158a099ee7a74ab11fb"
msgstr "Its function is to understand nonorigination."

msgid "334dcd45094243e38704966a3ad556ae"
msgstr "Willing acceptance is a source of insight."

msgid "a6ee2683f61c47c58e4f23391a5c35c9"
msgstr "Its function is to accept the unborn nature of phenomena."

msgid "adb8ec42ba34492ca061d7066dec29c6"
msgstr "The level of nonregression is a source of insight."

msgid "420668c8e58945bca19dc4c4055025b6"
msgstr "Its function is the level of empowerment."

msgid "3192c745e44643cb92ac006b4c8b7aaf"
msgstr "Sitting down on the seat of awakening is a source of insight."

msgid "f35658c079f1482fa78c940a241d3094"
msgstr ""
"Its function is to perfectly awaken to unsurpassed complete and perfect "
"awakening through insight that thinks, in a single moment, of everything "
"whatsoever that is to be known, learned, realized, and perfectly awakened "
"to.”"

msgid "9bea5090710c468d80634f16eff5e888"
msgstr ""
"As this account of the sources and functions of insight was delivered, the "
"countless unfathomable buddhafields of the ten directions trembled six "
"times, as did the pavilion made of jewels."

msgid "251b12288745484f984a52f32e2f53dd"
msgstr "Prajñākūṭa asked the Blessed One,"

msgid "68fd4f015eef4fabb5cbd4e65a8ffe04"
msgstr ""
"“What has caused these countless, unfathomable buddhafields of the ten "
"directions, as well as this pavilion hovering in the sky, to tremble six "
"times?”"

msgid "b2c1206838094479a98d996969598880"
msgstr "The Blessed One replied,"

msgid "be2a90c2d36448238816a3dd8e8a430b"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, when the tathāgatas of the past previously explained "
"this Dharma discourse on the sources and functions of insight, upon your "
"request and inquiry, son of noble family, it caused the great world to "
"tremble and the earth to quake in the very space that holds it.”"

msgid "d04bbc7f88734736bdffe9363e5ead73"
msgstr ""
"Then a bodhisattva called Prati­bhāna­pratisaṃvid asked the Blessed One,"

msgid "384fe3b04a7b4d189ba1ed1f74b5292d"
msgstr "“Blessed One, why is the bodhisattva Prajñākūṭa called Prajñākūṭa?”"

msgid "fda89a23a6af49508a6432edbbf9d0c8"
msgstr "The Blessed One replied,"

msgid "45d84e85ea894885b81f75c0e9108fc6"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, once in past times, during the Stainless eon, in the "
"world Virtuous Occurrence, there appeared a tathāgata, a blessed buddha "
"named Glorious Secret."

msgid "69bb71b0c3fd49768f6d35a5a2a84b20"
msgstr ""
"The inhabitants of that world lived with a bliss-filled state of mind."

msgid "08f9cf4c39d2431792ae67d404ef4af5"
msgstr ""
"The Tathāgata’s bodhisattva saṅgha consisted of forty-two thousand "
"bodhisattvas, and his śrāvaka saṅgha comprised eighty-four thousand "
"śrāvakas."

msgid "6a98828309f242659a4e092f1c2dcb61"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, this blessed one apprehended that the eloquence of "
"those bodhisattvas was extensive, and he deliberately posed a large number "
"of questions."

msgid "1ea15ab3817a49828bba31fbe2255894"
msgstr ""
"He then inquired, ‘Noble beings, who among you would like to give "
"comprehensive explanations in reply to each and every one of my many "
"questions, at a time of your own choosing?’"

msgid "9e771260fcc047449031445929c28992"
msgstr "“One of them said, ‘I shall reply tonight,’"

msgid "5804f52c14314145b62d87370ec1af19"
msgstr "and another one said, ‘I shall reply in a week.’"

msgid "cb2e005f06c84aebbd56346023d8f000"
msgstr "Another said, ‘I shall reply in a fortnight,’"

msgid "7364abea2a8c4c7087a6ac241e8ec5cc"
msgstr "and yet another said, ‘Blessed One, I shall reply in one month.’"

msgid "7e0c3a611fa94ed59704b47977e847aa"
msgstr ""
"Thereupon, a bodhisattva called Smṛtibuddhi, who was present in the retinue,"
" replied,"

msgid "b5fa3e7f5d0543fdb6777bc93bb4682a"
msgstr ""
"‘Blessed One, with the Tathāgata’s permission, without further ado, and "
"without rising from my seat, I shall provide answers to the questions.’"

msgid "9abee54b096945d7b4305041e358d76d"
msgstr ""
"“As soon as the lion’s roar of this noble being resounded, the entire "
"trichiliocosm trembled six times."

msgid "19eebc1bda7648f9ae79b3fa143f9271"
msgstr "A great illumination appeared in the world."

msgid "cf0eb9d16bbc4402b27be179a99bbb78"
msgstr ""
"Inspired by this light, all kinds of gods gathered, from the celestial gods "
"up to the gods of the pure abodes."

msgid "12aa7456793f4b02bada3e5d9e9df7cf"
msgstr ""
"Many thousands of monks and nuns, as well as male and female lay devotees, "
"also congregated. All at once and in a single instant, they were transformed"
" into a single ten-thousand-league maṇḍala retinue."

msgid "4f6a0963718340cf9baad6b324e12821"
msgstr ""
"“Then, once the bodhisattva had seen this assembly gather, by the power of "
"his own merit, wisdom, mindfulness, dhāraṇī, eloquence, and fearlessness, as"
" well as by the power of the blessing of the buddhas, he fielded all the "
"many well-considered questions that had been asked."

msgid "5198f5a6529a4b1aa6f50e9a42b0746e"
msgstr ""
"In the presence of that buddha and in front of the entire assembly, he "
"provided countless explanations for each and every one of the many "
"questions."

msgid "4aa90e32c6c6427b812fea3b99481438"
msgstr ""
"He replied fluently, without interruption, coherently, and with the right "
"words, syllables, and etymologies."

msgid "49a3e4d7affe4ab59c06c607a1c32560"
msgstr ""
"In that manner, sixty thousand members of the assembly generated the thought"
" of perfect awakening, and forty thousand bodhisattvas attained acceptance "
"of the nonorigination of phenomena."

msgid "39a7695d9f6e455dbc5c6a9b6f6cc226"
msgstr "The Blessed One expressed his approval of the answers."

msgid "8512c66538404c17b96fdae570483a83"
msgstr ""
"The melody carrying the sound of his approval reverberated throughout the "
"entire trichiliocosm."

msgid "1aebcc23fe0a46208fd9d97cb5f5322b"
msgstr ""
"“All the gods, from the celestial gods up to the gods of the pure abodes, "
"proclaimed, ‘Listen!"

msgid "3118b46e91cc44b2a7804ad60faad8be"
msgstr ""
"Someone of such insight, eloquence, and skill in teaching will become a "
"bodhisattva called Prajñākūṭa!’"

msgid "6a167de18e544d748b1d26e792c3d244"
msgstr "In this way, Prajñākūṭa received the name Prajñākūṭa."

msgid "50bdace8a54a4f9bb4396e2451e48266"
msgstr ""
"“Son of noble family, you may wonder, doubt, or ponder whether the "
"bodhisattva called Smṛtibuddhi was someone else at that time, but you should"
" not."

msgid "ca14caa39ab248d398f689ecd72b3747"
msgstr "Why not?"

msgid "2c02a0de4f7740afa35eb96a4782652d"
msgstr ""
"It was bodhisattva Prajñākūṭa himself who was the bodhisattva called "
"Smṛtibuddhi at that time!”"

msgid "a895d5afa4e1495f8071e235b5ca154f"
msgstr ""
"At this point, the Blessed One spoke these verses in order to elaborate on "
"this point:"

msgid "b517072b3ee74c208fd406b653cd977f"
msgstr ""
"“Listening constantly to teachings not yet heard or sought, Pure beings "
"attain the source of insight."

msgid "cd1c5b520ed148c28db5160216243fad"
msgstr ""
"Retaining them and teaching beings with love, Bodhisattvas continually "
"perform the function of insight."

msgid "1fed185c98fc4747a9927c72b9d934df"
msgstr ""
"“Great mindfulness in investigation is a source of insight. Its function is "
"to constantly teach beings on the basis of such investigation."

msgid "49ca60e6a27b45458d084ae05e48b6ee"
msgstr ""
"Proper incineration of false views is a source of insight. Its function is "
"to teach based on such engagement."

msgid "7442495175444581ba3ba8aa88166b34"
msgstr "“Correct application is a source of insight."

msgid "875526d6d2244d0a8d95b6b166f7241b"
msgstr "Its function is to yield accomplishments and teachings."

msgid "d13472a3e4e54722ae15f36c57a6873f"
msgstr "Finding mental certainty regarding the mind is a source of insight."

msgid "90a9343738614cb5bf82d5062db6657f"
msgstr "Its function is to act upon this certainty."

msgid "b130630343914381bb3374a6ba404811"
msgstr "“Practicing alone in solitude is a source of insight."

msgid "777fbfb56303458a87ac657505499b85"
msgstr "Its function is to be without an I in body or mind."

msgid "d301d1ea2336441daaad6b94f456caee"
msgstr "Being wary of hustle and bustle is a source of insight."

msgid "df256d1868d4479494891c0f6611b839"
msgstr ""
"Its function is to raise awareness regarding the path traversed alone."

msgid "8c592429500a4ad78b2f944502b37fee"
msgstr ""
"“Delighting in tranquil abiding and special insight is a source of insight."

msgid "60ac52b961254ad8ad3a663d48d9fe91"
msgstr "Its function is to get in touch with awareness and liberation."

msgid "c81d16fe29494cd0bff68743f952fcc6"
msgstr "Pursuing the three liberations is a source of insight."

msgid "23f7f437cf564b4297cf901513e18bb1"
msgstr "Its function is to manifest threefold awareness."

msgid "d84d5770332d485cac4b02eb0400475f"
msgstr "“Cultivating the application of mindfulness is a source of insight."

msgid "d84f2b2be322490490bfadcd4ab9a3eb"
msgstr ""
"Its function is to be without mindfulness and without and mental activity."

msgid "b9802e2122bd4989891d7b873c9969ae"
msgstr "Abandoning evil and practicing virtue are sources of insight."

msgid "83c2618889e84c6993db2bc7a8694756"
msgstr "Their function is to naturally abandon these factors."

msgid "921c583ecc22401885d93a5780f0166e"
msgstr ""
"“Cultivating the four bases of miraculous powers is a source of insight."

msgid "6d10949274e246caabad0e328a5f59b4"
msgstr "Its function is to spontaneously attain miraculous power."

msgid "e85f2ce5425240e2ba3e477b829bf720"
msgstr "Confidence with faithful devotion is a source of insight."

msgid "88fc77a0ba5f4f10a404256b1505a2ed"
msgstr "Its function is to be free of any attachments whatsoever."

msgid "59105515ea5e43978e7a1ab4f6c17ee5"
msgstr ""
"“Striving constantly and without growing fainthearted is a source of "
"insight."

msgid "6c8b587a6db04b629fbf010e1f384aad"
msgstr "Its function is to be well trained in body and mind."

msgid "f4c472c90170464980804843b7cef338"
msgstr "Mastery in mindfulness and introspection is a source of insight."

msgid "ba362239a7214ad0a2d0b3d2dee34ae9"
msgstr "Its function is not to fixate on any point."

msgid "143c889b60f04e49a6a0955b15c1ac0f"
msgstr "“Realizing meditative absorption by oneself is a source of insight."

msgid "83688520aa704219bde9b4d929fcfb62"
msgstr "Its function is to progress naturally in equipoise."

msgid "1029ac7931454bd8a5564a41fbb59f80"
msgstr ""
"Being well established in the faculty of insight is a source of insight."

msgid "a87ba1c4829b4111baaf82285aa53915"
msgstr "Its function is to know all the faculties of beings."

msgid "f31497d6f31e4d7b8fe99d0efaf6508c"
msgstr "“Cultivating the five strengths is a source of insight."

msgid "7756f4a826a1442496bf755d130281df"
msgstr "Its function is to attain wisdom following such victory."

msgid "92f12578e5f54cbd871c05c4a85fbcd4"
msgstr ""
"Harmoniously accepting the factors of awakening is a source of insight."

msgid "fa2e38f91b0b49c194f59cde720dbbf8"
msgstr "Its function is to gain realization that accords with all phenomena."

msgid "4aab9e47afdb427e94c1cc96e2ac5059"
msgstr ""
"“Practicing the branches of the path in this birth is a source of insight."

msgid "0f7055e84eef47a48816ee235661c006"
msgstr "Its function is to leave behind both Dharma and non-Dharma."

msgid "5c8060245f2b41e6aa3e195946531b3b"
msgstr "Being skilled in the nature of suffering is a source of insight."

msgid "503181efcc7442299a35dc27d7850132"
msgstr "Its function is to actualize cessation."

msgid "e7f69a1e4c3f485f8dd95b6388adcebf"
msgstr ""
"“Retaining the words of the provisional sūtras is a source of insight."

msgid "94c03a3877d24f9f9dfb353a048fc85e"
msgstr "Its function is to rely on the definitive meaning."

msgid "0f192d552b6f44eabd0d86341e9f903d"
msgstr "Not being content with what one has learned is a source of insight."

msgid "d79780d2ea2948a4b4033fbefcc9e40c"
msgstr "Its function is to rely on the meaning."

msgid "3a16d54581ff4fd2aff3302cbe6a584c"
msgstr "“Investigating consciousness is a source of insight."

msgid "693baf54980741e3a1d1c1e642a1fa3f"
msgstr "Its function is to rely on wisdom."

msgid "8a38a7fcb5c84d71a9d39901373208c7"
msgstr "Not clinging to any individual is a source of insight."

msgid "2ddcfdecb5dc47c990dc12f7e6144921"
msgstr "Its function is to rely on the nature of reality."

msgid "7c0069105ce94da4ac68224781e31be0"
msgstr ""
"“Scrutinizing karmic formations as impermanent is a source of insight."

msgid "1f597c9526c949a2b4f0a058c5aecd7e"
msgstr "Its function is to know they are originally unborn."

msgid "80cd6f3880f24fc3899136692280433c"
msgstr "Attending to formations as painful is a source of insight."

msgid "7be0424632e543748dbab5f9c499d43f"
msgstr "Its function is to attend to phenomena as being unconditioned."

msgid "2dc9d5d15012468e9cb6153d33549d86"
msgstr ""
"“Having no doubt that all phenomena are without self is a source of insight."

msgid "f656af2e684348d0af666d3ecbf6ec39"
msgstr "Its function is to know the primordial purity of beings."

msgid "f1a67a4c068e4d5b9281ad2d5339f06c"
msgstr "Appreciating that nirvāṇa is peace is a source of insight."

msgid "a9ed43c994594a708fd74f64e25161d5"
msgstr "Its function is to know that beings are nirvāṇa."

msgid "1d04a639047a49a5a1374b04ab0c8d36"
msgstr "“Realization that accords with truth is a source of insight."

msgid "deb5b64f2c2e48d4937245de37889c97"
msgstr "Its function is to have special awareness of the truth."

msgid "6f87cc12e06c4446a6e25e612b4a1d22"
msgstr "Gaining appreciation of the nature of reality is a source of insight."

msgid "4c2e4752a81c4394af58d415afa65e88"
msgstr "Its function is to have special awareness of phenomena."

msgid "740044661536467a94c1bf56ba51956f"
msgstr "“Being unintimidated by any words is a source of insight."

msgid "5144cad4a8694937a7e4d8e63941cf64"
msgstr "Its function is to have special awareness of etymologies."

msgid "8d6668c06c914a0dbf120fe042de4e79"
msgstr "Being unintimidated by eloquence is a source of insight."

msgid "224f9417d08d49b38aea600180099c59"
msgstr "Its function is to have special awareness of eloquence."

msgid "9af5357c1d9a4b908e421c55bd3c0cab"
msgstr "“Feeling abiding love for beings is a source of insight."

msgid "572afc341fdd4aafbad17e728db2e1b6"
msgstr "Its function is to attain nonreferential love."

msgid "57ee4052bddd472ca3a7d40ca83a0ad5"
msgstr "Feeling compassion for self and others is a source of insight."

msgid "83f0393c6da44cd4873ba2f1f3dd5685"
msgstr "Its function is not to conceive of either."

msgid "cbb1da5c18de4c51a06eb4d21d136ed6"
msgstr "“Delighting in supreme joy is a source of insight."

msgid "6605e980111a4516887f1a0fc6b4c675"
msgstr "Its function is not to feel joy or anguish."

msgid "b51f33e8a6ac49f6b6e7af287f37775f"
msgstr "Being neither desirous nor harmful in conduct is a source of insight."

msgid "cda44df5b120464fb1c9b5e536232048"
msgstr "Its function is to attain mental release from duality."

msgid "b807692feb3d4ec794d9b42e4ccd68da"
msgstr "“Recollecting the wise Buddha is a source of insight."

msgid "4c115c6883044cd9a890e029ce599798"
msgstr "Its function is to realize dharmakāya."

msgid "b8b9519187fe418d875d15034a93a503"
msgstr "Constantly recollecting the Dharma is a source of insight."

msgid "3c12569ee0854fc993d51de512ef7362"
msgstr ""
"Its function is to realize the nature of reality without any attachment."

msgid "95e14bb6afc64f51a6c8a7e2663c5146"
msgstr ""
"“Recollecting the Saṅgha in terms of its qualities is a source of insight."

msgid "8e17f47b76964c539bc58e8e067cecbd"
msgstr "Its function is to realize it as it as unconditioned."

msgid "f67d95f119e34f3ba09a19caeb3ad6e7"
msgstr "Recollecting wise generosity is a source of insight."

msgid "834a0d38f7864635b2cbfe2f53375da4"
msgstr "Its function is to let go of all afflictive emotions."

msgid "5d457f19f76243c2a3b156cc30c9bb6c"
msgstr "“Recollecting pure moral conduct is a source of insight."

msgid "986d549688c240e985ba8d533d1a7ea9"
msgstr "Its function is to abide in unsullied moral conduct."

msgid "acc8c46d391043f58c43cedd322141b9"
msgstr "Recollecting the gods, the great beings, is a source of insight."

msgid "8a5d83cc66b74a2e83b0bd5585d2205d"
msgstr "Its function is to recollect the purest of the pure."

msgid "e776266491bd474a86461a9776f0715f"
msgstr ""
"“Scrutinizing what has been learned with focused attention is a source of "
"insight."

msgid "3944b50387a3438a9d965127a6896cfe"
msgstr "Its function is not to scrutinize later what has come from others."

msgid "99bf151e5050443d841d8abc5642add6"
msgstr "Performing virtuous actions is a source of insight."

msgid "6d15bceabdee43b8aca16058325c8c2f"
msgstr "Its function is to know that actions do not manifest later."

msgid "8d26c15932c34aabbf55d4ca8cf7b3b0"
msgstr "“Acting respectfully without pride is a source of insight."

msgid "b87a7f84dc9547699c7929f1d51ab534"
msgstr "Its function is to attain the nature of great wisdom."

msgid "b212b044497c423a8f2d728f999a2e48"
msgstr "Striving for one’s own benefit is a source of insight."

msgid "b831cff7fdcc409baa2f3001b6996720"
msgstr "Its function is to act for the benefit of sentient beings."

msgid "f51e24378b3a4e87b5e7fcd7e16603ed"
msgstr "“Upholding the collections of the Dharma is a source of insight."

msgid "267c31dcf6d343ccb1a1e2618754f431"
msgstr ""
"Its function is to foster understanding regarding the behavior of beings."

msgid "4619281c1a1a4eaea9e20a5ba2b5fe8c"
msgstr ""
"Fostering spiritual attainment in the minds of others is a source of "
"insight."

msgid "fe144e96e27b4b519d6c51083ecf2176"
msgstr ""
"Its function is to bring them to deliverance through the three vehicles."

msgid "ea14a5a57145406cb56fa3ecc37adce0"
msgstr "“For wise ones to mature beings by generosity,"

msgid "afccc603e5b1451794c73a2492db8e9a"
msgstr ""
"Speaking pleasantly, and working for their benefit is a source of insight."

msgid "75b259f0dda94c87af0cba50604e9b87"
msgstr "Its function is for noble beings to display buddha qualities"

msgid "033b5929e3c44f90a16e257287bfa41e"
msgstr "Through alignment with beings’ aims."

msgid "d10ca340e37243b4a854045beea0f8d6"
msgstr ""
"“Being intimidated by the knowledge that existence is an inferno is a source"
" of insight."

msgid "d07e58066e27434ead674fcfe8a2eb73"
msgstr "Its function is to attain acceptance of the unoriginated."

msgid "10e85bbf65ff462c92d41f82c205d627"
msgstr "The level of nonregression is a source of insight."

msgid "0b64783b8fe947699ff88f065fe5c251"
msgstr "Its function is to attain the level of empowerment."

msgid "a7358224e30a4855913f1d13cf2342d2"
msgstr "“Standing in front of the tree of awakening is a source of insight."

msgid "3e5dc72e2ff34cbd88a5ca8e4fe80b21"
msgstr "Its function is to attain omniscient wisdom."

msgid "f51ffdce46cd4721accf455406192956"
msgstr ""
"The so-called thought of awakening is itself known to be a source of "
"insight."

msgid "d952260492a64aff906cc02638b44c05"
msgstr "Its function is to bring about whatever one sets one’s mind to."

msgid "e7619a2064b1429491012f775fc0e306"
msgstr ""
"“Those who are unwavering and abide constantly in the thought of awakening"

msgid "1c0c826f2c4742c9ad704fa9a71029e1"
msgstr "Consistently perform the function of insight."

msgid "5be3ac4067ff4d9fbeae06f86d494021"
msgstr ""
"Were one to praise such a source—the supreme thought of awakened conduct, "
"Buddha strengths, and discriminating knowledge— For many thousands of eons, "
"One would never reach the end of buddha qualities."

msgid "e0edbb52845c4786af4d8bc53870e444"
msgstr "“Sugatas of the past, as well as the present"

msgid "157e5a5c5e2c4a368f5b6e2b5e526b7b"
msgstr ""
"And the future, along with the capable ones of the ten directions— Those who"
" wish to perform immeasurable service to these immeasurable beings Take a "
"sober delight in the thought of awakening.”"

msgid "ad4b6fe66cdd41f79b24eb3a178ca5f3"
msgstr "Thereupon, the bodhisattva Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja said,"

msgid "f4db8f1559514cf2b842c3e2910cbf88"
msgstr ""
"“Alas, Blessed One! The full extent of this unsurpassed complete and perfect"
" awakening of the blessed buddhas has been precisely ascertained."

msgid "72170eb568f64eb8aab9517a9701153e"
msgstr ""
"What is taught by way of words is infinite, and what is accessed by way of "
"meanings is infinite, yet it is difficult to access by those who are not "
"diligent."

msgid "9b390dc75af8414b97e7b83ab48a32d1"
msgstr ""
"It is profound since it is realized in accordance with dependent arising."

msgid "bc9e0595b50743f6a064849655135413"
msgstr "It is difficult to fathom by those who engage in duality."

msgid "7e0eb4c093f94813bd9caa8a03b055d4"
msgstr "It is difficult to see for those who rely on the six sense fields."

msgid "1ebc5539acbe4449846aec31ec080e78"
msgstr "It is difficult to trust for those dedicated to the lower vehicles."

msgid "6fa02a122b3048989eb5550d47e45e30"
msgstr ""
"It is not for śrāvakas or pratyekabuddhas but is the provenance of "
"bodhisattvas."

msgid "f72c390c026e4da7b5096cdf3f6d510a"
msgstr "“This awakening is the seal of all phenomena."

msgid "43d8bd0b22ff4fd390181c8e3eb5898c"
msgstr ""
"It is the equality of the realm of phenomena and thus inseparable from it."

msgid "b463a56d69dd42e79d91cc9ebe368b34"
msgstr "Having the characteristic of space, it does not become defiled."

msgid "7c71908abeb14b58ad09592fd2b09874"
msgstr "Since it is totally transcendent, it is not a substratum."

msgid "595371ce518d4a24aa0a3731bed6bb36"
msgstr ""
"It has knowledge of the behaviors of all sentient beings and knowledge of "
"all causes."

msgid "f2fa0ce5e22041bba85392b0d6766bef"
msgstr "“This awakening is the illumination of the perfection of wisdom."

msgid "dab8039f768c4239aa44bd2c21b63601"
msgstr "It is the source of deliverance."

msgid "06e438c3c2ba41849bdc32359b4577dc"
msgstr "It is the method of the roots of virtue."

msgid "353a6ecce98d4667b016002f26c5cf58"
msgstr ""
"It is what is discerned by those who have attained discriminating knowledge."

msgid "cdf2920067624af894710d969b37faa5"
msgstr "It liberates those who have attained superknowledge."

msgid "dfe101a0a233443193b1e32c2f327c2e"
msgstr ""
"“This awakening consists in the realization of equality by those who abide "
"in the single way."

msgid "143fc980464d495c8332c122f2d31f80"
msgstr "Not being multifarious, it is not differentiated among practitioners."

msgid "45f183f0e9234bc0a9a175fde30905f8"
msgstr "Since it is the same as space, it is equal."

msgid "da6dd9b8ed8645bf83cde8cca68a6d79"
msgstr "But since is not a counteragent, it is unequal."

msgid "0aca99d3966b4dce80bd0a6a8eb134b4"
msgstr "Since it is equal to all buddhas, it is both equal and unequal."

msgid "d787f7ad80d7498588dfeaf601f2cd54"
msgstr "Since it is distinguished by way of cessation, it is free of dualism."

msgid "a057d0ac37f54b9a8dc642dadd41abbb"
msgstr "It is not something to be analyzed by letters."

msgid "8d040faab8544f15944428900a2a8def"
msgstr "“This awakening is truly established as real."

msgid "c1ef282d75ce4424926f51cc24d56b70"
msgstr ""
"It is something known by language, yet ultimately it does not exist as "
"something expressible."

msgid "26ef7577645746909b7be0ba04bb1785"
msgstr ""
"It exists conventionally, it is endowed with the might of the Three Jewels, "
"it is conceived of in terms of the three vehicles, it is shown to be the "
"three gates of liberation, it totally transcends the three realms, and it "
"consists in the comprehension of threefold awareness."

msgid "8a0fc8a179f941e293f59cc963dc4968"
msgstr "“This awakening generates the vajra-like absorption."

msgid "bf50517080e04e64b6bd07c50281ca22"
msgstr "It is the abode of all phenomena."

msgid "cd8316004c2e4ced8f27bbbef1ebc4d3"
msgstr "It has arisen from the wisdom of the Buddha."

msgid "66b8411fa45046a9aaaa2d0b88b89407"
msgstr "It is the sustenance of all beings."

msgid "c9e56681bebf464d8c03a24ec9d04138"
msgstr "Being made clearly present by all buddhas, it is truly wonderful!"

msgid "2f57ebf5106d4505a34b21cd0ee58237"
msgstr ""
"“Blessed One, sons or daughters of noble family who have faith in this vast "
"account of the awakening of the blessed buddhas, who generate the thought of"
" unsurpassed complete and perfect awakening, who listen to this sūtra in "
"order to retain the holy Dharma, who are faithful, and who recollect it, "
"uphold it, read it, master it, or teach it in detail to others—they, Blessed"
" One, will generate a vast amount of merit."

msgid "4fdf9833ad7b414daea94ce6956649f3"
msgstr ""
"They will thereby pay homage to and repay the kindness of the tathāgatas.”"

msgid "fdd1b9673d7e4de8adfb1983ab47a383"
msgstr "The Blessed one responded,"

msgid "3d1eb5e8403240b481471904343dabc5"
msgstr "“That is correct, son of noble family."

msgid "d3a3b2b7c7e348f8b27e67024fec8458"
msgstr ""
"It is just as you have said: these beings will indeed generate a vast amount"
" of merit."

msgid "c357ffaa66ac4fafabd270e93c0bce3b"
msgstr ""
"Some may fill all buddhafields visible to the tathāgata eye with all jewels "
"and offer them to the tathāgatas, but if others, in order to uphold the holy"
" Dharma and ensure the continuity of the Three Jewels, were to listen to "
"this sūtra, have faith in it, retain it, uphold it, read it, master it, "
"teach it in detail to others, or diligently persist in the yoga of "
"cultivating it—these beings would generate a much larger amount of merit.”"

msgid "d8e07599ed344d2c9a7c99fe86bc5537"
msgstr "Then the Blessed One uttered these verses:"

msgid "2dcca1ad29c344169308043bd224fd1e"
msgstr ""
"“If some were to fill the fields that I behold with buddha eyes With jewels "
"and offer them to the Tathāgata, But fail to listen to this teaching,"

msgid "ce14123cd39b4dc4a9ce9cd4eb9dee54"
msgstr "I declare that their merit would be small."

msgid "4bb8ca09ce16477195c2ad5e19ada21a"
msgstr ""
"“If others were to hear this good sūtra, which is subtle and profound And "
"embodies the ultimate truth, And were to retain, uphold, and read it,"

msgid "817a7525d5eb47a3880a27982d3ac98d"
msgstr "Their merit would be far superior."

msgid "184a8874018340869bdd0e413ac34d8f"
msgstr ""
"“Thus, attainment through the Victor’s Dharma And deliverance through the "
"Dharma are not trifling things."

msgid "202ac379977542fa9e95d762c2c70ab9"
msgstr ""
"Those who thereby uphold the Sugata’s Dharma Repay the kindness of all "
"buddhas.”"

msgid "1ef5b25702a7413186ba554613738814"
msgstr "Then the Blessed One asked the great bodhisattva assembly,"

msgid "7942e67850f84a7a94f85897d5ae0ed8"
msgstr ""
"“Noble beings, when I pass into nirvāṇa, who among you would like to expound"
" this Dharma discourse and safeguard the awakening of the blessed buddhas in"
" order to ensure the continuity of the holy Dharma?”"

msgid "718361367fe943c3ae8938cff5869e0e"
msgstr ""
"Among the bodhisattva assembly, sixty billion bodhisattvas said with one "
"voice,"

msgid "746fb9bfa7d3401e9abff937da7ccb68"
msgstr ""
"“Blessed One, we will retain the awakening of the Tathāgata, accomplished "
"within countless eons, and we would like to expound it in future times as "
"well."

msgid "6ac17f41db21487496e02ad54c99fca4"
msgstr ""
"But, Blessed One, just to be sure, we request the Tathāgata to please bless "
"this Dharma discourse so that, among the many beings who will live at that "
"time, those who have created roots of virtue will come to hear about it.”"

msgid "eb9702730ea14452aa5e5c58ee58dceb"
msgstr "Then the Blessed One, spoke these verses:"

msgid "000d1a03e1654fe9969624996ac307d5"
msgstr "The true speech of the perfect Buddha."

msgid "e4b9062811c546599ad5cedb4cb1d88f"
msgstr "Since it abides as the true Dharma,"

msgid "1a7696baeef7404dafc5aa3553772c72"
msgstr ""
"“This sūtra is blessed for the sake of those future beings. It is blessed"

msgid "f93a1bea553743048da874937ed62900"
msgstr ""
"“This sūtra is blessed: Since it is universal love itself, It abides in "
"great love And dons the armor of great compassion."

msgid "7c589641f2a84f289d647dc29235d098"
msgstr ""
"“This sūtra is blessed: It is endowed with all accumulations And emerges "
"through the accumulation of wisdom And the most excellent accumulation of "
"merit."

msgid "0663358784f842a581de8fa2197a78c3"
msgstr ""
"“This sūtra is blessed: It eradicates all philosophical stances, Tames all "
"those who hold dogmatic views, And conquers all demons for good."

msgid "14add15b0ecd487c8d9a81a07bc1243f"
msgstr ""
"“I also bless The protectors of the world, Śakra, And the asuras, the gods, "
"and the demons, As well as the nāgas,"

msgid "1b7ffad5fd1d46ca9143ea900d136c09"
msgstr ""
"“The many gods, wherever they are, On the earth as well as in the heavens, "
"So that they will uphold this method By way of the blessings of the buddhas."

msgid "256f2901b7ab44fabee010ab39a0bcfc"
msgstr ""
"“This sūtra is blessed With the endowment of the abodes of Brahmā And the "
"adornment of the four noble truths, In order that this assembly may "
"safeguard it."

msgid "cfc12b3f8668474eb0a17eda2022eb1c"
msgstr "“It is possible to make space into form,"

msgid "48102726ed874438a6073e0e5624ce7f"
msgstr "And it is possible to make form formless,"

msgid "f259b07aea9743a9817403b5006be598"
msgstr ""
"But it is not possible to tamper With what is blessed by the buddhas.”"

msgid "787fe8144ecb49d080c97bca328d023e"
msgstr ""
"Thereupon the Catur­mahā­rājas recited this pair of verses, in unison, to "
"the Blessed One:"

msgid "3b3c63ec8a144d37865793c35440c303"
msgstr ""
"“Dear Tathāgata! In order to safeguard this sūtra, We, along with our kin, "
"Pledge to guard it well!"

msgid "52346844119b40acac1ce2b057940572"
msgstr "“Those skilled ones who uphold it With awakened intelligence—"

msgid "0ce52251a81a41bbb67d01d37d1cd7a2"
msgstr "We pledge to constantly safeguard them From the four directions.”"

msgid "d8cb25292b784245b0c06ca4ca3580cd"
msgstr ""
"Then Śakra, lord of the gods, recited this pair of verses to the Blessed "
"One:"

msgid "503548bbf0d34caabec78880df472193"
msgstr "“I will repay the kindness of the Blessed One."

msgid "4f7257b6ade94b93b052370e136be194"
msgstr "He is the guide, the master of the Dharma."

msgid "cca85a14af234a8f8a7329becb57559d"
msgstr "The protector taught that buddhas emerge From this supreme sūtra."

msgid "da9dd97983c349c593c6d7350fd8d37c"
msgstr "“To repay the kindness of all buddhas, I shall offer my protection."

msgid "9c0eea220bd74cffad30da085218a1f5"
msgstr ""
"I wish to safeguard sūtras such as this, And likewise those who uphold "
"them.”"

msgid "35ce285614954896a25c20dc34315d29"
msgstr ""
"Then Brahmā, ruler of the universe, recited this pair of verses to the "
"Blessed One:"

msgid "a429ff869cc9468bbe93f9ae6dab6a13"
msgstr ""
"“The concentrations and the immeasurables, As well as the goals of all the "
"vehicles, Emerge from this Profound and meaningful sūtra."

msgid "fda7541e4b7446fdadf548a40b344515"
msgstr ""
"“I will set out from the bliss of Brahmā And be present to listen And to "
"provide protection Whenever this method is explained.”"

msgid "8a90a6aab22f4a72b2ad3571fd22fc36"
msgstr ""
"Then Pramodita, the divine being, recited this pair of verses to the Blessed"
" One:"

msgid "c682e52cd56a45a2932e686b7089cfab"
msgstr ""
"“Those who uphold this sūtra That the Buddha has proclaimed Will be born "
"among the Tuṣita gods In their next life."

msgid "24d6dd517bb8492fbccea659328a70e4"
msgstr ""
"“O protector! Once I set out From the most excellent divine realm, I should "
"like to abide in Jambudvīpa And teach this method.”"

msgid "a0dade1d33d44d7a8293b0030cfb9387"
msgstr "Then Māraputra recited this pair of verses to the Blessed One:"

msgid "46e5f482d52e42ebbd2aa81a2132fa59"
msgstr ""
"“Those who uphold This meaningful sūtra, Because they have abandoned "
"negative acts, Will not come under the sway of evil,"

msgid "8a4f5a33d66444298050531778b0058f"
msgstr ""
"“O Tathāgata! In order to safeguard this sūtra, I shall also dedicate myself"
" And strive to make it flourish by any means.”"

msgid "a8d97ceb01b045b5821b95ad106d5092"
msgstr ""
"Then the demon Pāpīyān recited this pair of verses to the Blessed One:"

msgid "4934163de0e84fd5856f4d82b89ef72b"
msgstr ""
"“Guide! I shall not obstruct Those who uphold this text, Which eradicates "
"all afflictive emotions."

msgid "d440c3a0ca03419789537550977a34fe"
msgstr ""
"“Wherever this supreme sūtra appears, There will be no chance for evil."

msgid "265cfae14a9147c2a1a0c9d5a4a568dd"
msgstr ""
"I wish to give protection to those Who recollect the protectors’ speech.”"

msgid "7787cfc2b9344cea82fcb9f44eb13627"
msgstr ""
"Then the divine being Prasīmā recited this pair of verses to the Blessed "
"One:"

msgid "9aca9d6f4e4641548b02a4b7117ecc46"
msgstr ""
"“Whoever upholds this sūtra Pays homage to all buddhas, Since it explains "
"The awakening of all buddhas."

msgid "3ba91dfcfac74216bcd6c4901c6b6afe"
msgstr "“Protector! I shall explain this sūtra To millions of gods."

msgid "b57f20fbbbd44d84b6fd489aad0652c8"
msgstr "Whoever listens devotedly Will take hold of awakening.”"

msgid "023eeeac757c426a80d987e81f18bb25"
msgstr ""
"Then, the bodhisattva Maitreya recited this pair of verses to the Blessed "
"One:"

msgid "e34a1d326e384da1a26309af03837ba6"
msgstr ""
"“In order to safeguard the holy Dharma, I will likewise praise People who "
"set out for awakening,"

msgid "7562d81ed9a14c9cb8bc2c2ab117fd28"
msgstr "And I will act as their unsolicited spiritual guide."

msgid "bdba00799dd649e0af8b66a0ebc2b430"
msgstr ""
"“Having resided in Tuṣita, With the Buddha’s blessing I pledge to make this "
"sūtra Flourish widely.”"

msgid "72437e36bdbc459cadc87761d73bbedb"
msgstr ""
"Then the venerable Mahākāśyapa recited this pair of verses to the Blessed "
"One:"

msgid "62520b840bd243aea0a29a9cd7c8beb3"
msgstr ""
"“Even though I have heard Many thousands of sūtras from the Teacher, I have "
"never before heard A sūtra such as this!"

msgid "c8752fdd322d41118304f672c58b0c50"
msgstr "“I have directly received And embraced this sūtra."

msgid "20ac9669fcad4964bde922910ef6ffa4"
msgstr "I pledge to make it flourish For the sake of bodhisattvas!”"

msgid "5912d058185d41cca01b29aa8e2c05ad"
msgstr ""
"Then the Blessed One voiced his approval to Śakra, Brahmā, and the "
"protectors of the world, to the divine beings, to the bodhisattvas, and to "
"the great śrāvakas:"

msgid "ae50d6b6896e4b27b3ed30da280b29a6"
msgstr ""
"“Excellent, Noble beings! Excellent! Your lion’s roar of proclamation on "
"account of your support for the holy Dharma is excellent."

msgid "5a1bee83111f49eea78fc52c5a59a3cb"
msgstr "Noble beings, I instruct you: may you master it!"

msgid "50cd06944c264f22bd2a151f3e18966e"
msgstr ""
"Those beings who have embarked on the Great Vehicle, who have not attained "
"acceptance, and who have embraced this Dharma discourse with the blessing of"
" the blessed buddhas who have mastered it and comprehended it—they will not "
"pass beyond the seventh tathāgata until they have received their prophecy of"
" awakening."

msgid "655b6393e2fa44ea8f677ab98bddf1a4"
msgstr ""
"Those who have become śrāvakas will be included in the first śrāvaka "
"assembly of Maitreya."

msgid "d4894e69512048f1a2bf49aef808225c"
msgstr ""
"Those who have become pratyekabuddhas and who have mastered this Dharma "
"discourse will, following my own nirvāṇa, attain solitary awakening without "
"learning from others.”"

msgid "73fbcc6a10c84993b894953d8eb5b762"
msgstr ""
"When the Blessed One had taught this Dharma discourse as requested by "
"Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja, countless beings generated the thought of awakening."

msgid "0f9b63ba39294df8a886ac05217a7e5c"
msgstr ""
"Countless bodhisattvas became established in a state of nonregression."

msgid "6190ec4e18e048d6883ea88477e9a637"
msgstr ""
"Countless world realms trembled six times, were illuminated, and were filled"
" with swirling flower petals."

msgid "8b0984b144b64578a3eafb3cd40a4c52"
msgstr ""
"The bodhisattvas who had gathered from the world realms of the ten "
"directions and had decorated the entire pavilion Jeweled Array with flowers "
"of the seven precious substances as an act of worship to the Blessed One and"
" this Dharma discourse made the following proclamation:"

msgid "f3d3b3bc1d6a4af0aa11b2dcde3370e9"
msgstr "“Blessed One, we shall acquire it and acquire it well!"

msgid "a20efb7f37814c86a9540fe460134523"
msgstr ""
"Because we have heard this exegesis of the Dharma discourse, it was not "
"meaningless for us to be here!"

msgid "4d741fc0b7c04dbc885ac367b7685df1"
msgstr "“O Blessed One! May the life of Śākyamuni be protected!"

msgid "7107ba9443ad4841b1cea7ddc3ff9779"
msgstr ""
"May this Dharma discourse remain for a long time among the people of "
"Jambudvīpa!"

msgid "56a791b4b98b4024b7b24c50142a39dc"
msgstr ""
"May the lives of those monks, nuns, and male and female lay devotees who "
"uphold this sūtra be guarded for a long time! May it bring benefit to all "
"sentient beings!”"

msgid "edc2084c4db743d99531ba2155789f7e"
msgstr "At this point, Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja said to the Blessed One,"

msgid "4122d918431d4b5ba5bc6c96ce0e650b"
msgstr ""
"“O Blessed One! How wonderful is this definitive Dharma discourse, which is "
"of excellent meaning, well composed, and well adorned, which delights all "
"bodhisattvas, which overcomes all the hostility of evil ones and "
"adversaries, skillfully embrace all teachings, and satisfies the thoughts of"
" all beings, which emerges as the perfection of all vehicles, and which is "
"vividly taught to those who emulate the qualities of all tathāgatas and to "
"all who apply themselves to it!”"

msgid "493b1f9745ad4b5182b12254f88db9e4"
msgstr ""
"Then he asked, “Blessed One! What is this Dharma discourse called? How will "
"it be transmitted?”"

msgid "1736e1cf9c0e4cf59845d3096d32c0be"
msgstr "The Blessed One replied,"

msgid "1ba501495b0040e7908e433cf054afff"
msgstr ""
"“Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja, because of your request, you shall transmit this Dharma "
"discourse known as The Explanation of the Great Compassion of the Tathāgata!"

msgid "408186c940a44dee8aaa09f0303a5d92"
msgstr ""
"You shall transmit it as The Prophecy of Listening to the Meaningful "
"Activity of the Tathāgata!”"

msgid "9e9dd1aec6684e51bd450a6b9ee62cff"
msgstr ""
"After the Blessed One had spoken, Dhāraṇīśvara­rāja, together with everyone "
"in the bodhisattva and śrāvaka assemblies, as well as the world with its "
"gods, humans, asuras, and gandharvas, rejoiced and praised what the Blessed "
"One had said."

msgid "3b58b34161d94665a958a643653236cb"
msgstr ""
"This completes the noble Great Vehicle sūtra “The Teaching on the Great "
"Compassion of the Tathāgata.”"

msgid "03de411446c34be28614deec665ce1c1"
msgstr ""
"This text was translated and edited by the Indian scholar Śīlendrabodhi and "
"the principal editor-translator, Bandé Yeshé Dé. It was reviewed and "
"finalized in accordance with the new language reforms."
